entle, safe, non invasive and effective system of self-healing.\n',' BEST MASSAGE IN PORTLAND','[\"Maine\"]','I_A_M_KEY'),(NULL,'','[\"Boston\"]','WholeVisit Health'),('Herbalist\'s Antrodia Cinnamomea Mushroom drop pill is a dietary supplement that has anti-inflammation and anticancer effect.  Because of its unique active faction, Triterpenoid, this product is an alternative-medicine  solution to cancer, hepatitis, hypertension and prevent/reduce hangover. \n','Provide high quality Antrodia Cinnamomea Mushroom products.','[\"Kaohsiung\"]','Herbalist'),('The Meditation Gym provides a daily, affordable, retreat close to home. ','A Workout for the Soul','[\"Miami\"]','The Meditation Gym'),('Nirogam is a Natural Wellness and Supplements marketplace focussing on helping consumers discover products for improving Health and Nutrition. The products are Ayurvedic, Organic, Nutritional in nature. ','Zappos for Nutraceuticals and Ayurvedic Products','[\"New Delhi\"]','Nirogam'),('myHolisticServices.com is an online market place to save time, money and energy looking for certified holistic practitioners in your area. Think of it as Priceline for massage, acupuncture, hypnosis or any other holistic field. Choose the service you are looking for, the maximum price you are willing to pay for it and the time you need it. We will notify all service providers in the area. Within moments you will receive bids from practitioners that are willing to accept the terms you set. ','Think of us as the Priceline for massage, accupuncture and other holistic services','[\"Austin\"]','Zennity'),('An all natural AWARD WINNING Body Care Line specifically created to enhance/return to emotional wellness.\nI AM AWESOME- confidence, self love, courage\nPEACE OF MIND calms irritability, impatience, brings peace & calm \nFOCUS -concentration, focus, motivate\nDONT WORRY BE HAPPY calms the chronic worrier & helps the overactive thinker REJUVENATE restores energy, brings lightness & joy\nCHILL OUT helps the stress/overwhelmed to calm & achieve \nAID FOR THE ANXIOUS-struggles with panic, fears, irrational thoughts & anxious   \nOur expertise in creating chemical free, high end moisturizing healthy care for skin coupled with our intense formulas for emotional wellness, will bring your family calm, motivation, smiles! Don\'t discard because you have not heard of it-This is powerful TRY IT! Once you experience the remarkable and innovative approach to skin/mind care you will never go back to ordinary skin care! \nOur bar soaps won an award with Entrepreneur.com and were featured on MSNBC TV!','Emotional Wellness Naturally','[\"New Jersey\"]','Strongest MInds'),('What do MarCom\'s clients have in common? Last year was their best year yet. \r\n\r\nMarCom creates positioning that persuades, websites that wow, social media that sizzles and ad designs that dazzle - all with affordable results that hit the target. This is what it takes for companies to penetrate new markets and grab new customers again and again. \r\n\r\nIt all starts with business goals and smart marketing strategies that integrate technologies and tactics that work for your business. We will help protect your brand name, optimize for top Google rankings, initiate the buzz, handle lead generation, and measure for the best results.\r\n\r\nLet MarCom help you survive the digital world and prosper. ','We offer strategies for interactive marketing, SEO, public relations and social media.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','MarCom New Media'),('Therapeutes.com is the 1rst booking website for practioners of alternative medicine in france: Psychologists, Osteopaths, Dieteticians etc.\n\nTherapeutes.com is the unique online solution :\n\n- To find the good practioner among more than 500 000 praticioners in France, according to the price, specialization, localization, availability, reviews etc.\n\n- To book the appointment with your practioner once you have found him.\n\nThe customers are the 26 millions of French people who are looking for alternative medecine practicioner (French National academy of medecine, April 2013) and booking around yearly 15 millions of consultations in France.\nMarket estimated: 1 billion euros.\n\n\n','Therapeutes.com is the 1rst booking website with practitioners of alternative medicine','[\"Paris\"]','Therapeutes.com'),('Whole Body Rehab is an outpatient physical therapy clinic fusing eastern & western practices including acupuncture and herbs to help our patients take their therapy to another level.','Eastern / Western Integrative therapy and medicine','[\"West Palm Beach\"]','Whole Body Rehabilitation'),('These products are mainly embodied in the following types\n- Supplements\n- the Beverages\n- the personal care\n- the skin care\neach one of these products act in a particular mechanism to maintain naturalization of human body and re compensate essential element that the organic system need to maintain proper bio functions\nAs Ganozi we intended to extensively market our successful products for the magnitude of helping people in destitute and desperate situations and that is mainly embodied in success to get people treated and restored body sound condition using our products that are comprehensively confined to natural types of nutrient and concurrently therapeutic type of mushroom that called Ganoderma, as most of the nations in continent of Africa are desperately in need of affordability to meet treatment cost when they get sick as soaring prices of medicines is dramatically affecting most of the poor countries of Africa because of importation cost of medicines(  go to video','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f4Sin8GC91k','[\"Sudan\"]','Ganozi SD'),('SATIVFACTION INC  - reduction of harmful effects of hard drugs','Reduction of harmful effects of hard drugs','[\"Wilmington, DE\"]','satiVfaction Inc'),('We connect those seeking alternative / organic health providers with the appropriate provider.\n\nTwo revenue streams: Lead generation for providers looking for clients and advertising for organic health products. This model is working in other industries. See http://www.homeadvisor.com/.','Service Advisor for Alternative Medicines','[\"Denver\"]','Organic Health Connection'),('Country bed and breakfast inn centered around holistic treatments. The Center will be available to the public for treatments only or as overnight guests. The retreat house will have several holistic treatments including the following:\n\nSalt cave: aids in alleviating sinus problems, allergies, skin disease for children and adult.\nSalt beadrooms: sleeping quarters in the B&B with special walls made of salt to further enhance the detoxification experience.\nIonic Detox: purges cellular debris from the body.\nEar Candling: a 2000yr old treatment for ear problems\nSalt Water Sensory Deprivation Tak\nMassage therapy\nYoga/Tai Chi\n\nHH Holistic Retreat is a family friendly escape for a day or stay the weekend. Optimal well being is the goal. Enjoy what Upstate NY has to offer and relax while removing toxins and extra cellular wastes from your body. Return home completely rejuvenated.\n\nAdditionally, we offer salt walls custom built for your home.','Salt room therapies at a  B&B','[\"New York City\"]','HH HOLISTIC RETREAT CENTER'),('Dear Investor,\n\nI would like to introduce to you my Dietary Supplement for Chronic Lung Diseases. I believe my product has great potential and a huge market. I would like to explore the possibility of cooperation with you and your company. I am enclosing my presentation and would appreciate your response! \n\nSOLIAIR™ is a food supplement that contains a unique composition of ingredients, which has reported beneficial impact. SOLIAIR™ can contribute to strengthening the respiratory system and may help patients in chronic respiratory diseases such as Obstructive Lung Disease, Asthma, Bronchitis, COPD (Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease) and other respiratory infections. Each SOLIAIR™ food supplement has been authorized and defined by the Israeli Ministry of Health and according to Pharmacists Regulation. The SOLIAIR™ has a patent pending! \n\n\n** SOLIAIR™ Company Presentation Slide Show: http://goo.gl/2RU1O4  \n*** SOLIAIR™ Product Overview Video: http://goo.gl/UhK0Qx \n ','SOLIAIR™: New Pulmonary and Respiratory Diseases Drug Discovery!','[\"Haifa\"]','SOLIAIR™ - Breathing Made Easy!'),(NULL,'','[\"Ecuador\"]','Mad Dog Mining, LLC'),('Floatation Tanks (also known as Isolation Tanks or Sensory Deprivation Tanks) are designed to create a condition which is ideal for the relaxation and rejuvenation of the Mind/Body. Research shows that the effects of a float session are equivalent to eight hours of deep sleep, making it one of the most efficient and comprehensive relaxation techniques available. A Floatation Tank is an enclosed structure which diminishes light and sound. Each tank holds 10 inches of water with 800 lbs. of dissolved Epsom Salts, which enable a person to float effortlessly. The water is heated to an average skin temperature (93.5F) which reduces the sensation between body and water. The tanks are fully ventilated and the water/salt solution is sterilized after each use using a combined system of ozone, concentrated hydrogen peroxide and diatomite earth filters.\r\n','Floatation Tank Center','[\"Milwaukee\"]','Float:Milwaukee'),('DNAnexus is a software technology company that aims to be the DNA data platform of the future. Fueled by technological advances spanning biochemistry, microfabrication, optics, and high-performance systems design, DNA sequencing is advancing at an unprecedented rate of approximately 10-fold improvement in cost and throughput every 18 months. As a result, data output and compute requirements have vastly outstripped Moore\'s law, shifting the bottleneck toward the data management challenges. Soon it will be possible to sequence a full human genome for well under $1,000, making sequencing the first million genomes commercially viable, but will require compute infrastructure on the order of 100,000 CPUs and Exabytes of storage.','Genomics platform in the cloud','[\"Mountain View\"]','DNAnexus'),('Benchling is a platform for life science data management. It allows scientists to edit, analyze, and share DNA sequence data.\n\nScientists build with DNA, just like programmers do with code. Major biotech companies account for 2% of the US GDP. Despite this value, there is no version control in life science. These companies have no cloud-based tools for facilitating collaboration and sharing between their scientists.','GitHub of Biology','[\"San Francisco\"]','Benchling'),('The UK’s first dedicated synthetic biology company with a world leading platform of technologies for the rapid engineering and optimisation of novel biological production systems.  A spin out of University College London, Synthace harnesses the ability of micro-organisms to produce complex, high-value chemical and biological products from sustainable and renewable feedstocks. In addition to equity funding, the company has received a £500,000 Technology Strategy Board award entitled ‘Rapid Engineering of Cellular Factories’, in collaboration with University College London and University of Manchester. While Synthace bioengineering is broadly applicable across multiple industry sectors, the company is initially focused towards applications in the production of specialty chemicals.','Applied Synthetic Biology','[\"London\"]','Synthace Limited'),('Genome Compiler - Democratizing the tools of creation\n \nGenome Compiler is delivering an innovative Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) computer-aided design (CAD) and collaboration platform for Synthetic Biology.  \n\nOne can design and order the DNA program directly from Genome Compiler as physical DNA, that can be shipped internationally and be used to transform living things with new functions. \n\nLearn more and download our software at genomecompiler.com','Democratizing creation ','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Genome Compiler'),('We build software that helps doctors, scientists, and programmers make sense of massive amounts of health data. The past decade has seen a revolution in molecular technology, which means we can now collect large amounts of precise medical data about anyone at low cost. The problem is that the data are not in a language doctors can understand.\n\nOur API for Medicine helps programmers and scientists at research hospitals, diagnostic companies, biotech and pharma companies, and CROs translate molecular data into information doctors can use to diagnose and treat patients. We\'ve compiled the world\'s molecular data and made it easy to work with and understand.','The Data Platform for Medicine','[\"New York City\"]','SolveBio'),('MedWhat is a personal medical assistant app providing automatic personalized answers to your health and medical questions.  Users can create a quick anonymous health profile telling MedWhat their age, gender, and current medical conditions. This allows MedWhat to provide personalized answers and have a contextual conversation with the user by following up with questions and pushing health notifications to your phone. MedWhat uses natural language processing and bioinformatics to understand and create medical logic.  The team is made of statistics and computer science engineers, and a medical adviser from Stanford University Hospital. The free MedWhat app is currently ranked as a new and top medical app by the Apple app store and already being used by thousands of people.','Personalized Healthcare Assistant providing answers to your health and medical questions.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','MedWhat'),(NULL,'','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Syapse'),('Spiral Genetics makes high performance software for analyzing DNA.  We help researchers, pharmaceutical companies and clinicians derive meaningful results from their data. Using our proprietary distributed computing algorithm on large DNA datasets, Spiral Genetics quickly, affordably and accurately identifies the genetic causal mechanisms for disease and drug metabolism. \n\nThis technology significantly accelerates genomic research, reduces the cost of clinical trials and enables new diagnostics.','Data Mining for Genomics','[\"Seattle\"]','Spiral Genetics'),('Our team is currently working on a forehead band for sleeping, but not a normal one though. Apart from modern design and comfortable using, our band will be an advanced diagnostic electronical device. It will be cordlessly connected with an application on a smartphone in order to monitor our sleep to wake us up in the most adequate moment. This should contribute to making our sleep more effective and reveille – pleasant. Our data are collected using technologies used in hospitals.','Biomedical signals processing devices','[\"Warsaw\"]','Intelclinic'),('Desktop Genetics makes software to make biotechnology easier. The company has developed AutoClone™, an automated software platform that enables the optimal design, construction, management and exchange of DNA constructs to be deployed in vector/plasmid manufacturing, genome-editing, protein production and Synthetic Biology work-flows. Our products have a meaningful impact on companies everyday.\n','Faster and more accurate genetic engineering.','[\"London\"]','Desktop Genetics'),('Enables research scientists in academia and corporations to interact directly with genomic data, rather than requiring the expertise of a bioinformatics specialist. This increases our potential market by two orders of magnitude. Our open science, cloud-based platform provides for storage and management of high throughout sequencing data, analysis and exploration using proven, journal-published methods and applications, and enables on-the-fly creation of genome browsers that allow researchers to interact with and visualize their genomic data in an entirely new way, helping them to detect previously hidden patterns and insights. This dramatically increases research and development productivity, especially for biomarker discovery, in applications such as therapeutics, molecular diagnostics, biotech, and agribusiness.','Next generation genomic data management, exploration, and visualization','[\"San Mateo\"]','Maverix Biomics'),('Sanguine is a technology-enabled company innovating at the intersection of personalized medicine, biobanking, and biomedical research. It has a simple and attractive, proven business model. Sanguine collects blood samples and associated medical data from patients diagnosed with specific conditions. It processes those samples to extract biospecimen such as cells, serum, plasma and DNA, and stores them along with the medical data. It then sells the biospecimen and data to academic and pharmaceutical entities for research purposes.  \n\nProblem & Solution:\nTraditionally, research companies need to wait for physicians to set up appointments with patients and to find some willing to sign up. Patients go to Sanguine because Sanguine offers increased transparency in the research process, showing them where samples are used and how they advance biomedical research in areas they care about. ','Empowering Patients & Accelerating Personalized Medicine R&D; Biological/Clinical Data','[\"Santa Monica\"]','Sanguine BioSciences'),('3Scan creates new analytical perspectives on the structure of disorders such as cancer, cardiovascular disease, Alzheimer\'s, and strokes.  The patented Knife-Edge Scanning Microscope allows cells, tissues, and organs to be seen in 3D at microscopic resolution.\n\nImmediate applications are in drug discovery, biotech, basic research, and will eventually be applied clinically. Current techniques are manually handled by humans, thus orders of magnitude slower and not suitable for 3D modeling.','Automated pathology','[\"San Francisco\"]','3Scan'),('Prime Genomics has identified a signature for identifying breast cancer from saliva samples using its proprietary tool for evaluating the expression patterns of a large number of genes thermodynamically.\n\nCurrently the compliance rate, in developed countries, is 50% for women who should get mammograms. In developing countries, with compliance rates around 5%, access to mammography is the challenge to early Dx. Testing saliva samples in a Drs office at low cost with minimal necessary infrastructure is an effective way of increasing Dx.','Population screening for breast cancer through salivary samples. ','[\"San Francisco\"]','Prime Genomics'),('','','[\"Moscow\"]','Universe Ventures'),('Miinome is the first solution to provide direct-to-consumer genetic data\nmanagement, storage, and brokerage.  Our platform allows anyone to quickly see recommendations for a growing list of genetic traits, and take action immediately.  We provide a safe, and secure method for sharing traits with marketers, researchers, and family or friends.  Our platform is always opt-in, and the data is always yours.','The first member controlled human genetic marketplace','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Miinome'),('InSilico DB https://insilicodb.org is a complete web-based solution for storing and managing genomics data. 100,000s of public profiles are pre-installed and ready to analyze.\n\nInSilico DB takes care of the data issues with cutting-edge genomics applications in cancer and hereditary diseases. Research hospitals can use InSilico DB as a complete solution for getting started in genomics, to increasing patient benefit.','Taking care of the informatics in bioinformatics','[\"Brussels\"]','InSilico Genomics S.A.'),(NULL,'Private research and development consulting.','[]','ASTRO Ltd'),('Through the purposed application, GeneDrop looks to create a computational pipeline and database capable of correlating human genetic variation with pharmaceutical molecule efficacy. This program has application in the identifying patient subpopulation for prescription labeling via pharmacogenomics. This can also be applied to the resuscitation of abandoned molecules through evaluation of gene-drug interactions in the case of adverse event reporting.','The Informatics Pipeline to Correlate Drug Response with Genomic Variablity ','[\"San Francisco\"]','GeneDrop'),('GenomeCruzer - real-time 3D for integrative visualization and analysis of genomic data. See genomecruzer.com for details.\n\nGilgamesh - Interactive 3D Visual Mining for Big Data\nGilgamesh uses high-performance 3D graphics to create an interactive 3D scene representing the data elements, where hundreds of thousands of items can be visualized at once, together with the relations among them.\n','Interactive 3D tools for Big Data','[\"Turin\"]','Kairos3D'),('The ilumivu System combines wearable biosensors, mobile apps and online patient-centered platforms to help facilitate patient behavior change.\n\nThe entire system can be replicated and customized for health and mental health providers wishing to provide continuous physiological monitoring, real-time interventions and patient-centered care to their clients. \n\nModule architecture allows rapid replication, customization and set-up of new systems.','Facilitating behavioral change for better health','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','ilumivu'),('We are developing innovative solutions for life sciences. Some of our projects:\n\nNimbusGene (www.nimbusgene.com): Platform as a Service (PaaS) to perform bioinformatics analysis in a cloud environment with a friendly interface to manage and collaborate their genetics projects.\n\nDodo (www.dodofunding.com): first crowdfunding platform for genetics project.','Creative ideas and innovative solutions for life sciences.','[\"Santiago\"]','Beagle Bioinformatics'),('- Biophotonic Scanner to screen non-invasively antioxidant levels and provide a nutritional health score.\n- Cloud-based management software for Health and Wellness Services Providers, to record and track end-users progress, interact with them through a mobile application.\n- Cloud-based management software for Employers and Health Plans, to track populations progress anonymously, to build health-contingent and outcome-based Benefits programs through nutritional health (antioxidants) score improvement goals setting.\n- Mobile application for management of nutrition data, track progress and interact with service provider. In the future, application will provide benefit (financial incentives) and health score driven discovery services from items at food retailers and restaurants menus. ','Nutrition Wellness Platform to help Populations eat healthy, daily and 1 person at a time','[\"San Francisco\"]','NUFITSCAN'),('Dodo is a novel solution for biotechnology exploration and science outreach. It is the first crowdfunding platform exclusively for biotech projects. Our goal is to promote the scientific knowledge, funding low and high-risk but promising biotech projects, approximating ordinary people to the development of science. It is a powerful new incentive for scientists to engage the public with science: the potential for raising money for research directly from the public. Ordinary people is excited with science! Now they have the opporunity to be part of an important research by making direct donations, receiving or not a pledge for its donation. Those pledges can be even a participation as a object of study. Kind of nerd? Maybe, but we believe it\'s cool to have your gene sequenced or to have your name in a new gene discovered. ','Crowdfunding for biotech projects','[\"Santiago\"]','Dodo Biotech Crowdfunding'),('Intrepid’s genomic/genetic data management system supports any and all NGS data, along with SNP and genotyping datasets.  A mantra of ours is, sequence once, genotype many times.\n\nWe are uniquely built to support the analysis, delivery, management and publication of genotypes derived from sequencing. \n\nRegister for a free account:\nhttps://server1.intrepidbio.com/FeatureBrowserPrivate/account/createfree','Genomic/genetic data management system facilitates access, collaboration & publication.','[\"Louisville\"]','Intrepid Bioinformatics'),('A 90 day accelerator specifically to help idea stage startups in the field of Synthetic Biology cross that valley. \n\nThose accepted into SynBio axlr8r will receive:\n*$30k in funding\n*Bench space in a Wet Lab\n*Mentorship from some of the top experts in biotech and business. \n\nOur first batch will run from in the Summer of 2014, from May to August and take place in the scenic Cork City, Ireland.\n\nThe call for applications is currently open.','Design, Build and Launch your Synthetic Biology Vision!','[\"Cork\"]','SynBio axlr8r'),('Isentio offers unique online software solutions to facilitate analysis, interpretation and management of DNA sequencing data. Isentio\'s RipSeq® product is the fastest, most user-friendly and complete solution for DNA identification of clinically important pathogens, making identification consistent and accurate. \n\nRipSeq enables sequence-based identification from both mono- and poly-microbial samples, a unique feature that results in enhanced problem solving qualities. The bacterial identification time can be reduced up to 90% and answers can be provided where other methods fail. Fast, precise pathogen identification will also support selection of optimal antibiotic regimes, with the potential to reduce health care costs.\n\n50k Foot View of Isentio:\n•	SaaS product + curated proprietary database\n•	Clinical AND research lab utility\n•	Existing global customer base\n•	2 filed and 3 provisional patents','Pathogen Identification as a Service','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Isentio'),(NULL,'Protecting Privacy, Furthering Research','[\"Pensacola\"]','Bionymity'),('VOXCE is a cloud based clinical research application framework that implements a standard structure\nfrom different data sources to provide a centralized interface to manage single, and multiple clinical\nresearch studies.\n','Clinical Trial Framework implements a standard structure from different data sources','[\"Minneapolis\"]','VOXCE'),('Stillwater Supercomputing, Inc. designs and markets the Stillwater Genome Appliance, a hardware accelerated server that connects to a NGS instrument to create a high productivity workflow for genetics and drug discovery, and ultimately personalized healthcare research and deployment.','Personalized medicine platform','[\"San Jose\"]','Stillwater Supercomputing'),('Our product accelerates the processing of DNA sequencing data. It is about 5x faster, uses 20x less power and requires 15x less space than conventional CPU solutions. We believe that the arrival of personal genomics in the next 2 to 5 years will bring huge computational requirements that will put large demands on conventional compute solutions. Our product is faster, cheaper and more compact. ','High Performance Compute Hardware and Software for DNA Sequencing','[\"Baltimore\"]','Stone Ridge Technology'),('DNA researchers are buying a new generation of small and fast DNA sequencers that are revolutionizing bioscience and medicine.  The price is still out of reach for many small labs, though.  Cheap-Seq hooks up sequencer owners with non-owners who just have a few jobs to run.  Owners can squeeze them in during downtime or between their own runs, and monetize.','AirBnB for Next-Gen DNA Sequencing','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Cheap-Seq'),('Recently allows life science researchers and medical doctors to stay up to date with what is being published in their field. It provides a personalised feed of new and relevant scientific publications. From tedious search to easy discovery, Recently is the personalised scientific journal.','Discover relevant publications','[\"Barcelona\"]','Recently'),('Sequencing DNA is becoming cheaper and faster, and is fundamentally changing medical research and practice. However, the ability to analyze and interpret the data is lagging behind. Currently, the analyses workflows are complex so typically a biologist needs to hire an analyst to write a bunch of scripts to do the job. Further, the data size is growing so rapidly (3x of Moore\'s law) that the computing infrastructure is not able to scale.\n\nWe have developed a cloud based platform, where users will upload their data and select the type of analysis with just a few clicks. The workflow and computations will run automatically and results will be available on the web.','cloud-powered DNA sequencing data analysis','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Basepair'),('Bioseka is focused on advanced research and applications of antisense\r\noligonucleotides (ASOs) as antimicrobial agents against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. The company’s primary target is control of bacterial biofilms through inhibiting the synthesis of exopolysaccharides, which compose structural matrix of the biofilms.\r\nBioseka ASOs have potential applications in the therapy of medically\r\nimportant oral, nasopharyngeal, skin and cardiovascular infections. Bioseka ASOs can also be combined with other antimicrobial agents, thus providing a novel path for combating multidrug-resistant bacteria.\r\nThe company is currently developing several lead phosphorothioate\r\nand peptide nucleic acid ASOs and is working to establish the optimum\r\neffective dosage, to improve their penetration into the biofilm and target cells, and to test stability of the chemotherapeutics under various conditions involving the complex environment of natural microbiota.','Antisense Antimicrobials','[\"Vilnius\"]','Bioseka, UAB'),(NULL,'','[\"Toronto\"]','Divergent Rays Computing Inc.'),('GenSupport (in development): bioinformatics consulting service–building pipelines, writing scripts, data analytics etc. The purpose is to build relationships, experience and recognition that will help us build the web distribution channel later on.\n\nGenLocator (public): our flagship product–gene prioritization as a service. We integrate customers’ data with open databases and provide a prioritized list of target as the result. The goal is to gradually transform it into a web-based product.\n\nGenExpress (in development): web application for visual analytics of gene profiles. We will migrate users from its predecessor, dictyExpress, developed by our partner Biolab, to GenExpress and up-sell GenLocator and GenSupport to them. \n\nGenCloud (private beta): web and cloud-based genomic data organization, analytics and visualization platform. The basis for GenLocator and GenExpress products. ','Accelerating innovation in life sciences','[\"Ljubljana\"]','Genialis'),('Everybody deserves a good night sleep, especially new parents. Monbaby is an active health baby monitor that helps parents to sleep better. One of the founders, as any first-time parents, remembers worrying about SIDS and not being able to fall asleep or to rest. Monbaby is designed to solve this problem, to alleviate parents anxiety about their newborns well-being.\r\nOur solution is Monbaby, an active, real-time, wireless baby heal monitor in the shape of an oval button that could be attached on almost any article of baby clothing.\r\nWe believe that a combination of conveniently attached sensor, sleep helping application and our cutting edge Bio-Data Analytics Library make this an awesome product and a killer technology suite','Sleep analyzer that helps parents of newborns to sleep','[\"North Bergen\"]','Mondevices'),('SWITCHBIOTECH uses its broad knowledge and expertise of the molecular biology of the skin to develop drugs for various skin disorders. By using proprietary technology we can rapidly profile potential new and re-profile existing compounds for possible treatments for a variety of diseases. Therapeutic areas of interest include -- Psoriasis, Atopic Dermatitis, Vitiligo, Androgenic Alopecia and other non-dermatologic areas.','Innovative Dermatology Drug Development','[\"Little Rock\"]','SWITCHBIOTECH'),('MoB Bioinformatics Team comprises of experienced analysts, developers and researchers committed to developing novel solutions to the problems of the biosciences community.\nAlongside bioscience research, MoB has a profound sense of responsibility towards national progress and is therefore actively involved in developing Information and Communications Technology (ICT) solutions for development. Particularly, we focus on ICT for agriculture, healthcare, and education.\n\n','Information Communications Technology, Bioinformatics','[\"Pakistan\"]','Modus Operandi Bioinformatics'),('An online science community and resource built by researchers and service providers in the life science industries.\n\nBitBio provides access to new resources, providers, and equipment that may have otherwise not been found. Researchers can exchange science projects or services with hospitals, universities, research institutes, or other service providers across the globe.\n\nThey may also discover scientific methods other researchers or service providers are using. At the core of this online web application is a search tool used to facilitate the exchange of science, advice, opinions, and services.\n\nLearn about new research, methods, and technologies to use for your project and what the science market has to offer. Quickly promote research questions and answers in the science community to help a fellow colleague.\n','Science Community and Marketplace','[\"Chicago\"]','BitBio'),(' Product/Services\n\nThe FDA cleared swallowable screening device is comprised of a medical grade foam ball is compressed into a swallowable capsule which is deployed and withdrawn orally within 5 minutes. Since this device is spherical in shape and will be harvesting cellular samples from the entire length of the esophagus, the resulting specimen has a higher likelihood of capturing the diseased indicator cells than conventional, single site, pinch biopsies.\n\n Customer problem\n\nWith the recent developments in Genome Sequencing, several corporations and medical institutions have developed Biomarker Test Kits to detect diseases of the esophagus without requiring the use of invasive and uncomfortable endoscopic techniques. The problem is that these Biomarker and H-pylori quick test companies do not have efficient non-endoscopic (non-invasive) methods of obtaining cellular specimens from patents.\n\n','FDA Cleared! Non-Endoscopic cellular collection Device for Barretts Esophagus & H-Pylori.','[\"Philadelphia\"]','CapNostics, LLC'),('iBinom lets you make your genome analysis in 30 minutes','Genome interpretation in the cloud','[\"Moscow\"]','Binom'),('We provide a data discovery platform for Life Sciences. Through a visual and interactive approach to analytics, companies are able to explore their clinical and omics data, and see results instantly. Our solution also enables researchers without extensive data analysis skills to mine their data using state-of-the-art methodologies in a simple, user friendly, and task-driven manner.','Big-Data Analytics for Life Sciences','[\"Lisbon\"]','GeneConnect'),('The methods of disease diagnosis have certainly been revolutionized by numerous technologies over the past 20 years. In Ophthalmology, this progression has lagged behind other sectors, while blinding eye diseases continue to grow at a staggering pace because of the baby-boomer generation. Ocular Proteomics (OPL) aims to change this by using their discovery of proteins that are differentially activated in blinding diseases.\n\nThe Diagnostic Vitreous Proteome is a molecular based tool to provide Ophthalmologists with a better understanding about which treatments may work best, and conversely which ones that won\'t work at all! The benefits of this are two fold: administering effective treatment to patients at the earliest possible time saves their long term vision, &  costs savings from extended periods of non-effective treatments.\n\nIdentifying an individual patient\'s \"protein fingerprint\" is the future bedrock of disease treatment, much like HER2 is in breast cancer today.','Individualized Medicine for Eye Diseases','[\"Baltimore\"]','Ocular Proteomics'),('BioDatomics produces computational biology solutions which provide analysis software for scientists using the latest high throughput techniques such as NGS which produce huge datasets that have to be analyzed to be useful. We have already built a platform that caters for research in genomics and are working towards adding functionality for those researching proteomics. We want to position BioDatomics as a world standard in computational biology;there is a fast-growing market for this technology.','Big data analysis for personalized medicine','[\"Pittsburgh\"]','BioDatomics'),('Providing the service of transporting unused cellulose biomass from leftover crops straight from the farmer\'s field to the biomass plant. Helps further research biomass as well as reuses the wasted leftovers.','Biomass transportation, field-to-plant.','[\"Westerville\"]','TransBio '),('We are developing a Bridg(www.bridgmodel.org) Complaint cloud based  Master Data product  that would provide   a Governance HUB as well as  Analytics.It helps customers  in Governance , Data cleaning and automated submissions. All companies  in Life Sciences , Medical Devices , Food , cosmetics and Spirits would need this Single source of Truth.','A Cloud based Master Data  product for  Life Sciences','[\"Edison\"]','Kaizen Bio-Informatics'),('Life Science Network (lifescience.net) is an internet platform for professional networking and sharing of knowledge in life sciences. Our aim is to bring together all stakeholders in life sciences, and through a unique way of integrating places, people and content, make sharing and access to life science related information easier than ever before. ','A web platform dedicated to life sciences','[\"Heidelberg\"]','Life Science Network'),('PIR (Premier Information Retrieval®) is a multi-faceted software application that is currently being developed as a means of having a \"multiple purpose\" and being multi-functional.\n\nOriginally, it was in the process of being designed and developed by research scientist, Desmond J. Watson, as an algorithm that would search for \"hidden data\" outside of normalized search parameters and would \"penetrate\" data points with the larger of the data points being the first to be penetrated by the algorithm.\n\nNow, the research project has scaled to the point that the purpose of PIR has been re-defined. PIR now serves the purpose of detecting probable causes of certain immuno-responses, i.e., allergies, by utilization of biometric sequences mapped to principle component analyses (PCAs) that will minimize averaged squared projection errors, permitting more singular results assigned to individuals.\n\nThis project is not \"big data\" oriented.','Unorthodox research at its finest','[\"Atlanta\"]','The Hexagon Lavish'),(NULL,'Prevent Genetic Disease before Pregnancy with a DNA Test','[\"Redwood City\"]','Counsyl'),('When its time to transform a big idea into a great company, entrepreneurs want a venture partner who understands and believes in the power of big ideas – those bold visions that have the power to disrupt an industry, a market and ideally the world. Moreover, entrepreneurs want a proven venture partner who has the resources and experience and knows what it takes first hand to help a company succeed, to turn those big ideas into an action, and to make those strategies a reality.\nIf you’re looking for a venture investor with whom you can build a long term supportive and collaborative relationship, then we are the right venture partner. \n\nWhether you are seeking a venture investment to get your big idea off the ground or looking to propel your proven idea toward greatness, we invite you to learn more about us and the companies we have invested in, and to speak to the founders and teams we have partnered with. Their experience with Artis Ventures has always been our best reference.','','[\"San Francisco\"]','ARTIS VENTURES '),('DNAnexus is a software technology company that aims to be the DNA data platform of the future. Fueled by technological advances spanning biochemistry, microfabrication, optics, and high-performance systems design, DNA sequencing is advancing at an unprecedented rate of approximately 10-fold improvement in cost and throughput every 18 months. As a result, data output and compute requirements have vastly outstripped Moore\'s law, shifting the bottleneck toward the data management challenges. Soon it will be possible to sequence a full human genome for well under $1,000, making sequencing the first million genomes commercially viable, but will require compute infrastructure on the order of 100,000 CPUs and Exabytes of storage.','Genomics platform in the cloud','[\"Mountain View\"]','DNAnexus'),(NULL,'Seed and Early-stage Venture Capital Fund based in Houston, TX','[\"Houston\"]','Mercury Fund'),('Transcriptic is building a revolutionary laboratory virtualization platform: \"cloud computing\" for the life sciences. We\'ve developed machine-readable protocol and robotics technology for carrying out experiments quickly, cheaply, and highly repeatably. We remove the need for on-site infrastructure, decimating costs and freeing up the endless days spent moving small volumes of liquids around by hand.','Science as a service','[\"Menlo Park\"]','Transcriptic'),('Cambrian Genomics makes the first hardware/systems for laser printing DNA. \n\nResearchers in academia & industry order or clone >$1b/year of DNA. CGI plans to deliver high quality sequence verified DNA to buyers in this existing/growing worldwide market.\n\nAusten on Bloomberg\nhttp://bit.ly/11lLnFh\n\nGeorge on Colbert Report\nhttp://bit.ly/T9g2WG\n\nAusten on TWiT Live\nhttp://bit.ly/LgM3bx\n\nResurrection (Neanderthals & Dinosaurs)\nhttp://bit.ly/10FdN28\n\nGlowing Plants\nhttp://kck.st/146llfq\n\nFirst Gene Party\nhttp://bit.ly/1cdM1ux\n\n','DNA Laser Printing ','[\"San Francisco\"]','Cambrian Genomics'),('Ritter\'s lead compound, RP-G28 has the potential to become the first FDA-approved drug for the treatment of lactose intolerance. RP-G28 has successfully completed Phase 2a clinical trials, and Ritter Pharma plans to partner the drug.','Therapeutic Treatments for Gastrointestinal Diseases','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Ritter Pharmaceuticals'),('Benchling is a platform for life science data management. It allows scientists to edit, analyze, and share DNA sequence data.\n\nScientists build with DNA, just like programmers do with code. Major biotech companies account for 2% of the US GDP. Despite this value, there is no version control in life science. These companies have no cloud-based tools for facilitating collaboration and sharing between their scientists.','GitHub of Biology','[\"San Francisco\"]','Benchling'),('The UK’s first dedicated synthetic biology company with a world leading platform of technologies for the rapid engineering and optimisation of novel biological production systems.  A spin out of University College London, Synthace harnesses the ability of micro-organisms to produce complex, high-value chemical and biological products from sustainable and renewable feedstocks. In addition to equity funding, the company has received a £500,000 Technology Strategy Board award entitled ‘Rapid Engineering of Cellular Factories’, in collaboration with University College London and University of Manchester. While Synthace bioengineering is broadly applicable across multiple industry sectors, the company is initially focused towards applications in the production of specialty chemicals.','Applied Synthetic Biology','[\"London\"]','Synthace Limited'),('Genome Compiler - Democratizing the tools of creation\n \nGenome Compiler is delivering an innovative Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) computer-aided design (CAD) and collaboration platform for Synthetic Biology.  \n\nOne can design and order the DNA program directly from Genome Compiler as physical DNA, that can be shipped internationally and be used to transform living things with new functions. \n\nLearn more and download our software at genomecompiler.com','Democratizing creation ','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Genome Compiler'),('Biomeme\'s platform transforms your smartphone into a mobile lab for advanced DNA diagnostics and real-time disease surveillance. The system includes a docking station for real-time qPCR, a mobile app to control the system and analyze results, and targeted test kits for preparing samples and identifying pathogens or diseases by their specific DNA or RNA signatures. The cutting edge platform performs to the gold standard used by the world\'s most advanced central labs but requires no lab equipment or special experience to use.\n\nThe low-cost, user-friendly system enables mobile testing at the point-of-need for health care (mobile clinics, disease tracking, home use), agriculture (plant disease tracking, food safety), vector surveillance (Malaria, West Nile, Lyme disease), veterinary medicine, environmental monitoring (soil and water safety), and even education and citizen science.','Mobile real-time DNA analysis on your smartphone','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Biomeme'),('Hackers / Founders Co-op is our incubator:  It\'s like TechStars / Y Combinator, only better.  \n\nBetter class size:  Small classes of 6 to 7 startups, 4 times a year\nBetter partner time:  80 to 100 hrs over 3 months\nBetter long term services:  Talent + Design + Growth + Sales + Immigration / Policy + Space\nBetter Selection process:  Blind applications, top tier investors are part of screening\n\nTrack record:\nWith a budget of $220k / 5 years.  We\'ve built a portfolio with a market cap of $70M, including 2 acquisitions\n4 of our last 13 startups have declined acquisition offers already\n\nBackground:  \nIn 5 years the Hackers / Founders global community has grown from 5 dudes in a bar to…\n\n・Silicon Valley: 11,000 members\n・20 countries\n・51 chapters\n・70,000 members\n\nWe do tons of free events:\n・We produce 1 to 5 events in Silicon Valley every week\n・HF organizers do 30 free events per week around the globe for the community\'s benefit\n\nGlobal membership is doubling every 8 months: http://hf.cx/','Like TechStars / Y Combinator only better','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Hackers / Founders'),('We build software that helps doctors, scientists, and programmers make sense of massive amounts of health data. The past decade has seen a revolution in molecular technology, which means we can now collect large amounts of precise medical data about anyone at low cost. The problem is that the data are not in a language doctors can understand.\n\nOur API for Medicine helps programmers and scientists at research hospitals, diagnostic companies, biotech and pharma companies, and CROs translate molecular data into information doctors can use to diagnose and treat patients. We\'ve compiled the world\'s molecular data and made it easy to work with and understand.','The Data Platform for Medicine','[\"New York City\"]','SolveBio'),('Tute Genomics is cloud-based software that can rapidly analyze entire human genomes. The cost of whole genome sequencing is dropping rapidly and we are in the middle of a genomic revolution, with the potential to transform medicine. Tute is opening a new door for personalized medicine by helping healthcare providers analyze human genomes for health & disease.','Cloud-based Whole Genome Analysis for Precision Medicine','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','Tute Genomics'),('Exo Labs is the first company to create cameras that directly connect microscopes to iPads and iPhones, enabling amazing collaborative experiences for science and education.\n\nExo Labs produces the Focus Camera system, accessories, and app - enabling users to seamlessly connect iOS devices to virtually any microscope, opening up the unseen world to exploration.  Interchangeable lenses allow the Focus Camera to be used as a standalone imaging system for viewing and recording dissections, looking at bugs, leaves, coins, electronics, etc.  The system can even be connected to telescopes and other imaging systems.  Exo Lab’s products are sold through their website and through value-added retailers around the world.\n','iPad-connected cameras and apps for science and education','[\"Seattle\"]','Exo Labs'),('MedWhat is a personal medical assistant app providing automatic personalized answers to your health and medical questions.  Users can create a quick anonymous health profile telling MedWhat their age, gender, and current medical conditions. This allows MedWhat to provide personalized answers and have a contextual conversation with the user by following up with questions and pushing health notifications to your phone. MedWhat uses natural language processing and bioinformatics to understand and create medical logic.  The team is made of statistics and computer science engineers, and a medical adviser from Stanford University Hospital. The free MedWhat app is currently ranked as a new and top medical app by the Apple app store and already being used by thousands of people.','Personalized Healthcare Assistant providing answers to your health and medical questions.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','MedWhat'),('Problem\n\nCompanies in the Consumer Packaged Goods and Food & Beverage industries rely on flavors and fragrances but have no scientific method to measure their effect on the consumer brain.\n\nSolution\n\nWe provide a scientific, reproducible way to record tastes and smells, to digitally represent them, and see how they affect the consumer brain to speed, simplify and lower R&D, product development, manufacturing and QA costs.','Digitizing the Human Sense of Smell & Taste','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Aromyx'),('Spartan is bringing complete sample-to-result DNA testing systems to medicine. Spartan’s technology fully integrates DNA collection, extraction and analysis, with an intuitive interface that is easy to operate. For the first time, healthcare providers and their patients can get DNA results on demand.','Sample to result in 1 hour','[]','Spartan Bioscience'),(NULL,'','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Syapse'),('Spiral Genetics makes high performance software for analyzing DNA.  We help researchers, pharmaceutical companies and clinicians derive meaningful results from their data. Using our proprietary distributed computing algorithm on large DNA datasets, Spiral Genetics quickly, affordably and accurately identifies the genetic causal mechanisms for disease and drug metabolism. \n\nThis technology significantly accelerates genomic research, reduces the cost of clinical trials and enables new diagnostics.','Data Mining for Genomics','[\"Seattle\"]','Spiral Genetics'),('Angel Capital Group invests in early stage companies with great potential.  We invest domestically without preference to geography.  We typically invest within six months before and after a company begins to generate revenue.  We are looking for great companies in which to invest and investors who would like to join an organized angel network.','We invest in exciting early-stage companies.','[\"Denver\"]','Angel Capital Group'),('ZernikeMeta Ventures has extensive experience in managing public-private venture capital funds that co-invest with angel investors in various regions including Southern Europe, Central Europe, Eastern Europe. Primary industry of focus are ICT, Biotech, Medical Devices, Manufacturing companies.\nActive funds are in Italy, Slovenia and Poland for an overall amount of around 90Mln Euro under management.','Early stage investor','[\"Europe\"]','ZernikeMeta Ventures'),('Our team is currently working on a forehead band for sleeping, but not a normal one though. Apart from modern design and comfortable using, our band will be an advanced diagnostic electronical device. It will be cordlessly connected with an application on a smartphone in order to monitor our sleep to wake us up in the most adequate moment. This should contribute to making our sleep more effective and reveille – pleasant. Our data are collected using technologies used in hospitals.','Biomedical signals processing devices','[\"Warsaw\"]','Intelclinic'),('Synbiota radically reduces barrier-to-entry for creating blockbuster Life Science, Health, Cleantech, and Greentech products by virtualizing the entire Synthetic Biology research and development pipeline.\n\nWith Synbiota, anyone with a web-connected device, and a desire to change the world can leverage Biotechnology to create disruptive applications and products in medicine, materials, food and fuel.\n\nUsing Synbiota, groups of any size, or even an individual can, with the click of a button, create a virtual research institute complete with DNA development tools, integrated data storage and management, colleagues, secure communication, attribution, IP, and performance metrics.\n\nwww.synbiota.com','GitHub for Bio, & Beyond','[\"Montreal\"]','Synbiota'),('BaseTrace provides an attractive solution to settle accountability and liability issues for both communities and industry using environmentally friendly DNA technology. The tracers a provide a powerful, unique fingerprint that can follow any fluid source and be used to determine whether there are leakages or efficiency losses--the next step in DNA technology applications.','DNA Fingerprinting for Fracking','[\"Durham\"]','BaseTrace'),('A new way to read, organize and annotate scientific papers in your browser. \n','Journal discussion platform for scientists','[\"San Diego\"]','Plasmyd'),('Desktop Genetics makes software to make biotechnology easier. The company has developed AutoClone™, an automated software platform that enables the optimal design, construction, management and exchange of DNA constructs to be deployed in vector/plasmid manufacturing, genome-editing, protein production and Synthetic Biology work-flows. Our products have a meaningful impact on companies everyday.\n','Faster and more accurate genetic engineering.','[\"London\"]','Desktop Genetics'),('Tired of investing in X for Y?  Join us and solve a REAL problem. Insulin-dependent diabetics have a daily grind that is humbling:\n\n- 4-6 injections/day, basal insulin in the morning, mealtime insulin before each snack/meal;\n- Constant finger pricks to monitor blood sugar; and\n- You are always worried about what you eat... diabetes is a \"lifetime sentence.\"\n\nThat\'s ~6,000 procedures/year.  We solve all 3 problems with a true once-a-day insulin.   Ask any diabetic, this would be _huge_.','Once-a-day insulin for type I/II diabetes, that gives patients a chance at a normal life.','[\"Houston\"]','Sensulin'),('Integrated strategy, technology and marketing company committed to helping healthcare companies build long-lasting, profitable relationships with key opinion leaders (KOLs).','Creating Customer Connectivity™','[\"New York City\"]','Voltage'),('Enables research scientists in academia and corporations to interact directly with genomic data, rather than requiring the expertise of a bioinformatics specialist. This increases our potential market by two orders of magnitude. Our open science, cloud-based platform provides for storage and management of high throughout sequencing data, analysis and exploration using proven, journal-published methods and applications, and enables on-the-fly creation of genome browsers that allow researchers to interact with and visualize their genomic data in an entirely new way, helping them to detect previously hidden patterns and insights. This dramatically increases research and development productivity, especially for biomarker discovery, in applications such as therapeutics, molecular diagnostics, biotech, and agribusiness.','Next generation genomic data management, exploration, and visualization','[\"San Mateo\"]','Maverix Biomics'),('Sialix is developing two distinct products based on the same discoveries from the Ajit Varki lab at UCSD in glycobiology and cancer.\n\n1) Therapeutic antibodies targeting glycan alterations seen in multiple solid tumors.\n2) Anti-inflammatory nutrition products targeting these same cancer-associated glycans found in dietary red meat.','cancer therapeutic with early exit potential','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Sialix'),('DataGenno is an interactive portal containing a database on genetic and rare diseases, a search engine for differenial diagnosis of diseases and a professional web page fo users. Th portal helps healthcare professionals, scientists, among others to find the most updated information on diseases. There is no similar portal offering these services in the web the way we will do. The portal is free of charge.','Portal for health care professionals and patients','[\"Chicago\", \"Rio De Janeiro\"]','DataGenno'),('A PCR machine is essentially a xerox machine for DNA. PCR machines are expensive ($3,000+), but necessary for doing most DNA work. This puts DNA discovery out of reach of many. We\'re changing that!\n\nWe engineered OpenPCR over the past year and started shipping kits worldwide in July.  Researchers, teachers, and hobbyists bought 48 OpenPCR kits (and counting!) for $25,000 in sales.\n\nNow we need investment for salaries and initial prototyping of a new fully-assembled product.','DNA on your desktop','[\"San Francisco\"]','OpenPCR'),('Sanguine is a technology-enabled company innovating at the intersection of personalized medicine, biobanking, and biomedical research. It has a simple and attractive, proven business model. Sanguine collects blood samples and associated medical data from patients diagnosed with specific conditions. It processes those samples to extract biospecimen such as cells, serum, plasma and DNA, and stores them along with the medical data. It then sells the biospecimen and data to academic and pharmaceutical entities for research purposes.  \n\nProblem & Solution:\nTraditionally, research companies need to wait for physicians to set up appointments with patients and to find some willing to sign up. Patients go to Sanguine because Sanguine offers increased transparency in the research process, showing them where samples are used and how they advance biomedical research in areas they care about. ','Empowering Patients & Accelerating Personalized Medicine R&D; Biological/Clinical Data','[\"Santa Monica\"]','Sanguine BioSciences'),('Our goal is to develop the first globally recognized mainstream brand focused on bioplastic durable consumer products, made from plants!  \n\nWe entered the market in 2010 with protective covers for smart phones made from bioplastics and are the first and only brand in the world producing USDA Certified, 100% bio-based bioplastic smart phone covers. \n\nOur next target market is TOYS for 0-2 years old babies where we can emphasize the inherent health safety of fully natural and biobased materials we use, in addition to environmental and sustainability benefits of bioplastic products. The entry product line up will consist of teethers, rattles, cutlery and stacking toys. Bioserie toys will hit the market towards the end of 2013.','Bioplastic consumer products made of plants','[\"Hong Kong\"]','Bioserie'),('Target aging to treat disease. \n\nWe are a seed fund with closed capital, finding, funding, and helping companies to do the above. \n\n','Invest in healthy life','[\"San Francisco\"]','The Longevity Fund '),('UBM is applying synthetic biology and genetic engineering to improve the productivity of organisms used to produce 10% of worldwide copper. We are engineering novel forms of these organisms to improve the efficiency of the process and to apply the process to other types of ore. ','Improving the productivity of bacteria used in the mining industry.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Universal Bio Mining'),('3Scan creates new analytical perspectives on the structure of disorders such as cancer, cardiovascular disease, Alzheimer\'s, and strokes.  The patented Knife-Edge Scanning Microscope allows cells, tissues, and organs to be seen in 3D at microscopic resolution.\n\nImmediate applications are in drug discovery, biotech, basic research, and will eventually be applied clinically. Current techniques are manually handled by humans, thus orders of magnitude slower and not suitable for 3D modeling.','Automated pathology','[\"San Francisco\"]','3Scan'),('In the next several years the pharmaceutical industry will hit a wall.  The volume of data that must be considered to make informed decisions is increasing at an exponential rate and is becoming overwhelming.   Current resources do not adequately aggregate both scientific and market data or enable the level of insight required to transform this complex information into actionable decisions.  Relay has developed a software platform, The Relay Innovation Engine, to addresses these issues faced by corporate strategy, intellectual property, business development, licensing, and human resources departments in the biopharma industry. By aggregating data from public and private sources, displaying this information in unique dashboards, and using advanced machine learning algorithms to provide users with actionable insights, The Relay Innovation Engine provide its users increased efficiency and competitive advantages.','Harnessing Software Analytics to Improve Drug Delivery Efficiency','[\"Boston\"]','Relay Technology Management'),('Evolutionary Solutions is an early stage biotech venture developing a novel technology for synthetic oligonucleotide-free DNA synthesis, capable of scaling from primer- to genome-length at the benchtop.\nSynthesis technology is severely limiting progress in synthetic biology; it is a fundamentally enabling tool, but has shortcomings including high error rates, short construct lengths, and time (long orders may take weeks). Our solution allows the creation of genes in a single \"write\" process. ','DNA on Demand (TM) long-write DNA synthesis','[\"Mountain View\"]','Evolutionary Solutions'),('Prime Genomics has identified a signature for identifying breast cancer from saliva samples using its proprietary tool for evaluating the expression patterns of a large number of genes thermodynamically.\n\nCurrently the compliance rate, in developed countries, is 50% for women who should get mammograms. In developing countries, with compliance rates around 5%, access to mammography is the challenge to early Dx. Testing saliva samples in a Drs office at low cost with minimal necessary infrastructure is an effective way of increasing Dx.','Population screening for breast cancer through salivary samples. ','[\"San Francisco\"]','Prime Genomics'),('','','[\"Moscow\"]','Universe Ventures'),('','','[\"Mountain View\"]','H4Y Corp'),('Leveraging a proprietary diagnostic device, assay, and analytics, Cellanyx\'s testing service will use live-cell analysis of our patent-pending pool of biomarkers from a new and proprietary class of markers.  Based on cellular behavior and bio-mechanics rather than gene sequences, Cellanyx will provide urologists predictive and quantitative measures of metastatic potential and local aggressiveness. ','Harnessing the Predictive Power of Biomarkers to Revolutionize Prostate Tumor Treatment','[\"Boston\"]','Cellanyx Diagnostics'),('Neurogastrx is a pharmaceutical company developing products to treat gastrointestinal disorders, focusing on diseases where patients have clear unmet needs and leveraging our expertise in neurogastroenterology.\n\nNeurogastrx\'s lead product, NG101, is a peripherally restricted, selective and potent dopamine D2/D3 receptor antagonist. Neurogastrx has generated data showing the potential value of NG101 in treating chronic nausea such as gastroparesis. Chronic nausea and vomiting is a condition greatly affecting the life of millions of patients in the US alone. Currently approved treatments, although effective, have side effects potentially debilitating, or life-threatening.\n\nThe pipeline also includes NG202 for Irritable Bowel Syndrome with Diarrhea (IBS-D) and NG301 for constipation associated with Parkinson\'s disease. \n','Pharmaceutical products for gastrointestinal disorders','[\"Campbell\"]','Neurogastrx'),('BioHealthonomics Inc. is a research and development biotechnology & healthcare company dedicated to developing and commercializing high-impact, effective and side effect free therapeutics that address critical unmet needs in the treatment of migraine headaches, Parkinson\'s disease and ALS. ','Migraine headaches, Parkinson\'s disease, ALS: Treatment and prevention leading to cure.','[\"Santa Monica\"]','BioHealthonomics '),('Mcule.com: online drug discovery platform for pharma and biotech companies.\n\nMcule.com provides an easy-to-use web interface integrating all the necessary steps in drug discovery.\n\nMolecular modeling and compound delivery components for hit identification and lead optimization are already implemented. Bioassay database is currently being set up.\n\nVision: Speed up the drug discovery process tremendously by providing the ultimate drug discovery platform supporting the whole drug discovery process.','Do drug discovery lightning fast!','[\"Budapest\"]','mcule'),('We are seeking to discover disease-modifiying drugs for two important indications in Parkinson\'s disease: neuroprotection and improved Quality of Life measures in early patients and to delay the onset of L-Dopa induced dyskinesia.  We are using a highly innovative approach, based on the principles of network pharmacology, to generate multi-interventional drugs that are able to target the complex biology that drives the disease. In order to shorten development time and accelerate time to market (with an aim to generating earlier investor returns), the main focus is on identifying proprietary drugs (single drugs or combinations) with existing safety profiles that can be repurposed to a newly discovered indication.','Disease-Modifying drugs for Parkinson\'s','[\"Oxford\"]','MitoDys Therapeutics limited'),('Journal Lab makes it easy to navigate the universe of published scientific literature. \n\nWe do this by incentivizing scientists to share the notes that they take every time the read a paper: a short summary and one or two opinions about that paper\'s integrity. This makes it easy for doctors, investors, biotech startups, and other scientists to browse the literature and see what experts think of it.','Yelp for cancer research.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Journal Lab'),('Brier & Thorn is a Managed Security Service Provider (MSSP) that delivers Penetration Testing through a subscription service in a scalable, multi-tenant cloud platform.\n\nThe company\'s flagship product, RedInk, is vulnerability management in the cloud; allowing companies to eliminate the painful headache of managing, reacting to, and remediating vulnerabilities in their systems and network.\n\nThrough our partnership with the Cyber Defense Center at UT Dallas, customers can get a real-time feed into zero-day vulnerabilities from the \"dark web\" that affects their organization before the vulnerabilities become weaponized into exploits. This gives customers active foresight into exploits and malware about to hit their organization before anyone else.\n\nCustomers can import vulnerability scan results from third-party scanners, such as Qualys, Nessus, Retina, and vulnerabilities found during Brier & Thorn\'s Penetration Testing service; making RedInk a cloud service that can be used by anyone.','Penetration Testing delivered through managed services and a cloud-based SaaS platform','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Brier | Thorn'),('ArborVita Associates (AVA) is a biotechnology company that leverages a simple and faster way to modify DNA using a product called DRAP (Drosophila Recombination-Associated Protein). AVA intends to use DRAP to change the way genes are manipulated in order to rapidly advance biomedical research, drug development, and the production of novel human therapies. ','Fast, Simple, Cost Effective Genome Editing','[\"Chicago\"]','ArborVita Associates'),('     The mission of ZappyLab is to create a user-populated online repository of science protocols.  The repository will contain free, up-to-date, and evolving protocols in biomedical sciences, chemistry, medicine, and other disciplines.  A social networking layer will enable scientists to connect by expertise, with geographically proximal option, to troubleshoot the use of similar techniques.\n     Biology is hypothesis-driven scientific cooking.  Protocols are recipes and reagents are ingredients.  ZappyLab’s protocol repository will create the equivalent of allrecipes.com for the scientific community.\n     The protocol repository will revolutionize scientific laboratory practice.  It will lead to more efficient research and will become an integral part of the daily work of an experimental scientist.  Importantly, it will create a new venue for researchers to share new method findings.','Allrecipes for biomedical protocols','[\"Berkeley\"]','ZappyLab'),('We focus on the natural products compound discovery space with a primary focus in the $500+ billion pharmaceutical industry.  Compounds are derived from the highly biologically active micro-organism consortia found in the natural aquatic environment.  We will acquire these compounds that are uniquely accessible to us today at the necessary scale by leveraging our proprietary, state of the art technologies, deep research skills and relationships to become a premier partner in drug discovery.  ','Novel Compounds from Natural Unculturable Microorganisms','[\"Dublin, OH\"]','Biosortia Pharmaceuticals '),('SiliconHillsNews.com is a news organization covering the technology community in the Austin and San Antonio region, known as Silicon Hills. ','News about the Austin and San Antonio tech community ','[\"Austin\"]','SiliconHillsNews'),('CloudClinica is the 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials. This is the first Cloud Data Capture (CDC) system, to empower business users to build clinical studies themselves, remove today\'s high IT dependency and eliminate any financial barrier of entry through a pay-per-CRF pricing and a solution five times cheaper than existing solutions. CloudClinica offers a built-in integration layer for additional eClinical systems on its fully validated and compliant platform.','The 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials introducing Cloud Data Capture (CDC)','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','CloudClinica'),('Rodin Therapeutics is leveraging groundbreaking biology and a quantum-mechanics inspired chemistry approach to develop new drugs for Alzheimer\'s disease. \n\nPatients with Alzheimer\'s Disease and other causes of cognitive decline lack effective therapies to reverse or slow the progression of the disease and loss of quality of life. \n\nRodin\'s novel drug target, when inhibited, can enhance the expression of genes critical for the formation of new memories. Animal models of Alzheimer\'s treated in this way show a profound improvement in learning.   The Rodin compound, when approved, could help slow cognitive decline and improve quality of life for patients throughout the course of their disease. \n','Novel treatments for Alzheimer\'s disease','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Rodin Therapeutics'),('PaperBox lets researchers to share scientific publications easy within team. It also lets them to manage their same library over many computers.','PaperBox, Share Paper Easy!','[\"San Jose\"]','PaperBox'),('We have developed a scalable, multipurpose system for production of human therapeutic proteins that provides us with a tremendous cost advantage.  Our first product is factor IX for the treatment of hemophilia B.  This is currently an underserved $1.4 billion market.  Only about 25% of the worlds patients are adequately treated due to limitations of cost and supply.  Our product can be produced and sold for about 20% of the cost of current recombinant factor IX.  For comparison, the entire yearly supply of recombinant factor IX is about 2.6 kg, produced in an animal cell line in multiple 2000L batches.  Our human cell line could produce 2.6 kg in a 100L culture in six months.  Our system can be used to produce large quantities of essentially any protein.  Cell Machines has intellectual property protecting the cells and the system.  We expect to follow factor IX with several other proteins such as factor VIII for hemophilia A and alpha-1-antitrypsin for COPD.   ','High efficiency production of human therapeutic proteins','[\"Houston\"]','Cell Machines, Inc.'),('NordicHug’s goal is to bring cleaning and disinfection into 21st century - instead of developing harsh chemicals, that are harmful for the user and the environment, our scientists are putting all of their effort into understanding nature and how it fights bacteria. \nWe have developed an innovative and effective natural based formula for cleaning and disinfection of touch screens. This innovation is supported by multiple patents pending and is recognized by the Foundation for Finnish Inventions.','Innovative natural based disinfection solutions for touch screens','[\"Finland\"]','NordicHug'),('Secure Send is the first choice for companies looking for an intuitive, efficient way to stay compliant by sending sensitive, confidential communications securely through the Internet. Help your company build trust - use Secure Send.','Connect. Build. Trust.','[\"Pleasanton\"]','SecureSend'),('Boreal is developing a new antibody discovery technology that involves breaking tolerance in vivo to generate broader antibody diversity against tough to immunize drug targets, like GPCRs and other transmembrane proteins. ','Next Gen Antibody Platform','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Boreal Therapeutics'),('Miinome is the first solution to provide direct-to-consumer genetic data\nmanagement, storage, and brokerage.  Our platform allows anyone to quickly see recommendations for a growing list of genetic traits, and take action immediately.  We provide a safe, and secure method for sharing traits with marketers, researchers, and family or friends.  Our platform is always opt-in, and the data is always yours.','The first member controlled human genetic marketplace','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Miinome'),('Glytrix is an early stage biotech company that is developing a novel platform technology for tissue healing and regeneration. We are leading this development with Pellagen, a locally delivered drug in late stage preclinical development for promoting healthy scar-free healing in the skin.','Pellagen promotes scar-free healing in the skin','[\"San Francisco\"]','Glytrix'),('Contact lenses with disappearing ink. Why?  Outside the eye they are hard to find, can get mixed up between right and left eyes & most importantly can be flipped and inserted backwards into the eye. This is a disruptive technology that will provide a significant edge to contact lens manufactures - in addition to increased margins.     ','Contact Lenses With Disappearing Ink that are Better, Friendlier & Safer   ','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Leuko Tech'),('Venture Catalysts is a company focused on commercialization of technologies through entrepreneurship. By supporting visionary researchers and entrepreneurs releasing the full potential of their technologies, the company acts as a catalyst on the development of new technology–based ventures','Shaping Technologies into Business','[\"Porto\"]','Venture Catalysts'),('ImmuneSafe® is composed by mesenchymal cells isolated from the bone marrow of healthy donors and expanded using Cell2B\'s proprietary technology. These cells are able of modulating the immune and inflammatory responses in our bodies. There are no compatibility issues and no need for matching donor and recipient, making this a much more attractive business model that other cell therapies currently on the market.\n\nCell2B\'s proprietary technology was licensed and developed at MIT during the founder\'s PhD work. \n\nAn early clinical study of the technology showed that it was safe and, in three patients already suffering from Graft-versus-Host-Disease, resulted in either complete or partial response.\n\nWe have Orphan Designation for ImmuneSafe for Graft-versus-Host-Disease.\n\nImmune and inflammatory disorders have no effective treatment available today, affecting affect more than 20 M people in the U.S. and Europe and leading to 3 M deaths/year. ','Treat transplant rejection','[\"Lisbon\"]','Cell2B - Advanced Therapeutics S.A.'),('Innovation Choice Group is bringing to market a professional network that allows vetted scientists to crowdsource answers. By providing a community of verified experts, users can extend their reach and increase their professional clout. Using the portal allows these professionals to voice their inquiries to the world.','Life Science Social Network','[\"San Francisco\"]','Innovation Choice Group '),('InSilico DB https://insilicodb.org is a complete web-based solution for storing and managing genomics data. 100,000s of public profiles are pre-installed and ready to analyze.\n\nInSilico DB takes care of the data issues with cutting-edge genomics applications in cancer and hereditary diseases. Research hospitals can use InSilico DB as a complete solution for getting started in genomics, to increasing patient benefit.','Taking care of the informatics in bioinformatics','[\"Brussels\"]','InSilico Genomics S.A.'),(NULL,'Private research and development consulting.','[]','ASTRO Ltd'),('Through the purposed application, GeneDrop looks to create a computational pipeline and database capable of correlating human genetic variation with pharmaceutical molecule efficacy. This program has application in the identifying patient subpopulation for prescription labeling via pharmacogenomics. This can also be applied to the resuscitation of abandoned molecules through evaluation of gene-drug interactions in the case of adverse event reporting.','The Informatics Pipeline to Correlate Drug Response with Genomic Variablity ','[\"San Francisco\"]','GeneDrop'),('GenomeCruzer - real-time 3D for integrative visualization and analysis of genomic data. See genomecruzer.com for details.\n\nGilgamesh - Interactive 3D Visual Mining for Big Data\nGilgamesh uses high-performance 3D graphics to create an interactive 3D scene representing the data elements, where hundreds of thousands of items can be visualized at once, together with the relations among them.\n','Interactive 3D tools for Big Data','[\"Turin\"]','Kairos3D'),('Ardic Instruments is a high precision analytical instruments company developing a pipeline of products ranging from atomic force microscopy, single-point vibrometry, and molecular diagnostics. \n\nOur disruptive core technologies allow us to dramatically lower the cost of production for scientific instruments. We serve the global scientific community by designing and manufacturing innovative and flexible instruments delivered with unrivaled service.','Precision Analytical Instruments','[\"Taipei\"]','Ardic Instruments'),('Soundbites targets the root causes of noise-induced hearing loss, and stops it. Soundbites is an FDA drug. Except it isn\'t. Soundbites is the world\'s first commercially available micronutrient pharamaceutical for hearing preservation. Safe, fully-patented, directly derived from pioneering research at University of Michigan Medical School.  NIH and European Commission-funded clinical trials are underway. Leading pro musicians and audio engineers are signed up for our field trials. ','World\'s first commercially available micronutrient pharmaceutical for hearing preservation','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','Hearing Health Science'),('Excelerol is a new cutting edge nutraceutical dietary supplement. Excelerol supports memory, focus, concentration and alertness. The ingredients in excelerol are backed by extensive clinical and scientific research. \n\nSeveral of the ingredients in excelerol like citicoline and phosphatidylserine may be important chemical nutrients for the brain.','Live Better Think Smarter','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Accelerated Intelligence  '),('The ilumivu System combines wearable biosensors, mobile apps and online patient-centered platforms to help facilitate patient behavior change.\n\nThe entire system can be replicated and customized for health and mental health providers wishing to provide continuous physiological monitoring, real-time interventions and patient-centered care to their clients. \n\nModule architecture allows rapid replication, customization and set-up of new systems.','Facilitating behavioral change for better health','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','ilumivu'),('We are developing innovative solutions for life sciences. Some of our projects:\n\nNimbusGene (www.nimbusgene.com): Platform as a Service (PaaS) to perform bioinformatics analysis in a cloud environment with a friendly interface to manage and collaborate their genetics projects.\n\nDodo (www.dodofunding.com): first crowdfunding platform for genetics project.','Creative ideas and innovative solutions for life sciences.','[\"Santiago\"]','Beagle Bioinformatics'),('Our first product is a drinkable mouthwash made of natural ingredients and is formulated to meet the guidelines of The American Academy of Pediatrics and American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry in its recommendation for cavity prevention.  Our second product has two active ingredients that specifically eliminate the cavity-causing bacteria and prevent the bacteria from adhering to the surface of the teeth. ','Pediatric Drinkable Anti-Cavity Mouthwash','[\"Hamilton\"]','Apollonia Health'),('- Biophotonic Scanner to screen non-invasively antioxidant levels and provide a nutritional health score.\n- Cloud-based management software for Health and Wellness Services Providers, to record and track end-users progress, interact with them through a mobile application.\n- Cloud-based management software for Employers and Health Plans, to track populations progress anonymously, to build health-contingent and outcome-based Benefits programs through nutritional health (antioxidants) score improvement goals setting.\n- Mobile application for management of nutrition data, track progress and interact with service provider. In the future, application will provide benefit (financial incentives) and health score driven discovery services from items at food retailers and restaurants menus. ','Nutrition Wellness Platform to help Populations eat healthy, daily and 1 person at a time','[\"San Francisco\"]','NUFITSCAN'),('Dodo is a novel solution for biotechnology exploration and science outreach. It is the first crowdfunding platform exclusively for biotech projects. Our goal is to promote the scientific knowledge, funding low and high-risk but promising biotech projects, approximating ordinary people to the development of science. It is a powerful new incentive for scientists to engage the public with science: the potential for raising money for research directly from the public. Ordinary people is excited with science! Now they have the opporunity to be part of an important research by making direct donations, receiving or not a pledge for its donation. Those pledges can be even a participation as a object of study. Kind of nerd? Maybe, but we believe it\'s cool to have your gene sequenced or to have your name in a new gene discovered. ','Crowdfunding for biotech projects','[\"Santiago\"]','Dodo Biotech Crowdfunding'),('Obtaining a homogenous population of cells from a complex mixture is essential for improved downstream applications like QPCR, genomics, and imaging. Fluorescence Activated Cell Sorters (FACS) analyze and sort thousands of cells per minute and are essential systems for most biomedical research labs ($1B instrument market). NanoCellect was spunout from UCSD to commercialize a disruptive technology for analyzing and sorting cells at 1/5th the cost of current systems. The initial product, WOLF Cell Sorter is a small, affordable, and easy-to-use bench-top cell sorter with features and performance comparable to high-end complex flow cytometers that are primarily found in shared core facilities. The platform is accompanied by disposable microfluidic chips that makes setup and sorting easier while reducing contamination and improving cell viability during sorting. Since inception, NanoCellect has won 7 grants and contracts from the NIH for over $3.3M in non-dilutional funding.\n\n','Cell sorting made accessible (CoinStar for Cell Biologists)','[\"San Diego\"]','NanoCellect Biomedical, Inc.'),('We develop fluorescently labeled antibodies for the diagnostics and life science research industries. Our new low production cost technology is based on the novel combination of fluorescent quantum dot nanoparticles and hen antibodies purified from egg yolk, this competitive advantage will allow antibody technology to colonize the diagnostics industry!','Inexpensive fluorescent labeled antibodies','[\"Santiago\"]','ImmunotEGG'),('Greenstreak helps startups grow, find the right people, create high performing teams, develop employees & promote from within to build a strong culture of success based on merit and core values.','Recruiting & Growth Consulting for startups','[\"San Francisco\"]','Greenstreak Consulting'),('Milkeeper is the first product developed by Phage Technologies S.A for the animal feed industry, which is focused on the prevention of infectious diarrhea syndrome (SDI) caused by Escherichia coli in calves. Its technology is based on bacteriophages, which are highly specific particles and biological origin that act as controllers of bacteria naturally in ecosystems.','Applying high-impact technologies in animal and human food industry.','[\"Santiago\"]','Phage Technologies S.A'),(NULL,'Lab equipment with cool design, high connectivity & easy-to-share results.','[\"Santiago\"]','Pump!'),('We produce biological compounds in microalgaes. \nIn particular, we are interested in the synthesis of recombinant proteins using microalgae as bioreactors','Biological Products generated in microalgaes.','[\"Santiago\"]','Green Biofactory'),('NEON - Creative Labware develops innovative tools for the Life Science research lab that stand out on their design and low cost achieved by integrating consumer technologies into labware. Currently we commercialize a Gel Documentation system (OctoDoc) with added functionality such as WiFi broadcasting of pictures and a novel design proposal, and various accesories that make the life of the scientist easier. \r\n\r\nWe are working on the development of a Fluorescent imaging system highly competitive in price and functionality that will bring the cost of this technology down to a forth. \r\n\r\nWe constantly interact with our clients, as we are in part consumers of these technologies. Through these interactions we come up with new products with these attributes which come to refresh a market in much need of design, colors and easy access technology.  \r\n\r\n','Technology and Design for the Life Sciences Lab','[\"Santiago\"]','NEON - Creative Labware'),('Planet Hatch is an entrepreneurial hub with a core accelerator program named ACcelR8. \n\nACcelR8 is a 12 week accelerator program featuring 2 cohorts per year. \n\nWe\'re looking for the most ambitious and talented entrepreneurs who are capable of disrupting large markets with their startup. We are on the prowl for companies within the Knowledge sector (E.g. ICT, Digital Media, Bio Tech, Clean Tech, Aerospace...etc)\n\nThrough our network, we provide instrumental resources such as funding, workshops, mentorship and other programs. ','Connecting startups to the best resources','[\"Fredericton\"]','Planet Hatch'),('Our company is bringing stem cell therapy to the skin rejuvenation field, with a fast and inexpensive method to use your own cells to make your skin look young again!','Next-generation skin rejuvenation','[\"Santiago\"]','Cell Therapy'),('We create highly realistic virtual laboratories for science education and add edutainment elements to increase the student learning and engagement.\n\nOur prototypes are already very successful and used many high schools and universities world-wide.\nWe are unique, because we build ultra high quality products, with photo-realistic 3D labs, fun gamified missions, and allow teachers to create their own laboratories to fit their curriculum, using a simple Lab Builder tool.\nAnd we have an awesome team.','Fun Science Education with Virtual Labs','[\"Copenhagen\"]','Labster'),('Intrepid’s genomic/genetic data management system supports any and all NGS data, along with SNP and genotyping datasets.  A mantra of ours is, sequence once, genotype many times.\n\nWe are uniquely built to support the analysis, delivery, management and publication of genotypes derived from sequencing. \n\nRegister for a free account:\nhttps://server1.intrepidbio.com/FeatureBrowserPrivate/account/createfree','Genomic/genetic data management system facilitates access, collaboration & publication.','[\"Louisville\"]','Intrepid Bioinformatics'),('Previously \'neglected\' infectious diseases, such as Dengue Fever and Chagas Disease, are emerging as global health problems and are becoming increasingly relevant to the for-profit pharmaceutical industry as a result of shifting population dynamics and incentivized research paradigms.\r\n\r\nReaniMed Biotech develops breakthrough therapies for infectious diseases through an approach to drug discovery that is designed to reduce financial and scientific risk at all stages of development.  Our proprietary discovery tools and expedited development strategy allow us to rapidly develop novel therapies to treat these debilitating diseases. \r\n\r\nReaniMed will be entering Phase II clinical trials with our lead Dengue Fever therapeutic early in 2014.  ','Breakthrough Therapies for Emerging Infectious Disease','[\"San Francisco\"]','ReaniMed Biotech'),('Pareto generates novel, high-value chemicals using flexible enzymatic and microbial platforms - which together enable an 80/20 & long-tail approach to leverage success from one product to another.','We create designer molecules: In the near-term consumer goods; later for high impact.','[\"Berkeley\"]','Pareto Biotechnologies'),('A 90 day accelerator specifically to help idea stage startups in the field of Synthetic Biology cross that valley. \n\nThose accepted into SynBio axlr8r will receive:\n*$30k in funding\n*Bench space in a Wet Lab\n*Mentorship from some of the top experts in biotech and business. \n\nOur first batch will run from in the Summer of 2014, from May to August and take place in the scenic Cork City, Ireland.\n\nThe call for applications is currently open.','Design, Build and Launch your Synthetic Biology Vision!','[\"Cork\"]','SynBio axlr8r'),('The LifeCradle preserves, monitors and transports hearts used in transplantation and will replace the picnic cooler currently used.  The LifeCradle has been proven in published research at leading academic research centers to significantly extend the life of procured hearts from 4 to 24 hours.  Over seventy percent of donated hearts are NOT transplanted in many cases because of a lack of preservation time in the picnic cooler...the LifeCradle will save lives and improve transplant outcomes.  ','Organ Preservation Device for Transplantation','[\"Dallas\"]','Organ Transport Systems'),('Top-tier facilities, mentors and community for exceptional startups in the rapidly-converging worlds of life science, healthcare and information technology. ','Boston\'s leading high tech incubator ','[\"Boston\"]','Venture Development Center'),('Longevity Biotech is developing novel therapeutics to treat the unmet needs of Cardiovascular, Metabolics and Oncology patients worldwide.  Our Hybridtide molecular scaffold has unprecedented and medically necessary characteristics which enable us to pursue novel mechanisms of action, a requirement in todays competitive biotechnology marketplace.','','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Longevity Biotech'),('Immudicon is developing MacroVax, an intracellular vaccine delivery technology, to activate the immune system against cancer and potentially other disease indications.\n\nInitial research & trials of our technology have been shown in vitro in both mouse and human cell types, as well as in vivo to explicate T-cell specificity to tumor antigens, cytokine activation profiles, and early-stage prophylactic trials.','Training the body\'s immune system to defeat cancer & other deadly diseases.','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Immudicon'),('Biomatters creates applications for omics analysis.\n\nOur WebApp Development Group builds production quality, public- and private cloud based responsive web applications to deliver the highest usability and visualized insight for applied genomics workflows. By collaborating with clinical and molecular diagnostics developers, we build the platforms that crunch their data and deliver results reports to their customers. We turn genomic research workflows into production-ready, regulatory-compliant diagnostic pipelines.\n\nGeneious, our desktop app for research biologists, features tools for DNA/RNA/protein sequence analysis, data management, database searching, and publication-quality image generation. Geneious is used by university, government, and medical research labs worldwide in disciplines such as agricultural genomics, evolutionary biology, biofuels, synthetic biology, microbiology, virology, and next-gen sequence analysis.\n','Apps for omics analysis.','[\"New Zealand\"]','Biomatters'),('ZSG’s platform technology will address the major pain points in key areas of genomics research (what can be studied, the pace at which data can be understood, and the cost of discovery research) and thereby become a valued resource to the genomics industry, molecular diagnostics, and the future of personalized medicine. The ZSG approach provides key answers to market challenges:\n\n• Dramatically superior read lengths: 20,000+ bp\n• Single-molecule capability \n• Very competitive costs and throughput \n• The ability to perform applications that cannot be done today \n\nThe Company created its unique approach by combining existing commercially proven and available capabilities into a powerful, patented technology. ZSG technology provides high-quality genetic sequencing with the exceptional advantage of extremely long read lengths and single-molecule sampling. When commercialized, ZSG’s technology will provide solutions that make it unique in the marketplace, with significant cost efficiencies.','Third Generation DNA sequencing','[\"Wakefield, MA\"]','ZS Genetics'),('FertiLab’s aim is to grow innovative scientists into the next generation of Biotechnology entrepreneurs and workers in Lane County. ','  The Next Generation Community Lab ','[\"Eugene\"]','Fertilab Thinkubator'),('LabGenius allows you to securely design, view and share DNA sequences in an intuitive and easy-to-use way, allowing you to convert all those long wasteful hours at the computer into valuable hours in the lab.\n\nDNA is the code for life and as areas such as Synthetic Biology grow and develop into core industries it is vital that there are tools available to streamline how sequences are designed, viewed and shared.','Design, View and Share DNA online','[\"London\"]','LabGenius'),('Helix Health Initiative: Expected average contribution per individual client of $1,000 annually or $100 monthly. Helix Health Initiative clients are collectively paying Double Helix to develop, demonstrate and put through clinical trials, therapies that they wish to have available in the future.\n\nDuring the typical 15 to 20 plus year period that it takes to obtain FDA or equivalent approvals for a new therapy, Helix Therapy access will be limited to participation in clinical trials.\n\nClients who contribute towards the development and testing of the therapy will be the first to benefit from any available early access. Cumulative contributions will qualify for priority of access to limited pay-for-treatment clinical trials at international medical clinics in jurisdictions where pay-for-treatment clinical trials are allowed.\n\nThis innovative approach provides a mechanism for clients to fund the development of desirable therapies.','The ultimate health initiative - Reversing Human Aging','[\"Toronto\"]','Double Helix'),('We are revolutionizing the process of scientific information search and laying the foundation for intelligent interpretation and mining of scientific data and publication.\nWe are turning search into research. ','Turning Search into Research','[]','Pubsonic'),('Sword Diagnostics is a life sciences company committed to improving healthcare outcomes through the use of innovative detection technology for clinical diagnostics and life science research. Sword has demonstrated sensitivity improvements of 2X - 10X and larger in tests for markers used to diagnose disease and perform medical research. Sword has recently launched its detection kits jointly with Tecan to deliver a complete detection system in the market.','Highly Sensitive Diagnostic Tests','[\"Chicago\"]','Sword Diagnostics'),('Genicell is developing a functional laboratory model of the blood-brain barrier that is capable of using human or animal cells. This system, which consists of tissue engineered blood vessels grown inside custom built chambers called bioreactors, allows Genicell to conduct drug permeability tests that are otherwise conducted on animals with much greater ease of scale up. This results in a service that would allow pharmaceutical companies to perform drug permeability tests cheaper and faster.','Expedited drug discovery','[\"Berkeley\"]','Genicell'),('Return on Change is a next generation equity crowdfunding platform which will allow high impact startups to raise early stage capital on the internet by posting their business idea for the public (general non accredited investors) to invest in.','Equity Crowdfunding platform for high impact startups','[\"New York City\"]','Return on Change'),('At the base of all human tissue is a form of skeleton or scaffold. We developed a broad technology platform that creates these scaffolds in a way that the body readily accepts, bridging the significant performance gap between the existing markets for biologics and synthetics.  Unlike competing solutions, we create and align a variety of FDA-approved fibers smaller than 1/100th the size of a human hair in multi-layer scaffolds that control cell growth and proliferation.  Our tissue integrates into the body quickly and without immune repression drugs. Our trachea technology and products were used for all the first five nanofiber human trachea replacements and can be used for a host of products including esophagus, tendon, bone, wound care, arteries and veins, intestine, etc, on a $20 billion annual global market.','Create revolutionary scaffolds for human tissue','[\"Columbus\"]','Nanofiber Solutions, LLC'),('The morbidity of most cancers is related to the metastatic dissemination of cells sloughing off the primary tumor.  Sub-Micro is developing a novel therapeutic device to aid in the removal of residual tumor cells, which will limit metastatic spread and significantly improve long-term survival for cancer patients. The therapeutic system targets and mechanically removes malignant cells from the body using magnetic nanomaterials and a pump driven extracorporeal circuit containing a magnetic filter.','Novel Targeted Cancer Therapy','[\"Atlanta\"]','Sub-Micro'),('Instant Chemistry is a biotechnology company that’s revolutionizing the way people use dating services. After decades of scientific research, we now know the simple, stunning and provable fact: up to 40% of physical attraction can be determined through your genes alone. There’s far more depth to human relationships than we could have imagined. It’s a fact that genetically compatible partners are more physically attracted to each other. They also experience higher fertility rates and have healthier children. \r\n\r\nWith Instant Chemistry, dating companies can now integrate a genetics-based algorithm into their matching methods. Instant Chemistry’s genetic test kit and proprietary algorithm allow them to easily determine the biological compatibility among individuals and use the results to create more successful matches. Instant Chemistry’s genetic test kits are only available through partnered matchmakers. ','Revealing the Science of Attraction','[\"Toronto\"]','Instant Chemistry'),('For more information related to CombImmune, it\'s products, and business plan, please inquire via info@combimmune.com ','Medical oncology & diagnostic company','[\"Palo Alto\"]','CombImmune, Inc.'),('Label-free biomolecular interaction monitoring','Instrumentation for biotechnology (sold to Horiba Scientific)','[\"Orsay\"]','Genoptics'),('Medical device for the treatment of nail fungal infections, a $3 billion US market affecting over 35 million Americans.  Our device promises to have higher efficacy than the best of breed oral medications without side effects and can be done in one or two treatments in a doctor\'s office.','Revolutionizing fungal nail infection therapy','[\"Newark, CA\"]','DeviceFarm'),('The cloud-based bio-repository management utility\nSpecitrack is the perfect middle-ground between free home-brew solutions and expensive custom informatics. It\'s designed to be an affordable, long-term solution to maximize your lab\'s potential through smarter sample management.','Cloud-based Medical-Research Informatics','[\"New York City\"]','Specitrack'),('Curewize Health Ltd. commercializes leading-edge technologies that can significantly improve the overall survival and health of young cancer patients. Curewize was awarded an Israeli Office of Chief Scientist grant for the commercialization of ProALL and is seeking matching funding. \n\nProALL  is a prognostic assay that can help improve ALL patients’ survival and quality of life by determining whether the patient needs a standard or intense treatment.  ProALL solves several drawbacks of MRD, which are currently used to determine ALL patients risk based treatment group. \n\nProALL results are available 2 days from diagnosis vs 1-3 months from diagnosis with MRD.\nUnlike MRD, ProALL is universal; there is no need to design the assay for each patient.\nProALL is performed in standard clinical labs; MRD is performed in a few labs with specific expertise.  ProAll has proven monitoring ability and fits well with routine practice. ProALL and MRD can be used together for even higher accuracy.','Personalizing  young cancer patients treatment','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Curewize'),('Isentio offers unique online software solutions to facilitate analysis, interpretation and management of DNA sequencing data. Isentio\'s RipSeq® product is the fastest, most user-friendly and complete solution for DNA identification of clinically important pathogens, making identification consistent and accurate. \n\nRipSeq enables sequence-based identification from both mono- and poly-microbial samples, a unique feature that results in enhanced problem solving qualities. The bacterial identification time can be reduced up to 90% and answers can be provided where other methods fail. Fast, precise pathogen identification will also support selection of optimal antibiotic regimes, with the potential to reduce health care costs.\n\n50k Foot View of Isentio:\n•	SaaS product + curated proprietary database\n•	Clinical AND research lab utility\n•	Existing global customer base\n•	2 filed and 3 provisional patents','Pathogen Identification as a Service','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Isentio'),('Many students who graduate in science field cannot find a job because they have no experience. I am here to change that. I want to create a laboratory business that would hire students and allow them to work for a period of time. After that they can apply to their dream job. I apologize but the information is limited in order to prevent the idea. ','Provide graduate student with a jobs in science fields. High unemployment in this field.','[\"Toronto\"]','Roman Laboratory'),(NULL,'Protecting Privacy, Furthering Research','[\"Pensacola\"]','Bionymity'),(NULL,'Optogenetics & Gene Therapy','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eos Neuroscience'),('Annexon is developing drugs to inhibit the complement cascade, which the\r\ncompany believes is a key mechanism in neurodegenerative diseases. These drugs are\r\nexpected to halt the progression of these diseases and allow the body to reverse the\r\ndamage that has been done. In addition to halting progression, the drugs can also be used to image the state of neurodegenerative diseases so that treatment efficacy (of any\r\ntreatment) can be seen and quantified.\r\n\r\nOur mission is to develop a new class of drugs to halt the progression of multiple\r\nneurodegenerative disorders including Alzheimer’s disease, glaucoma, Parkinson’s\r\ndisease, spinal muscular atrophy, stroke, traumatic brain injury, Multiple Sclerosis,\r\nNeuromyelitis Optica and peripheral nervous system diseases including Guillain-Barre\r\nSyndrome and Myasthenia Gravis.','Innovative neurodegeneration therapeutics by targeting complement','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Annexon'),('VOXCE is a cloud based clinical research application framework that implements a standard structure\nfrom different data sources to provide a centralized interface to manage single, and multiple clinical\nresearch studies.\n','Clinical Trial Framework implements a standard structure from different data sources','[\"Minneapolis\"]','VOXCE'),('We take technology from semiconductor manufacturing, and have developed a process in which to fill and finish injectable drug products. Using sterilized, sealed robotic systems, our SA25 Aseptic Workcell enables pharma companies to reduce their operating costs by >50%, achieve high of levels of flexibility, and eliminate human-borne contamination. \n\nWith the focus towards personalized medicine and biologic therapies, Vanrx\'s technology is at the core of enabling tomorrow\'s medicines.  ','Robotics for Injectable Drug Manufacturing','[\"Vancouver\"]','Vanrx Pharmasystems'),(NULL,'Adult autologous olfactory stem cells','[\"Louisville\"]','RhinoCyte'),('Stillwater Supercomputing, Inc. designs and markets the Stillwater Genome Appliance, a hardware accelerated server that connects to a NGS instrument to create a high productivity workflow for genetics and drug discovery, and ultimately personalized healthcare research and deployment.','Personalized medicine platform','[\"San Jose\"]','Stillwater Supercomputing'),('First Warning Systems (FWS) is an early breast cancer screening technology targeting the dense breast tissue population and improvement of mammography false positive biopsy results.  With over 650 patients completed through 3 clinical trials, and an additional 5 years of advanced predictive algorithm development out of Singapore\'s prestigious Nanyang Technical University, FWS intends to deliver an automated quantification screening system consisting of an advanced neural network predictive analytic software solution.\n\nUtilizing a wearable acquisition device, the FWS  will reduce human intervention and institutional costs, while delivering a low COG product with high margins. With a patient charge less than the average co-pay for current screening and diagnostic procedures, the FWS solution can be prescribed by the physician/healthcare worker, and used routinely and repetitively, supporting software as a solution (SaaS) economics, and scalable high-volume deployment of the product.','Non-invasive, Non-irradiative Predictive Analytics for Early Breast Cancer Screening','[\"Reno\"]','First Warning Systems'),('Direct-Light” Technology is the world’s 1st renewable energy platform that delivers an immediate solution for increasing profit margins, sustainability, and commercial viability for manufacturers of biofuel (1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th generations