E SPECIAL TECH-DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS \n\nSeeking sales agents/Purchase orders-LOI\'s/IP SAle-Manuf.under license\nSPECIAL OFFER:Solar Power/Wireless transmission systems from 1W/hr-USD1.50,Power Plants-10MW/HR-USD15MM\n\nSystem A:\nUnlike solar cells,A System that is capable of capturing cosmic rays,(full spectrum \nof known universal rays)convert/store them uniformaly and releasing this stored \nelectric energy(AC/DC)on demand CONTINOUSLY,irrespective of weather conditions\n(Heat/Cold,day/night,cloudcover.snow,rain,etc).\n\n.\n\nEmail:loist967@yahoo.ca\nrainbow17670@yahoo.ca','24hr/7day  cosmic energy conversion panels','[\"Vancouver\"]','ADVANCED UNIVERSAL TECH'),('Our product accelerates the processing of DNA sequencing data. It is about 5x faster, uses 20x less power and requires 15x less space than conventional CPU solutions. We believe that the arrival of personal genomics in the next 2 to 5 years will bring huge computational requirements that will put large demands on conventional compute solutions. Our product is faster, cheaper and more compact. ','High Performance Compute Hardware and Software for DNA Sequencing','[\"Baltimore\"]','Stone Ridge Technology'),('The Agent Z Project generates intellectual property which is then a commodity that can be sold , in part or in its entirety. That IP would relate to identifying infectious triggers of autoimmune diseases such as Multiple Sclerosis, Juvenile Diabetes and Inflammatory Bowel Disease. Identification would then lead to treatment and prevention via vaccination. This could help millions of affected and at-risk individuals and their loving families. ','Curing Autoimmune Diseases ','[\"Grand Haven\"]','The Agent Z Project'),('Scicasts is a media-tech company that connects science professionals and decision makers to a dynamic network of critical information, new ideas and thought leaders.\n\nWe employ a distinctive editorial model that focuses exclusively on reporting the most critical and ground-breaking scientific developments around the world, and in highly targeted vertical sectors. All of our reports are brought directly from the sources and verified prior to publishing. As of March 2013, Scicasts have published over 6,000 news articles and reports.\n\nIn addition, our editorial process is combined with specialist algorithms that provide us with a unique insight into the past, current and future scientific R&D trends and opportunities. The aim of which is to facilitate knowledge that may lead to such revolutionary developments that were reported on Scicasts within different sectors.','The \'Bloomberg\' for science','[\"London\"]','Scicasts'),('Q: How to avoid an expensive, protracted push to close your VC, corporate or other complex deal?\r\n\r\nA:  Go with Will -- a veteran of major law firm and in-house positions, he has a keen sense of the important and won\'t let your deal get derailed. ','Best deal advisor','[\"San Francisco\"]','William M. Kushner'),('enventure is your home for medical entrepreneurship in Houston.\n\nThrough regular meetups, stimulating lectures, hands-on workshops, one-on-one mentorship, diverse educational programs, and accessible funding for early stage medical startups, our non-profit aims to be the community and networking hub for young and aspiring medical entrepreneurs.\n\nJoin us in giving Houston the momentum it needs to become the #1 city for life science entrepreneurship.','houston\'s medical entrepreneurs','[\"Houston\"]','enventure'),('Aeon ferments and grows food.','ferment the future','[\"San Francisco\"]','Aeon'),('XperiDesk is the Manufacturing Intelligence solution for R&D departments in companies. It can be applied to any high tech production process development and has been used already in Nanomaterials, Solar, Semicon, MEMS and other domains. In these industries XperiDesk has proven to turn vast amounts of data into actionable knowledge. It is a cloud enabled software and runs on local networks as well as on cloud installations. ','Manufacturing Intelligence for Technology Research','[\"Dortmund\"]','Process Relations'),('The Integrated Proteomics Pipeline (IP2) is a proteomics data analysis platform that has been designed with researchers in mind. At Integrated Proteomics Applications, we know that you do not want to spend your time writing code. We understand that you want to receive your results fast without trading accuracy. Consequently, the IP2 has been designed to easily handle high-throughput proteomics data with a comprehensive interface that gives you confident results. The IP2 can also be integrated with our cloud computing service which eliminates the need for computational clusters and increases the data analysis speed.','cloud-based one-stop data analysis platform for proteomic data analysis','[\"San Diego\"]','Integrated Proteomics '),('DNA researchers are buying a new generation of small and fast DNA sequencers that are revolutionizing bioscience and medicine.  The price is still out of reach for many small labs, though.  Cheap-Seq hooks up sequencer owners with non-owners who just have a few jobs to run.  Owners can squeeze them in during downtime or between their own runs, and monetize.','AirBnB for Next-Gen DNA Sequencing','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Cheap-Seq'),('Metrad Biosystems Inc. is developing patented technology to recreate the barrier between the cerebrospinal fluid and the brain, on a cellular level. The success of this project requires an interdisciplinary approach blending biomedical engineering and neuroscience, but will yield a tool with heretofore unseen capability to study neurodegenerative disorders.','Cerebrospinal Flow Engineering','[\"Menlo Park\"]','Metrad Biosystems'),('Santa Barbara, California-based VG Life Sciences Inc., formerly known as Viral Genetics, is a biotechnology company focused on discovering and developing drug therapies for cancer, infectious disease, and inflammatory, autoimmune disorders. VGLS controls over 50 US and international patents and pending patents protecting its exclusive biotech platform technologies. ',' VGLS is focused on developing treatments for cancer, infectious disease, and inflammation','[\"Santa Barbara\"]','VG Life Sciences'),('BCISim has discovered a major advancement in diagnosis and treatment with a new technology called predictive neuro-stimulation (PNS) to detect then prevent the occurrence of seizures. Our methodology has been implemented in patients with an 86% accuracy rate in predicting Epileptic seizures before they occur in children 8-12 years old.  Our methods include finding the small, local area in the individual’s brain where initial seizure activity is measured. As this area grows and begins to take over the individual’s brain, we short-circuit this activity by sending a small electrical stimulation to the individual’s brain, thereby stopping the train of seizure pathologies.   We have developed a neuro-device to predict and reduce seizures, and we are looking for investment to increase patient testing to quickly bring our product to market.','Seizure prediction device','[\"Memphis\"]','BCISim, Inc'),('Recently allows life science researchers and medical doctors to stay up to date with what is being published in their field. It provides a personalised feed of new and relevant scientific publications. From tedious search to easy discovery, Recently is the personalised scientific journal.','Discover relevant publications','[\"Barcelona\"]','Recently'),('KannaLife intends to profit from the acquisition, development, marketing and sale of phyto-medical drugs and products derived from cannabinol (“CBN”) and cannabidiol (“CBD”) compounds as part and parcel to the Company’s drug development plan. The disease indications to which the Company intends to target for the development of its products are centered on patients suffering from diseases with neuro-degenerative and/or neuro-toxic profiles. Exclusive license holder of US Patent 6630507, Cannabinoids as Antioxidants and Neuroprotectants, NIH-OTT','Cannabinoids as Antioxidants and Neuroprotectants, Exclusive license US Patent 6630507','[]','KannaLife Sciences'),('Ceramic Knee and Hip Implants. Patented Design and Material. Ceramic implants last 10x longer than the typical Metal Alloy implants commonly used in the market today. Ceramic is also 99.9% allergenic free. Roughly 14% of patients are allergic to metal alloy implants, resulting in medication for life, removal of implant, fusion of joints (peg leg), amputation, and even death. Ceramic is far superior to metal alloy in almost all medical applications.  ','7 World-Wide Patented Orthopedic Implants w/Plant and International Distribution','[\"San Francisco\"]','Ceramic Medical Devices (CMD)'),('Vecoy Nanomedicines develops a novel nano-medical therapy which is essentially a use of tailor-made virus-decoys that mimic human host cells (\"Vecoys\"). \nVirus particles entrapped by the Vecoys are destroyed in the process. This core technology is fundamentally different than any available anti-viral treatment, as viruses are inactivated before a cellular infection takes place. \n\nArticle:\nhttp://israel21c.org/health/new-israeli-tactic-makes-deadly-viruses-commit-suicide/','Vecoy Nanomedicines develops a groundbreaking technology for treatment of viral infections','[\"Ramat Gan\"]','Vecoy Nanomedicines '),('Wave Tech\'s material is a nano-tech film which may be applied to new or existing biological systems in order to increase outputs and decrease operating expenses.  The film can dramatically reduce cooling costs by rejecting heat from the sun while increasing algae growth rate. Initially, production of high-value outputs such as nutraceuticals and pharmaceuticals will be targeted. future markets may include basic terrestrial crops.','Scalable optics for agriculture','[\"Cincinnati\"]','Wave Tech'),('We are the Leading Facilitator of Science Based High Technologies Startups in EU.\nOur Aim is to Boost Creation of HiTech Ventures focused on global markets.\n* \nCommercialization Reactor is a process which actually has connections with a number of Universities from the ex Soviet Union and EU. Members of the team behind the reactor are based in Latvia, Russia, Kazakhstan, Armenia, Ukraine, Georgia and Germany.\n* \nThe concept itself is pretty simple: entrepreneurs often lack the technology to support their business and scientists lack the desire or skills to promote the technologies that they develop.\n* \nThere are events about every 1/2 year to bring these two groups together. Commercialization Reactor brings 10-18 science based technologies to be presented each time. \n* \nThe first event was held in 2009. The next will be held 28-29 March, 2014. Riga, Latvia\n* \nEvents followed by 10 weeks accelaration resulted in more than 30 startups in the pipeline and 19 have received EUR2.9M funding','EU Leading Facilitator of Science Based High Techs for Startups. PreAccelerator. PreSeed.','[\"Riga\"]','Commercialization Reactor'),('NVX-108 is an oxygen therapeutic to treat life threatening conditions such as cancer, heart attack, stroke and hemorrhagic shock.  As an emulsion of dodecafluoropentane, the product was previously approved for sale in Europe as an ultrasound contrast imaging agent.  We have data to show that it is safe in human subjects and shown to be effective in animal models of ischemic/hypoxic disease.  Most companies have spent $10+M get to this point.  Now all we have to do is a human clinical trial.','Oxygen Therapeutic for Life Threatening Conditions','[\"Tucson\"]','NuvOx Pharma'),('Sequencing DNA is becoming cheaper and faster, and is fundamentally changing medical research and practice. However, the ability to analyze and interpret the data is lagging behind. Currently, the analyses workflows are complex so typically a biologist needs to hire an analyst to write a bunch of scripts to do the job. Further, the data size is growing so rapidly (3x of Moore\'s law) that the computing infrastructure is not able to scale.\n\nWe have developed a cloud based platform, where users will upload their data and select the type of analysis with just a few clicks. The workflow and computations will run automatically and results will be available on the web.','cloud-powered DNA sequencing data analysis','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Basepair'),('We offer an incubator environment at Ljubljana’s Technology Park and do angel/seed investments in companies we work with. Since we deal with a wide range of startups at various stages, we needed a flexible business model that takes that diversity into account.\n\nThe programs we run are usually partly sponsored by a partner (we’ve worked with mobile operators, universities and variety of other ventures). Participants pay a small participation fee to ensure their commitment and to cover the most basic costs (books, snacks, etc.). Putting your money where your mouth is focuses teams\' perspectives, puts us in a constant state of testing and reevaluating our business model as well as ensures the community growing out of the basement of a Tito-era technology park is minimally self-sufficient.','Providing targeted accelerator courses to hackers, entrepreneurs & academia','[\"Ljubljana\"]','Hekovnik Startup School'),('General Biomass develops advanced enzymes to convert nonfood biomass to sugars for making renewable jet fuel, advanced biofuels, bioplastics and green renewable chemicals. The cost of DNA sequencing has dropped faster than Moore\'s Law, resulting in sequencing of tens of thousands of new genes coding for high performance biomass deconstruction enzymes, eg those from extremophiles living at 100C. Our technology converts gene data to real scalable enzymes with superior industrial  properties.','Transforming Waste to Biofuels and Bioplastics','[\"Evanston\"]','General Biomass Company'),('SBE’s alternative financing instrument enables sustainability for clinical-stage biotechnology companies by offering an insurance policy on the high attrition rate of Phase II drug candidates – the ability to transfer technical risk to the capital markets at the time in a drug candidate’s lifecycle when the greatest amount of uncertainty is traded for the greatest amount of enterprise value.','Insurance for sustainable drug development.','[\"New York City\"]','Structured BioEquity (SBE)'),('BHV Pharma is developing a novel, best in class, Sodium Glucose Transporter 2 (SGLT2) inhibitor indicated for Type 2 Diabetes and NASH. Remogliflozin has been dosed in over 800 subjects in over 20 clinical trials. In 12-week phase 2b studies in type 2 diabetics, remogliflozin lowered HbA1c greater than 1% and demonstrated a best in class side-effect profile. Remogliflozin is the only positively differentiated SGLT2 approved or in development with best in class efficacy, best in class side-effect profile, and best in class effect in the >35% of diabetics with renal impairment. \n\n ','Metabolic Drug Development','[\"Raleigh\"]','BHV Pharma'),('Confluence Pharmaceuticals is the exclusive licensee of a\nclinically discovered, novel therapeutic treatment for core social and communication impairments in individuals suffering from Autism Spectrum Disorders (ASD) and Fragile X Syndrome (FXS). There is no FDA approved medication for these life-long impairments. According to published studies, the potential success of a therapeutic drug could reduce the cost of life-long care by as much as two-thirds.','Novel, patented Autism & Fragile X Drug Discovery','[\"Indianapolis\"]','Confluence Pharmaceuticals'),('We are developing novel anti-cancer compounds based on our patented EVade™ Ribonuclease technology. Our most advanced lead candidate, QBI-139, has shown efficacy in animal models against a variety of tumor types including: colon, non-small cell lung, ovarian, pancreatic and prostate cancer. QBI-139 is 95% identical to the human RNase 1. A first in human dose escalation Phase 1 clinical trial in solid tumors is ongoing.','Phase I Oncology Drug','[\"Madison\"]','Quintessence Biosciences'),('Neoprospecta has two main products:\n\n1) Enzyme discovery and development: Enzymes discovered from the vast Brazilian biodiversity coupled with specialized molecule development through protein engineering and directed evolution\n\n2) Enviromental diagnostics and biomonitoring: Proprietary technology for large  scale metagenomics analysis of enviromental samples ranging from water to complex samples.','Enzyme discovery and development','[\"Porto Alegre\"]','Neoprospecta'),('{m}brace is a software framework for developing big data algorithms that will execute on a private or public cloud. It is similar to Hadoop in functionality but its main difference is that it is not confined to the map-reduce programming paradigm. \n\n{m}brace is taking care of all things that have to do with task orchestration and data flow between computer nodes, allowing the user to deal just with the algorithm that he wants to execute. It can be utilized in various business and research sectors like Stock market and finance.\nMoreover, it abstracts the underlying cloud infrastructure which means that any code developed using {m}brace can either run on a private or a public cloud that is supported.\n\n{m}brace is also providing the {m}brace shell where someone can delve into REPL style programming which enables fast code prototyping in a cloud scale. Moreover it enables you to monitor your computer nodes, deploy new code and get information about the jobs that are currently executing.','A big data framework (like Hadoop) for private and public clouds','[\"Athens\"]','Nessos/{m}brace the cloud'),('The life sciences are relatively untouched by the advent of microfluidics, our mission is to facilitate research and development in clinically relevant areas using microfluidics.\r\n\r\nMicrofluidics are small devices that contain channels that can handle liquid. These devices can be used in diagnostics, vasculature models, urology models, nanoparticle synthesis etc.\r\n\r\nFlow Microfluidics operates a simple service of taking clients digital chip designs and turning them into the real product which they receive a week later in the post. With the custom microfluidic chip in hand the researcher can push the boundaries of important research in the life sciences.','Contract fabrication of devices for handling microscopic amounts of liquid.','[\"London\"]','Flow Microfluidics'),('ApoVax, Inc. is based on the work of Haval Shirwan, Ph.D. at the University of Louisville.\n\nApoVax104, an immunostimulatory adjuvant construct, consists of streptavidin fused to the costimulatory molecule 4-1BBL. It is well differentiated from other adjuvants. ApoVax104 can be mixed with or conjugated to any biotinylated antigen (or peptide)--cancer or infectious disease. \n\nApoVax is also developing ApoFasL—a means of immunomodulation for tolerance induction—for the treatment of Type 1 diabetes.','Immunotherapy','[\"Louisville\"]','ApoVax, Inc.'),('Since 2006, Intanna is providing specialized medical devices consulting to bay area clients (start-ups, funded incubators and private funded companies). As a result of our products and services, we are proudly encourage to say, Intanna is about saving lives, mitigate or reduce suffering, relieving  pain, giving hopes to a child by controlled drug released technologies. Examples: \n1. Infusion pump \n2. Dental Tissues \n3. Capsule camera for screening your gut\n4. Orthopedic tools, sensors\n5. Other\n','Medical Devices Engineering and Consulting','[\"San Francisco\"]','Intanna Corporation'),('Currently, there is no single test to detect and predict multiple types of cancer throughout the body.  Instead, multiple different tests are used to find cancer in a variety of ways.  The diagnostic test Lazarus is developing will make checking for cancer as simple as checking cholesterol levels and may become a common part of a regular physical, leading to earlier detection, lower treatment costs and better patient outcomes.','Molecular Diagnostics to Detect Cancer','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Lazarus Bioscience'),('Looking for private equity investors for drug development, medical devices, nutraceuticals and healthcare IT technology ','Business Networking, Technology, Drug Development, Medical Devices, Healthcare','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Pharma Connections Worldwide'),(NULL,'Large-scale genomics, transcriptomics and bioinformatics solutions','[\"Porto Alegre\"]','Harpya Sciences'),(NULL,'Selectively Blocking Th22 Cells That Drive Autoimmune Disease','[\"Aurora\"]','Western States Biopharmaceuticals'),(NULL,'Repurposed Combination Treatment for ADHD ','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Attentive Therapeutics'),('I\'m in the process of launching a company called PSS Herbs India that provides herbal products (supplements, OTC drugs, extracts/APIs and processed herbs) to the global markets. \r\n\r\nPSS offers the $62 Billion global herbal market with high-quality and proven herbal supplements, medications and also bulk actives (APIs) for manufacture of Allopathic, Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani, medications. \r\n\r\nMy team of business and domain experts has extensively worked on this for over 8 months to make it a complete business plan that elaborates the unique working model of PSS Herbs. To implement the plan successfully and establish PSS as an internationally trusted brand in the areas of: Dietary supplements, OTC drugs, Extracts/APIs and Processed herbs, we are working to raise a capital of $8.18 Million in a Seed Round. \r\n\r\nI look forward to your support.','Goodness of plants','[\"India\"]','PSS Herbs India'),('Mariam Medical Inc. is an emerging biotechnology company focused on bringing cancer and broad spectrum antiviral therapeutics (BSAV) to market:\nMariam Medical is developing RNAi (“gene silencing”) based therapeutics against genetically-defined targets in multiple cancer areas, including liver, breast, prostate, NSCLC, ovarian, thyroid, melanoma, and neuro and glioblastoma cancers. \nWe have successfully killed human breast cancer cells in vitro using gene silencing techniques, indicating potential blockbuster therapies for breast and prostate cancer (over $17 billion in addressable markets). \n\nMariam Medical holds global exclusive rights on the patent for silencing this gene target.\n\nMariam Medical has identified and has exclusive global rights to broad spectrum antiviral small molecule compounds that can block SARS-CoV (SARS), EBOV (Ebola), HeV (Hendra), and NiV (Nipah) viral infections.','Pursuing a cure for Breast Cancer','[\"Peoria, IL\"]','Mariam Medical'),('DoveTail Integrated Systems (DTIS) has created the technology platform to fundamentally transform the future of sourcing biologics. Based on standardization, it gives developers and manufacturers of biologics the production capability to bring therapeutic proteins, MAbs and vaccines to market faster than traditional methods by providing turnkey, pre-engineered, pre-fabricated, pre-qualified, scalable manufacturing facilities in 8 to 12 months, versus an industry average of 42 months. \n\n','Transformative Biopharmaceutical Manufacturing ','[\"Nijmegen\", \"Raleigh\"]','DoveTail Integrated Systems'),('Tidemann&Co is an angel and investment company with interests in tech, cleantech, and biotech.','','[\"Copenhagen\"]','Tidemann&Co'),('User-designed, Bio/Pharma product data management (PDM) software.  Consumers reap up to 70% lead time reduction when transferring GMP drug products from lab to manufacturing, and between manufacturing sites, saving millions in headcount and rework.','Life-saving, blockbuster drugs to market.  Faster.','[\"Pacifica\"]','Prospect Software Solutions'),('BioInvaders produces scientific laboratory research and teaching specimens out of invasive species which the firm collects in areas where they are doing harm:  thus accomplishing ecosystem restoration.  Scientists use our product in their research, and educators use our products for exploration instruction.  Stakeholders use our services to restore degraded habitats and biomes.  ','Invasive Species Marketplace TM','[\"Houston\"]','BioInvaders Incorporated'),('Bioseka is focused on advanced research and applications of antisense\r\noligonucleotides (ASOs) as antimicrobial agents against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. The company’s primary target is control of bacterial biofilms through inhibiting the synthesis of exopolysaccharides, which compose structural matrix of the biofilms.\r\nBioseka ASOs have potential applications in the therapy of medically\r\nimportant oral, nasopharyngeal, skin and cardiovascular infections. Bioseka ASOs can also be combined with other antimicrobial agents, thus providing a novel path for combating multidrug-resistant bacteria.\r\nThe company is currently developing several lead phosphorothioate\r\nand peptide nucleic acid ASOs and is working to establish the optimum\r\neffective dosage, to improve their penetration into the biofilm and target cells, and to test stability of the chemotherapeutics under various conditions involving the complex environment of natural microbiota.','Antisense Antimicrobials','[\"Vilnius\"]','Bioseka, UAB'),('Exogensis is incentivizing and expanding synthetic biology research and development through web platforms and automated systems. SynBioSys, our web based marketplace for synthetic DNA, provides a means for developers to buy and sell synthetic genomic code. We are also making the creation, validation, and research of newly developed synthetic organisms and parts easier and cheaper through automated systems and machine learning algorithms. ','Incentivizing and Automating Bioscience','[]','Exogensis'),('A control unit that optimizes your fermentation process. This is applicable to fermented beverage and food production, fertilizer production, biodigestion of waste products, and natural gas generation. ','fermentation controller','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Sensa'),(NULL,'','[\"Toronto\"]','Divergent Rays Computing Inc.'),(NULL,'Transforming ALS & Neurodegenerative Disease','[\"Vancouver\"]','ImStar Therapeutics'),('Disruptive innovation in biological manufacturing technology enables us to produce off-patent biological drugs more cost-effectively compared to the current biological manufacturing technologies.  \r\n\r\nWe will produce a biosimilar insulin analog, Lantus (which grossed $7 billion last year and will go off-patent in 2015), as it is a very simple biological molecule and can be thoroughly characterized to be identical to the innovator drug.  \r\n\r\nWorldwide diabetic population will increase from 366 million in 2011 to 552 million in 2030.  The annual worldwide insulin demand has increased from 12 tons in 2007 to 22 tons in 2012. and is expected to further increase to 40 tons by 2020.  \r\n\r\nWhile it is reported that it costs about $500 millions to produce every ton of additional insulin in developed countries, we expect our cost of production to be much less than $50 million per ton (i.e cheaper by more than a factor of 10) due to our innovative manufacturing technology.\r\n\r\n\r\n','low-cost biosimilar manufacturing ','[\"Superior, CO\"]','Sudhin Biopharma Co.'),('LabCloud is dedicated to the implementation of laboratory software designed to bring out the full capabilities of Research and Development organizations by providing them with an integrated cloud or server based system to effectively manage their data, inventory and R&D Pipeline.\n\nFounded in 2013, LabCloud Inc. was incorporated on the basis of creating a browser based Integrated Laboratory Management Software that accelerates the process of research and development by automating reporting, analytics, and experimental parameter selection, allowing researchers to make better-informed decisions in their research, while effectively managing their inventory and logistics, allowing for streamlining of the R&D Process.\n\nUsually, similar systems that