nt epilepsy. Approximately 40% of epilepsy patients suffer from poorly controlled seizures; ~1% of the world population has epilepsy.\n\nThere are countless examples of neurological drugs (including all neuroprotective treatments) that showed promise in laboratory tests only to fail subsequent clinical trials. Clearly, these technologies are unable to predict whether or not drugs will work in people.  Yet, they continue to be used.\n\nOur approach is entirely different from the status quo. This is our advantage.\n','Bleeding-edge drug discovery for neurological disorders','[\"Frankfurt\"]','Expesicor UG'),('Starting with abundant, low cost natural gas, KnipBio\'s best-in-class bioconversion technology produces high value, essential biomolecules to aquaculture and agriculture industries. ','From Fuel to Food - A novel biotechnology to support a sustainable tomorrow','[\"Boston\"]','KnipBio'),('Innoventius has and acquires equity positions in start-up companies with the potential for creating substantial value and returns.\r\n\r\nInnoventius provides services to start-ups to create substantial value.','High Value Diversified Innovation Development','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','Innoventius LLC'),(NULL,'','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Medical Device Entrepreneurship Association at Drexel University'),('BioCep has developed a novel cell separation technology for rare cell isolation facilitating the development of novel clinical applications such as prenatal diagnosis, stem cell therapies and disease management. BioCep will market application-specific systems and consumable kits to customers in these fields. BioCep’s first application is fetal nucleated red blood cell separation from the maternal bloodstream in the 1st trimester for non invasive prenatal diagnosis (NIPD), a $1.8B annual market. ','Effective Cell Isolation Platform','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','BioCEP'),('Melanovus Oncology is developing therapeutics for the treatment of metastatic melanoma, which is classified by the FDA as an orphan disease, yet represents a $3B US market and $7.5B WW market. Our approach is novel, and our management team has 120+ years of experience operating under a capital efficient model. We are currently seeking investment to further the development of these target immunotherapies. ','Developing therapeutics for metastatic melanoma','[\"West Palm Beach\"]','Melanovus Oncology'),(' Product/Services\n\nThe FDA cleared swallowable screening device is comprised of a medical grade foam ball is compressed into a swallowable capsule which is deployed and withdrawn orally within 5 minutes. Since this device is spherical in shape and will be harvesting cellular samples from the entire length of the esophagus, the resulting specimen has a higher likelihood of capturing the diseased indicator cells than conventional, single site, pinch biopsies.\n\n Customer problem\n\nWith the recent developments in Genome Sequencing, several corporations and medical institutions have developed Biomarker Test Kits to detect diseases of the esophagus without requiring the use of invasive and uncomfortable endoscopic techniques. The problem is that these Biomarker and H-pylori quick test companies do not have efficient non-endoscopic (non-invasive) methods of obtaining cellular specimens from patents.\n\n','FDA Cleared! Non-Endoscopic cellular collection Device for Barretts Esophagus & H-Pylori.','[\"Philadelphia\"]','CapNostics, LLC'),('The device is currently \"patent pending\" and intended to artificially maintain lymphatic circulation when one does not move.  Applications include every hospital bed, nursing homes, the elderly, or anyone seeking to maintain lymphatic circulation throughout the day.','Maintaining Lymphtic Circulation Synthetically','[\"Chicago\"]','Lymphatic System Mover'),('Plant based lifestyle version of Hacker News\r\n\r\n\r\n','a community. Eating plants to feel good. (www.plantdietlife.com)','[\"Berkeley\"]','PLANTDIETlife'),('Comprehend Systems makes cloud-based, cross-datasource visualization and analytics tools.\n\nOur first product, Comprehend Clinical, is a next-generation clinical visualization and analytics tool for the pharmaceutical industry, based on Comprehend\'s LiveET technology. Comprehend Clinical enables every user in an organization answer their questions across multiple disparate data systems, regardless of where the user is, or where the data resides.\n\nComprehend Clinical is software-as-a-service.','End-to-end insights and collaboration for life science companies','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Comprehend'),('Reify Health provides scientists in academia with a web platform that allows them to create custom mobile health solutions without doing any programming themselves. Users can leverage mobile technologies like text messaging, a smartphone app, and mobile sensors to create custom algorithms for engaging patients and test the effectiveness of their mobile health solutions at changing health behaviors in clinical trials. ','The lab bench for digital health.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Reify Health'),('Corengi has developed an online search engine to help patients find clinical trials for which they may be qualified.  The Corengi technology includes all ongoing trials in the U.S and Canada for a specific condition and is available both on a dedicated website and via an embeddable widget.  We provide augmented exposure for paying clinical trial sponsors and also give a new revenue stream for health-related websites.','AdSense for clinical trial recruitment','[\"Seattle\"]','Corengi'),('','','[\"Mountain View\"]','H4Y Corp'),('Our genomes are going to be integral to our future healthcare. Creating structure from populations of genomic data and their associated attributes and integrating this with an individual\'s health profile will be central to this exciting future.  Station X is already creating the software that will power this future, and it\'s called GenePool.  \n\nGenePool is a secure, cloud-based software environment for analyzing and visualizing population-scale human genomic data for biomarker discovery, clinical interpretation and population studies. It seamlessly traverses between healthcare and IT challenges and empowers scientists and medical professionals to comfortably manage, analyze, interpret, and communicate patient-oriented genomics data in a user-friendly environment with the promise to do so much more.\n\nView our full slide deck at http://bit.ly/1cnbEcZ and if you\'d like a trial account, contact info@stationxinc.com\n','Decoding genomes for better healthcare','[\"San Francisco\"]','Station X'),('Pushing Innovation is a for-profit venture with a social mission - to fund research. We are changing the way science and innovation gets funded by matching donors with researchers in a simple and effective, low cost way. \n\nWe connect funding sources like high net worth individuals, private banks, corporate donors, and foundations with researchers through our portal which cuts down on overhead and increases transparency. Donors get to pinpoint where the money goes, follow progress, and ultimately gain an investment opportunity if/when research becomes commercialized.\n\nInvestment banks capture a new revenue stream out of a current loss. Grant writing institutions can drastically reduce their overhead when it comes to funding research. Companies can keep track of what\'s going on in their space.\n\nUniversities get a new source of funding to make up for the billions in cuts. The world benefits from the technologies, cures, economic gain, and job creation that results from Pushing Innovation!','1st Philanthropic Financial Product for Investment Banks','[\"San Diego\"]','Pushing Innovation'),('RegulatoryBinder saves hospitals time and money spent on research documentation.\n\nThe Clinical Trials Transformation Initiative and Institute of Medicine, however, have recently said that clinical research is a \"paper-based, slow, & costly\" \"burden\" on hospitals already under increasing cost-constraints.\n\nLimited revenue-generators at hospitals, spend copious amount of time managing printed pages of regulatory documentation in three-ring regulatory binders! This represents a $50B documentation opportunity cost.\n\nRegulatoryBinder has developed a novel SaaS solution that enables staff to reduce the time spent on research documentation by 33%, resulting $15B in potential annual savings. Only RegulatoryBinder is designed for hospital regulatory binders and bundles compliance services to ensure that software is compliant with FDA eRecord regulations from the very first login. Existing software can take $3-5M and over 1 year to customize, validate, and implement.','Document clinical studies better','[\"Cleveland\"]','RegulatoryBinder'),('CloudClinica is the 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials. This is the first Cloud Data Capture (CDC) system, to empower business users to build clinical studies themselves, remove today\'s high IT dependency and eliminate any financial barrier of entry through a pay-per-CRF pricing and a solution five times cheaper than existing solutions. CloudClinica offers a built-in integration layer for additional eClinical systems on its fully validated and compliant platform.','The 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials introducing Cloud Data Capture (CDC)','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','CloudClinica'),('Omicia Opal empowers researchers and clinicians to analyze genomes and prioritize disease-causing variants and genes.\n\nOmicia Opal combines powerful, peer-reviewed analysis tools with proprietary disease gene sets into an interactive genome mining, filtering, prioritizing, and reporting environment.\n\nOmicia Opal is cloud-based, scalable, and secure. Genome interpretation is now at your fingertips.','Genome Interpretation Platform','[\"San Francisco\"]','Omicia'),('The New Generation of Analytics for Healthcare\'s Big Data \n\nBig data is relatively easy to generate but hard to analyze properly. Correlating complex sets of genotypic, phenotypic and clinical data means working with huge combinatorial complexity. GenoKey’s suite of innovative data analytics use a powerful new mathematical approach to cut through this complexity and identify combinations of factors that together are responsible for an effect or outcome.','The New Generation of Analytics for Healthcare\'s Big Data','[\"Aalborg\"]','GenoKey'),('MediCard is a patient searching service for medical organizations which take part in clinical trials Our internet-service helps medical organizations, universities and hospitals to find easily and fast patients for clinical trials at any stage. We find patients from online-marketing (SMM, forums, Google.Analytics etc.). Also we cooperate with hospitals and doctors, who recommend their patients our service.','Clinical trials patient searching engine','[\"Moscow\"]','MediCard'),(NULL,'','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Innovation and Choice'),('Sense.ly is an avatar-based, emotively reactive platform that helps clinicians better manage their chronically ill patients.  After the clinician enters in the clinical protocol and goals, a virtual medical assistant follows up with patients, collects clinical data from medical devices and assessments, tracks progress, and helps patients to stay on course with motivations and reminders.  All the information is analyzed and presented to the doctor so patients can get better faster, hospitals can bill for telemedicine procedures, and reduce operational costs.','Taking \'Siri\' to medical school','[\"United States\"]','Sense.ly'),('Sword Diagnostics is a life sciences company committed to improving healthcare outcomes through the use of innovative detection technology for clinical diagnostics and life science research. Sword has demonstrated sensitivity improvements of 2X - 10X and larger in tests for markers used to diagnose disease and perform medical research. Sword has recently launched its detection kits jointly with Tecan to deliver a complete detection system in the market.','Highly Sensitive Diagnostic Tests','[\"Chicago\"]','Sword Diagnostics'),('SherlockMD is a platform for researchers to collect data on the web and iOS. Our beta users think it is like Survey Monkey, but with additional tools for performing clinical trials. There is no programming required so the design to launch time can be accomplished in minutes rather than weeks. The application works through a browser to create the studies and data can be collected in the browser or on iOS devices.','Survey Monkey for Clinical Trials','[\"Santa Monica\"]','SherlockMD'),('The cloud-based bio-repository management utility\nSpecitrack is the perfect middle-ground between free home-brew solutions and expensive custom informatics. It\'s designed to be an affordable, long-term solution to maximize your lab\'s potential through smarter sample management.','Cloud-based Medical-Research Informatics','[\"New York City\"]','Specitrack'),(NULL,'Protecting Privacy, Furthering Research','[\"Pensacola\"]','Bionymity'),('Clinical Cloud™ brings technology solutions to the clinical research industry and is available to research sites, CROs and sponsors. \n\nThe Clinical Trials Transformation Initiative (CTTI) is providing feedback to reduce costs and introduce efficiencies in the drug development cycle. Source Data Verification (SDV) estimates are $12-16 billion/year.\n\nClinical Cloud™ provides an alternative SDV approach to study monitoring via remote-access, improving data quality & efficiency while reducing costs.','EMR for Clinical Trials: Paperless Data Capture - Innovative Clinical Research Solutions','[\"Houston\"]','Clinical Cloud'),('SaaS for Clinical Trials - Create, manage and analyze clinical trials data. Navigate clinicians through clinical trials process to reducing data errors. Manage visits and paperwork scheduling. \r\nRecruit new patients via social network. \r\nManage study from anywhere. \r\nSetup multiple distributed world wide sites.\r\nRaise warnings for poorly performing sites and personal.\r\n\r\nAs well as Software consulting and outsourcing services.','Software consulting & outsourcing. Software for Clinical Trials','[\"San Diego\"]','Tateeda'),(NULL,'iSpecimen’s technology provides data-rich human biospecimens to medical researchers.','[]','iSpecimen'),('The pharmaceutical industry spends billions on new drug development, but the tools that it uses for these activities are outdated and consist of a hodgepodge of vendor applications that a stringed together. We plan to get rid of this clutter by providing one seamless data management platform that simplifies the process of data collection and analysis, a platform that enables faster decision-making and timely trial completion.\n \nWe will provide an Android tablet that allows clinical data to be entered in real time in front of the subject and any patient reported outcomes(PRO) can now be collected during the subject visit. The data from these sources, along with any third party data (labs, ECG data, radiology scans etc) will be stored in cloud servers. Finally, we will provide a tablet dashboard with data visualization tools that will enable real time decision-making and a robust web-based analytics platform for data analysis and report generation. ','Next generation clinical data entry and analysis platform','[\"Edison\"]','iClinical'),('VOXCE is a cloud based clinical research application framework that implements a standard structure\nfrom different data sources to provide a centralized interface to manage single, and multiple clinical\nresearch studies.\n','Clinical Trial Framework implements a standard structure from different data sources','[\"Minneapolis\"]','VOXCE'),('Many brain diseases, Alzheimer\'s in particular, as well as traumatic brain injuries are both difficult to detect early and difficult to monitor. Existing measurements are often not sufficiently precise or discriminating.\n\nWe believe that we have the solution for early detection and monitoring of Alzheimer’s, Parkinson’s, MS, ALS and other brain diseases as well as traumatic brain injuries. Habit DX has a patent-pending method for sub-clinical measurement and analysis of typing cadence which improves detection of highly granular, unique typing patterns. The data produced is eight orders of magnitude richer than current methods. Medical experts believe this invention has huge implications for early detection of Alzheimer’s et al. \n\nWe envision that we can help the medical community to diagnose most of these brain diseases much earlier – allowing families to make life changes and plan better, and allowing drug companies to test patients at a stage where the drugs can actually help. \n','Measuring Brain Health','[\"San Francisco\"]','Habit DX'),('Clinata is the world\'s largest marketplace for clinical research. Our platform connects Sponsors to Sites and Service Providers worldwide. Using a state of the art recommendation engine Clinata analyses millions of data points to find the most optimal sites and service providers for any research project.An intelligent patient recruitment system helps drive patient recruitment for each site in the study and makes recommendations to meet recruitment goals.','World\'s Largest Marketplace for Clinical Research','[\"Dallas\"]','Clinata'),('CliniTrial has developed an innovative patent-pending solution that leverages latest technology via use of smartphones, tablets & private cloud, to support clinical trial research. CliniTrial aims to  bring in back-office process automation by simplifying the data capture, data storage and data management process at the source, thereby bringing in efficiency and transparency in the process.','Technology Enabled Solutions to support Clinical Trials','[\"Fremont\"]','CliniTrial'),('We have developed a novel platform of genome-editing, organelle-localized and ligand-targeted nanoparticles. We are working to merge next-generation diagnostic tools with our ability to design precisely engineered nano-constructs. We are bringing the world truly personalized medicine and need your help in building a laboratory with the appropriate scaling capabilities.\n\nAt the moment, we have preclinical data validating our ability to perform one-time genomic-level treatment of diseases relating to bone and bone marrow. We additionally have alpha customers ready to go spanning multiple fields, with some particularly revolutionary things in store with immuno and neuromimicry. \n\nSoon, we\'d like you to be able to walk into a hospital and have a customized cure tailored to your individual biology. In creating this future, we aim to increase the speed of feedback between academia, pharma and the clinic to parallelize innovation. \n\nWe want you to live longer, and to be happier about it too. ','Genomically Personalized Nanomedicine','[\"Berkeley\"]','Ligandal Technology (LNT)'),('“LARA – your health companion” is a digital decision aid program for women between diagnosis fibroids and treatment decision. Every 3rd woman suffers from fibroid related symptoms. Fibroids are benign non-cancerous tissue growths of the uterus womb. Symptoms strongly influence womans’ physical, emotional and sexual wellbeing. They can harm fertility. LARA stands for L=learn, A=appreciate, R=reach decision, A=take action. LARA assists women in understanding their diagnosis and treatment options. LARA lets women manage their own care. LARA prepares them for a shared-decision-making on their individual treatment together with their physician.','LARA – your health companion is for best medical treatment decisions ','[\"Berlin\"]','Die Artverwandten GmbH'),('Santa Barbara, California-based VG Life Sciences Inc., formerly known as Viral Genetics, is a biotechnology company focused on discovering and developing drug therapies for cancer, infectious disease, and inflammatory, autoimmune disorders. VGLS controls over 50 US and international patents and pending patents protecting its exclusive biotech platform technologies. ',' VGLS is focused on developing treatments for cancer, infectious disease, and inflammation','[\"Santa Barbara\"]','VG Life Sciences'),('Creates certified redacted mirror images of site source documents for remote monitoring. Service ready to launch in January 2013. Sponsors, CROs, and universities as clients. Reduces cost while improving efficiency and raising the quality of study monitoring. Allows for real-time study site management, improving protocol compliance, and increased monitor productivity. Consists of three interconnected closed systems that are fully compliant with 21 CFR Part 11, HIPAA, and EU privacy directive. ','Remote monitoring of clinical trials','[\"Cary\"]','The ROMaN Project'),('PaperCritic is a gateway for review, critique and appraisal of scientific literature. Apart from serving the scientific community by offering an open review functionality, it allows individuals, research groups as well as professional literature analysts, such as public policy-makers in the health industry, to organize, appraise and easily make conclusions about the vast amounts of scientific literature by directly integrating into available reference management systems (e.g. Mendeley).','Critical appraisal tool for scientific publications','[\"Dublin\"]','PaperCritic'),('A health app that finally does more than just track - Using big data (electronic health record) analytics, it shows users their chances of getting better or worse, inspires them to set health goals that are meaningful and finds providers with the best clinical outcomes. Oh, and for pharma companies, it allows them to reach the most relevant and engaged patients for participation in clinical trials.','Predictive Health Apps for Empowered Patients','[\"Philadelphia\"]','BeeHenzo'),('ViS\' collaborative analytics platform facilitates the process of finding researchers and research sites for clinical trials using public and private data together with advanced analytics. The platform uses an intuitive, highly navigable, graphical interface to facilitate finding active research centers in a given therapeutic area, at the country, state, city, or zip code level. ViS\' platform also allows research centers to provide technical information about their expertise and internal capabilities in conducting trials within specific disease areas. Headquartered in New York City, ViS has offices in Brazil, Germany, India, and Korea.','The power of online feasibility assessment','[\"New York City\"]','ViS'),('LabCloud is dedicated to the implementation of laboratory software designed to bring out the full capabilities of Research and Development organizations by providing them with an integrated cloud or server based system to effectively manage their data, inventory and R&D Pipeline.\n\nFounded in 2013, LabCloud Inc. was incorporated on the basis of creating a browser based Integrated Laboratory Management Software that accelerates the process of research and development by automating reporting, analytics, and experimental parameter selection, allowing researchers to make better-informed decisions in their research, while effectively managing their inventory and logistics, allowing for streamlining of the R&D Process.\n\nUsually, similar systems that meet the strict compliance requirements are out of the reach of customers based on integration and initial software costs. LabCloud has made that platform that is powerful and affordable for an under-served market, both in the US and abroad.','Better and Accessible Laboratory Software','[\"Boston\"]','LabCloud Inc.'),('Biocentric Developments has developed a revolutionary device that creates a low-humidity environment localized around the eye. With a standardized climate around the eye, researchers and clinicians alike will be able to gather quantitative data consistently. The current industry leader relies on the construction of climate-controlled testing facilities available in only limited locations and costing millions of dollars. In contrast, our goggles will cost less than a fraction of the price and their small size will allow for their incorporation into nearly any ophthalmic research lab or clinic in the world. \n\nThe widespread availability of our goggles will streamline the development of dry eye treatments, increasing the quality of patient lives in both the home and work environments. \n\nOur goggles were developed with support from the Cullen Eye Institute at Baylor College of Medicine in Houston, Texas as well as the Oshman Engineering Design Kitchen at Rice University.','Medical Device for Dry Eye Research','[\"Austin\"]','Biocentric Developments'),('Advanced mathematical and statistical modeling software.  See\nwww.civilized.com','mathematical and statistical modeling software','[\"Silver Spring\"]','civilized software '),('For cancer patients and pharmaceutical companies worldwide who annually spend over 10 billion dollars on biomarker discovery and diagnostics, Apollo’s multivariate highly sensitive and specific non-invasive cancer signatures would predict clinical performance in diagnostics, as well as prognosis of disease progression, patient’s response to treatment options and the outcomes of the proposed therapy.','Non-invasive multivariate cancer biomarkers and signatures for early disease detection','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Apollo Diagnostics'),('Drug repositioning is broadly defined as the application of known therapeutic compounds to novel indications for which they were not originally intended. We will use an innovative quantum-based technology for drug discovery and design for the systematic repositioning of known drugs or compounds with safety data for AD therapy.','Systematic drug repositioning for neurodegenerative diseases','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Gradient Biomodeling'),(NULL,'Digital strategy and patient engagement for clinical trials','[\"New Orleans\"]','Rebar Interactive'),('Business Summary: Nuveogen delivers a \"disruptive research model\" utilizing a \"proven consortium approach\" dedicated to growing businesses focused in oncology research, trial management, and companion diagnostics. Customers include drug development companies, CRO\'s, and leaders in the oncology research space. Demand for outsourced services has increased sharply as drug sponsors have downsized in response to a sharp global economic downturn. Product/Services: The Nuveogen consortia collaborate with multiple industry sponsors who contract with Nuveogen to provide full service operations for trial execution and management, utilizing a team of research professionals who are highly experienced in oncology drug development. Customer problem:  As the largest drug sponsors increasingly adopt more integrated and strategic outsourcing relationships with top contract research organizations, smaller more niche contract research organizations like Nuveogen will benefit greatly by this trend.','Disruptive oncology research platform joining top research institutions','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Nuveogen'),('Our starting point is TrueMethylTM oxidative bisulfite sequencing (oxBS-Seq), a novel technology that pioneers quantitative, single-base resolution sequencing of the modified bases hydroxymethyl cytosine (5-hmC) and methylcytosine (5-mC). TrueMethyl enables analysis of the DNA methylome with unprecdented accuracy and opens new avenues for basic research, pharmaceutical discovery and diagnostics.\r\n\r\nRecent studies have shown that at some sites in the genome the level of 5-hmC can be comparable to the level of 5-mC, emphasizing the importance of identifying these variants accurately.  However, traditional bisulfite sequencing cannot discriminate between 5-hmC and 5-mC.\r\n\r\nTrueMethyl enables:\r\n\r\nQuantitative measurement of 5-hmC and 5-mC in parallel\r\nSingle-base resolution methylation and hydroxymethylation analysis\r\nConfirmation of the location of unmethylated cytosines','Next generation bisulfite sequencing','[\"Cambridge, UK\"]','Cambridge Epigenetix'),('100Plus believes in the long-term health benefits of small healthy actions. The 100Plus App serves users recommendations for health opportunities (Hopps), which are small healthy actions created by users and served to other users based on location and preferences.  We sell a customized version of our service to companies and organizations interested in the health, wellness and engagement of their employees. Initial paying customers include Kaiser Permanente and Practice Fusion.\n\n','','[\"San Francisco\"]','100Plus'),('RallyOn brings the power of social gaming to corporate wellness. We help companies build healthier, more productive cultures through tailored, team-based challenges and engagement-based incentives.  Our platform delivers an infinite variety of challenges from exercise to weight-loss and stress reduction. We provide HR with turnkey implementation, custom reports driven by analytics, and a challenge/incentive creation engine to give them the flexibility they need to make wellness strategic.  \n\n\n\n','Corporate Challenge and Rewards Platform','[\"Menlo Park\"]','RallyOn'),('Validic is interoperability for mHealth. Our API platform integrates dozens, and eventually hundreds, of consumer health apps, fitness devices, home health devices, and medical devices. We provide healthcare providers, insurers, and corporate wellness vendors a single API connection with access to over 80 integrated apps and devices, removing the need for those organizations to build and maintain connections with each individual app or device.','Health behavior data pipeline for insurance, healthcare, and corporate wellness.','[\"Durham\"]','Validic'),('DueProps fosters continual positive reinforcement to encourage good employee behavior via recognition and fair apportioning of bonus pools. Crucially, our game elements encourage high employee engagement and enthusiasm levels over time.\n\nManagers get unprecedented visibi