ist Dr. Michael Stosich that provides orthodontics for children in Kenilworth, Gurnee, Winnetka, Round Lake, and Grayslake, IL. Adult orthodontics demands continue to increase in his practice, due to the aesthetic treatment options such as Invisalign and SureSmile that are offered. The patient experience begins with a comprehensive evaluation by Dr. Stosich, an orthodontist who possesses educational credentials and training that are twice that required of orthodontists today. His extensive experience in working with some of the most complicated orthodontic cases as part of the University of Chicago Hospital’s craniofacial team equips him for addressing all manner of orthodontic issues.','iDentity Orthodontics is the private practice of family orthodontist Dr. Michael Stosich','[\"Chicago\"]','iDentity Orthodontics'),('Parents love the compassionate care their children receive from Cosmic Smiles for Kids and Dr. Tamara Robison, a Marco Island children dentist. When young patients are nervous about visiting the dentist, Dr. Robison makes sure they are put at ease before starting any treatment. Her calm and friendly demeanor and welcoming office puts children at ease from the moment they step in the door. She has two offices conveniently located in Marco Island and Naples. Fluoride treatments, tooth whitening and standard cleanings are provided in her state-of-the-art office. She also offers more in-depth treatments for patients who require additional dental work, such as crowns, fillings and even root canals for baby teeth. She and her staff at Cosmic Smiles for Kids can adeptly handle it all, and even educate patients in proper oral health care techniques. ','Fluoride treatments and tooth whitening are provided in Cosmic Smile for Kids','[\"Naples, FL\"]','Cosmic Smile for Kids'),('Taking your child in for a regular dental checkup is important for maintaining their overall health. Many parents do not realize that they should be taking their child to visit Dr. Nanna Ariaban, a pediatric dentist in Alpharetta, as young as 1 year old, or when they start getting their first set of teeth. Unfortunately, when parents delay these early pediatric dentist visits, it becomes more common for them to need a kid\'s pulpotomy. Alpharetta is fortunate to have a pediatric dentist as qualified as Dr. Nanna, as her patients and staff affectionately refer to her. She is a well-researched pediatric dentist who strives to stay on top of the current research in her field so she can bring the best care possible to all of her young patients.','Taking your child in for a regular dental checkup is important','[\"Alpharetta\"]','Polkadot Pediatric Dentistry'),('BuscatuDoctor.Mx es una plataforma logística que facilita el contacto entre la sociedad Médica y los pacientes, ligándolos de una manera sencilla y directa.\n\nBajo un estudio de selección, agrupa a los mejores especialistas de tu ciudad, por medio de una base de datos arrojados en el sitio, lo cual da como resultado un acceso simple y rápido, encontrando ágilmente a los profesionales del ámbito Médico a convenir.\n','Directorio Medico','[\"Guadalajara\"]','BuscatuDoctor.Mx'),('Common Sensing is developing GoCap, a pen cap for insulin pens that automatically tracks doses and transmits wirelessly to a mobile phone. The goal is to empower diabetics with better interfaces that connect family and members of the care community while providing actionable safety reminders and trends by contextualizing insulin dose information with blood glucose, exercise and meal data.\n\nWe are tired of medical interfaces that are dysfunctional, clunky and down-right ugly. We want to design an experience for diabetics as people, and not as patients. We can create an experience that caters to the needs of different lifestyles, integrates contemporary data visualization, and is fun and engaging to use. We want to see the line between consumer products and medical products merge into one. This is how we can change the face of diabetes care.','Simple Dose Tracking for Diabetics','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Common Sensing'),('EnteroWave is creating innovative needle-delivered neurostimulation devices for gastrointestinal (GI) disorders.  We use proprietary neuromodulation methods that elicit specific physiological responses, including the ability to mimic the therapeutic effect of a gastric bypass. Diabetes and obesity are a worldwide epidemic, and our devices offer a low-cost, low-risk alternative to surgical intervention.  These versatile devices can also be reconfigured for the treatment of other conditions including GERD, IBS, or motility disorders.  Our patented miniaturization technology comes from Stanford, and our proprietary neuromodulation techniques come from years of research at both Johns Hopkins Medical Center and the University of Texas Medical Branch.\n\nOur millimeter-sized devices are externally powered and controlled, and open a new realm of applications because of the lower costs and risk without surgery.  Currently we are building wireless prototypes for animal and clinical studies. ','Minimally Invasive Neurostimulators for GI Disorders','[\"San Carlos, CA\"]','EnteroWave'),('HealthEngage helps people live better lifestyles with diabetes. We make  easy to use daily tools and engaging health data intelligence programs to make life analysis and diabetes tracking availalble to anyone around the world. Easy, free and in 58 languages, already used by over 100 thousand people.','patient-driven health opinion & data platform','[\"Washington, DC\"]','HealthEngage'),('Tired of investing in X for Y?  Join us and solve a REAL problem. Insulin-dependent diabetics have a daily grind that is humbling:\n\n- 4-6 injections/day, basal insulin in the morning, mealtime insulin before each snack/meal;\n- Constant finger pricks to monitor blood sugar; and\n- You are always worried about what you eat... diabetes is a \"lifetime sentence.\"\n\nThat\'s ~6,000 procedures/year.  We solve all 3 problems with a true once-a-day insulin.   Ask any diabetic, this would be _huge_.','Once-a-day insulin for type I/II diabetes, that gives patients a chance at a normal life.','[\"Houston\"]','Sensulin'),('Dropsense is a convenient and affordable low blood sugar alert system created by harnessing the power of modern sensing, mobile, and machine learning technologies. \n\nDropsense monitors continuously overnight and alerts you upon sudden drops in blood sugar for a fraction of the price of continuous glucose monitors. \n\nNighttime hypoglycemia is one of the biggest risks for the roughly 94 million people with diabetes worldwide using insulin. These individuals are living without a painless monitoring solution to keep them safe. \n\nAt Dropsense, we believe everyone should be able to monitor their blood sugar overnight. Our goal is to provide this technology at a price anyone can afford.','non-invasive low blood sugar alert systems','[\"Berkeley\"]','Dropsense'),('Diabeto is a non intrusive, bluetooth powered hardware device which wirelessly transmits glucose readings from a Glucometer into a smartphone. These readings can then be analysed with the help of a smartphone application for better manageability of Diabetes. ','Diabetes management made easy! ','[\"New York City\"]','Diabeto'),('Our software provides impactful diabetes management insights at the right time; when people test their blood sugar levels. We can present feedback on undesirable patterns occuring in upcoming problem areas of the day, patterns of glucose variability, risk of hypoglycemia, estimated HbA1c, and insulin sensitivity on monitoring devices or on connected mobile phones. ','Actionable diabetes management insight','[\"Charlottesville\"]','InSpark Technologies'),('Created by a group of type one diabetic students at the University of California, Davis, Liveabetes aims to be both a resource for diabetics to track and monitor their condition and a way to let those closest to you stay up to date with live updates for blood glucose, insulin delivery, and more.','The central hub for diabetics and those around them.','[\"Davis\"]','Liveabetes'),('Vital Nanometrics is developing a new class of glucose monitors that provide accurate diabetes management in a pain-free manner. Pain-free, automated and accurate blood-sugar monitoring awaits the diabetic. Significant cost reduction will result for both the patient and insurer. The device is based on patented nanotechnology developed by our team members.','A glucose monitor that is truly pain-free yet cost effective.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Vital Nanometrics'),('Adaptive is commercializing advanced diabetes technology research from the University of Virginia\'s Center for Diabetes Technology.\n\nThe CDC predicts 1 in 3 in the US will have diabetes by 2050.\n\nWe move diabetes care from a dumb, context-free regime to a connected, contextualized one.  We improve diabetes sufferers\' lives, differentiate and increase profit for our customers (big pharma device makers), and create an ecosystem of applications around data previously considered dark matter.','Diabetes Care for the Internet Age','[\"Charlottesville\"]','Adaptive Medical Technologies'),('Diabetes Daily helps people around the world become healthier, happier, and less expensive to the health care system. Originally founded as a social network for people with diabetes, we have evolved into a social educational platform powered by behavior modification techniques. With over 70,000 members, 3 million annual visitors, and major advertisers like Sanofi-Aventis, Roche Diabetes Care, Novo Nordisk, and Medtronic, we have the traction, influence, and platform to save lives and money!','Empowering healthier and happier lives','[\"Cleveland\"]','Diabetes Daily'),('Tidepool is building an open platform and better apps to help people reduce the burden of managing type 1 diabetes.','Open source diabetes platform and apps.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Tidepool'),('Longevity Biotech is developing novel therapeutics to treat the unmet needs of Cardiovascular, Metabolics and Oncology patients worldwide.  Our Hybridtide molecular scaffold has unprecedented and medically necessary characteristics which enable us to pursue novel mechanisms of action, a requirement in todays competitive biotechnology marketplace.','','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Longevity Biotech'),('\"It has been a long time since a new app has changed the way I look at how a task can be accomplished. LogFrog DB is a truly new experience in diabetes management on a mobile device.\" —diabeticnerd.com\n\nAmphistyle\'s flagship product, LogFrog DB, helps people with diabetes track and understand the myriad factors that affect and reflect control of their condition.  Its beautiful, uniquely non-clinical user interface has gained a passionate user following and praise in the press.','Mobile health rethought + redesigned','[\"San Francisco\"]','Amphistyle'),('The Surfacer™ Inside-Out Access Catheter System is a proprietary instrumentation set that allows physicians to perform a novel “inside-out” approach to gaining venous access. With the Surfacer™, physicians insert a guide wire through the femoral vein in the groin area and, using fluoroscopy, navigate it up through the torso with an exit point in the jugular or subclavian vein. The procedure is performed while the patient is under light sedation.','Medical device development company focused on complex central venous access cases.','[\"Lexington-fayette\"]','Bluegrass Vascular Technologies, Inc.'),('Moving Analytics is a Health and Wellness Start-Up whose mission is to provide actionable information to help individuals lead healthy lives.\r\nOur platform Strides is an intelligent assistant to help people meet physical activity goals. We also provide enterprise solutions for clinics that facilitates the exchange of daily physical activity habits between patients and care providers for the treatment of chronic diseases (diabetes, obesity and hypertension) and provides analytics to measure outcomes.\r\nStrides is currently available to consumers via an Android app and to clinicians through a web dashboard.','A smart assistant that keeps you active.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Moving Analytics'),('Rimidi Glucose Manager helps diabetics and their health care providers manager their diabetes in a predictive, proactive way. Our decision support software predicts glucose levels and demonstrates what changes should be made to get the patient into target range.','Data analytics software for diabetes','[]','Rimidi'),('BeatDiabet.es is a predictive diabetes self-management app and glucose meter test-strip subscription service for underserved markets (Latin America initially).\n\nUsers can:\n\n- Understand their glucose trends and receive predictive alerts with practical advice to take control of their condition\n\n- Get affordable self-monitoring supplies delivered monthly to their door.\n\n\nMedical teams will be able to: \n\n- Monitor multiple patients remotely without the need for paper logbooks.\n\n- Get automated risk alerts to predict imminent hospitalizations.\n\n- Connect with patients and their families to jointly enact timely preventative interventions.\n\nAnd Health Insurers will be able to lower the risks and costs of diabetes-related complications.\n','Take control of your diabetes','[\"London\"]','BeatDiabet.es'),('The SugarTrac app is a convenient tool for diabetics to track and manage all avenues of diabetes. Entering vital information such as: blood glucose levels, food intake, basal/bolus rates, and insulin intake are performed on one screen for quick input. As the journal expands, visual graphs become available to give the user an overall perspective of their unique diabetes management plan.','Convenient diabetes management','[\"Reno\"]','SugarTrac'),('AkibaH enables users to intuitively manage their diabetes on the go, free from carrying bulky and easily forgotten glucometers. It\'s a BLE-enabled glucometer built into a smartphone case that communicates with an app to give diabetics personalized suggestions to manage their diabetes. ','Alivecor for Diabetes meets Waze for Wellness','[\"San Jose\"]','AkibaH'),('ManageBGL provides Type 1 (insulin dependant) diabetics with the dose calculators and Active Insulin Tracking only found on expensive insulin pumps - but without the pump. This saves patients 5000 in pump purchase price, as well as 1000-2000 a year in consumables - with the same health outcomes.\n\nIt provides prediction of Hypos (low blood sugar levels) before they cause driving accidents (a world first); integrated coaching to fix up dosing ratios (a world first), and reminders for eye/nerve/kidney tests. \n\nIt shares data live between diabetic kids at school and parents at home, or between patients and their doctors (a world first). \n\nIt has a unique points system that can be used to incent teenagers to take a more active interest in managing their diabetes.\n\nIt imports data from multiple manufacturer\'s devices - Meters, Pumps and CGMS, and integrates them into the cloud accessible from iPhone/SmartPhone/PC/Mac. It has an API for import/export for new devices.\n','Revolutionizing diabetes self-management','[\"Melbourne\"]','ManageBGL'),('Disease Information, Health Care Tips, Health Education, Treatment Options, Alternative Treatment, Health Blog, Health Tool','health care, Health and Fitness, health education, disease information','[\"Rockville\"]','IControlMyHealth.org'),('BHV Pharma is developing a novel, best in class, Sodium Glucose Transporter 2 (SGLT2) inhibitor indicated for Type 2 Diabetes and NASH. Remogliflozin has been dosed in over 800 subjects in over 20 clinical trials. In 12-week phase 2b studies in type 2 diabetics, remogliflozin lowered HbA1c greater than 1% and demonstrated a best in class side-effect profile. Remogliflozin is the only positively differentiated SGLT2 approved or in development with best in class efficacy, best in class side-effect profile, and best in class effect in the >35% of diabetics with renal impairment. \n\n ','Metabolic Drug Development','[\"Raleigh\"]','BHV Pharma'),('Mums Original Superfoods are healthy additions to everyone\'s cupboard.  Traditional recipes with foods that help heal.  We are farm specific producers where we only purchase products from the farmers we know - have visited and the results are in our superior products.\nOur platform is excellent value!  Not price point specific, but rather having an excellent gram for gram nutritional and dollar analysis to allow folks to take charge of there own spend / investment in food!','Superfoods for Superpeople.','[\"Stayner\"]','Mum\'s Original '),('Diabetics monitor their blood glucose levels multiple times a day, and the burden of this task is difficult for many to manage. The Shield is a smartphone protective case that has an embedded glucose monitor capable of bluetooth communication with native diabetic mobile applications. Shield Diagnostics is trying to make monitoring your blood glucose convenient and effective, by reducing the time and effort required to complete, log and visualize one\'s glucose levels. ','Smartphone hardware for diabetics','[\"Edmonton\"]','Shield Diagnostics'),('Sweet Factor Seasonings are made from 100% natural stevia plant parts which includes leaves, stalks and roots blended into our own formulated propriety preparation method.\n\nThe core product currently market is the Sweet Factor Seasonings that will be available in sample test taste package 3 x 6g sprinkle plastic container and in 50g both stick sachets and shaker container model\n','Our mission is to contribute to good health promotion of good food culture','[\"Asheville\"]','MelStevia Inc.'),('Disruptive innovation in biological manufacturing technology enables us to produce off-patent biological drugs more cost-effectively compared to the current biological manufacturing technologies.  \r\n\r\nWe will produce a biosimilar insulin analog, Lantus (which grossed $7 billion last year and will go off-patent in 2015), as it is a very simple biological molecule and can be thoroughly characterized to be identical to the innovator drug.  \r\n\r\nWorldwide diabetic population will increase from 366 million in 2011 to 552 million in 2030.  The annual worldwide insulin demand has increased from 12 tons in 2007 to 22 tons in 2012. and is expected to further increase to 40 tons by 2020.  \r\n\r\nWhile it is reported that it costs about $500 millions to produce every ton of additional insulin in developed countries, we expect our cost of production to be much less than $50 million per ton (i.e cheaper by more than a factor of 10) due to our innovative manufacturing technology.\r\n\r\n\r\n','low-cost biosimilar manufacturing ','[\"Superior, CO\"]','Sudhin Biopharma Co.'),('We are developing high-tech, low-power, user-friendly sensor-based, \"smart\" insoles that wirelessly communicate with feedback systems.  Healthcare applications include prevention of diabetic foot complications and rehab from stroke, spinal cord and nerve injuries.  Sports applications include athletic optimization in high performance athletes.','Pressure-sensing insoles and feedback systems.','[\"Calgary\"]','Orpyx Medical Technologies'),('Timesulin is a timer enabled replacement caps, for insulin pens that people with diabetes already use, that helps the user avoid dangerous double doses. The product was launched in January 2012 and is now available in app 40 countries through big Pharma partnerships, partnerships with diabetes associations, and with a mix of carefully selected medical device distributors. Timesulin was created in 2011 to address the needs of co-founder and CEO, John Sjölund, who has been living with Type 1 diabetes since he was three years old. John wanted a simple solution that would confirm the time since he last took an insulin shot and help avoid an accidental missed or double dose of insulin. After searching high and low for a solution that would allow him to maintain his current insulin treatment program John and his brother Andreas (co-creator of Skype) decided to create a solution that would make life for him – and all other people living with diabetes – just a little bit easier.','Replacement cap for growing insulin pen market to make life easier with diabetes','[\"London\"]','Timesulin'),('Ultradian has developed a pain-free and accurate continuous glucose monitor (CGM) for people with diabetes who require insulin to control their blood glucose levels. The device attaches to the skin and measures glucose within the interstitial fluid, just below the skin surface. Our CGM provides a continuous read-out of glucose levels on a hand-held monitor with built-in alarms for impending high and low glucose levels. ','continuous glucose monitor for diabetes','[\"Albany\"]','Ultradian Diagnostics'),('WINNING DIABETICS™ is developing 3MAP (3 Point mHealth Action Plan), the FIRST MULTILINGUAL mobile/online diabetes platform & Web-Based SaaS EHR (Electronic Health Record) system, based on \'HEALTHY LIFESTYLE\' technique integration- for the approximately 175 MILLION DIABETIC PATIENTS with mobile/online access & their HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS. The platform is compatible with 13 of the most popular glucose monitors on the market. ','Multilingual mobile/online diabetes management & Web-Based SaaS EHR platform','[\"New York City\"]','WINNING DIABETICS™ 3MAP'),('Sugar Doctor helps you control diabetes in 5 days through nano tech and clinical experience.','Control diabetes in 5 days','[\"India\"]','Sugar Doctor'),('Diabetes is the only chronic disease of a man, which immediate therapeutic effects (eg, using insulin-therapy) on the patient provides the patient himself.\nFor the daily work with patients, doctors do not need personal meetings with them – it’s necessary and sufficient to evaluate the data (eg, blood glucose), which patients receive themselves.\nAt the same time, traditional patterns of care and treatment of diabetes at the present suggest that to obtain doctor\'s advice, the patient must necessarily come to the clinic/doctor. Because of the huge level of morbidity of diabetes there»are not enough» doctors and patients often do not have time and resources to consult a diabetologist, the consequences of this situation are dramatic.\nThe use of Internet technologies, coupled with mobile to provide each patient with diabetes timely, qualified and adequate medical help. Having this as the aim, we have created our system for remote reatment of patients with diabetes.','Remote diabetes treatment','[\"Moscow\"]','NormaSugar'),('CHARGED Incorporated is the Manufacture of the World\'s first Naturally Sweetened, Naturally Flavored, Naturally Colored, Zero Calorie Energy Infused Sports Drink without any preservatives or additives.\n\nOur product addresses a growing need in the beverage industry for naturally sweetened and zero calorie energy drinks that are engineered to be friendly to the 20+ million people who live with Type 1 and Type II Diabetes in America, over 78% of them are physically active. Since our beverage is naturally sweetened, naturally flavored, naturally colored and contains zero calories, zero additives and zero preservatives, we also target a healthy conscious consumer market - representing a segment over 50 million people in the United States alone. \n\nUpon company launch, we intend to leverage our extensive retail and distribution relationships under a proprietary and exciting brand name, as well as actively promote international private licensing. ','Zero Calorie Energy Infused Beverages','[\"Las Vegas\"]','CHARGED Incorporated'),('Oleoylethanolamide (OEA) is a fatty acid metabolite that regulates hunger & lipolysis. Innovastics has exclusively licensed two patents from UC Irvine, and engaged in development of dietary supplement and milkshakes for management of body fat.\n\nObesity is the foremost health issue in America. According to the National Health and Nutrition Examination Surveys (2009-10), approximately 69% of adults are overweight/obese (154.7 million). About 17% of American children ages 2 to 19, or 1 in 6, are obese (12.7 million). It is mainly caused by lack of physical exercise combined with the intake of too many calories. Between increased risks of diabetes to hypertension and other ailments, obesity brings a whole host of unwanted factors to sufferers. The food and dietary supplement products that reduce the appetite (calorie intake) and increase breakdown of body fat will address this problem.\n\nU.S. consumers spent more than 322M dollars on weight-loss dietary supplements, shakes and bars.','Novel Dietary Supplement for healthy body weight','[\"Plano\"]','Innovastics'),('Oral drug for Type 1 Diabetes that eliminates or  lowers the need for insulin','Developing and Oral Drug for Type 1 Diabetes','[\"Chapel Hill\"]','Combs Lab'),('Virtual Scientific Research & Development Private Limited is the first company of the world who developed first complete non-invasive, painless, bloodless, convenient and affordable blood glucose diagnosis and monitoring device \"Diabete Watch\". This revolutionary product is the result of six years continuous research & development process and the hard labor of our highly qualified team of experts in scientific research, development and engineering.\n\nOur mission is to develop affordable non-invasive health diagnosis & monitoring devices, real time health monitors and health reporting systems to ease the life of common people and save & extend their life. Diabete-Watch is the first milestone of our journey, now we are working on some other devices as cardio watch, nutri watch, gastro watch, who will bring a revolution in the field of health diagnosis and reporting and will provide most accurate diagnosis about all major organ system of human body.','World\'s First Noninvasive, Bloodless & Painless Diabetes Test & Monitoring Smartwatch','[\"Varanasi\"]','VSRD Private Limited'),('Distribution of all MelStevia Inc product in Hong Kong','Investments and Trading Company ','[\"Hong Kong\"]','C8R Asia Limited'),('We are developing the world’s best patch pump that will impact the lives of millions of people suffering from chronic diseases such as diabetes and Parkinson’s worldwide. From the day of inception, we partnered with one of the top manufacturers of disposable flow control solutions to ensure highest design standards, manufacturability and the right production costs.\r\n\r\nThis is the third pump our team is involved in; the last was sold to Roche for $200M. We have been working under the radar until now, developing a fully functional patch pump prototype and building the IP. We are now ready to accelerate our activity and move to the next phase.','The World’s Best Patch Pump','[\"Haifa\"]','touchemedical'),('The BioLingus technology has been developed over many years.  The focus is to allow \"biological drugs\", which are almost all administered by injection, to be administered in an oral (sublingual) tablet.\r\nThe technology is mature and can be applied to peptides, proteins and vaccines.  \r\nProof of concept is available for each of these types of molecules.  Our initial key therapeutic focus for internal development is diabetes (patients take injections daily over their lifetime) and inflammatory diseases.','convert injectable drugs into oral tablets ... imagine you are a diabetes patient ...','[\"Zurich\"]','BioLingus'),('True Link is a fraud protection service that protects the elderly from black- and gray-market scams, a $100b/yr problem. The service is currently available on a Visa card issued by the company, but will be expanded to checks and credit cards issued by both True Link and third-party financial institutions. Issuing cards to 11m cognitively-impaired elderly people is an existing $1.9b revenue stream, and current issuers (Wells Fargo, Chase, …) license software rather than building it, so would partner rather than competing.\n\nWhen an elderly person swipes the True Link card, the transaction is routed over the Visa network to our servers. There, we compare it to personal spending limits, restricted categories, and a continuously updated fraud database. So when you\'re out paying bills, getting ice cream, or shopping with friends, True Link works just like any other Visa card. But if someone is trying to take your money, we decline the transaction, alert the family, and keep your money safe.','Fraud protection for seniors','[\"San Francisco\"]','True Link Financial'),('TenderTree allows families to find and hire trusted caregivers. Our platform and mobile app manage payments, payroll/taxes, insurance - all online.\n\nAmericans spend $80B on home health care for the elderly. \n\nIt\'s a massive market that\'s almost entirely offline and inefficient. It shouldn\'t cost $30/hr for a caregiver that gets paid only $10/hr.\n\nIsn\'t it crazy that you can see reviews for plumbers and electricians but not for the caregiver for your parents? TenderTree is changing all that.\n','Marketplace for senior care','[\"San Francisco\"]','TenderTree'),('Silver Living helps families find the right senior care community. We use our own mystery shoppers, photographers, and researchers to create an unbiased, expert review that families trust.\n\nFamilies spend over $115k for an assisted living community, which is not covered by health insurance or Medicare. They are frustrated with lead-gen websites that are not helping them with this huge decision.  For example, communities average 4.4 demerits on state inspections. We are the only service that unlocks these reports from the state capital’s filing cabinet and provides the information to families.  \n\nIn only four months, our unique reviews and photos leapfrogged us ahead of the 13-year market leader in organic search. The cost of our high touch content is repaid 6x with the first referral to a community. ','Honest Expert Reviews for the Senior Care Industry ','[\"New York City\"]','Silver Living'),('Care at Hand is a real-time care coordination platform using direct care workers to decrease per capita costs and improve population health.\n\nManaged long term care providers and other software vendors are embedding our technology to add clinical impact to their home care offerings.','Empowering $10/hr lay caregivers to prevent $10,000 hospitalizations','[\"Boston\"]','Care at Hand'),('Amulyte is an emergency response and activity tracking system that connects seniors with their friends, family and caregivers - providing them help when they need it, freedom when they don’t. \n\nThe Amulyte Pendant, worn by a senior, uses cell networks to work anywhere and leverages GPS and WiFi for both outdoor and indoor location detection. It contains a speaker and microphone to allow for 2-way voice communication via the pendant, a battery indicator light, and a help button. It is also equipped with an accelerometer to track activity.\n\nThe Amulyte Portal is an online web app used by family members and caregivers to find location, monitor activity level and trends, check battery life, and ensure everything is working.','Activity tracking & emergency response system for seniors','[\"Mountain View\"]','Amulyte'),('Founded by MIT scientists, QMedic\'s wearable medical alert service passively detects emergency events and functional decline in the home, while alerting caregivers in real-time to these problems.  With 3 patents pending, the platform is the first of its kind to continuously sample behavioral data and not require battery recharge.  By applying machine learning, QMedic is able to baseline behavior longitudinally, which is critical to helping caregivers proactively identify functional mobility and decline in the home.','Passive medical alert service for seniors (wearable computing meets machine learning)','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','QMedic'),('Winner of the Most Innovative Company Award in long term care!\n\nCaremerge is a healthcare coordination and transition platform. Our mobile/web apps allow senior living communities simplify their care coordination efforts with various onsite and offsite stakeholders (facility staff, physicians, hospitals, families, etc.), all providing care for residents. \n\nCaremerge is at the center of five influential trends of our time: Boomers, Healthcare IT, Cloud/Mobile, Social/Collaboration, Big Data.\n\n\n','Healthcare Communication and Care Coordination Platform','[\"Chicago\"]','caremerge'),('OpenPlacement is disrupting the $4.5Bn patient care transition industry by replacing antiquated materials and manual research with an easy to use web application. Today discharge planners rely primarily on a stack of brochures, old printed “lists” and hours of phone calls in order to locate care providers that fit the particular needs of a patient. We solve this acute pain just as Travelocity helped the travel industry solve the problem of locating airline availability and streamlined booking.','Real-time matching of patients with care providers','[\"San Francisco\"]','OpenPlacement'),('There are more then 50 000 families in Poland per year, looking for someone who can look after their child. Our passionate team which enjoys solving problems in most simple way created service which makes this process easier and faster.\n\nNiania.pl connects families looking for best care for their children with nannies and babysitters. Together with OpiekaSeniora.pl (elderlycare), PomoceDomowe.pl (housemaids), Remontuj.pl (renovations) form a group services that allow you to quickly find reliable help for your household. After registration families are provided with easy to use interface to browse caregivers in their area and are able to contact them. They also can leave job offer, and wait for caregivers to apply. Caregivers are building their reputation, creating unique, online resume by publishing references, confirming identity, uploading photos etc.\n\nFinding help for your household was never so easy.\n\nAt the moment Niania.pl is 2nd (after Betreut.de) service of this kind in Europe.','Simply connecting families with caregivers','[\"Warsaw\"]','Niania.pl'),('CareLinx is a professional caregiver marketplace that is disrupting the +$100 Billion in-home come care service delivery market.  CareLinx is saving families over $10,000 a year compared to traditional agencies. CareLinx eliminates the need for traditional brick and mortar agencies by empowering families and caregivers to directly connect online. \n\nCareLinx helps those in need of finding and managing in-home care services (hospital discharge planners, families and home care agencies) to easily find, video interview, run background checks, hire, manage and pay professional caregivers that match their specific needs and budget online. \n\nCareLinx has over 20,000 caregivers within its network and is already helping many families across the United States. CareLinx recently won the AARP National Conference LivePitch event and has been featured in BusinessWeek, Forbes, Bloomberg, more.\n\nThe company earns a 15% service fee on all invoices paid through its platform, similar to Airbnb & Uber. \n','Caregiver Marketplace:  Disrupting the $100B+ in-home care market. AARP Winner!','[\"San Francisco\"]','CareLinx'),('Great news: finding home help just got simply awesome.\n\nmyBestHelper is an essential digital utility that gives families a easy way to access and use all options of care that they need. Families can find and manage helpers (child/elder care) most suited to their needs - not just available and affordable, but also a great fit. We combine social circles and Airbnb-like reputation system (to build trust) with eHarmony-like matching system (for fit between personalities and values). \n\nModern families need better options - and we deliver. 99% of families today still resort to word of mouth and poster board ads to find the help they need to be able to care for loved ones so the parents can work and play. Fully 25% have tried online ad sites, but found it long and complicated. We transform all that.\n\nBottom line: Great team and business model in a large new market focused on building a rapidly scaling profitable company. 4000+ users and early small revenue, but 30% month over month growth.  ','#musthave solution for families who need helpers (child/elder)','[]','myBestHelper'),('GeriJoy relieves stress from families by providing a tablet-based companion for older loved ones. They leverage the proven mental health benefits of pet therapy to combat dementia while reinforcing family connections and memories with daily conversations. ','Virtual companions for the elderly','[\"New York City\"]','GeriJoy'),('Aevi enables people to record videos, write messages and/or upload files. The user designates recipients to the files and/or messages and when the user passes away the system delivers the messages automatically. It is meant to provide people in often difficult situations with a certain ease of mind. There are especially three groups of people that instantly see the value Aevi creates: people battling with degenerative or possibly terminal illnesses, The Elderly and People in dangerous occupations. The messages stay 100% private until after the user has passed away.','Connecting Generations','[\"Reykjavik\"]','Aevi'),('Cariloop is taking the hassle out of finding quality care and services for our seniors.   Cariloop’s digital platform is utilized by seniors, caregivers, and healthcare professionals to access real-time information about geriatric care and service providers.   By supplying a portal where these providers can easily share key information about their availability, pricing, services, and more, Cariloop users can quickly browse through dynamic search results to read patient ratings, discover which providers meet their needs, and connect with them immediately.  \n\nThe days of turning pages in a magazine to bring seniors and providers together have come to an end.   With Cariloop, our seniors, caregivers, and healthcare professionals get the help they need, when they need it.\n','Yelp for the Geriatric Care Industry','[\"Dallas\"]','Cariloop'),('Lively is a consumer product company that gives older adults greater independence with a tighter connection to family.  It provides an activity-sharing experience with its product using passive activity sensors that are applied to everyday objects in an older adult\'s home and LivelyGram, which gives family members a way to share the events of their life with elder loved ones through pictures and short messages. Lively is currently available in the U.S.. Iggy Fanlo, David Glickman and Keith Dutton founded the company in 2010 with collective backgrounds that include bringing loved products and services to market. ','Activity sharing for elders and family','[\"San Francisco\"]','Lively'),('eCareDiary, Inc.is a leading online community and cloud-based tool that helps caregivers manage long term care. It is a trusted, centralized resource that provides the content, tools, and services that caregivers need to manage care more efficiently and with less stress. eCareDiary was founded by healthcare industry experts and caregivers.','Simplifying life for the caregiver','[\"New York City\"]','eCareDiary'),('eCaring generates actionable real time health care data from a patient\'s home. Its intuitive system enables home health aides, caregivers and patients to enter extensive behavioral, clinical and medication adherence data, which the system integrates and configures alerts from. eCaring enables hospitals, healthcare providers, payers & families to keep people in their homes and out of the hospital, by communicating vital in-home care information as it occurs, to: intervene early to prevent significant deterioration; substantially lower care costs while improving quality of care; and reduce hospital and ER admissions. eCaring is a critical tool for care and disease management markets for the elderly and patients with chronic conditions. In trials with Medicaid/Medicare dual eligibles, eCaring substantially reduced ER and hospital use, MD and nurse visits, saving hundreds of dollars per patient per month. We were also selected as winners of the NYC PILOT Health Tech program.','Real time actionable health care data from the home','[\"New York City\"]','eCaring'),('We\'ll aggregate eldercare: housing, resources, information, services and products for boomers navigating through the maze for their aging loved ones. \nBringing together the people, resources, information and assistance to \nthose who need eldercare, and to those who love them the most.','Angie\'s List of Eldercare','[\"Los Angeles\"]','RTime'),('LifeBio makes it simple to capture life stories in health care and senior care settings. LifeBio\'s web-based platform instantly creates very brief or longer biographies -- especially for the 50+ market or those facing health challenges. LifeBio promotes better health through reminiscence. It brings purpose and meaning and generates positive emotions--by asking the right questions to create a lasting legacy.  LifeBio publishes the stories too -- in hardcover, leather-bound books. ','Capture life. Now. Better health through reminiscence','[\"Columbus\"]','LifeBio'),('We run a portfolio of job marketplaces for underserved niches. Users buy subscriptions to have Featured Listings which increase the visibility of their listings and add capabilities to their accounts. We have thousands of paying customers.\n\nPart of our approach to being the leader in each niche is building a strong brand from the best domain name in each category.\n\n- http://sitter.com\n- http://housekeeper.com\n- http://eldercare.com\n- http://petsitter.com\n- http://housesitter.com\n\nThe user experience of our sites is a collation of the best matchmaking mechanisms from online dating sites, classified ads sites, and traditional job boards. Voice, email, and SMS messaging is deeply integrated.\n\nThe front end of our platform is up to date with all the latest good stuff--responsive design, live maps, parallax scrolling, faceted geo-spatial search--and is delivered quickly over a CDN.','Care Provider Marketplaces (Children, Seniors, Pets, and Home Services)','[\"Toronto\"]','CareGuide'),('web and mobile apps for senior care coordination and communication\n including social connectivity, medication adherence, physician visits and caregiver services.\n\nThe platform is open and other developers can build their apps on it, using the data available, to make the experience better for elder people. \n','Senior Care through Communication','[]','Second Light'),('Tapestry is a beautiful, simple, private social network that lets families connect with each other, and together care for the seniors in their lives. ','Connecting seniors to the people who care for them','[\"San Francisco\"]','Tapestry'),('NurseBuddy is a communication tool for home care professionals and the families of people receiving care at home. It\'s a cloud-based mobile planning and communication system which creates a new kind of connectivity between all the participants in the ecosystem: carers/nurses, managers and families.','Use NurseBuddy to effectively manage your home care company\'s communication. ','[\"Dublin\"]','NurseBuddy'),('CareBooker is a central platform to find, book, and pay for all types of family care services, such as babysitting, pet care, tutoring & lessons, housekeeping, personal fitness, and senior care. Parents can easily search for service providers, book interviews and appointments, and pay online. Service providers have a business profile with custom URL web address, showing a menu of service and prices, certified reviews, background checks, qualifications, and their real-time schedules to check availability.\n\n','The \"OpenTable\" for booking family care services.','[\"New York City\"]','CareBooker'),('Linked Senior Inc., a resident engagement solution provider, helps senior care leaders improve the quality of life of their residents. By using technology to support programming, therapy & wellness the service opens communities to the world while helping management improve resident & family satisfaction, productivity and efficiencies.','Engagement solution for the senior housing market (AL, SNF, Memory Care)','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Linked Senior'),('Sensevery\'s first product, Aayu, is Fitbit® for Grandma - a HIPPA-compliant web platform for care providers and their aging loved ones.\n\nIt is becoming increasingly difficult and stressful for the sandwich generation to care for aging parents while supporting their own children. Right now, $80 billion is spent yearly on elderly home health care.\n\nSensevery\'s hardware-as-a-service platform monitors the daily activity of loved ones and alerts care providers when unusual behavior occurs. Our hardware is a combination of a wristband and gateway device; neither requires phone nor internet connections. The wristband collects data about the wearer and shares it with our cloud platform. Our web and mobile applications allow you to access that data and provide a detailed report on activities, including: steps taken, motion, and sleep. It can also detect unusual activity, such as falls, and alert emergency personal immediately.\n\nSensevery helps your loved ones live a safe and independent life.\n\n','Fitbit® for Grandma - Monitors health needs for the elderly','[\"Chattanooga\"]','Sensevery'),('CareTree is a collaboration platform designed to replace the paper records in the home health and senior care industries with an online platform that centralizes information and automates communication with care stakeholders (the individual, their caretakers, family, and doctors).\n\nThe second phase of CareTree is to be a Mint.com for EMR records.  Using EMR patient portals, CareTree will give caregivers access to all of a patient\'s records from one easy portal.','Better communication and collaboration for caregivers','[\"Chicago\"]','CareTree'),('Carevium automates planning, tracking and managing resident assessments, care activities, and medication management in Senior Living communities such as Assisted Living Facilities, Residential Care Homes and Alzheimer\'s Care communities.\n\nCarevium enables family members access care information in real time and provides timely alerts and notifications on Activities of Daily Living (ADLs), Medications, Incidents, and remote monitoring sensors / tools.\n\nElder care facilities can focus on resident care rather than wasting time on paper records creation and maintenance. Carevium usage (1) increases family and resident satisfaction, (2) reduces manual errors and redundant labor, (3) increases compliance, and (4) automates entire workflow in senior communities.\n\nCarevium empowers staff by providing proactive reminders, alerts and notifications to the administrators, nursing staff, and professional and family caregivers. Carevium platform applications delivered as mobile apps and web apps.\n','Empowering senior facilities, care givers and families','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','Carevium - Solutions for Senior Living'),('ChipperList has built an in-depth senior housing directory to let families search and compare online. \n\nWe personally visit every community, taking pictures and writing an expert review. We then compile the world\'s best Senior Housing profile complete with room prices, an activity calendar, and a patent-pending interactive building map that let\'s families see pictures of every room side-by-side with an aerial view of the building so they can get a feel for what it\'s like to live there even before they tour.\n\nThe website is free to users and we get paid on a lead-gen model when someone moves into a community.','Better Senior Housing Listings','[\"San Diego\"]','ChipperList'),('Agility4Life is a health monitoring system for seniors. The system uses latest sensor & imaging technologies to detect when a senior falls and alerts emergency responders quickly. In addition, it monitors activity patterns of seniors unobtrusively and uses sophisticated algorithms to assess risk of falls, early signs of dementia or such diseases, and recommends interventions by physicians, family, and caregivers *only* when needed, giving seniors complete privacy, while providing timely care.','Fall detection, health monitoring & assessment for seniors','[\"Mountain View\"]','Agility4Life'),('beepcare provides a multi-platform service that establishes a long-term relation between patients and their doctors. \n- We provide patients the tools to create their own personal health record (allowing on-the-fly context access by doctors) and\n- Tools to doctors regain control over their patients-lists, while maintaining personal privacy.','Helping doctors get lifetime patients, Helping patients get lifetime care.','[\"Lisbon\"]','beepcare'),('We build voice enabled apps that remove the learning curve from using current accessible tools (aka. screen readers).\r\n\r\nThe current market leading screen reader costs ~$2k and takes special training to learn how to use. \r\n\r\nUsers interact with this software via keyboard commands or swipe gestures to navigate what is displayed visually on the screen, and then reads it back to the user (imagine browsing Facebook with just the tab key...while blindfolded). This design is fundamentally flawed.\r\n\r\nOur design approach structures content to be easily navigated via voice commands and audio feedback.\r\n\r\nRoadmap\r\nVoice enabled version of Yelp\r\nVoice enabled version of Amazon\r\nAPI to create voice interface for any app (provide integration as a service).\r\n\r\nMarket\r\n6.5 million people in the US with a severe, uncorrectable visual impairment (2010 Census). As the babyboomer generation ages, this number will continue to grow.','iOS apps for the Blind.','[\"Pittsburgh\"]','Conversant Labs'),('The CloudPhone 3G is a next generation wearable smartphone for healthier, safer, families. \n\nIt keeps seniors & children connected to their family, and delivers powerful insights into their health and wellbeing. We\'re bringing the Quantified Self to family care.\n\nKey points of difference from existing solutions:\n\n- All \'smarts\' are in the cloud. Voice and data are routed through a cloud-platform. \n\n- Voice controlled dialing brings flexibility to 1 button interface. \'Call a taxi\' \'I need help\'  \n\n- Lifestyle Analytics monitors physical activity & relates it to medical info to identify changes in health.\n\n- Automated fall & motion monitoring - asks the wearer \"Are you Ok?\" before causing a fuss.\n\n- Safe Path, a proprietary geolocation system, monitors regular travel like too and from school.\n\n- CloudPhone requires no end user configuration. \n\n- Functionality can be extended to other devices, feature & smartphones via the cloud platform.\n\nSold as a subscription service.','A voice controlled smart care device that monitors health & activity in seniors and kids.','[\"San Francisco\"]','CloudPhone 3G - by ollo mobile'),('Hello Doctor™ enables you to control your health. By managing medical records from multiple sources, we provide you easy real-time access to all the information you need in order to understand your medical condition.\n\nNow available in the App Store: www.hello.do/d/al','Medical records organizer','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Hello Doctor'),(NULL,'Ultra Low Powered WiFi Sensors and a SaaS to enable Seniors to live longer, better','[\"Washington, DC\"]','SaferAging'),('Cross Cloud Sensor Fusion Platform\n\nA SaaS, B2B solution for mobile health, safety and security monitoring\n\nOur Core: collecting multiple sensor information, transmitting them real time to our cloud platform where we analyze, classify and machine learn -> resulting specific actions.\n\nWe apply this first to mobile health-safety of seniors. And we are able to do it because of world\'s smallest & simplest 3G mobile device \n\nBut we are NOT a device company, have no device revenues and no inventory.',' \"Xross Cloud Sensor Fusion\" platform for mobile health, safety & security monitoring','[\"Menlo Park\"]','BlueLibris'),('Our company Caring in Place is developing an iPhone, Android, and web app to help family caregivers,  typically a female age 45 to 54, care for their aging loved one by creating intelligent check lists helping them know what to do and how to do it.  Caring in Place will selectively introduce products and services to help caregivers complete these tasks.','Digital Health Tools for Family Caregivers','[\"Boston\"]','Caring in Place'),('Oxirate delivers continuous mobile vital sign monitoring and reporting enabled by a proprietary low power sensing platform.\nOxirate transmits raw PPG (Photoplethysmography) and inertial data from the earlobe sensor to a smart phone or a server for processing. Complete data log and results of data processing are available for “cloud” based apps. Oxirate’s sensing platform uses innovative reflective pulse oximetry, advanced signal processing, and low power wireless technology\n','Mobile low power vital sign monitor','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Oxirate'),('Online Memorials \n\nCreate a memorial website in honor of your loved ones. Enshrine your photos, memories and tributes with your friends and family. \n\nSend a Free Funeral Notice\n\nWe offer the free funeral notice to inform friends and family members of a loved ones passing, while keeping control of your privacy and security. \n\nCreate your Bucketlist\n\nMy Bucket list is a free application which helps you build and fulfill your life goals with your friends and family. \n','Social \"Deathworking\" - Crowdsourced photos and videos of your loved ones','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','Remembered'),('CareSolver is a simple, safe, & comprehensive care management platform for the 43M informal family caregivers providing 83% of senior care in the US. CareSolver delivers dynamic, customized task-based careplans covering the clinical & non-clinical aspects of providing care to an aging parent alongside content, vendor services, & collaboration tools necessary to complete tasks successfully. CareSolver increases care quality while decreasing caregiver burden.','A care management platform for family caregivers providing care to aging loved ones','[\"Boston\"]','CareSolver'),('SpeakSet aims to be the communications network for all care services. By connecting older people by enabling simple video calling on their TV we bring a scalable method of care delivery to the people who use care services the most. \n\nLoneliness is a huge healthcare problem. It has a massive impact on mortality and morbidity. SpeakSet combats loneliness and isolation in old age by turning an older person’s TV into a really simple video calling device. It’s been built specifically for older users and works through the TV because this is the one piece of technology they are familiar with. SpeakSet makes video calling accessible and so enables older people to speak face to face with their loved ones and carers wherever they are in the world. ','Video calling for the elderly','[\"London\"]','SpeakSet'),('CareTrio makes it easy to bring together family, friends, and caregivers\nto help manage your loved one\'s health. Coordinate care for a sick sibling, disabled child, or aging parent no matter where they are, how many family members are involved, or how complex their needs are. We securely store all of your important information about your loved one - news, photos, stories, medical records, medications, appointments, and more - in one place, accessible from anywhere in the world, on any device.\n\n','Secure family caregiving','[\"Seattle\"]','CareTrio'),('Living Well offers specialized care for adults with chronic and debilitating conditions — like Alzheimer\'s, Parkinson\'s, ALS, stroke, and mental illness — that compromise their ability to live safely in their homes, where they want to be.','Personalized Care for Chronically Ill Seniors','[\"Tiburon\"]','LIVING WELL ASSISTED LIVING AT HOME'),('There are two parts to the PressVi solution: (a) The PressVi wireless help button that the end user presses in times of need, and is sold through the major pharmacies and health care provider channels, and (b) The PressVi cloud platform that services the PressVi calls on a two-tiered (pay-as-you-go or monthly subscription) basis. The end-to-end technology is fully automated and remains invisible making PressVi easy & accessible to any non-tech-savvy user.','personal help button to instantly Call, SMS & Email remote friends & family','[\"Portland\"]','PressVi'),('Help Find Care is an online caregiving matching service.  It combines the best in job posting, searching, screening, payroll, scheduling, and ratings \n\nEasy to use, and free to join. We Empower caregivers and those looking for care\n\nHelp Find Care charge a hourly fee to the care recipient for each caregiver that they hire using our system.','Disintermediates in-home caregiving by matching caregivers and care seekers','[\"Austin\"]','Help Find Care'),('MyBillRegistry is a crowd-funding platform that can be used by many different groups.  Our first product, MyClassroomRegistry.com, was launched in conjunction with Scholastic and is used to help defray the $400 that the average school teacher spends--out of pocket--on the classroom each year.\nWe have been running a pilot program with Scholastic since January, 2013 and are helping teachers in more than 300 schools.\n\nWe are currently negotiating with a large US cellphone company to help their customers crowd-fund for their bills, accessories and new phones.','A platform to collect consolidate and pay bills directly to product and service providers','[\"New York City\"]','MyBillRegistry'),('Care Architecture builds online and business infrastructure and partners with senior-living, aging-services, and healthcare providers to create local membership programs that keep older adults socially connected and independent by connecting them to other seniors, classes and social activities, service providers such as transportation and home repair, and local merchants.','Local social networks for seniors','[\"San Francisco\"]','Care Architecture'),('One in three of us who live over the age of 65 will develop dementia. Right now there\'s 800,000 people with this condition in the UK and its set to double over the next 40 years.\n\nLosing the ability to communicate is one of the most frustrating and difficult problems for people with dementia, their families and carers. Conversation is challenging for people because words can become abstract concepts, whereas images often retain their meaning. \n\nSee What I Mean is an application that displays the words you say as images while you talk. It\'s designed to help people with dementia and those around them to overcome the stress and damaged confidence that can arise through trying to force ourselves to remember by facilitating enjoyable conversation.','A communication tool for people with dementia','[\"London\"]','See What I Mean'),('Would you know what to do if someone you loved needed help to stay at home? OurCareDirect is a free online service that allows patients and their caregivers to find and manage care services. With OurCareDirect say goodbye to complicated paperwork, hours on the phone, and hidden fees.  Simply create a profile on our site and we walk you through the process of obtaining high quality, affordable care services from providers you can trust. ','Caregiving made simple. ','[\"Norfolk\"]','OurCareDirect'),('Vekami.com – digital technology company addressing care and living interests/needs of 80 mil. senior citizens (50+)  in the CIS region (former USSR).\n\nVekami (stands in Russian for “For ages”) is targeting existing market inefficiencies with B2B2C market/community where brands, local pros and senior consumers could achieve their key objectives with the support of digital tools provided.','mCare for 50+ in the CIS region','[\"Moscow\"]','Vekami'),('CarePredict triggers just in time care for seniors aging independently at home.  We provide a unique wearable sensor that not only tracks activity but also deduces behaviors using context awareness to detect when a senior’s health is declining and triggers social and clinical interventions.   The service is an automated predictive data analytics platform that analyses activity and context deduced behavior data to trigger family and clinical caregiver responses.  CarePredict’s ability to discern changes in a senior’s behavior using its patent pending technology is unique and disruptive.\n\nCarePredict was created because the crisis of insufficient money and caregivers to take care of the rising ranks of seniors can only be addressed by using automated machine learning and predictive systems to monitor and raise alerts when human intervention from family or clinical caregivers is warranted.','CarePredict triggers just in time care for seniors aging independently at home.','[\"Fort Lauderdale\"]','CarePredict, Inc.'),('Sense.ly is an avatar-based, emotively reactive platform that helps clinicians better manage their chronically ill patients.  After the clinician enters in the clinical protocol and goals, a virtual medical assistant follows up with patients, collects clinical data from medical devices and assessments, tracks progress, and helps patients to stay on course with motivations and reminders.  All the information is analyzed and presented to the doctor so patients can get better faster, hospitals can bill for telemedicine procedures, and reduce operational costs.','Taking \'Siri\' to medical school','[\"United States\"]','Sense.ly'),('Disrupting the $2 Trillion senior care industry.','Connecting Baby Boomers with Local Senior Services for their Aging Parents','[\"Denver\"]','SeniorSource'),('Our values are simple. Open Arms strives to offer excellent and affordable ways to connect home healthcare and community-based social services to Senior individuals and families of the US. \n\nIt is our goal to match certified, competent, caring, and well-trained individuals who are responsive to the needs of their Clients, their families, and the communities they serve.\n\0','A Match.com for Clients and Caregivers','[\"San Francisco\"]','Open Arms Healthcare Network'),('Fourth Vital, Inc. has developed a simple, non-invasive, real-time method to measure and track the “elusive” fourth vital in medicine - “volume status”.  Until today, no gold standard has existed for accurately measuring volume status (the amount and ratio of fluids throughout a person’s body).  For the elderly, frail, and chronically ill, volume status turns out to be the most critical vital in predicting and preventing many serious and costly complications and hospitalizations.','Non-invasive, real-time method for tracking and measuring patient \"volume status\"','[\"San Francisco\"]','Fourth Vital'),('H.A.N.A., the Health Assist Networked Agent extends independence and care in the comfort of your aging parents own home. Bringing awareness and interactivity through a digital agent you and they get a vigilant helper 24/7. H.A.N.A. is a realistic animated avatar that lives in their home prompting and interacting in areas of health, wellness, fitness and mental activities.','Health Care Magic Mirror Avatar','[\"Vancouver\"]','H.A.N.A. Digital Home Care'),('Visit www.YourSeniorLiving.com\n\nYourSeniorLiving.com (“YSL”) is a specialized resource website that delivers high-quality senior living resident referrals for senior facilities offering assisted living, memory care, nursing home, and related senior care services.\n\nThe YSL website lists over 55,000 senior facilities nationally with a focus on providing unbiased facility reviews and a forum for interaction with other families during this often challenging time.\n\nLuxury and midrange senior facilities will pay on a referral basis that is featured at the top of “Search Results.”  Featured facility listings include 20 facility photos, property details, pricing, types of care, services, amenities, and activities.\n\nYSL improves the experience of searching for senior living facilities by supplying rich content to assist during the research period; in-turn, YSL delivers senior facility partners high-quality referrals that lower their cost per new resident.\n\n','Yelp of Senior Housing - Senior Living Referrals and Reviews for Senior Facilities','[\"Chicago\"]','YourSeniorLiving'),('What if your doctor knew what drugs would work for you before they ever prescribed them?  The science and technology to make that, and many other immediately useful care decisions based on individual genetics, is now ready for use.\r\n\r\nCoriell Life Sciences is developing a Genomic Data Ecosystem that offers storage of genomic data, expert interpretation and an interchange framework that delivers clinically-relevant genomic interpretation at the point-of-care. CLS\'s three core products, GeneVault, GeneExchange, and GeneDose, allow providers to order genomic sequencing, access expert interpretations, and securely store data for further interpretation when needed.  CLS has created a partnership with IBM to provide the IT infrastructure and joint marketing.\r\n\r\nBased on 6 years of research Intellectual Property, CLS will initially provide doctors with a simple, easy to read report that shows what prescription medications will actually work in a given patient.  ','Real world use of Genomics','[\"Camden\"]','Coriell Life Sciences'),('www.CallSeniorCare.com instantly connects seniors/families with in home caregivers, home care agencies, nursing homes, assisted living facilities, retirement communities, Alzheimer\'s care, elder care advisors, support groups, products and all other senior care services, and vice versa with just a few clicks while providing easy to use senior care collaboration and support tools with full-fledged privacy controls to communicate, share information, and remain involved in caregiving decisions ','Compassionate Caregiving Community with a built-in Intelligent Senior Care Matching System','[\"New York City\"]','Call Senior Care'),('The Healthcare Interchange is a community based care coordination concept comprised of a Consumer Portal, Care Coordination Portal and Healthcare Partner Portal. The composite of these 3 portals aim to support innovative care delivery processes that promote consumer centric, cost effective, and continuous improvement quality care concepts for consumers, healthcare providers, community based teams, and healthcare organizations.\n\n\n\n','Community Based Care Coordination Portal for innovative care delivery','[\"San Francisco\"]','The Healthcare Interchange'),('Great technology helping family members better care for their older relatives.\n\n- Tools for managing care - Keep in touch and engaged with family and friends. Understand and monitor all aspects of care.\n- Source of knowledge for family caregiving - Access experts\' opinions, ask questions, share experiences. Collaborate and connect with other carers.\n- Peace of mind for you and your family - Feel reassured that you are doing the right things. Be recognized for your progress as a carer.','Great technology helping family members better care for their older relatives.','[\"Dublin\"]','Preludio'),('A platform for patients and families to connect with caregivers in their area and interview them online. It would allow families and caregivers to negotiate a pay rate without the added administrative and overhead costs of traditional caregiver services. It also offers a marketplace for families to purchase and lend equipment needed to make the home environment as safe as possible. It features a forum for families to exchange ideas and receive support from others in a similar life circumstance.','Internet based in home care','[\"Nashville\"]','home health care assistance'),('Our mobile solutions promote the the independence of elderly people by monitoring them and sharing relevant events with family and care givers.','Elderly monitoring solutions','[\"Porto\"]','Suricare'),('A digital media company for people who weren\'t born yesterday (boomers and seniors). We inform, inspire, educate, support and engage people 50 and older about the challenges and opportunities in a world in which 50% of our population will soon be 50 or older. An innovative web hub is supported by AgeNation Radio, AgeNation Live, NEXT Magazine, and AgeNation Consulting and Coaching.  Soon - AgeNation Television, Publishing, Travel and Life Learning and Living Communities.  \n\n  ','A Conscious AARP for 50+','[\"Santa Fe, NM\"]','AgeNation'),(NULL,'A tool to coordinate financial & non-financials tasks for families managing health crisis','[\"San Francisco\"]','Sharefund'),('Optimal Home Care is committed to deliver professional health care services directly to you.\n\nDuring a transition into the home from a hospital, nursing home, or rehabilitation center, Optimal Home Care is committed to deliver professional health care services directly to you. We can provide service to our clients who suffer from illness or disability, those recovering from surgery, or to a home-bound individual who would benefit from health care at home.\n\n','\"Care that comes to you\"','[\"Denver\"]','Optimal Home Care '),('In-home, non-medical care service provider; licensed in the state of Florida as a Homemaker and Companion Services company.','in-home non-medical care service provider ','[\"Boca Raton\"]','Lifestyle Keepers'),('We provide elderly whom private care has refused based on high needs and public care has wait-listed with a private care solution that is as highly focussed on the individual as on their medical needs. We do this in a house providing as close to an at-home feel as possible and for an all-inclusive price. This model has been proven here in Ontario with a single pilot home, catching the eye of the Alzheimer\'s Association of Canada as a calming environment and is loved by all who have experienced it.','Private assisted living care for high needs','[\"Toronto\"]','Together Care'),('ECCOpay is a cloud-based online payment portal designed to streamline billing, collection, and payment processing for senior living, assisted living, nursing and home healthcare. Through strategic partnerships with industry leading clinical and billing software providers we are able to automate the billing, collection, and reconciliation activities for our communities; while providing a seamless user experience for their residents and families. This full integrated solutions handles all the private and patient liability payments.','Your Senior Living Online Payment Portal ','[\"Minneapolis\"]','ECCOpay'),('LDS provides the only passive non-contact biometric sensing system that monitors the vital signs of target individuals. This includes babies in cribs, adults with cardiovascular and related disease, residents in care facilities and patients in medical facilities. Existing solutions have limited capability, are impractical to use, require trained staff and are expensive to deploy.\n\nIn the US parents spend more than $48MM annually to monitor only the motion of their sleeping children. More than 80MM Americans suffering from diseases like COPD, cardiovascular disease, chronic respiratory failure and obstructive sleep apnea have no practical way of monitoring the progress of their disease.\n\nWe can monitor multiple individuals within a defined space and can read their respiration and ECG simultaneously. Our system is low cost and requires no special training on the part of the user. Our solution is patent pending.','Non-contact ECG and biometric sensor','[\"San Jose\"]','Life Detection Systems'),('Elderly are living longer and staying at home. Our Next Generation calling help to call centers and/or family members without pressing a button. No more wearing any pendant for calling or falling down to get HELP.  Full coverage of 2 way voice conversation that covers the whole house. We provide redundancy in our system, as well when there is no electricity in the house we offer with our own LED Bulbs light a battery backup for seniors to see in emergency and not get frighten. The emergency lights will also be a standalone product that offers light at homes when there is no electricity. This product will also address a very big problem in the home security with cameras. Cameras do not work when there is no electricity until now. UPS is to expensive and time consuming. Our plug and play is easy to install for full protection when there is no electricity either by electricity company blackout or someone breaking in and no electricity is working.  ','Emergency alert system w/o pendant. Emergecny lighting & power home security cameras.   ','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Gestiphy'),(NULL,'','[\"Detroit\"]','Mazur Senior Care Services'),('Almost everyone knows that caring for seniors is going to present many challenges in the coming years. With those challenges however comes a great opportunity to provide quality, and prosper. \n\nOver the last 2 years I have built a small and successful senior care/assisted living business in Southeastern Michigan which has grown very quickly from 1 to 7 locations.Our primary focus has been on perfecting the operational and managerial processes while focusing heavily on marketing in order to keep beds filled. My ultimate goal all along has been to learn and perfect processes on this smaller scale and to eventually take everything that I have learned, and use that information to build a large national quality focused assisted living company.\n\nFamilies have made it known that they want the best of both the small environment and large environment. Personalized care, home-like non institutional setting with the ability for a lot of customized services and activities.That is what we provide.\n','Customized Assisted Living','[\"Detroit\"]','Havencrest Senior Living'),('Medici’s device enables stress urinary incontinence patients to control leakage.  Stress events are short-duration, high-pressure on the abdomen, such as from coughing & sneezing. The device resembles a self-catheter, and comprises a series of physiologically-controlled valves that achieve control by opening under low pressure from the bladder and by closing in response to the short, high-pressure bursts associated with SUI. Convenience is achieved through weekly, self-replacement by patients. ','Urinary incontinence medical device','[\"Arlington, VA\"]','Medici Medical Technologies'),('PEC will offer an unlimited care service to corporations and individuals. PEC will provide a wide range of services for clients, from grocery shopping, gift wrapping, picking up dry cleaning, pet care, event planning, and car repairs. We help seniors stay independent and maintain their standard of living. For corporations we help facilities retain clients, attract clients and lower overhead cost.','PEC help seniors improve their quality of living and maintain their independence','[\"New York City\"]','Premium Elderly Care'),('Valor provides a low cost, discreet delivery service of incontinence supplies  Our service eliminates embarrassment, and saves people money-especially those on on fixed incomes.  These supplies are generally not covered by Insurance, or Medicare.','Discreet Delivery of Adult Incontinence Supplies','[\"Manchester, NH\"]','Valor Medical'),('I have discovered a triple niche market that really needs our help. I will be working mainly with the caregivers of patients who have Alzheimer\'s disease and early-onset dementia. If you have aging family members like I do, you’ll appreciate what I’m doing. \n\nThe second niche is a safety system for individual sportsmen \n\nThe third niche is at the totally opposite end of the spectrum of the first niche where teens are just starting to drive and/or create trouble for their parents.\n\nThe product line consists of 6 badly needed products with my company having exclusivity on 2 of the 6 products and a 3rd in R&D.\n\nSold individually, the products the products I intend to sell retail for over $700. I am putting them in a kit and selling them as a system with specific directions on how to use them for $499 marketed separately to the three different genres.','The 5.5 million people in the U.S. with Alzheimer\'s disease need our products','[\"Alabama\"]','Gardanĝelo, Inc.'),('Musekick is a platform that helps people discover what matters to them most.\r\n\r\nWorld class coaches of businesses and executives transform people and organizations by asking the right questions. Musekick makes this approach accessible to a wider public, through an online platform and (currently being developed) an app.\r\n\r\nUsers answer inspirational personal questions that help them reflect:\r\n- “What inspires you?”\r\n- “What was your favorite moment last week”\r\n- “if the phone rings next week, who do you hope will be calling?”\r\n- “Why?”…\r\n\r\nThese and hundreds of other questions were tested with dozens of test users in various workshops in Amsterdam. Musekick so far triggered people to change their jobs, quit their relationship, bake pies, and focus on what matters most to them.','Discover what matters most','[\"New Amsterdam\", \"Amsterdam\"]','Musekick'),(NULL,'','[]','CareCrunch'),(NULL,'Person centric health and social data integration SaaS platform','[]','Nourish Care'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"San Francisco\"]','CareMonitors'),('VoiceFriend is developing a vital communications network for connecting communities, care teams, families and seniors.  It will provide a platform for management and communication of community calendars, care plans, safety and security alerts, and chronic disease management. ','We are developing and marketing a voice-centric social networking system for seniors.   ','[\"Waltham\"]','VoiceFriend'),('Boxie\'s mission is to improve the aging at home experience, trough an integration of many useful functions in one single hardware, powered with an user friendly voice interface, and a beautiful design.\n\nIt is composed by a tiny wearable device for the user, as well as a software application hosted in the cloud for the caregiver. It substitutes up to 5 current product categories, making possible:\n\n-User monitoring: fall detection, user positioning, as well as SOS call, anywhere the user is, no matter indoor or outdoor.\n\n-User apps: calendar, schedule, shopping list, pill reminder or remote control.\n\nBoxie allows caregivers to save time, and users to gain freedom.\n\nThere are three customer segments: end user (those who buy the product directly), care service companies (they buy the product and lease it to their users), and finally the government (optimize their public program\'s home care staff costs).','Smartness and beauty for the elderly','[\"Spain\"]','Boxie'),('The Rosebud Open Fit Ready-to-Wear Digital Hearing Aids will help you to; understand speech more clearly, Enjoy watching TV at a comfortable volume and filter out that annoying background noise, while simultaneously amplifying human voices.  Rosebud Open Fits are digital hearing aids and are best suited for individuals with mild to moderate high frequency hearing loss.   ','Sell Hearing Aids Online','[\"Tucson\"]','Century Hearing Aids'),('SASH assists families with the sale of their senior loved one\'s home. This is a life event that can be overwhelming and stressful for the entire family, with financial, emotional, and physical challenges that can last many months. We remove the pain of this difficult life step with our services. \nAs a blend of social work, senior care, and real estate, SASH provides families with a range of first-to-market services that relieve the hard work, expense, and unknowns of the home sal