ver its program to diabetic patients within Mayo\'s family clinics. ','Behavioral Prescriptions for Weight Loss & Inactivity','[\"San Francisco\"]','Sessions'),('Stealthy company by Raj Kapoor & Paul Twohey that will disrupt the fitness industry.  It\'s a massive multi-billion dollar opportunity with network effects.  I have never been as passionate about a business before.  We are on a mission to change the world.....\n\nMore details later....\n\nwww.fitmob.com','\"uber/lyft\" for fitness','[\"San Francisco\"]','fitmob'),('https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/omies-yoga-with-friends/id673465209','Technology for the modern yogi','[\"San Francisco\"]','Omies'),('Atlas takes a new approach to wearable technology in the fitness industry. We have developed a device for weight training that detects which exercise the user is performing and counts reps and sets.\n\nAtlas combines top talent from Johns Hopkins University, Philips Healthcare and Maxim Integrated Products. ','A new approach to wearable technology in the fitness industry.','[\"Austin\"]','Atlas'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','MyFitnessPal'),('5700+ tennis lessons have been purchased nationwide through MyTennisLessons.com since our launch in March 2012.\n\nAs the online marketplace for tennis instruction, customers can compare pre-screened coaches, schedule online, and pay for tennis lessons in their local area. \n\nHeadquartered in Austin, TX, our 7 person team is dedicated to improving the process of finding a lesson or class in your area.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','Find and book lessons with local instructors','[\"Austin\"]','MyTennisLessons'),('Sprout is a start-up that is redefining how companies engage their people on fitness and wellbeing with some outstanding early results. We offer a web based solution that helps companies and their employees manage and quantify the benefits of wellness initiatives. We focus on driving engagement that leads to a significant change in employee behaviour and quantifiable ROI for the 