ysical therapy, nursing homes and home health agencies services. Informedika replaces paper/fax exchange with digital processes through mobile app and web portal. When ordering doctors compare pricing, vendor quality, turn-around time. Once the order is placed doctors and patients gain access to the results of the orders. Informedika automates documents workflow, eliminates fax and paper complete with digital signatures and aggregates tremendous amount of patient electronic data. Informedika is free to doctors and collects fees for orders from vendors. IM Signed contracts with major providers like Quest, LabCorp, Counsyl, RadNet. Informedika is growing virally by referrals and direct sales to Accountable Care Organizations.','Healthcare marketplace powered by electronic ordering and instant results delivery.','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Informedika'),('Hyde Park Venture Partners (HPVP) is an early stage venture capital fund investing in seed and Series A software companies in the Midwest. We invest in technology-enabled business, consumer service and healthcare IT startups with incredible founding teams raising their first or second round of institutional capital. We invest $500K-$1M in rounds of $1.5-3M as well as smaller amounts in seed rounds of $1.5M or less. Yes, we are happy to lead.','Early stage venture capital fund. Chicago based, Midwest focused','[\"Chicago\"]','Hyde Park Venture Partners'),('EveryMove is the Rewards Program for your health. Earn rewards from your health plan, employer and brands for living an active lifestyle. Connect devices, services and apps you are already using to earn points. Get your friends active to earn even more points and rewards.','Rewarding people for the healthy lifestyle.','[\"Seattle\"]','EveryMove'),('A platform for collaborative health: learn from the collective wisdom of patients and professionals alike','Revolutionizing the way people discover health and connect online. ','[\"New York City\"]','Meddik'),('Eligible makes it simple for healthcare companies to pass and receive financial transactions with over 1,000 health insurance companies across the country.  Transactions include queries to determine patient’s health coverage for certain services, claims (invoice) submissions, remittances (payments), preauthorizations, and more. \n\nTransaction pricing varies by type with a range of 5 cents per for coverage information queries to 25 cents per for claims (invoice) submissions. \n\n','Stripe for Health Care Transactions - YCS12','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eligible'),('2.4 billion people around the world don\'t have glasses who need them because of lack of access to eye diagnostics and care. We connect patients to eye care providers/vendors around the globe on our revolutionary cloud based platform, Test2Connect, through developing and disseminating low cost eye diagnostics on mobile phones that allow almost anyone to take an eye test, receive measurements for glasses, and access care from anywhere, at anytime. \n\nSee us on TechCrunch:  http://tcrn.ch/qmCUHZ','On-Demand Eye Care through Mobile Phones','[\"Boston\"]','EyeNetra'),('We digitize a doctor\'s existing phone line by providing a communication platform (mobile application, web, & standard phone) that allows them to more efficiently and more affordably manage their phone calls from patients and other healthcare professionals. $49/user/month.\n\nWe give patients 24/7 direct access to their doctor via virtual care. $40 per call when you need it.\n\n','The Frontline of Virtual Care','[\"San Francisco\"]','Ringadoc'),('Retrofit is the data-driven weight loss company. Created by the nation’s leading obesity experts and using groundbreaking internet technology, we intend to deliver the industry’s best outcomes. Obesity is America\'s #1 healthcare crisis. Because diets do not work, Retrofit has created a 12-month online behavior modification program. Client feedback has been exceptional, with the average client losing 1.2 pounds per week.','Expert-led, data-driven weight loss.','[\"Chicago\"]','Retrofit'),('Patients Know Best is a highly secure data platform for moving patient medical data between settings, people and connected devices. We were recently recognized as the leader in patient-controlled medical records in a Microsoft-sponsored report commissioned by the UK Department of Health (http://tinyurl.com/pkbpif). \n\nThe problem is that the healthcare landscape is composed of many, many silos (hospitals, physicians\' offices, home healthcare, pharma, government, research, etc.) and putting the patient in control is legally and practically the only way to solve this fragmentation problem in one fell swoop and enable truly integrated, cost-effective care.\n\nFundamentally, we\'re solving the data transfer/mobility and interoperability problem. Because it\'s such a bedrock problem, we touch on every part of the healthcare economy, which positions us to act as the highly secure data hub that processes every healthcare data transaction. \n','','[\"Cambridge, UK\"]','Patients Know Best'),('Nveloped helps companies send secure email directly to a recipient\'s existing inbox without complicated plugins or portals. Companies can be up and running quickly by making a simple change to their existing email client or web app. \n','Secure, dynamic content delivery for email','[\"Arlington, VA\"]','Nveloped'),('Digital Assent is a healthcare technology company that helps physicians and brands more effectively engage patients at the point of care. The company’s award-winning PatientPad® technology is transforming the patient experience at doctor’s offices throughout North America.\n\nCompany highlights include being selected by Forbes Magazine as a finalist for its \"List of America\'s Most Promising Companies\", being named \"Mobile Marketer of the Year\" at the third annual Tech Marketing Awards, and winning the \"Cool Technology of the Year Award\" presented by TechAmerica.','PatientPad® reputation marketing and patient engagement platform','[\"Atlanta\"]','Digital Assent'),('Wildflower Health brings mobile engagement to healthcare for enterprises and consumers. We offer a rules-based mobile program and predictive analytics, integrated with health plan and employer programs to give their members a more personalized, highly actionable experience.\n\nOur first product, Due Date Plus, addresses maternity, which is the #1 driver of hospital charges in the US. Our mobile maternity program makes pregnancy healthier and safer by helping pregnant women self-identify and take action on health issues in pregnancy – leading to healthier pregnancies for our users and lower medical costs for our payor clients.\n\nWe are currently implementing programs for payor clients including a large self-insured employer  and a Medicaid administrator that serves more than 30% of all pregnancies in the US.','Mobile programs that make healthcare smarter','[\"San Francisco\"]','Wildflower Health'),('Careport Health is an online booking engine for post-hospital care. 8 out of 10 patients leaving hospitals need additional care such as at a nursing home or at home through visiting nurse services. Our matching algorithm finds patients the post-hospital care they need when they need it. Additionally, we aim to track patient care to improve communication with family and primary care providers.','Finding the right care for patients','[\"Boston\"]','Careport Health'),('We combine convenient packaging, personalized service, and modern technology to create a system that enables people to take the right medication at the right time - resulting in healthier, happier customers who have more time to spend living well instead of managing medications. \n\nPrescriptions, over-the-counter medications and vitamins are delivered from our pharmacy in Manchester, NH to your door in pre-sorted packets organized and labeled by when each dose is taken. The packets fit neatly into a well designed, recyclable dispenser. You receive a new shipment every two weeks, along with a clear medication list that highlights any changes or new instructions.  PillPack pharmacists coordinate with your physician to manage refills and are available on email or by calling the pharmacy anytime you have a question.','We are making the process of managing multiple medications simple.','[\"Boston\"]','PillPack'),('AboutOne’s Family Management System provides one place to manage memories and household information.','Online Family Management System','[\"Philadelphia\"]','AboutOne'),('Care at Hand is a real-time care coordination platform using direct care workers to decrease per capita costs and improve population health.\n\nManaged long term care providers and other software vendors are embedding our technology to add clinical impact to their home care offerings.','Empowering $10/hr lay caregivers to prevent $10,000 hospitalizations','[\"Boston\"]','Care at Hand'),('ZappRx connects patients with doctors, doctors with patients and patients with caregivers by building tools to help all three mobilize recovery directives and prescription information. ZappRx lies at the intersection of healthcare, technology and privacy, enabling the end user to obtain medication quickly and take it safely.','GoogleWallet meets ePrescribing','[\"Boston\"]','ZappRx'),('ScriptPad lets physicians send prescriptions electronically to pharmacies, monitor their patients\' medication histories, and prescribe cheaper drugs based on patients\' insurance information. We will receive revenue from pharmacies for every prescription sent and also release a premium subscription version. This will allow the government to pay physicians directly once these physicians are able to to qualify for federal incentives (more than paying for the cost of our system). See screenshots at http://bit.ly/an7qyj or a one minute demo at http://bit.ly/9rXlNv.','Electronic prescriptions on mobile devices','[\"Boulder\"]','ScriptPad'),('Secure web and mobile application that enables remote diagnosis of dermatology cases, dramatically reducing wait times for patients while driving increased revenues for providers. US-based consumers wait on average 1 month to access a dermatologist. DermLink enables consumers to receive from US board-certified dermatologists an accurate remote diagnosis, treatment plan and prescription within 24 hours by submitting a photo and answers to a few symptom related questions. ','Online dermatology for remote diagnosis of skin issues','[\"Palo Alto\"]','DermLink'),('CATALYZE let\'s developers build secure, scalable, interoperable health and wellness apps without any backend development.\n\nYou want to build a health app? No problem, we\'ve got your API ready. \n\nWant to connect to additional services? We\'ll handle that too, giving you one RESTful JSON API for it all. \n\nNot a HIPAA expert? Never heard of CCD/CCDA, HL7, x12? Don\'t worry, we\'ll handle that so you can focus on your core value. \n\nWant to prove your app works? Use our clinical effectiveness analytics.','compliant cloud-based platform for healthcare','[\"Madison\"]','Catalyze'),('We\'re developing a powerful mobile health monitoring platform that will reveal new insights about stage-zero care.','API for the Bloodstream','[\"San Francisco\"]','Sano'),('BioBeats is an adaptive media company. \n\nWe build technologies that respond to physiologic data and learn from how you interact with them, to help people live more engaging, healthier lives. \n\nWe are currently developing programmes for entertainment, consumer health and wellness and clinical medicine. \n\nOur first experiment ‘Pulse’ was awarded the 2013 EchoNest prize at SXSW and was in the top three finalists in the Music Accelerator. Our adaptive health technologies are built on a cloud-based responsive platform designed to support the management of chronic conditions and general wellness. \n\nOur team is based in Beverly Hills, London and Pisa, which allows us to understand the nuances of healthcare in the both the US and Europe.','Merging entertainment and healthcare.','[\"Beverly Hills\"]','BioBeats'),('Amulyte is an emergency response and activity tracking system that connects seniors with their friends, family and caregivers - providing them help when they need it, freedom when they don’t. \n\nThe Amulyte Pendant, worn by a senior, uses cell networks to work anywhere and leverages GPS and WiFi for both outdoor and indoor location detection. It contains a speaker and microphone to allow for 2-way voice communication via the pendant, a battery indicator light, and a help button. It is also equipped with an accelerometer to track activity.\n\nThe Amulyte Portal is an online web app used by family members and caregivers to find location, monitor activity level and trends, check battery life, and ensure everything is working.','Activity tracking & emergency response system for seniors','[\"Mountain View\"]','Amulyte'),('Filament Labs is building PatientIO, a patient engagement platform. We give health professionals tools to track & manage their patients when patients are away from the clinic. We specialize in adherence problems for chronic disease therapies, with an initial focus on the infusion & dialysis space, a 14,000 clinic / $27B market.\n\nBy early Q1, we will power patient engagement for 20 infusion clinics nationwide. The CEO of our first customer is also an investor in Filament. We also have a relationship with a specialty pharmaceutical supplier, which offers a channel to thousands of clinic locations. \n\nFilament Labs is a Techstars Austin \'13 company. Filament\'s founders have previous exits to WebMD, Expedia & Rev Worldwide.','Patient Engagement Platform','[\"Austin\"]','Filament Labs'),('The patient referral process is broken. Fibroblast\'s connected care platform fixes it. With Fibroblast, providers and payors can actively manage referrals. In the fee-for-service context, Fibroblast drives top-line revenues, increases patient satisfaction, and improves patient outcomes. In the evolving fee-for-value context, Fibroblast eliminates out-of-network patient leakage, which in turn substantially lowers costs, improves profitability, and promotes population health.\n','Automated, closed-loop healthcare referrals','[\"Chicago\"]','Fibroblast'),('Kinsights is a vertical social network for parents. Each member\'s profile, activity, interests, and pediatric\nhealth record work together, helping us proactively surface a relevant community – personalized for each parent.\n\nBy safely monitoring your child\'s medical records, you\'ll be able to ask questions of parents who have been in your shoes before, and see the questions parents in your situation are asking. Along the way, we\'ll give you access to great resources and useful, well-designed data. ','Share great advice with parents like you.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Kinsights'),('Figure 1 is a crowdsourced medical image library and a platform allowing for photo sharing by healthcare professionals. They can upload and tag images, use each other\'s images for information and education, rate images for accuracy or clinical representativeness, and discuss cases. It is safe and deeply conscious of patient privacy, but simple and easy to use.\n\nFigure 1 launched in the app store this past summer, but already has tens of thousands of active users, who are uploading hundreds of images, and engaging in conversation about them. \n\nIt has been featured by CBS, The Atlantic, Mashable, Gizmodo, Smithsonian Magazine, Medgadget, Canada\'s National Post and Globe and Mail, and many others. \n','Photo sharing for Healthcare Professionals','[\"Toronto\"]','Figure 1'),('Each year over 70M Americans struggle to find the right doctor. \n\nBetterDoctor solves this problem by offering web and mobile apps that make doctor discovery simple and transparent. Just select the type of doctor you are looking for, pick your insurance plan and select from verified and well-rated doctors near you.\n\n★ Available nationwide with 1 Million doctors\n★ Find a top-rated doctor you trust at http://betterdoctor.com\n★ iPhone App https://itunes.apple.com/app/betterdoctor/id588931415\n\nBetterDoctor web and mobile apps have helped over 5 million Americans find the right doctor.','Find the Best Doctor Near You','[\"San Francisco\"]','BetterDoctor'),('BetterFit uses FDA datasets and big data analytics to predict how patients will react to medication. We leverage these insights to get patients on the right drug faster, anticipate adverse events and engage with patients in real time using SMS conversations.  \n\nOur adaptive learning algorithms enable us to parse each response, and use this information to detect problems and decide which questions to ask next.\n\nTarget customers for this service include health care providers and pharmacies.','personalized medicine for everyone','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','BetterFit Technologies'),('We’re changing the way healthcare technology is purchased, consumed, and delivered to patients through our collaborative platform.  Our overarching mission is to enable life saving technology to be at the right place, at the right time, for the right cost.  Join our team in building more incredible partnerships with some of the best hospital groups, physicians, and clinical staff in the world.\n\nOn our platform doctors get access to any device in their health system\'s network through our proprietary application and logistics service.  Push a button on their smartphone, a robot or a laser shows up at their next surgery.\n\nWe have combined this on-demand capability with a real-time medical device and supply marketplace.  Our goal is to enable providers to have the same type of pricing transparency that consumers get when buying products off of Amazon.  We are flipping the archaic healthcare supply chain market on its head.  Join us.\n','Bringing collaborative consumption to healthcare','[\"Boston\"]','Cohealo'),('We build software that helps doctors, scientists, and programmers make sense of massive amounts of health data. The past decade has seen a revolution in molecular technology, which means we can now collect large amounts of precise medical data about anyone at low cost. The problem is that the data are not in a language doctors can understand.\n\nOur API for Medicine helps programmers and scientists at research hospitals, diagnostic companies, biotech and pharma companies, and CROs translate molecular data into information doctors can use to diagnose and treat patients. We\'ve compiled the world\'s molecular data and made it easy to work with and understand.','The Data Platform for Medicine','[\"New York City\"]','SolveBio'),('FlexMinder saves consumers money on healthcare expenses by making Flexible Spending Accounts (FSAs) work.  FlexMinder is a free online tool to manage your Flexible Spending Account.  FlexMinder tracks all your healthcare expenses, prepares and submits your FSA claims, estimates how much to contribute, and makes targeted suggestions for spending your money.\n\nwww.flexminder.com','Automating Healthcare Claims Workflow ','[\"Seattle\"]','FlexMinder'),('HealthCrowd\'s engagement platform allows health insurers to engage their Members, earn government incentives & avoid financial penalties. \n\nWe do this by leveraging the ubiquity of mobile messaging coupled with proven consumer engagement techniques from the online advertising industry to motivate action!\n\nOur patent-pending approach delivers atypically high & unprecedented engagement rates (5-10x better), sustained over long periods of time (> 500 days), as demonstrated with paying customers. \n\n','We\'re turbocharging patient engagement. SaaS + mobile + big data for Healthcare.','[\"Cupertino\"]','HealthCrowd'),('Augmedix is a service for medical doctors that\'s powered by Google Glass. \n\nWith Augmedix, doctors can focus on what they do best: taking care of patients.\n','A service for medical doctors that\'s powered by Google Glass.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Augmedix'),('InCrowd provides our clients with realtime market feedback directly from their Crowds (e.g., physicians, nurses, patients, etc.) via a do-it-yourself proprietary moble and browser based technology.  We are currently serving Life Science clients (pharma, biotech and medical device).','Connects life science companies to their Crowds providing in-the-moment insights ','[\"Boston\"]','InCrowd'),('Common Sensing is developing GoCap, a pen cap for insulin pens that automatically tracks doses and transmits wirelessly to a mobile phone. The goal is to empower diabetics with better interfaces that connect family and members of the care community while providing actionable safety reminders and trends by contextualizing insulin dose information with blood glucose, exercise and meal data.\n\nWe are tired of medical interfaces that are dysfunctional, clunky and down-right ugly. We want to design an experience for diabetics as people, and not as patients. We can create an experience that caters to the needs of different lifestyles, integrates contemporary data visualization, and is fun and engaging to use. We want to see the line between consumer products and medical products merge into one. This is how we can change the face of diabetes care.','Simple Dose Tracking for Diabetics','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Common Sensing'),(NULL,'OSTP is an early stage vc firm that founds, accelerates, and invests in start-ups.','[\"Baltimore\"]','OSTP Ventures'),('Founded by MIT scientists, QMedic\'s wearable medical alert service passively detects emergency events and functional decline in the home, while alerting caregivers in real-time to these problems.  With 3 patents pending, the platform is the first of its kind to continuously sample behavioral data and not require battery recharge.  By applying machine learning, QMedic is able to baseline behavior longitudinally, which is critical to helping caregivers proactively identify functional mobility and decline in the home.','Passive medical alert service for seniors (wearable computing meets machine learning)','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','QMedic'),('Pipette helps reduce complications and unplanned readmissions after surgeries. Preventable readmissions burden the healthcare system with an extra 4.4M hospital stays and cost $30B a year. Our mobile application monitors and educates patients during their recovery. Pipette uses proprietary algorithms to enable early intervention by identifying high-risk patients.','(Acquired by Ginger.io) Remote patient monitoring on mobile phones','[\"San Francisco\"]','Pipette'),('Kit Check allows hospitals to track consumables starting with kitted medications.\n\nEvery hospital has scores of kits that are used for emergency situations and everyday surgeries. State board of pharmacies require these kits to be checked by pharmacy technicians and double-checked by registered pharmacists, costing the pharmacy about 30 minutes per kit.\n\nKit Check automates the processing of kits by applying RFID tags to medications. With Kit Check, hospitals can process a kit in seconds.','Automated hospital pharmacy kit tracking. Reduce kit processing time by more 90%.','[]','Kit Check'),('Winner of the Most Innovative Company Award in long term care!\n\nCaremerge is a healthcare coordination and transition platform. Our mobile/web apps allow senior living communities simplify their care coordination efforts with various onsite and offsite stakeholders (facility staff, physicians, hospitals, families, etc.), all providing care for residents. \n\nCaremerge is at the center of five influential trends of our time: Boomers, Healthcare IT, Cloud/Mobile, Social/Collaboration, Big Data.\n\n\n','Healthcare Communication and Care Coordination Platform','[\"Chicago\"]','caremerge'),('Hint Health provides software for a rapidly growing (capitated) healthcare model commonly referred to as direct primary care. By removing insurance from routine care and paying healthcare providers a fixed amount to keep patients healthy, incentives are aligned, overhead and cost of care is reduced, and patient experiences and outcomes are improved. \n\nAlthough a godsend, this model represents a departure from norms that have been established over decades. Consequently, most vendors do not support nor understand the customer needs - we are changing this by building software specifically designed to help direct primary care physicians start, run, and grow their businesses.\n\nOur beachhead product handles membership management, billing, and patient onboarding, and will soon integrate with popular EMR systems who are serving the market. And as they evolve, our product will support new payment models in the industry so that our customers do not need to use disparate technology systems.','Software for Direct Primary Care','[\"San Francisco\"]','Hint Health'),('Amplify Health is helping primary care physicians (PCP) reassert their role as the principal navigator of their patients\' healthcare journeys. Our software enables PCPs to direct contract with self insured employers (SIEs) and proactively manage their patients. When doctors are being paid for outcomes, they have one mandate: create effective treatment plans that their patients follow. \n\nWe created the software to measure and achieve this mandate. We combine medical record data (the plan of what should happen) with claims and other sources (what\'s actually happening) and surface two major deviations that are indicative of future avoidable healthcare costs\nOff the Plan: not adhering to prescribed treatment plan e.g. did not take $50 medication\nOff the Ranch(OTR): utilizing healthcare without the PCPs knowledge e.g. $50,000 self referral to spine surgeon\nThe examples in the 3rd slide are outputs from our rules engine that identified OTR activity.','Powering proactive primary care','[\"San Francisco\"]','Amplify Health'),('Care providers with an expanding member base and a rising risk volume can effectively utilize clinical data to segment their high risk populations and tailor interventions for high-risk, high-utilizing patients. CliniCast has pioneered in building highly predictive and adaptive models that generate actionable insights and can be incorporated into case management workflows.','Industry Standard Health Risk Score','[\"San Francisco\"]','CliniCast'),('Benefitter\'s software-as-a-service solution presents employers with health care coverage strategies, helping them evaluate, refine, and ultimately execute the coverage plan that delivers the greatest benefit to the company and its employees. Benefitter educates and guides employees throughout the insurance selection process, relieving them from the stress and confusion associated with buying an affordable plan that covers the doctors they want and the care they need.','Helps employers navigate Healthcare Reform, save money, and improve employee well-being','[\"San Francisco\"]','Benefitter'),('Aidin is a web application used by hospitals to connect hospital discharge planners and patients with the best performing post-acute care providers.  \n\nWith Aidin, post acute providers have access to every referral in their area, patients can choose the provider best-suited to serve their health needs, and hospitals save money from reduced readmissions and shortened length of stay.\n\nAidin is a member of the first class of Blueprint Health, a health IT incubator in NYC.','Discharge planning that’s faster, friendlier and powered by data.','[\"New York City\"]','Aidin'),('Sensentia automates complex healthcare administration/operation tasks that until now required human intervention, driving higher efficiency and better quality of service at lower costs:\n\n- Benefit eligibility inquiries to payers.\n- Claim processing and validation.\n- Claim adjudication.\n\nSensentia\'s platform is capable of handling such tasks automatically at a high reliability (>95%).\n\nOur first product helps health insurers handle the billions of complex real-time benefit eligibility inquiries from care-providers and members. \n\nCurrently handled by call-center agents, answering is slow, expensive, and suffers from high error rates. \n\nSensentia offers, for the first time, a fully automated, highly reliable, web/mobile-based alternative.\n\nIn a recent proof-of-concept pilot with a top 5 insurer, Sensentia\'s system demonstrated 97% accuracy answering real provider inquiries based on representative original policies.\n\nThe system is as intuitive as asking another human a question.','A new breed of intelligent systems for healthcare administration/operation','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Sensentia'),(NULL,'CRM for Doctors','[\"Mountain View\"]','Healthloop'),('Nurep is a mobile health company that has developed a medical device support network that links hospital systems with medical device expertise for real-time operative support.\n\nThe medical device industry spends over $40B a year to send expensive personnel onsite to support healthcare providers in the operating room. The evolution of value-based healthcare has made this expensive and inefficient in-person model no longer sustainable. \n\nNurep will improve patient outcomes, reduce healthcare costs and streamline healthcare delivery through a secure and trusted network that allows on-demand operative support to anywhere in the world. \n\nNurep is creating clinically relevant features to allow for quality support in a remote setting. They will be the first to track novel operative data, record procedures and obtain clinical info to improve healthcare.\n',' Medical Device Support Network (Stanford StartX Med, Blueprint Health)','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Nurep'),('CardioSleeve is the first FDA cleared stethoscope add-on device for clinicians to acquire 3-Lead ECG and Digital heart sound at any point of care. CardioSleeve enhances the traditional stethoscope by recording, displaying and analyzing the heart\'s ECG and acoustical footprints in real time via any wirelessly connected portable device.  \r\n\r\nPatient heart sound auscultations are subjective to the hearing, experience and training limitations of the clinician, leading to missed diagnosis and additional costly tests.  A traditional ECG requires wired electrode cart machines which limits their access.  \r\n\r\nCardioSleeve disrupts this cardio-diagnostic process by allowing clinicians an attachment to their current stethoscope to acquire digital heart sound and ECG and perform real time analysis at any point of care via mobile.\r\n\r\nCardioSleeve\'s device/ mobile app platform offers:   \r\nUniversal stethoscope attachment\r\nDigital Auscultation\r\n3- Lead ECG\r\nMurmur Analysis\r\nCloud EHR','Stethoscope attachment with mobile heart sound and ECG','[\"Pittsburgh\"]','Rijuven'),('CancerIQ helps providers manage the complexity of personalized medicine and deliver high quality cancer care. Our big data platform is designed to highlight the specific data elements needed to identify patient risks, interpret complex data, and highlight the best evidence-based interventions. By helping practices keep up with rapidly-changing advances in cancer genomics, we help them retain patients currently lost to referrals, deliver higher quality care and reduce costs. After seven years in private beta testing at the University of Chicago Medical Center, CancerIQ is now developing commercial software to help scale personalized cancer care.\n\nCancerIQ transforms important data buried in unstructured text into discrete data that generates insights. The platform integrates clinical, genomic, and outcomes data to power multiple use cases for providers and practices.\n\nKey Differentiators: \n•	Robust data model, including genomics \n•	Built by users for users \n•	Network of early adopters','Data-Driven Personalized Cancer Care (Rock Health)','[\"Chicago\"]','CancerIQ'),('MedWhat is a personal medical assistant app providing automatic personalized answers to your health and medical questions.  Users can create a quick anonymous health profile telling MedWhat their age, gender, and current medical conditions. This allows MedWhat to provide personalized answers and have a contextual conversation with the user by following up with questions and pushing health notifications to your phone. MedWhat uses natural language processing and bioinformatics to understand and create medical logic.  The team is made of statistics and computer science engineers, and a medical adviser from Stanford University Hospital. The free MedWhat app is currently ranked as a new and top medical app by the Apple app store and already being used by thousands of people.','Personalized Healthcare Assistant providing answers to your health and medical questions.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','MedWhat'),('DoctorBase allows any medical provider to have the same great patient communications platform as a Kaiser Permanente or a One Medical - without the multi-million dollar price tag and lengthy implementation times. \n\nWe know how to build engaging mobile experiences, drive B2B revenues and nail the CAC Ratio. \n\n\n\n\n','mHealth as a Service','[\"San Francisco\"]','DoctorBase'),('OpenPlacement is disrupting the $4.5Bn patient care transition industry by replacing antiquated materials and manual research with an easy to use web application. Today discharge planners rely primarily on a stack of brochures, old printed “lists” and hours of phone calls in order to locate care providers that fit the particular needs of a patient. We solve this acute pain just as Travelocity helped the travel industry solve the problem of locating airline availability and streamlined booking.','Real-time matching of patients with care providers','[\"San Francisco\"]','OpenPlacement'),('WebMD announced that it has acquired Avado, Inc., a developer of cloud-based patient relationship management (PRM) tools and technologies that enable better communication between consumers and health care professionals. \n\n“Our acquisition of Avado demonstrates WebMD’s commitment to playing a leading role in the emerging patient relationship management space because we believe that connectivity has the potential to make the delivery of care more efficient and improve patient outcomes,” said David Schlanger, WebMD’s Chief Executive Officer.  \n\n“WebMD reaches the largest audience of health-focused consumers and healthcare providers in the U.S. and it’s exciting to think that Avado’s technology will be built out and scaled for the benefit of such a significant audience,” said Chase.  “What’s more, since trust is paramount when it comes to the sharing of health information, it made logical sense for us to be joining a company that is the most trusted US consumer brand.” ','Hubspot for healthcare. Patient Relationship Mgmt built. Major customer traction.','[\"Seattle\"]','Avado'),('Reify Health provides scientists in academia with a web platform that allows them to create custom mobile health solutions without doing any programming themselves. Users can leverage mobile technologies like text messaging, a smartphone app, and mobile sensors to create custom algorithms for engaging patients and test the effectiveness of their mobile health solutions at changing health behaviors in clinical trials. ','The lab bench for digital health.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Reify Health'),('MadebyMedics is a task management and communication tool which aims to  reduce human error and improve patient safety in hospitals.\n','Reducing human error in hospitals. A ward management and communication app.','[\"London\"]','MadebyMedics'),('We are in the business of building businesses. Our approach is twofold. We partner with existing companies and assist with distribution and scaling. We also build businesses from idea generation through to launch and exit.\n\nVia our premier network, we have active engagement and extended touch points with our portfolio group of companies at all stages of the business development cycle. Leveraging these relationships and engaging though our network, we have increased our success rate.\n\n','LX Ventures launches, integrates, & acquires early stage high growth technology companies.','[\"Vancouver\"]','LX Ventures Inc.'),('Prevently.com provides 4 products and services.\n\n1) Health Content: Prevently will have content from Harvard Medical School Health Publications as well as from it\'s own network of thousands of freelance writers.\n\n2) Health Products: Prevently sells healthy/organic food, supplements, personal cares products, and devices like FitBit in an online shop via the Amazon Fulfillment program.\n\n3) Telemedicine: Prevently connects users to doctors and dietitians for live video consultations either through instant consults or through monthly subscription fee.\n\n4) Personal Health Record: Prevently offers an online personal health record that integrates data from 50 devices and apps into 1 profile. Healthcare providers can get notifications when patients do things like gain weight, don\'t exercise, or aren\'t sleeping enough. Providers can adjust the thresholds for these notifications. \n\n5) Social networking. \n\nPrevently also offers social networking features (inbox, live chat, notifications etc.)\n\n','Making the world a healthier and more connected place. ','[\"San Francisco\"]','Prevently'),('We look for investments where the product or service focuses on the use of technology to improve the business or consumer experience. \n\nThe business must scale in a repeatable fashion.\n\nMarket Segments:\n\nInformation and Communications Technologies (ICT)\nSoftware (Business and Consumer)\nMobile (Business and Consumer)\nSocial Media (Business and Consumer)\nSoftware as a Service (SaaS) (Business and Consumer)\nPlatform as a Service (PaaS)\nHardware \n\nVertical Markets:\n\n1. Financial Services\n2. Healthcare (Not Therapeutics): Medical Devices, Diagnostics\n3. Digital Media \n','','[\"Toronto\"]','Maple Leaf Angels '),('Procured Health is a web-accessible information platform that enables allows hospitals to tackle their fastest growing cost - medical devices. The platform leverages the collective knowledge of hospital members, along with public data from vendors and the FDA, to facilitate adoption of high value products to both reduce spend and improve care. ','Making the medical device market efficient','[\"Chicago\"]','Procured Health'),('More than 110M adult Americans suffer from musculoskeletal conditions each year. We help them get better fast, saving billions for their families, employers, and insurance companies.\n\nHow it Works: After evaluating a new patient, physicians and physical therapists Home Team Therapy to recommend exercise programs to their patients.  When the patient gets home, she can follow along with instructional videos, track progress, and message her therapist.\n\nWe\'ve got some great early traction, with private betas underway and user feedback pouring in.  If you\'d like to take part, please email tim@hometeamtherapy.com and we\'ll add you to the team!','Get better fast with free, doctor-designed exercise programs just for you.','[\"Boston\"]','Home Team Therapy'),('Using a web application, RefillWizard allows physicians to define custom protocols for medication refills allowing subsequent access by their team (e.g. MAs, RNs).  With access, the team can complete medication refills under certain circumstances (ie. defined by the physician) or at a minimum \"prepare\" the refill requests for the physicians so they have all the information needed to make a decision on the refill request.  ','We create physician productivity applications.','[\"Chicago\"]','healthfinch'),('Medicalrecords.com (http://www.medicalrecords.com/) is a lead generation business connecting 650K+ physicians and dentists with over 360 Electronic Medical Records (EMR) vendors.  \n\nStrong market demand is being driven by the 2009 Federal Stimulus Bill which directly allocated more than $27B to help spur EMR adoption (<20%). \n\nEvery physician and dentist can receive up to $66k in incentives and are mandated to adopt EMR software by 2015 to avoid Medicare and Medicaid reimbursement penalties.\n','World\'s Largest Directory of EMR Software','[\"Boston\"]','Medicalrecords'),('Everyone gets sick, but not all of us have equal access to state-of-the-art care.  Grand Rounds levels the playing field.  We connect patients to recognized experts from the top medical institutions. Founded by an academic physician from Stanford University, Grand Rounds  puts the top specialists on the case.  Grand Rounds  patients receive treatment based on the highest standard of care available.\n\n(Grand Rounds is formerly known as ConsultingMD)','Effortless access to world-class care.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Grand Rounds'),('Tonic is revolutionizing medical data collection by making it MUCH more patient-friendly and highly actionable.  This translates into greater patient engagement, more accurate data, improved patient screening and tracking, increased efficiency and lower costs for healthcare organizations everywhere.\n\nTonic\'s platform is in use or coming online soon at the following leading medical centers: Mayo Clinic, Kaiser, UCLA, UCSF, Georgetown, Palo Alto Medical Foundation, and the VA, among others.','Revolutionary iPad-based medical data collection platform built for patient engagement','[\"Menlo Park\"]','Tonic Health'),(NULL,'','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Syapse'),('Co-investment fund to expedite the close of early stage rounds for high growth companies. Partners have extensive operation experience running companies with deep bench of top level access to support with strategy and connecting the dots. \n','Early Stage Capital','[\"Chicago\"]','Pallasite Ventures Fund IV '),('Eko provides physicians with certainty when they are diagnosing heart conditions. We’ve built one of the world’s first stethoscopes that can automatically detect heart murmurs. Doctors currently have the almost impossible task of trying to hear minute differences between heart sounds, which results in frequent misdiagnosis and undetected heart abnormalities. Through a physician’s smartphone, the Eko software compares a patient’s heartbeat to a database of thousands of others and provides almost instantaneous feedback to the physician. Eko gives every physician the power of a cardiologist in their pocket.\n\nFEATURES\n| Digitize heart sounds from almost any analog stethoscope\n| Visualize the heart sounds; record and play them back\n| Get an instant analysis of a heart sound by comparing it to thousands of others\n| Attach heart sounds to patient\'s medical records\n| Securely share heart sounds with other physicians','A cardiologist in every physician\'s pocket','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eko Devices'),('Based in Chicago, we own and operate a suite of digital healthcare information networks delivering condition-specific video programming at point-of-care in all 50 states to over 50M patients a year. We empower healthcare professionals to engage patients while curating content personalized for each member practice. As a mission-driven organization, we strive to deliver media as a service to educate and inspire audiences utilizing the latest digital media technologies.','Pandora for Health Information','[\"Chicago\"]','ContextMedia'),('Vilicus Ventures manages an investment portfolio that is primarily focused on private equity. \'Vilicus\' is the Latin word for steward, usually as the caretaker of an estate. The goal of the company is to reflect this image in their management of the capital entrusted to them.','a seed and early stage venture fund focused on mobile health technology','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Vilicus Ventures'),('MyFitnessWallet is a complete health management and fitness analysis solution designed especially with the current health/fitness conscious generation in mind. \nThis multi faceted tool provides a simple and integrated platform for individuals with existing medical conditions and hospitals/clinics treating them, fitness enthusiasts as well as those who just want to keep a track of what they eat and do on a daily basis. \n','Monitor your health and fitness… the easy way','[\"Santiago\", \"Singapore\"]','MyFitnessWallet'),('Klinify is a document management system that helps private specialist clinics manage patient records while preserving their existing workflow. It takes 20 minutes to set up our software, scanner, and tablets. The clinic can stop paper from entering the clinic by substituting paper processes with our tablet app – without any downtime. \n\nOur customers are private medical specialists in Singapore and South East Asian nations with a medical tourism industry. These doctors charge a premium for each consultation and service to patients matters. ','Evernote for Private Medical Specialists.','[\"Singapore\"]','klinify '),('*  90M+ overwhelmed U.S. family caregivers managing their aging loved ones\' evolving health, insurance, legal, financial, housing and social needs.\n\n*  They need better tools and expert guidance.\n\n*  The CarePlanners Kit is a physical organizer designed to drive membership in CarePlanners.  Think of it as an Idiot\'s Guide to Caregiving.  We are in conversations to have this lead generation product distributed on QVC by Dr. Nancy Snyderman (the #30 most trusted person in the US according to a 2013 study) and through other channels.\n\n*  The CarePlanners online system is a robust interactive resource enabling caregiers to manage their loved one\'s care.  Our tools help caregivers orchestrate the challenges of caregiving.  \n\n*  The CarePlanners expert network are available to CarePlanners members to provide support during calm times and in a crisis.','Making life easier for family caregivers (90M+ Americans) (LearnVest for caregiving)','[\"New York City\"]','CarePlanners'),('The KyruusOneTM Platform is a Big Data information and analytics system that dynamically assembles and integrates comprehensive data from 1,000\'s of external and proprietary data sources about physicians. Our technology incorporates the latest healthcare domain-specific methods for ensuring high-confidence matching, disambiguation, and attribution of records so that users are always basing their critical operational decisions on complete, accurate, and up-to-date information. Our sources include structured sources, such as state medical databases, clinical trial registries, and claims / billing data, as well as unstructured sources, including hospital websites, journal articles, conference proceedings, and company websites. Our database contains billions of data points on all physicians licensed to practice in the U.S., and is updated daily to ensure freshness and up-to-date insights.','Bloomberg for Healthcare','[\"Boston\"]','Kyruus'),('CareInSync delivers real-time mobile care collaboration tools, helping healthcare providers reduce costs and improve quality by coordinating safe & timely patient care transitions. Why? Today 1 in 5 Medicare patients is readmitted to the hospital within 30 days of discharge. Today, providers use pagers, notepads etc for care planning causing unsafe and delayed care transitions and resulting in increased costs and in some cases even Medicare penalties providers.','Mobile care collaboration software to coordinate safe & timely care transitions','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','CareInSync'),('PinMyPet helps you to take care of your beloved pets, giving to you insight into what they\'re doing when you\'re not home, tracking their activities and location in real time. Anytime, anywhere, you can rest assured knowing your pet\'s safety is at your fingertips on your phone. \n\nThe PinMyPet collar device is compact and comfortable for your pet, and instantly recharges itself in the presence of Wifi. Over 10 million pets go lost each year, and less than 15% of those dogs & 2% of cats are returned to owners. Your pet depends on you for care. Don\'t leave their safety up to chance. Let PinMyPet help you care for your pet. \n\nPinMyPet Mobile is a powerful App to use alongside the PinMyPet collar device with a handy pet time-line that organizes all your pets vital records and information.  Inputting information about your pet is simple and fast, and sends reminders about medicine and vet appointments directly to your phone. ','The small collar tracking device for keeping your pet safe & healthy','[\"Mountain View\"]','PinMyPet'),('Earlydoc helps you make the right decisions about your health and that of your family and friends.  \n\nIt tells you exactly what your doctor would tell you: if you need to find help, what you have to watch out for, what you can do yourself & much more.\n\nEarlydoc is completely based on guidelines, validated by doctors and tested with patients.\n\nOur goal is to provide everyone with instant medical analysis. We aim to be the world’s safest, most relevant and reliable medical app.  ','Your doctor\'s brain online','[\"Amsterdam\"]','Earlydoc'),('Arthur Ventures is an early stage venture capital firm that invests in enterprise software companies.  We specifically focus on companies that sell software into the business, healthcare, agriculture and energy markets.  Our initial investment size in these companies typically ranges from $250,000 to $3,000,000, with most being in the $1,000,000 to $2,000,000 range.  While we invest nationally, the majority of our time is spent in the Midwest. We have offices in Fargo, ND and Minneapolis, MN.  \n\n','Midwest-based enterprise software VC','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Arthur Ventures'),('Starting in October 2012, Center of Medicare Services (CMS) will withhold 1% of a hospital\'s total payment if the hospital has more than 25% readmission rate for heart failure.  HRS has developed a mobile platform to help hospitals reduce heart failure readmissions by providing patients with an educational tool in the hospital that transitions to a early alert system for hospitals and patient engagement tool at home.  Real time data used by algorithm calculates a real-time readmission risk score','Reduce CHF re-admissions','[\"New York City\"]','Health Recovery Solutions'),('Valant provides an Electronic Medical Record and Practice Management Suite for psychiatrists. Our products help psychiatrists manage their practice, get their work done quickly, and provide better care to their patients.','SaaS EHR for Behavioral Healthcare','[\"Seattle\"]','Valant Medical Solutions'),('Umbie Health Corporation is a cloud based, HIPAA compliant application platform that structures the processes, communications, and productivity for specialty healthcare practices. Umbie DentalCare is our premier product that is designed for dental professionals; it can be accessed with just a web browser, is maintenance free to the end-user.\n\nUmbie DentalCare’s comprehensive office management solution streamlines: human resources; billing and receivables; insurances and medical records; appointment scheduling; charting and documenting exams and procedures, and so much more. In addition to office management, Umbie DentalCare offers practice accountability through role-based user authentication, customizable reports and metrics, and automated data entry tracking for each user. Lastly, Umbie DentalCare encourages patient engagement through an interactive office-patient communication portal, customizable appointment reminders, and chair-side x-ray viewing and treatment plans.  \n','We deliver office management, practice accountability,  and patient engagement solutions.','[\"East Hartford\"]','Umbie DentalCare'),('MEDIVIEW™ by Beyond Lucid Technologies is a multi-award-winning enterprise management software platform for Fire/EMS agencies. We are deployed in CA and PA – including the largest EMS agency based in California – and we are negotiating engagements with public, private, and hospital-based EMS organizations in New York, Pennsylvania, Colorado, and Alabama.\n\nWe help agencies complete their required patient records accurately and efficiently, even while they are still in the field. Our cloud-and-client system combines a clean interface with tools to help transfer patients from EMS to hospital emergency department, enabling patient pre-registration and clinical team activation, and improving care by reducing data loss at handoff.\n\nMEDIVIEW™ liberates medical and logistical data collected by EMS in the field so information moves seamlessly into the ED and across a care network, keeping patients and providers safe while improving operational efficiency and quality of care, and cutting costs.','Emergency incident management software that works both online AND offline during disasters','[\"Concord\"]','Beyond Lucid Technologies'),('Pristine EyeSight is a HIPAA compliant 1st person audio and video streaming solution built for Google Glass that\'s optimized for healthcare workflows and environments. It solves the problems of: \"I need help\" and \"Can you come look at this?\" \n\nSurgeons are using EyeSight for teaching / training and intra-operative consults.\n\nAnesthesiologists are using EyeSight with certified registered nurse anesthetists (CRNAs) so anesthesiologists can extend the MD-CRNAs ratio, driving cost savings.\n\nICU and ER nurses and residents are using EyeSight to beam in specialty consults.\n\nEmergency responders are using EyeSight for field support.\n\nWound care nurses are using EyeSight to beam in wound care doctors for complex cases.\n\nHomecare nurses are using EyeSight to beam doctors into patients homes.','Telehealth Communications Through Google Glass','[\"Austin\"]','Pristine'),('Think: The OnStar button for Doctors & Pharmacists using medical Apps.\n\nNeedl is a Q&A service that enables healthcare professionals to ask questions about the drugs they prescribe—within the web and mobile Apps they use to search for drug information every day. \n\nNeedl sells these questions directly to Pharma companies eager to engage HCPs.\n\nThrough the Needl Dashboard-API we provide up-to‐date business intelligence about the questions HCPs are asking, and the trends influencing their behavior.','The OnStar button for Doctors & Pharmacists using medical Apps.','[\"New York City\"]','NEEDL'),('Touch Surgery is a mobile app that is transforming surgical training.\n\nScientific methodology is used to teach surgical procedures in a step by step fashion, improving surgical decision making and critical thinking.\n\nSurgeons are now able to learn, rehearse and practice surgery, on a virtual patient, anytime and anywhere. Surgeons receive feedback on their performance, allowing focused improvement, and ultimately leading to improved patient care and surgical outcomes.\n\nPartnerships with leading surgical centres worldwide ensure that Touch Surgery simulations are always accurate and up-to-date, allowing the global surgical community to benefit from high quality and highly accessible surgical training.\n\nBe a better surgeon with Touch Surgery.\n\n\n\n','Surgical Simulation on Mobile Devices','[\"London\"]','Touch Surgery'),('AdhereTx enables Manged Care organizations and Providers to efficiently perform clinically validated and cost-effective comprehensive medication review for high risk patients, including dual eligibles and the chronically ill at the point of care. \n\n\n\n','Medication Reconciliation at Point of Care','[]','ActualMeds'),('Aevi enables people to record videos, write messages and/or upload files. The user designates recipients to the files and/or messages and when the user passes away the system delivers the messages automatically. It is meant to provide people in often difficult situations with a certain ease of mind. There are especially three groups of people that instantly see the value Aevi creates: people battling with degenerative or possibly terminal illnesses, The Elderly and People in dangerous occupations. The messages stay 100% private until after the user has passed away.','Connecting Generations','[\"Reykjavik\"]','Aevi'),('Corengi has developed an online search engine to help patients find clinical trials for which they may be qualified.  The Corengi technology includes all ongoing trials in the U.S and Canada for a specific condition and is available both on a dedicated website and via an embeddable widget.  We provide augmented exposure for paying clinical trial sponsors and also give a new revenue stream for health-related websites.','AdSense for clinical trial recruitment','[\"Seattle\"]','Corengi'),('Our first product is a disposable diaper that screens for ... .  Stay tuned!  ','Watching your children\'s health.','[\"New York City\"]','Pixie Scientific'),('Artemis is an analytics platform that helps self-insured employers save money on healthcare by analyzing their health data, visualizing hotspots where they can save money, and allowing them to create and track cost saving initiatives to verify that they\'re getting results.\n\nThere are over 65,000 self insured employers in the U.S. and in 2012 they paid for 30% of the country\'s total health bill -- $810B.  Unlike fully insured companies, these employers pay for each and every claim that their employees submit.  Today they have to use PDF or paper reports that they receive once a year from their plan administrators to make decisions that drive their health care spend, one of their top 3 costs.\n\nArtemis visualizes their data in a way that makes it easy for them to understand their costs, risks, and the steps they can take to control them.','Analytics for Optimizing Employer Healthcare Spending','[\"New York City\"]','Artemis'),('TalkSession is a telemedicine platform focused on increasing access in mental healthcare.\n\nTalkSession’s feature product is based on cutting-edge WebRTC video technology, in its first production application in a healthcare setting. TalkSession develops web-based solutions for existing patient/provider networks to make their systems more efficient and patients healthier, through increasing access to mental healthcare and integration of behavioral health into primary care settings.\n\nTalkSession brought the best therapists online as part of our founding member team. Together with this selection of leading providers, we are creating solutions to improve clinical care, reduce costs, improve access to quality treatment, and formulate best practices in telemedicine for the mental wellness field.','Technology Solutions Improving Access in Healthcare','[\"New York City\"]','TalkSession'),('We help physician practices and hospitals put down the phone and see more patients. Our automated medical interview turns a 15 minute phone call into a 1 minute review. A typical, mid-sized hospital can turn turn 25,000+ hours of unreimbursed and lost time into $800K revenue.','Put down the phone. See more patients.','[\"Chapel Hill\"]','Keona Health'),('DNA Guide\'s enterprise solution leverages the same mapping technology used by the defense and telecommunications industry to distribute personalized medicine genome maps at the point of care.   We help health IT networks rapidly deploy the necessary infrastructure for managing genetic interpretation and access across diverse user groups.','Enterprise Genome Mapping Software for Health IT Networks  \"a google earth for the cell\" .','[\"San Francisco\"]','DNA Guide'),('Cariloop is taking the hassle out of finding quality care and services for our seniors.   Cariloop’s digital platform is utilized by seniors, caregivers, and healthcare professionals to access real-time information about geriatric care and service providers.   By supplying a portal where these providers can easily share key information about their availability, pricing, services, and more, Cariloop users can quickly browse through dynamic search results to read patient ratings, discover which providers meet their needs, and connect with them immediately.  \n\nThe days of turning pages in a magazine to bring seniors and providers together have come to an end.   With Cariloop, our seniors, caregivers, and healthcare professionals get the help they need, when they need it.\n','Yelp for the Geriatric Care Industry','[\"Dallas\"]','Cariloop'),(NULL,'Operational Intelligence for Hospitals','[]','Intelligent InSites'),('NudgeRx is a healthcare software and services company focused on reducing surgical readmissions by improving patient adherence through a daily discharge plan, web/mobile interaction and 24/7 nurse support. NudgeRx\'s platform is turn-key and system independent, does not require physicians or hospitals to enter patient discharge instructions, has pre-built recovery pathways and serves as a first line of defense, referring patients back to their providers when medically necessary.','Virtually holding patients\' hands in recovery','[\"Redmond\"]','NudgeRx'),('Kyron uncovers patterns in clinical data to help make better decisions.\n\nOur unique platform for clinical discovery enables researchers and clinicians to identify interventions that lead to differences in outcomes by conducting virtual clinical studies on similar patients. Our focus is to learn new medical knowledge -- which we call Practice-based Evidence -- by analyzing patient-level data already being collected in medical facilities, and learning the patterns of care that lead to better outcomes. ','Big data for clinical insight','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Kyron'),('Honexus produces a health information system and a data collection platform for the developing world. We provide clinics and hospitals with a health information system featuring electronic medical records, pharmacy management, lab reports, report generation to fulfill government obligations and more. This same software is also used to collect information which is then used by NGOs and similar relevant stakeholders to improve the performance across multiple clinics either through sharing resources and improved monitoring or for research purposes. \n\nIt is the first solution that is built to meet the needs of policy makers, researchers, suppliers and the end-users (physicians and clinical staff) and is all integrated into one platform that is designed to be user-friendly (for users of low IT literacy), adaptable on the front-end and standardized on the back-end.\n\nWe are currently running a pilot in Kampala, Uganda and testing various hardware options for the rural context.','Progressive ICT','[\"Kampala\"]','Honexus'),(NULL,'Collaborative Software Platform for Chronic Disease Management','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Atelion Health'),(NULL,'early stage VC for healthcare and online/mobile','[\"Warsaw\"]','RTAventures'),('Innovate Wireless Health’s (IWH) RxMinder, is a multi-directional patient-centric communications platform designed to increase medication compliance and reduce long-term healthcare costs.  It provides the patient with chronic disease with medication reminders, prescription tracking, messages and alerts for care givers. It is the ONLY platform that allows for confirmation or denial of adherence by the patient in a mobile environment.','Wireless, Patient Communications Platform Produces Real-Time Healthcare Analytics','[\"Austin\"]','Innovate Wireless Health'),('We have built an easy to use platform that lets patients view a doctor\'s calendar, book appointments and carry out video consultations with physicians. Our platform is catered specifically to tele-psychiatry as a launching point into healthcare.','An online doctor\'s office','[\"New York City\"]','1DocWay'),('Fileklip is a credential management system for healthcare providers that reduces labor costs by 50%, turnaround time by 70%, and increases accuracy by 200%. In summary, it is a document-managing application that lets employees access, manage, update, and share their own credentials from anywhere. Ultimately, alleviating the burden for their hiring facility and affiliated staffing firm, in addition to minimizing the need for a compliance officer on staff. \n','A smarter way to manage credentials for health care providers','[\"Wellesley\"]','Fileklip'),('MediSafe is developing a digital health platform and app for patient engagement. \n\nConsuming medication is a responsible act that might be dangerous. In 2008, in the United States alone, 700000 people has had an emergency due to medication over consumption, 27000 people had died from it (putting it on the second place in accidental deaths only after car accidents. According to the CDC report).\nMediSafe has undertaken to solve this problem for medication consumers.','Changing medication consumption using mHealth','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','MediSafe Project'),('InSample is an early stage SaaS solution for health sector data science. Our platform packages proprietary analytics and high quality health data into web-applications, allowing our users to easily access information on any disease vertical. Our customers are health product vendors (digital health, biotech, pharma, devices) and providers/payers (insurers, health plans, hospital networks, employers).\n\nExample use case: A Life Science vendor configures an app to calculate their product ROI (see last 2 images above).\nTheir sales rep uses the app live in a meeting with a prospective customer, such as self-insured employer with young employees, aged 25-45. The app generates an ROI estimate specific to this population in real-time. In this case, the prospective customer pays $150.00/Patient/year for the intervention, saves $572.00 in medical costs over 2 years, and garners a 91% ROI. They use the same app for internal strategy and marketing materials.','Apps for Healthcare Analytics','[\"San Francisco\"]','InSample'),('SnapMD is a Healthcare IT company focused on the telemedicine market and provides a robust communications platform designed to enable healthcare providers to engage patients directly. SnapMD’s telemedicine platform enables secure one-on-one live video, audio and secure messaging consultations between ambulatory patients and their primary care and specialty care physicians. Our HIPAA and HITECH compliant platform is designed to accommodate consultations on-demand or on a scheduled basis. \n\nSnapMD can deliver virtual urgent care consultations to reduce avoidable visits to the Emergency Department, follow-up consultations for patients undergoing active treatment, and remote medical services such as in-school virtual clinics and physician-to-physician consultations. This service is sold to healthcare systems, hospitals and other healthcare providers, enabling them to more efficiently utilize their personnel to deliver accountable, efficient and affordable care.','Virtual Office Visits for Patients and Doctors','[\"Los Angeles\"]','SnapMD'),('SurgeryEdu aims to help healthcare professionals educate patients about their medical procedures.  We hope to improve patient satisfaction by facilitating more effective, interactive, and engaging doctor-patient communication.  \n\nwww.surgeryedu.com','Effective patient education','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','SurgeryEdu'),('The Ubiqi Health personal discovery platform combines a mobile-enabled data-gathering framework and a sophisticated data aggregation engine. We empower people to do their own investigations to identify which treatments and lifestyle changes improve their health. \n\nWith data amassed from our users, we create a store of clinical evidence that helps healthcare organizations ensure that people receive the best treatments for their individual needs.','Personalized investigations for chronic conditions','[\"Boston\"]','Ubiqi Health'),('SupraMed is a web-based medical recordkeeping and office management program for surgeons. There are very few software programs available focused on the needs of the private practice surgeon. Even fewer of these are web-based programs. For a low monthly fee, doctors will be able to securely store and manage patient information. SupraMed will simplify the process of writing notes, filling prescriptions, reminding patients of appointments, ordering labs and receiving test results. This will reduce human errors , missed allergies, and potential drug interactions leading to improved patient care. The ease of installation avoids the expense of IT consultants, office servers, and data loss due to computer crashes.\n\nOur product will have a version designed for each type of surgical specialists. These include general surgeons, ENT, plastic surgeons, dermatologists, ob/gyn, and orthopedic surgeons. Marketing will take place through national surgeons conventions and through surgeons magazines.\n. ','Office management and EMR for surgeons','[\"San Diego\"]','SupraMed'),('eCaring generates actionable real time health care data from a patient\'s home. Its intuitive system enables home health aides, caregivers and patients to enter extensive behavioral, clinical and medication adherence data, which the system integrates and configures alerts from. eCaring enables hospitals, healthcare providers, payers & families to keep people in their homes and out of the hospital, by communicating vital in-home care information as it occurs, to: intervene early to prevent significant deterioration; substantially lower care costs while improving quality of care; and reduce hospital and ER admissions. eCaring is a critical tool for care and disease management markets for the elderly and patients with chronic conditions. In trials with Medicaid/Medicare dual eligibles, eCaring substantially reduced ER and hospital use, MD and nurse visits, saving hundreds of dollars per patient per month. We were also selected as winners of the NYC PILOT Health Tech program.','Real time actionable health care data from the home','[\"New York City\"]','eCaring'),('At GoGoHealth, we’re creating on-demand, asynchronous health care delivery over the Internet.\n\nHalf of visits to primary doctor’s offices are for 40 common illnesses and conditions, such as shingles, pinkeye or infected ear.\n\nThese illnesses are not hard to diagnose or treat, but most people have to take time out of their day to see their caregivers. Many just skip going to their doctors, allowing these small illnesses to progress and sometimes become more serious and painful.\n\nGoGoHealth has developed a platform that allows for safe, secure, and quick relief for these ailments.\n\nDoctors determine how to treat illnesses, then dispense advice, a prescription, or -- if needed -- a request for an in-person examination.\n\nThe value to patients is clear: They get quick relief, get it from their own doctors wherever they are, and won’t skip seeking treatment.\n\nThe value to doctors is greater: They “see” more patients, don’t waste time on minor cases, and keep their patients happy and loyal.','A new way to deliver health','[\"San Francisco\"]','GoGoHealth'),('In collaboration with Qualcomm Life, Jointly Health provides an end-to-end Remote Patient Monitoring and Analytics Platform that can detect changes in health states much earlier and with greater specificity than anything on the market. Jointly Health also makes this information actionable by healthcare professionals within their existing workflow. \n\nThe first application of Jointly Health will reduce preventable hospital admissions in patients with complex chronic disease. In the U.S. there are 4M preventable hospitalizations resulting in $88B in preventable costs. Remote patient monitoring has the potential to reduce these hospitalizations but is plagued by missed intervention opportunities, false alarms and inefficiencies. Jointly Health solves these problems.\n\nOur revenue model is a recurring per-monitored-member-per-month fee of $80 to $100 and delivered as a platform-as-a-service model.\n','Big Data Analytics for Remote Patient Monitoring ','[\"San Juan Capistrano\"]','Jointly Health'),('DocMeIn helps healthcare providers manage their time and allocate it to patients in a way that maximizes their profits. On top of best-in-class scheduling and messaging capabilities, we help healthcare providers by delivering:\n- algorithmic patient segmentation;\n- dynamic pricing;\n- multi-channel distribution;\n- higher load factors;\n- increased reimbursement.\n\nGet a free account at http://DocMeIn.com.','Scheduling and pricing platform for the global healthcare industry.','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','DocMeIn'),('Innovation Garden is a Venture Incubator where we fund-advise-service early stage companies to help cross the chasm to series A financing. Our Venture Incubator provides essential, flexible, readily deployable, and capital efficient services to our portfolio companies customizing the offering to compliment the current teams legacy skill sets and reducing the risk associated with directly hiring and training key personnel, as well as taking on an active advisory role to guide, oversee, and engage with the business. ','Venture Incubator','[\"Princeton\"]','Innovation Garden'),('Enables research scientists in academia and corporations to interact directly with genomic data, rather than requiring the expertise of a bioinformatics specialist. This increases our potential market by two orders of magnitude. Our open science, cloud-based platform provides for storage and management of high throughout sequencing data, analysis and exploration using proven, journal-published methods and applications, and enables on-the-fly creation of genome browsers that allow researchers to interact with and visualize their genomic data in an entirely new way, helping them to detect previously hidden patterns and insights. This dramatically increases research and development productivity, especially for biomarker discovery, in applications such as therapeutics, molecular diagnostics, biotech, and agribusiness.','Next generation genomic data management, exploration, and visualization','[\"San Mateo\"]','Maverix Biomics'),('We provide data, analytics, and tools that help our enterprise customers lower their costs and improve patient outcomes.','Making drug safety information accessible, actionable, and predictable','[\"Healdsburg\"]','AdverseEvents'),('LifeBio makes it simple to capture life stories in health care and senior care settings. LifeBio\'s web-based platform instantly creates very brief or longer biographies -- especially for the 50+ market or those facing health challenges. LifeBio promotes better health through reminiscence. It brings purpose and meaning and generates positive emotions--by asking the right questions to create a lasting legacy.  LifeBio publishes the stories too -- in hardcover, leather-bound books. ','Capture life. Now. Better health through reminiscence','[\"Columbus\"]','LifeBio'),('Voted a Website to Watch by Entrepreneur Magazine, Pretty Padded Room provides online therapy to women on their own time and on their own terms. This revolutionary website for women connects clients from anywhere in the world with an all-female team of licensed counselors through video chat or Digital Diary, an interactive journal that lets clients consult with their therapist anytime and anywhere. Once seen as intimidating and expensive, Pretty Padded Room has transformed traditional therapy into an experience that is low-cost, convenient, and completely confidential.','Online therapy for women on their own time and in their own space','[\"New York City\"]','Pretty Padded Room'),('Seratis is a team transparency platform that enables care coordination for healthcare providers. Unlike pagers and simple secure messaging software, Seratis captures the patient-centric context of each message, enabling powerful analytics.','Team transparency platform enabling care coordination for healthcare providers.','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Seratis'),('Symcat is on a mission to empower consumers to take control of their health care.\n\nHealth care is a black box. The complex vocabulary creates a barrier to patient decision making. Treatment and pricing information are intentionally obscure. Symcat\'s consumer vocabulary and data-driven algorithms can help. Through a TurboTax-like interface on web or mobile, patients can research potential diagnoses, learn about treatments they are considering, and find appropriate care. \n\nFounded by a team of physicians, developers, and data scientists, Symcat has won over $100,000 from the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation and health plan Cigna as well as received funding from experienced healthcare investors. They are working with healthcare stakeholders including health plans and integrated care delivery systems to help patients navigate the healthcare maze.','Take control of your health care.','[]','Symcat'),('AirCare is a mobile application that helps hospitals prevent readmissions and improve patient outcomes through tele-nursing and patient-specific analytics','A trusted health expert - anywhere, anytime, face-to-face','[\"Philadelphia\"]','AirCare'),('Creating an online marketplace for consumers to compare healthcare prices in their local area.\n\nPatients will be able to compare healthcare procedure pricing and quality ratings at the facility level, including detailed rates whether insured or uninsured.\n\nSite access is open to everyone in the U.S., and will be free for Beta.','Blowing the roof off healthcare pricing (Kayak-like experience)','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','Pricing Healthcare'),('EasyAid is a healthcare software startup creating tech-based solutions for sustainable and accessible care. Backed by Tim Draper and working out of his new incubator, Hero City, EasyAid is developing a communication platform between patients and providers that allows patients to have access to their doctor(s) anywhere and physicians to more efficiently deal with patient requests than emails and triage calls with the opportunity to be reimbursed.','Healthcare smartphone application','[\"San Mateo\"]','EasyAid'),('Operating Venture Capital (OVC), LLC is an investment firm that is incorporated in the state of Louisiana and headquartered in the city of New Orleans, Louisiana. OVC recognizes the value of supporting the entrepreneurial community for the economic benefit of the entire region and beyond. The founding partners in OVC have been investing in New Orleans since 2011 and have a combined total of over 50 years of experience in the investing, executive management, and consulting spaces around the world.\n','Early Stage VC','[\"New Orleans\"]','Operating Venture Capital'),('As a seed fund, we invest in Digital Health companies. Applications are now open. Please apply on AngelList or through our website.','Full Service Seed Fund','[\"Princeton\"]','Tigerlabs'),('FORCE Therapeutics was founded in 2010 to transform the delivery of injury rehabilitation through best in class, web and mobile applications. In addition to its smart platform for mobile and web content delivery, FORCE produces high definition, evidenced based exercise videos for its applications. \nProducts include FORCE TherEx, an online patient management suite for physical therapists; FORCE Connect, a mobile app for patients and most recently FORCE Injury Packs for physicians. We\'re NYC based','We create web and mobile solutions for physical therapy patients and active individuals','[\"New York City\"]','FORCE Therapeutics'),('One Million by One Million (1M/1M) is a global virtual incubator that aims to nurture a million entrepreneurs to reach a million dollars each in annual revenue and beyond, thereby creating a trillion dollars in global GDP and ten million jobs.\n\nWe offer a case-study-based online educational program, video lectures, lean, capital-efficient methodology guidance, online strategy consulting at public and private roundtables, as well as introductions to customers, channel partners and investors. The public roundtable is a free program accessible from anywhere in the world. The rest of the services are for our paying members only. Pls note that we focus on business strategy and execution; capital is optional, and may or may not be appropriate for your particular business. Less than 1% of businesses that seek funding are actually fundable. However, we are perfectly happy to help the other 99% build sustainable businesses as well, irrespective of fundability or interest in external financing.','Global Virtual Incubator HQ\'ed in Silicon Valley','[\"Menlo Park\"]','One Million by One Million (1M/1M)'),('MentQ is the first-ever data analytics tool for mental healthcare.\n\n\nMentQ drags the mental health field from the era of scrawled notes and educated guesses into the era of metrics, data visualization and analytics (Evidence-Based Practice). \n\n\nThis platform allows practitioners to seamlessly capture, track and access patients’ data. \n\n\nWith mental health touching virtually everyone (1 in 4, or 80 million Americans suffer from diagnosable mental health issues), MentQ helps improve clinical outcomes, increases practice efficiency, amplifies profits and more importantly, empowers patients.\n\n\nMentQ targets the $135B mental healthcare market, and drives down the $350B cost of mental health to the US economy.','Mental Health in the Cloud','[\"San Francisco\"]','MentQ'),('MatchedFlicker helps the clinician perform two of their most important functions, disease diagnosis and patient engagement, faster and more effectively using the medical images they already have available. Images are rapidly uploaded to the cloud and can be instantly compared using a single button. The system can be accessed from anywhere via a web browser, and is also enabled for future mobile medicine and telehealth applications.','Automates \'Spot the Difference\' to improve diagnosis and patient engagement','[\"Philadelphia\"]','EyeIC'),('StaffInsight enables healthcare facilities to adapt to reimbursement cuts and deliver more care with less revenue.  \n\nWe make cloud software that analyzes and benchmarks labor productivity, allocates staffing accordingly , and measures actual labor usage so that healthcare providers can achieve continuous improvement in workforce productivity. \n\nOur initial focus is on small to medium sized hospitals and the entire facility based long term care market. We identify 2,200 small to medium hospitals and 15,000 long term care facilities.','Workforce productivity for lean healthcare. ','[\"New Orleans\"]','StaffInsight'),('Sanguine is a technology-enabled company innovating at the intersection of personalized medicine, biobanking, and biomedical research. It has a simple and attractive, proven business model. Sanguine collects blood samples and associated medical data from patients diagnosed with specific conditions. It processes those samples to extract biospecimen such as cells, serum, plasma and DNA, and stores them along with the medical data. It then sells the biospecimen and data to academic and pharmaceutical entities for research purposes.  \n\nProblem & Solution:\nTraditionally, research companies need to wait for physicians to set up appointments with patients and to find some willing to sign up. Patients go to Sanguine because Sanguine offers increased transparency in the research process, showing them where samples are used and how they advance biomedical research in areas they care about. ','Empowering Patients & Accelerating Personalized Medicine R&D; Biological/Clinical Data','[\"Santa Monica\"]','Sanguine BioSciences'),('The Everplans website, articles, and tools can help you learn about your options, make the best decisions for you and your family, and take care of key tasks, all in one place, no matter your situation. And because death affects everyone—from the person approaching death, to those left behind, to those offering support—we offer advice for a variety of different types of people.','A new approach to end-of-life and death','[\"New York City\"]','Everplans'),('image32 provides seamless medical image sharing for doctors AND patients. \n\nDoctors can easily use their patient\'s imaging to get a curbside consult or arrange for an emergency patient transfer, all without privacy worries: we automatically strip out protected health information (PHI). With our patient-facing version, you can retain your PHI and take control of your own images to get a second opinion or curate your own medical information with the click of a button. ','Fast, simple, and secure medical image sharing','[\"Menlo Park\"]','image32'),('1. You Fund a Mama for $10 or more: On kangu.org, you can search and fund profiles of pregnant women from around the world. \n\n2. Mama Receives High-Quality Healthcare: Kangu has vetted and approved maternity clinics and hospitals that offer high-quality healthcare services (prenatal/postnatal care) to women who can\'t afford them.\n\n3. Safe Birth for Mama & Her Baby: 80% of maternal mortality can be avoided if a woman is given access to the basic healthcare services our partners offer.','Crowdfund a safe birth for a mama and her baby!','[\"New York City\"]','Kangu.org'),('Like with the airlines, PatientWay allows you to pre-register from home and on the day of your hospital visit you use our kiosks to check in. PatientWay saves you time and hospitals money.\n\nPatientWay is ideal for hospitals and larger medical clinics. They love PatientWay\'s flexibility, intuitive management screens, and its unique ability to interface with their legacy systems.\n\nPatientWay has a proven business case and successful installs at small and large hospitals.','Self check-in kiosks and online registration for hospitals & clinics','[\"Ottawa\"]','PatientWay'),('The Rounds is a physician-only professional network that enables and accelerates collaboration among physicians. With our tools doctors are able to communicate in real-time across specialties and across the continent.\n\nDid you know that it\'s against legislation for physicians to text each other? It\'s true. Email too! Physicians are limited to phone and fax.\n\nUntil now, that is - we give our users a tool that let\'s them send private messages (read: texts) and compose, send and mangage HIPAA-compliant email.\n\nOur network is free for users, exclusive (credentials verified), and secure.\n\nThe Rounds helps doctors to save time, save money, and save lives.\n','Healthcare is social.','[\"Halifax\"]','The Rounds'),(NULL,'','[\"New York City\"]','Healthcare Innovation World Cup'),('We have some of the largest health insurers and health systems as our paid trial customers. iQuartic has developed a patent pending data technology that determines the \"true risk\" of a patient population: \n\n--our approach can capture up to 40% of the conditions missed by traditional methods\n--this thereby produces a more reliable estimate for the expected financial cost of insuring a population.\n--our technology is important for and enables non-fee-for-service, especially risk based, contracts. \n\nMany health insurances and US states and federal government (CMS), are transitioning away from fee-for-service to risk based payments.','Utilizing big healthcare data to improve care.','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','iQuartic'),('Aavya Health helps you make sense of your medical lab data, and provides you personalized recommendations for food products and supplements to help you make improvements to your health.','Understand and take action on your medical lab data','[\"Boston\"]','Aavya Health'),('Prebacked walks entrepreneurs from \"I\'d like to get into healthcare\" to \"I\'m series A ready\" with enterprise revenue generating contracts.\n\nAt our core, we\'re a startup foundry and community.  We help entrepreneurs simultaneously create a startups based on enterprise problems and acquire their first enterprise client through a structured format that includes private events, one-on-one iteration with C-suite executives, and a community of entrepreneurs who want to help each other.\n\nHow does enterprise get involved?  They (i.e. Fortune 500s) pitch problems to high-potential startup teams.  Startup teams build solutions, with the goal of creating a client-vendor relationship with the enterprise.','Land your first major enterprise client in 1 week.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Prebacked'),('Doctor.com is the first vertical network that connects patients and providers across the web. We help doctors get online and tell their story, and we match them with patients looking for the specific services they specialize in. Once matches are made, we streamline appointment booking, pre-visit reminders, post-visit satisfaction surveys, and other important aspects of care.\n\nOur platform powers provider search not just on Doctor.com but also for a growing network of enterprise partners in the consumer health space, bringing thousands of new patients into our ecosystem every day.\n\nDoctors get well-qualified patients. Patients get better care faster. Everyone wins.','Match.com for doctors and patients. Millions of users. Proven traction w/Growing Revenues.','[\"New York City\"]','Doctor.com'),('iDoc24 is changing the field of dermatology. We have a portfolio of dermatology applications that provide both consumers and businesses a faster, more convenient means to receive professional advice on skin care.  Dermatologists are overloaded with patients and it takes weeks to get an appointment. After sending in an image our users are \"triaged\" by a dermatologist within 24 hours with a possible diagnosis & treatment. 70+% of the users skin conditions can be treated at home or with over the counter medications; there is an enormous cost savings to the user and allows dermatologists to take cases that matter. In our business side, we have developed a HIPAA-compliant researched platform that streamline primary healthcare patients to dermatologists. This is made possible with our dermoscope, a lens attachment for iPhones to ensure high quality, magnified images.  At the root of our product, we aim to improve the experience of getting you the care your skin deserves at the right time.','Skin Advice in any Device 24/7','[\"San Francisco\"]','iDoc24'),('The device is a proprietary, low cost, non-invasive, radiation-free tool that uses military grade thermal cameras to measure heat/vascular patterns which are indicative of breast cancer.  The test is painless and takes about 10 minutes. \r\n\r\nThe device will be used by OB/GYNs and Internists as part of an annual physical exam, as well as by oncologists to monitor patients subsequent to cancer diagnosis/treatment.  It’s projected sensitivity is 95% vs. a clinical breast exam by the doctor at 45% (mammogram at 75%. The device and software automate a manual process that has been perfected as a result of testing 1,000,000+ women over the past 40+ years.  The company has an exclusive worldwide license to this methodology that has been validated in a 2,000 woman clinical trial. The company has an experienced management team. Board is anchored by the co-developer of Lipitor, Roger Newton, PhD. \r\n\r\nCompany has potential to provide significant return to investors and save thousands of lives.','Revolutionary Early Breast Cancer Detection Device','[\"Pontiac\"]','First Sense Medical'),('Within3 is fundamentally changing healthcare by becoming the ubiquitous underlying secure web, mobile, and API platform. Through our social, professional, and community based products Within3’s is connecting all healthcare practitioners, institutions, and pharmaceutical companies worldwide to create better patient outcomes.','Fundamentally changing healthcare by becoming \"the\" platform for all communications. ','[\"Cleveland\"]','Within3'),('MedClimate works with corporate wellness companies and employers to provide solutions that reduce healthcare costs for employees. We partner health coaches with at-risk employees to reduce costs as much as possible. Our solution provides a risk assessment for patients, telemedicine dashboard for health coaches, messaging, monitoring, goal setting and more. We make it easier and more convenient for coaches to connect with patients remotely and get the outcomes they need. Our data reporting application provides extensive reporting for individuals and cohorts to prove ROI for employers and payors who implement the program.','Provider and consumer solutions for employer-sponsored healthcare.','[\"Washington, DC\"]','MedClimate'),('StrokeLink is designed to empower stroke survivors throughout their care journey by providing knowledge and self-care tools to bridge the gaps in care delivery. With stroke being the leading cause of disability in North America, StrokeLink provides a comprehensive toolkit of personalized resources for rehabilitation designed to guide and actively engage patients as they recover and gain independence. \n\n','A software ecosystem for the creation and sharing of specialized rehabilitative content. ','[\"Toronto\"]','Talem Health Solutions'),('MDmatic is a powerful mobile platform that gives healthcare providers control of patient report creation & management from the palm of their hand.  MDmatic allows providers to create, finalize, upload to EHR, and share patient reports, within minutes, from anywhere at any time.\n\nFederal legal mandates are driving U.S. medical providers to adopt Electronic Health Record (EHR) systems by 2014, but all are struggling to overcome decreased productivity due to inefficient data entry & access, yielding significant user frustration & diminished ROI.  \n\nMDmatic uniquely solves this challenge for both users and organizations - saving time, boosting productivity & facilitating universal connectivity.','Enhancing clinical connectivity & facilitating EHR adoption through the mobile cloud','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','MDmatic'),('EyeFormatics is the fastest, most efficient, and easiest-to-learn electronic medical records system available today.  Within minutes, you’ll be documenting patient encounters and managing clinical information better than you could ever do with a paper chart… or any other EMR system.','Digital records systems for eye care','[\"Norwich, CT\"]','EyeFormatics'),('InfraTrac lets you check substances (drugs, cosmetics, wine, food), in a second, with a special light (spectrometer).  Our patented enhancements help mobile spectroscopy protect brands and consumers against fakes (counterfeits) and mistakes (medication errors).  We use coded smartwrap to protect packages, and fingerprinting to protect what\'s inside.  In hospitals, we verify IV-bags and syringes directly, right through the container, so the patient gets the right drug and the right dose.','Fakes and Mistakes: Verify substances instantly','[\"Maryland\"]','InfraTrac'),('Careticker is a caregiver engagement platform that enables managed medicaid plans, dual eligible payors and accountable care organizations to engage, incentivize and reward their covered members’ primary, family caregiver. Our caregiver behavioral data and analytics solution provides health plans, including managed medicaid and medicare advantage plans with new insights into patient compliance and outcomes. \n\nCareticker is led by founder and CEO Chiara Bell, a seasoned entrepreneur and executive in healthcare. She sold her last company, ENURGI in 2008, to Univita Health, a Genstar backed company led by Ben Lytle (Chairman Anthem/Wellpoint) and Hugh Lytle. ENURGI was one of the first in the nation to disrupt the antiquated \"agency\" model in homecare - a $50B plus market. After leading Univita\'s consumer web and mobile division, she founded Careticker, once again identifying a ripe area for disruption in healthcare.\n','Incentive/Rewards platform for unpaid caregivers','[\"West Palm Beach\"]','Careticker'),('','','[\"Mountain View\"]','H4Y Corp'),('Our API (currently piloting at a NYC hospital) presents easy-to-consume evidence within the EMR and delivered at point-of-care, to change physician treatment behavior.\n\n-US healthcare costs are out of control.\n\n-Many common tests and treatments are of marginal value and expensive.\n\n-Accountable Care Organizations are here to stay. Fee-for-service is waning.\n\n-Given that bulk-buying savings of single payer are unlikely, the best place to save money is controlling provider discretionary spending.\n','Evidence transparency for health systems','[\"Menlo Park\"]','The NNT Group'),('United Preference is revolutionizing health and wellness incentives via our Tailored Spend Payments Platform. Health plans and employers spend over $60 billion annually to engage members in healthy behaviors.  Directly partnered with Discover Financial Services, our platform and tailored card products can only be used to purchase health related products and services. Proprietary analytics detail how incentive dollars are being spent, and their impact on engagement, behavior change, and outcomes.','Revolutionizing Health & Wellness Incentives Via Tailored Spend Payments Platform','[\"New York City\"]','United Preference '),('The average physician bills $450k/year that is owed directly by patients. 40-60% of this goes uncollected since patient obligations can\'t be determined at the time of service. This problem has grown 20% annually since 2007 and according to McKinsey is now a $60 billion dollar market.  PayRight\'s SaaS application provides tools to allows physicians to increase net income by 9% of gross billings through improved collection of patient out-of-pocket dollars, reduced collection times and lower cost.','Increase physician bottom line 9%','[\"Chicago\"]','PayRight Health Solutions'),('Medesk is a cloud healthcare platform, it makes management of medical practices highly effective and comfortable. Medical practices can quickly and easily negotiate documents with patients, corporate clients, insurance companies, and labs.\n \nMedesk delivers integrated digital healthcare ecosystem, fully featured and customised, it can be accessed on any browser or device. It facilitates collaboration of all healthcare market players – clinics, patients, CROs, employers, insurance companies, medical device vendors.\n\nMedesk is the expert of digital healthcare market in Russia. Medesk is a profitable company and our strategic plan is to become the leader in the digital healthcare market in Russia, and then to expand this model into other emerging counties. ','Cloud Healthcare Platform','[\"Moscow\"]','Medesk'),('ThoroughCare is changing the way the healthcare industry assess their patients.  We\'re taken basic assessments to a new level with our guided-interview style approach.  With workflows designed for clinicians, our easy to use interface makes it easy for Hosptials, Payers and Accountable Care Organizations to effeciently and effectively assess their member\'s care.  We\'re taking patient engagment to a new level.','Guided interviews for health assessments','[\"Spartanburg\"]','ThoroughCare'),('Access to care has never been easier.  Quickly find and book any provider for your schedule, secure message your physician.','','[\"San Francisco\"]','OpenMed'),('HealthCareLove is a mobile app that simplifies and highlights the most important aspects of healthcare: How will my family be taken care of and how much is it going to cost?\n\nA simple and well-designed mobile app, HealthCareLove answers these questions (and many more). \n\nInsurance companies can implement this fully-customizable mobile app with their existing infrastructure seamlessly, empowering their customers with a simplified tool for managing their healthcare plan like never before.\n\n','Your health in your hands','[\"San Francisco\"]','HealthCareLove'),('ScioMD is a cloud-based health care data visualization software as a service (SaaS). Our customers are health care providers, who would like to empower their patients by presenting their health care data in an easy to understand format. Because we\'re based in the cloud, it means patients have access to engaging, personalized health care data reports, without having to pay for, manage, and scale expensive hardware and/or software. See screenshot for current lab reports vs ScioMD\'s.','ScioMD makes it really easy for patients to understand their lab test reports','[\"Madison\"]','ScioMD'),('Our product does 3 things: (1) Provides visibility into home health services to verify interactions and visits; (2) Provides longitudinal data that will help better manage the clinical trajectory of home health patients; and (3) Acts as a preventive measure in billing error, waste, and fraud.\n\nAll of this is done without requiring the patient to have any special technology - they just carry a card that is readable by the provider\'s smartphone.','Home Health Care Transparency using NFC','[\"San Francisco\"]','PH mHealth'),('Grand Round Table is an innovative decision support tool integrated into the electronic health record (EHR) that helps doctors arrive at the correct treatment plan more efficiently by pattern matching their case against a database of millions of cases from leading institutions','Help doctors solve difficult cases','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Grand Round Table'),('Our products provide \"high assurance identity proofing\" regarding electronic or online identification, authentication and authorization with strong audit trails.  \n\nBioSig-ID is a patented [issued] \"behavioral biometric\" using human gestures via mouse, stylus or your finger on a touch screen/touch pad as a \"defense-in-depth\" measure for online identification & authentication.  \n\nIt exceeds NIST requirements for biometrics by a factor of 3!\n\nuSignOnline facilitates legal electronic signatures.\n\n','High Assurance Online Identity Proofing','[\"Lewisville\"]','Biometric Signature ID'),('Remote patient monitoring is expensive and limited. There are thousands of monitors, zero standards, pragmatically speaking and no connection for non-API hardware. Infometers is the abstraction layer, providing a standardized API to access monitoring-data streams.\n\nWe are working with premier centers (like UCSF) and patient management startups to test out solutions on their populations. Our goal is to help shave off a big chunk of Healthcare costs. ','aggregates patient monitoring data, provides a standardized platform','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Infometers '),('Open Cancer Network (OCN) Open Cancer Network (OCN)  is a  big  data platform.\n\nOCN provides advanced multi-dimensional data sets for use in bio-medical research, products and services. Our offering includes bio-medical, behavioral, science, social media, environmental and spatial data needed for understanding of health and disease. Data comes from three sources: (1) open government data sources; (2) social media; (3) patient data self-reported from a proprietary mobile platform.\n\nOCN data is one of the richest datasets available to identify patterns and correlations that may lead to advances in social epidemiology of cancer.','Uniquely complete massive data sets of non-clinical cancer epidemiology data ','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Open Cancer Network'),('The VerbalCare platform replaces hospital call-bell systems by gathering and analyzing patient interactions in order to improve patient engagement, satisfaction, care quality, efficiency, and safety. We leverage smartphones and tablets to deliver unprecedented patient care. Using customizable picture-icons displayed on iPads, patients select from a variety of options to inform care staff of their exact needs prior to the clinician’s arrival. The requests are categorized and sent to the caregiver\'s iTouch so that they can provide better, coordinated care. Our software allows caregivers and administrators in the hospitals/nursing homes to manage connected devices and how they interact. Our system dashboard analyzes interactions and allows administrators to track and manage care efficiency and quality so that hospitals and nursing homes operate more effectively.','We believe everyone deserves a voice.','[\"Boston\"]','Verbal Applications'),('We make medical credentialing simple for healthcare centers and health insurance companies.\n\nMedical credentialing is a mandated process that every facility and health insurance company must complete on a recurring basis. The process is critical because it ensures that doctors are qualified to see patients, and that those doctors with questionable competency, are prevented from practicing (yes, kinda like the movie \'Catch Me If You Can\').\n\nHowever, the way that credentialing is implemented today makes it a laborious, time consuming and expensive process that is becoming increasingly more complex and error prone every year.\n\n','Medical Credentialing, Automated','[\"New York City\"]','CredSimple'),('Up until now, smartphone-based medical devices have functioned as disparate tools, each performing siloed functions through various peripherals and applications. Attempts to coalesce these technologies have primarily focused on consumer-facing health and wellness tools. The Smartphone Physical is developing the first integrated platform that brings together an arsenal of mobile medical devices to collect clinically relevant data and information on a physician-focused app that can readily interface with an electronic health record. Our goal is to create a new sub-ecosystem of interoperable health data. We leverage these smartphone-based medical tools to abstract away the mundane and unreliable aspects of the physical exam and allow the focus of the clinical encounter to remain on the patient, not on the data collection process.','Clinically-relevant integration of smartphone-based medical devices','[\"Baltimore\"]','The Smartphone Physical'),('NurseBuddy is a communication tool for home care professionals and the families of people receiving care at home. It\'s a cloud-based mobile planning and communication system which creates a new kind of connectivity between all the participants in the ecosystem: carers/nurses, managers and families.','Use NurseBuddy to effectively manage your home care company\'s communication. ','[\"Dublin\"]','NurseBuddy'),('Medicare provides for an Annual Wellness Visit each year for over 45 million Medicare patients.  But primary care physicians generally cannot comply with the demanding requirements of Medicare\'s strict documentation standards.  This is our opportunity.  We have perfected the call center service and report processing surrounding the Annual Wellness Visit and have it running in dozens of physicians\' offices.  It generates significant revenue for them and us with virtually no effort on their part. ','Provides exact report required by Medicare for Annual Wellness Visit (AWV).','[\"Hilton Head Island\"]','WellTrackONE'),('SpeSo Health uses data and statistics to measure expertise in rare and complex conditions. Despite the name, there are over 25 million patients with rare and complex conditions in the US alone. We\'ve built a tool to help rare disease patients and their supporters find and connect with the best experts for them.','Data analytics meets rare disease','[\"Philadelphia\"]','SpeSo Health'),('Stat is re-imagining emergency and non-emergency medical transports. With a simple tap, the smartphone app matches patients and caretakers with a licensed ambulance, paratransit or wheelchair van - allowing drivers the ability to reduce idle or downtime.\n\nStat is the fastest, easiest and safest way to have your patient transported anywhere, anytime. With Stat you can request a transport for a patient from across town, for your mom from another state, and soon, from across the world. ','On-demand Medical Transport','[\"Austin\"]','Stat'),('Ideal for organizations in the healthcare, financial services and public sectors, ArmorText offers a seamless and secure channel for communication and collaboration. ','Securing Mobile Communications and Identity','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Gryphn'),('Summary: MedScores-as-a-Service (MSaas) are the ultimate cloud-administered bad debt busters for doctors and hospitals.\n\nProblem: Did you know that underinsured Americans default on 60% of their healthcare bills?  Doctors and hospitals do.  In fact, these parties write off $80Bn ($350K on a per practice basis) in bad debt associated with the “self-pay” portion of health care bills each year! Said another way, bad debt for these groups = 15% of revenue!  myMedScore drops that by 1/3, or 100K!\n\n Root cause: The reimbursement model of US healthcare. “Which part of the bill is mine???”\n Accelerant: The Affordable Care Act, which will triple High Deductible Health Plans by 2020.   \n                     “I’m insured. Treat me. Thanks, I’m better… what’s a deductible?”\n\nSolution: A trust-based, big data driven compliance score (a MedScore) and institutionalized payment protocols that ensure patients get served, each time, regardless of circumstance and doctors get paid, in-full, upfront.\n','Real-time health care engagement scoring.  215MM MedScores calculated to date!','[\"San Francisco\"]','myMedScore'),('Yingo Yango is an integration platform for health and wellness teams and resources.\n\nOur platform is a simple mobile and web-based app that cuts through the chaos of healthcare by introducing “Health Circles” to integrate eco-systems of care through ONE log-in. \n\nWe provide connectivity, communication and customization to connect the dots for the individual and all available health and wellness information, data, programming, vendors, resources, employers and providers -- all organized around specific conditions or topics. Enhanced information sharing and secure messaging allow the individual and her team to coordinate, make referrals, customize treatment plans, set reminders or alerts and share tools or data.\n\nEmployers, carriers, and provider systems use our system use our platform to bring to the forefront and leverage their established health and wellness benefits teams and programming, maximizing their use and efficiencies. The result is sustainable engagement and reduced costs.','Integration Platform for Health and Wellness Teams and Resources.','[\"West Hartford\"]','Yingo Yango'),('Global healthcare is fragmented, inaccessible, and expensive. To change that, UBDoc will enable patients throughout the world to diagnose their own ailments via the web. UBDoc will also give suggestions for tests and subsequent therapeutic recommendations. Finally, patients will be able to chat with physicians at any time of night or day via the web. The service will be very inexpensive, convenient, accurate and secure, in all major languages.','Web based diagnosis and treatment','[\"Bethlehem, PA\"]','UBDoc'),('Akros TechLabs, headquartered in Katy, Texas, is focused on developing small footprint security solutions. Our flagship solution is a unique, cost-effective Multi-Factor Authentication solution.  Akros is building an ecosystem of solutions around Multi-Factor Authentication, to effectively address the security and password management needs of the Cloud and Mobile technology markets.\n\n\n','Multi Factor Authentication for Mobile and Cloud Applications','[\"Houston\"]','Akros TechLabs'),('Vimty is a designed online experience that helps users connect with loved ones and make decisions for end of life care as simply as possible.\n\nVimty helps individuals easily and clearly understand and engage with end-of-life rights & choices than document, store, share, and update those decisions with family members and healthcare providers, enabling each patient’s decisions. \n','Vimty you can create, eNotarize and store a digital medical document for end of life care.','[\"Princeton\"]','Vimty'),('Sixty percent of our health and a fifth of US healthcare spending is driven by our social needs (food, mental health, substance abuse, etc). These needs have been overlooked for far too long. The Healthify platform allows managed care plans (insurers) and at-risk physicians to effectively address the social needs in their population to save money, boost quality metrics, and improve case management. We deploy a web-based tool to identify the social needs in a population and subsequently connect patients to the best resources to address their needs. We then automate follow up with patients via interactive texts and present this unique set of patient data back to staff via a population dashboard. Scalable case management!','A Social Worker for Every Patient','[\"New York City\"]','Healthify'),('Amadeus of Healthcare:\ne-health platform that facilitates through online booking and ehealth applications the relationship and interaction between the different actors of the private healthcare industry: patients, doctors, clinics and health insurance companies.\n\nIt´s free for patients. Doctors and clinics pay an annual fee to use the platform.\n\nNominated as finalist for best startup of 2011 in Madrid-Spain.\nIE Venture Lab 2010 winner.\nStarted generating cash.\nWill go international in 2012.','e-health SaaS & PaaS, amadeus of healthcare','[\"Madrid\"]','doctordoctor'),('An end-to-end healthcare platform that enables hospitals and clinics to record details of patient visits and generate medical claims for electronic submission to insurance companies. Insurance companies receive these claims via an online dashboard, where they can vet individual claims, send notes on rejected items to healthcare facilities and import key details for invoicing or further processing. \n','e-claims platform for Africa','[\"Ghana\"]','ClaimSync '),('Physician designed, cloud based communications and practice management platform for primary care practices. ','Connecting doctors and their patients','[\"New York City\"]','Patient Communicator'),('Our genomes are going to be integral to our future healthcare. Creating structure from populations of genomic data and their associated attributes and integrating this with an individual\'s health profile will be central to this exciting future.  Station X is already creating the software that will power this future, and it\'s called GenePool.  \n\nGenePool is a secure, cloud-based software environment for analyzing and visualizing population-scale human genomic data for biomarker discovery, clinical interpretation and population studies. It seamlessly traverses between healthcare and IT challenges and empowers scientists and medical professionals to comfortably manage, analyze, interpret, and communicate patient-oriented genomics data in a user-friendly environment with the promise to do so much more.\n\nView our full slide deck at http://bit.ly/1cnbEcZ and if you\'d like a trial account, contact info@stationxinc.com\n','Decoding genomes for better healthcare','[\"San Francisco\"]','Station X'),(NULL,'Where Brazilians find and schedule medical appointments.','[]','HelpSaude'),('VidDx is a collection of real patient video cases to help healthcare professionals and students improve their diagnostic abilities.  Cases including video, related test results and imaging, vital signs and a professional write up discussing patient history, differential diagnosis, patient disposition, common pitfalls, etc.  Video cases will be organized by specialty library.\nIndividuals may subscribe to each library for $49/year.  CME credit available for $10/credit.  Institutional discounts.','Revolutionizing medical education with real patient video cases','[\"Portland\"]','VidDx'),('Dropsense is a convenient and affordable low blood sugar alert system created by harnessing the power of modern sensing, mobile, and machine learning technologies. \n\nDropsense monitors continuously overnight and alerts you upon sudden drops in blood sugar for a fraction of the price of continuous glucose monitors. \n\nNighttime hypoglycemia is one of the biggest risks for the roughly 94 million people with diabetes worldwide using insulin. These individuals are living without a painless monitoring solution to keep them safe. \n\nAt Dropsense, we believe everyone should be able to monitor their blood sugar overnight. Our goal is to provide this technology at a price anyone can afford.','non-invasive low blood sugar alert systems','[\"Berkeley\"]','Dropsense'),('Compliant Games upgrades common respiratory therapy devices into low cost clinical telemetry instruments for doctors and entertainment for patients.  Our customers will be both patients and heath care providers.\n\nOur first product is a gaming system for children that encourages compliance with prescribed respiratory therapy.  Children who are at risk for developing conditions such as pneumonia will be encouraged to utilize fun and effective pulmonary exercises.','Channeling the Healing Power of Children\'s Video Games','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Compliant Games'),('KLUTCHclub is a subscription-based service allowing consumers to try new health and wellness products by receiving a monthly package in the mail.  \n\nOrganized around a monthly theme, products include healthy snack foods, fitness gear and workout tips, as well as skincare regimens.  \n\nMembership includes exclusive promotions, expert content (e.g., celebrity fitness tips), and access to an interactive, user driven online community (e.g., product reviews).','Monthly subscription of health, wellness, and fitness products','[\"Chicago\"]','KLUTCHclub'),('MedConnections iPharmacy and PACE Health Connect apps recruit and engage patients to improve their adherence with medication and medical condition instructions. We provide over 1,000 messages, alerts and reminders for 35 conditions to patients and caregivers through patent pending interactive notification technology.  Health plans, provider organizations and self-insured employers pay for patient\'s use of the apps through operational savings.','Empower self care solutions for patients and cost savings for sponsors.  ','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','MedConnections'),('Mediscale lets doctors understand the complete medical status of their pregnant patients and provides them with easy to follow recommendations over the web. It’s like having the best medical team constantly working for you at a touch of a button.\n\nMediscale\'s Prenatal Screener saves physicians precious time & reduces their misdiagnosis risk. The system is already being used by top-tier hospitals, including Kaiser Permanente, Baylor (TX), Cedars Sinai (CA), and Beth Israel (NY).','Helping Doctors Make The Right Decision','[\"Tel Aviv\"]','Mediscale'),('Clinixon is a powerful system to improve patient compliance, our product is specially designed for medical practices.\r\nWe include many automatic tools to increase the adherence to treatment of patients and increase the frequency of visits.\r\n','Cloud-based Patient Engagement System','[\"Montevideo\"]','Clinixon'),('Medyear is a personal health exchange. It allows you to transmit your health records however you want. It starts with digitally downloading your records from healthcare entities, so no more relying on fax or paper. Simply give them your Medyear address - it works a lot like an email address. \n\nOnce you have your records in Medyear, you control them. You can keep them for later, share with a friend or stranger, donate to science, or collaborate with your doctor. All through a simple social networking experience that makes ample use of common controls like hashtags, groups, and time limits.\n\nIn 2014, over 500 healthcare organizations (ranging from small clinics to the largest insurers) will support downloading clinical records into Medyear as a result of federal regulations.','Personal health exchange. Download and share your medical records.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Medyear'),('At Symvato we believe that HIPAA compliance tools should be as affordable as they are easy. Healthcare providers should be focused on their patients, not regulatory compliance. Symvato allows providers to focus on their patients by providing a creative and innovative HIPAA compliance solution. At Symvato, we are HIPAA compliance made simple!','HIPAA Compliance Made Simple','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Symvato'),('CredentialedCare is a complete recruitment solution for long-term care (LTC) workers and the enterprises seeking their services.  LTC agencies and facilities are burdened by a shortage of workers,  high turnover, an expensive and time consuming recruitment and  onboarding process, and there is burgeoning competition making it  difficult to find the right candidate. We simplify this for providers by offering access to pre-screened direct care workers available for immediate hire.','Placing on-demand workers in long-term care','[\"Louisville\"]','CredentialedCARE'),('Scannerside is disrupting the healthcare imaging market. Created by two Radiologists, Scannerside allows imaging centers to simply and efficiently track patient radiation dose, monitor exam volume and view real-time HTML5 analytics without heavy enterprise software. A unique workflow allows centers to print dose cards, improve patient loyalty , grow volume and meet important federal regulations for <10% of the cost. Scannerside patients connect with imaging facilities, book exams and more. \n','Google Analytics for Radiology / Imaging Centers','[\"Stony Brook\"]','Scannerside'),('AllazoHealth\'s analytics service helps clients turn data into actionable insight, revealing the most effective way to influence the behavior of each individual member. \n\nImproving medication adherence reduces medical spending, raises Medicare Star Ratings, increases HEDIS scores, and creates a better overall member experience for health insurers and PBMs. Despite the myriad of interventions employed today, increasing medication adherence still proves difficult.','Improving medication adherence through individualized intervention targeting','[\"New York City\"]','AllazoHealth'),('We help very early stage technology companies that are trying to solve social or environmental problems. We provide up to £15,000 of investment and a three month programme of support and office space based in central London.','An accelerator programme for technology startups working on things that matter.','[\"London\"]','BGV'),('Journal Lab makes it easy to navigate the universe of published scientific literature. \n\nWe do this by incentivizing scientists to share the notes that they take every time the read a paper: a short summary and one or two opinions about that paper\'s integrity. This makes it easy for doctors, investors, biotech startups, and other scientists to browse the literature and see what experts think of it.','Yelp for cancer research.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Journal Lab'),('Award winning* iRetainRx helps people take medications correctly between doctor visits and pharmacy refills, and provide payment support for a proven pharmacist care model–Medication Therapy Management.  It delivers interactive medication management services paid for by insurers and manufacturers. Provides benefits to several key participants in the value chain and aligns financial incentives for payers, physician groups, pharmacies and drug manufacturers. *Semi-Finalist US Innovation Challenge\n','Helps people take medications correctly between doctor visits and pharmacy refills.','[\"Silicon Valley\", \"Sunnyvale\"]','iRetainRx'),('iClinic is the leading SaaS EMR solution in Brazil.\n\niClinic allows health professionals to organise their patients records electronically, store all the data in the cloud and retrieve it late from any device, anywhere.\nThe best tool to increase health professionals\' productivity, reduce costs and improve the quality of the patient care.\n\nAvailable for physicians, dentists, psychologists, physical therapists and other health professionals.','Cloud app for health professionals','[\"Ribeirao Preto\"]','iClinic'),('Presm brings proven communication preferences (such as text messaging, mobile access and private online accounts) into the context of healthcare by enabling targeted, relevant, and timely information