 Health'),('Medtech product selection is often a haphazard, labor intensive process that takes way too long and leads to questionable outcomes.  Neither hospitals nor vendors can afford to do business this way any longer.  EvaluationRx provides a solution - it connects vendors, physicians, and hospitals through the cloud to a unified workflow that collects information from all parties and keeps the process moving efficiently.','We help hospitals evaluate medtech','[\"Boston\"]','EvaluationRx'),('Project InCare aims at providing technology enabled products and service to manage wellness at home especially for patients with chronic conditions and users dependent on regular wellness regiment to stay healthy.','Enabling access to wellness','[\"Fremont\"]','Project InCare'),('Treata Smart Caregiver system includes a Lost Item Finder technology to\r\ntrack individual’s personal belongings; a Smart Wandering Assistant, a\r\ntamper proof bracelet that helps navigate or locate the wearer; and a Smart\r\nReminder Smartphone app, which keeps caregivers informed about the\r\nlocation and condition of their loved ones. Treata helps people with memory\r\nloss live independently longer, and gives their loved ones peace of mind.','Assists connecting people who care for others','[\"Toronto\"]','Treata Smart Solutions'),('MouseHouse is using technology to transform all aspects of animal management in laboratories, from breeding and experiments to purchasing and veterinary management. In the US, scientists use 155M mice and spend $8.5B/yr housing and managing mice. MouseHouse is a mobile first solution that allows scientists to keep track of experiments, veterinary management, purchasing, care, and genetic breeding of these mice; transforming the manual processes and archaic systems used in laboratories. \n\nOn top of this, our proprietary Just-in-Time optimization software provides researchers with suggestions on which mice to breed and cull based on 21 factors--such as mouse age, strain, individual mouse fertility. This first-of-its-kind inventory system saves researchers direct costs. Together this application saves 15% in direct inventory costs and 85% of the time necessary to keep track of animals.\n\nWe are currently being used at over 40 universities across the world and are now looking to fund growth','Google docs for laboratory mice','[\"Chicago\"]','Laboratory Analytics Inc.'),('Today, eHealthInsurance.com has enrolled over 3 million people in health insurance coverage and is the leading online marketplace for individually and family health insurance products in the nation. Licensed to market and sell health insurance in all 50 states and the District of Columbia, eHealthInsurance was responsible for the nation\'s first Internet-based sale of a health insurance policy, and we have partnerships with more than 180 health insurance companies, and offer more than 10,000 health insurance products online.\n\nEvery day we provide thousands of visitors with information about a broad array of health insurance-related topics and plans, including a selection of price and benefit options, complemented by a full-service Customer Care Center of highly trained customer service representatives.','Expedia for Health Insurance','[\"Mountain View\"]','eHealth'),('Carevium automates planning, tracking and managing resident assessments, care activities, and medication management in Senior Living communities such as Assisted Living Facilities, Residential Care Homes and Alzheimer\'s Care communities.\n\nCarevium enables family members access care information in real time and provides timely alerts and notifications on Activities of Daily Living (ADLs), Medications, Incidents, and remote monitoring sensors / tools.\n\nElder care facilities can focus on resident care rather than wasting time on paper records creation and maintenance. Carevium usage (1) increases family and resident satisfaction, (2) reduces manual errors and redundant labor, (3) increases compliance, and (4) automates entire workflow in senior communities.\n\nCarevium empowers staff by providing proactive reminders, alerts and notifications to the administrators, nursing staff, and professional and family caregivers. Carevium platform applications delivered as mobile apps and web apps.\n','Empowering senior facilities, care givers and families','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','Carevium - Solutions for Senior Living'),('Stroll is a mobile health application that facilitates patient-physcian shared decision making. We surface optimal cost and location information for routine radiological treatments right in the doctors office. This allows patients to take an active role in lowering their own healthcare costs by showing exact personalized pricing with the comfort and support of their care team on hand. By guiding patients to a treatment facility and closing the loop, physicians and providers realize higher adherence, fewer hassles with insurance pre-approvals, and greater patient satisfaction. When patients choose low cost options, payers save big, and by simplifying the conversation around treatment options and cost, patients and physicians more easily build trust and lasting relationships. This results in fewer hospital visits, better health outcomes, and drastically decreased health care spend across the board. ','Enterprise Healthcare Cost Transparency for Insurers','[\"San Francisco\"]','Stroll'),('Everything starts by developing people. You may have the best business strategy but still you may not succeed without motivated people. You don\'t have to change or laid out your people, instead you can develop them along your business!\n\nOnce our users subscribe to our online service, the journey start by discovering what kind of potential they \'ve, how much they are using, road-map to achieve the full potential, discover in their net-workmate whom, how & why can develop each other. Special subscription package to organisation to build efficient teams matching t