ess to patients and doctors via our consumer- and provider-facing platforms.\n\nMany patients have to pay out-of-pocket in the range of $8-20K for IVF. Patients considering their first IVF treatment and those who have had unsuccessful treatments want to know what are their personalized chances of success.  Univfy IVF Prediction Tests empower patients to make more confident decisions about starting or doing IVF again.  Knowing their own success probabilities can save time, cost, and frustration that result from seeking multiple opinions from different doctors, and shorten the time needed to make these important decisions.   \n','Personalized Fertility Prediction','[\"Los Altos\"]','Univfy '),('DNA Health brings together healthcare professionals and manufacturers in ways that will disrupt the practice and business of medicine.\n\nOur solution enables pharmaceutical companies to unlock the commercial value of social networks through the ability to:\n\na) identify the way in which providers are connected to each other as well as the patterns and spheres of influence among them;\n\nb) optimize influence-driven marketing/scientific campaigns by turning these influencers into brand advocates;\n\nc) measure Return on Influence (ROI) by mapping the effect of their promotional efforts on physicians’ prescribing behavior. \n\nDNA Health’s patent-pending algorithm gathers attitudinal, behavioral and demographic data from helix.md, our proprietary online collaboration platform for healthcare professionals, quantifying and ranking the economic potential of each practitioner in the form of an Influence Index. ','Digital Network Analytics for the Healthcare Industry','[\"San Francisco\"]','DNA Health'),('Incendant helps caregivers easily provide patient education that saves time, improves patient comprehension and satisfaction. Videos are displayed on smartphones, tablets, laptops or facility televisions. Patients and family receive followup emails that link them to the same materials. Our library covers common diagnoses, procedures and medications and is constantly growing.\n\nWe have specially designed packages for Hospitals, Homecare, Hospice, ER and Urgent Cares.  IOS, Android & Win','Patient Clarity. Caregiver Simplicity.','[\"Pueblo\"]','Incendant'),('beepcare provides a multi-platform service that establishes a long-term relation between patients and their doctors. \n- We provide patients the tools to create their own personal health record (allowing on-the-fly context access by doctors) and\n- Tools to doctors regain control over their patients-lists, while maintaining personal privacy.','Helping doctors get lifetime patients, Helping patients get lifetime care.','[\"Lisbon\"]','beepcare'),(NULL,'Genetics marketplace for docs','[\"Nashville\"]','NextGxDx'),('2nd.MD connects people directly & easily with the nation’s leading medical specialists for advice & second opinions.\n\nThe Goal: Become the world\'s most valuable medical resource- bring the best doctors into peoples homes regardless of location or language.\n\n2nd.MD has nationally recognized doctors in 240 sub-specialties from 12 of the top 17 US institutions.\n\n2nd.MD is pioneering technologies that make it simple to:\nconsult via webcam/phone\ndeal with medical files\nschedule & pay\ncomply legally','Access the world\'s best doctors from anywhere.','[\"Houston\"]','2nd.MD'),('TrendMD Inc. is an academic content discovery platform, that instantly delivers personalized, high-impact articles. With over 2,000 new publications added across 33,000 journals daily, it has become impossible for readers to discover relevant academic content. Similarly, for researchers, it has become equally as difficult to get their content discovered. TrendMD solves this by monitoring Twitter for top-trending medical articles and filtering it it by specialty.\n\nThink of TrendMD as the Reddit for medical articles. We are a simple, efficient, and fun way for researchers to amplify their great content and for busy physicians to discover trending medical research in their field.','Stay current with trending medical research ','[\"Toronto\"]','TrendMD'),('Ayogo distributes highly-polished gamified health applications through organizations (such as non-profits and patient advocacy groups) that serve patients with serious or chronic diseases (diabetes, heart disease, childhood obesity). ','Gamification of chronic disease management.','[\"Vancouver\"]','Ayogo'),('Personal Medicine Plus lets you self manage your health using user health data metrics and behavior tracking on one easy to use and visually rewarding screen. \n\nPersonal Medicine Plus enables the user to avoid or eliminate diabetes, hypertension and heart disease.  \n\n','Revenue Cycle Management for Accountable Care Organizations','[\"Kentucky\"]','Personal Medicine Plus '),('CorCardia is a SaaS, cloud based medical device and pharmaceutical acquisition and supply chain management platform.  Our application creates partnerships between hospitals and suppliers to optimize the quality of care, reduce costs, and eliminate waste.\n\nWe also provide deep business intelligence related to: medical device & pharmaceutical utilization and real time visibility to hospital inventories for manufacturers and healthcare providers.','Amazon for Medical Device and Pharmaceuticals ','[\"Minneapolis\"]','CorCardia Group'),('Qnova sells access passes or Q-passes to the US health system. Subscribers are persons that are currently uninsured, under insured, or are paying cash out of pocket toward high deductible health plans. Q-passes help our users get the healthcare they need without insurance. Our customers are outpatient care providers who accept cash for service. Qnova is a cash payer for the provider. Our technology platform helps providers manage and maintain continuity of care with their self-pay patients. ','New payer model  in the US Healthcare System ','[\"Atlanta\"]','Qnova Health '),('Healthcare Cost Transparency\n