rsonal medicine and emerging opportunities in the healthcare industry to come together. SVHealth Meetup is a hub for enterprises, organizations and investors to present opportunities, provide mentorship and engage in conversation with Silicon Valley\'s developer the entrepreneur community.\n\nUltimately, SVHealth seeks to support innovators and transformation of great ideas into useful and sustainable solutions. We would like this group to evolve into a Health 2.0 entrepreneur accelerator program to speed the creation and distribution ideas, technology and products to help people live better and healthier lives.\n\nAlso join us on facebook: http://www.facebook.com/groups/HSV20/','Help foster an ecosystem of health and medical technology startups in the Silicon Valley','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','SV Health'),('Chiron Health is a secure web-based service that connects physicians with patients via video conference for routine follow-up appointments.\n\nWhile many physicians believe telemedicine will play an important role in the future of healthcare delivery, the technology is currently limited primarily to academic medical centers and large health systems. In addition, given complicated state medical board regulations, HIPAA privacy concerns, and difficult reimbursement, the majority of physicians in the U.S. simply don’t have the resources to offer telemedicine services to their patients who need it most.\n\nChiron Health changes this dynamic by providing a secure technology platform that leverages the existing computers, tablets, and mobile devices that physicians and patients use every day, and by providing a high-touch service component that handles all of the regulatory and administrative complexities of practicing telemedicine—including full reimbursement from private payers.','The future of follow-up care','[\"Austin\"]','Chiron Health'),('You are a software developer working in healthcare. You know you need to comply with HIPAA to get hospital and insurance customers, 