.  Join us.\n','Bringing collaborative consumption to healthcare','[\"Boston\"]','Cohealo'),('The NeuroEPG System will assist ER doctors and hospital staff in identifying potential stroke patients faster. \nFor the majority of stroke victims, damage caused by stroke can be reversed by a drug called t-PA if given within the first 4 hours of the stroke. However, less than 5% of stroke patients receive t-PA because they are not triaged and treated within the 4-hour time window. \nOur product provides objective neurophysiologic data to identify stroke patients sooner so more patients get t-PA.','Fast Emergency Room test to ID stroke patients.  An \"EKG-like\" test, but for stroke.','[\"Boston\"]','Strohl Medical'),('A recent report prepared by McKinsey & Co estimates that the cost of medical errors introduced by inadequate track & trace on medical devices is estimated to be between $18 and $115 billion annually. In response to the need in the industry for such a track & trace solution, 121nexus developed MDDTrack™, which is a cloud-based software solution integrated with product packaging for manufacturers to enhance recall management and post-market surveillance in the medical devices and diagnostics industry.','Cloud-based track & trace solutions for biomedical manufacturers','[\"Providence\"]','121nexus'),('Nurep is a mobile health company that has developed a medical device support network that links hospital systems with medical device expertise for real-time operative support.\n\nThe medical device industry spends over $40B a year to send expensive personnel onsite to support healthcare providers in the operating room. The evolution of value-based healthcare has made this expensive and inefficient in-person model no longer sustainable. \n\nNurep will improve patient outcomes, reduce healthcare costs and streamline healthcare delivery through a secure and trusted network that allows on-demand operative support to anywhere in the world. \n\nNurep is creating clinically relevant features to allow for quality support in a remote setting. They will be the first to track novel operative data, record procedures and obtain clinical info to improve healthcare.\n',' Medical Device Support Network (Stanford StartX Med, Blueprint Health)','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Nurep'),('CardioSleeve is the first FDA cleared stethoscope add-on device for clinicians to acquire 3-Lead ECG and Digital heart sound at any point of care. CardioSleeve enhances the traditional stethoscope by recording, displaying and analyzing the heart\'s ECG and acoustical footprints in real time via any wirelessly connected portable device.  \r\n\r\nPatient heart sound auscultations are subjective to the hearing, experience and training limitations of the clinician, leading to missed diagnosis and additional costly tests.  A traditional ECG requires wired electrode cart machines which limits their access.  \r\n\r\nCardioSleeve disrupts this cardio-diagnostic process by allowing clinicians an attachment to their current stethoscope to acquire digital heart sound and ECG and perform real time analysis at any point of care via mobile.\r\n\r\nCardioSleeve\'s device/ mobile app platform offers:   \r\nUniversal stethoscope attachment\r\nDigital Auscultation\r\n3- Lead ECG\r\nMurmur Analysis\r\nCloud EHR','Stethoscope attachment with mobile heart sound and ECG','[\"Pittsburgh\"]','Rijuven'),('The Blueprint Health accelerator program is geared towards healthcare companies that want an intensive three-month program to help find customers and capital. Blueprint Health is a Charter Member of the Global Accelerator Network, which was started by TechStars. Selected companies range from two founders with an idea to businesses that have customers, investors and are generating significant revenue.\n\nThe foundation of the program is a community of over 150 healthcare entrepreneurs, investors and industry executives that are committed to helping you build and grow your business. We have the largest network of mentors with healthcare expertise of any accelerator, which can provide you with warm introductions and the strategic and tactile advice you need. If you are accepted to the accelerator program, you will receive $20,000 in cash, over $50,000 in perks, office space at our SoHo office, and a community that is dedicated to seeing you succeed.','Community, Capital and Customers for your Health Startup','[\"New York City\"]','Blueprint Health'),('Lynx Design is developing a new class of assistive devices for the elderly and individuals with motion disorders. Our first product is an active tremor cancellation technology that will assist individuals affected by motion disorders such as Essential Tremor. The system will facilitate daily living, reduce social isolation, and re-enable the affected public to participate in activities/occupations that were lost upon disease onset.','Active Stabilization for Parkinson\'s and Essential Tremor Patients','[\"San Francisco\"]','Lift Labs'),('Innovative Surgical Designs, Inc. (ISD) is a medtech start-up company that has developed Altum, the first and only minimally invasive cure for lumbar spinal stenosis that maintains the natural dynamics of the spine. \n\nAltum is a percutaneous device that goes in through the pedicles and cuts the pedicles from the inside out. Our bone saw is the first and only saw in the world that can cut bone from the inside out.  After the pedicles are cut, we insert our implant that expands the central and foraminal opens on average 50%.  It is a simple procedure with advanced technology that takes about 30 minutes per level to perform.\n','Edwards Lifesciences SAPIEN for spine','[\"Bloomington, IN\"]','Innovative Surgical Designs'),('Procured Health is a web-accessible information platform that enables allows hospitals to tackle their fastest growing cost - medical devices. The platform leverages the collective knowledge of hospital members, along with public data from vendors and the FDA, to facilitate adoption of high value products to both reduce spend and improve care. ','Making the medical device market efficient','[\"Chicago\"]','Procured Health'),('Podimetrics is a system for keeping diabetic feet healthy.','Podimetrics is a system for keeping diabetic feet healthy.','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Podimetrics'),('Spartan is bringing complete sample-to-result DNA testing systems to medicine. Spartan’s technology fully integrates DNA collection, extraction and analysis, with an intuitive interface that is easy to operate. For the first time, healthcare providers and their patients can get DNA results on demand.','Sample to result in 1 hour','[]','Spartan Bioscience'),('Venipuncture is the most common invasive medical procedure, with over 1.4B procedures performed annually in the US alone. It is also one of the most overlooked problems in medicine. 20% of first attempts to gain access to a vein fail, often leading to patient complications and additional expenses for medical facilities. Veebot is automating venipuncture through computer vision and robotics, making it safer for both patients and medical staff, and cost efficient for medical facilities.\n','Automated Venipuncture Solutions (e.g., phlebotomy, IV insertion, blood gasses etc.)','[\"Mountain View\"]','Veebot'),('EnteroWave is creating innovative needle-delivered neurostimulation devices for gastrointestinal (GI) disorders.  We use proprietary neuromodulation methods that elicit specific physiological responses, including the ability to mimic the therapeutic effect of a gastric bypass. Diabetes and obesity are a worldwide epidemic, and our devices offer a low-cost, low-risk alternative to surgical intervention.  These versatile devices can also be reconfigured for the treatment of other conditions including GERD, IBS, or motility disorders.  Our patented miniaturization technology comes from Stanford, and our proprietary neuromodulation techniques come from years of research at both Johns Hopkins Medical Center and the University of Texas Medical Branch.\n\nOur millimeter-sized devices are externally powered and controlled, and open a new realm of applications because of the lower costs and risk without surgery.  Currently we are building wireless prototypes for animal and clinical studies. ','Minimally Invasive Neurostimulators for GI Disorders','[\"San Carlos, CA\"]','EnteroWave'),('iOS app for tracking your mindful brainwaves.','Consumer neurotechnology for health and wellness','[\"San Francisco\"]','BrainBot'),('SoniTrack\'s technology integrates robotics and ultrasound imaging to enable real-time markerless targeting for radiation therapy.','Precision targeting for radiation therapy','[\"Palo Alto\"]','SoniTrack Systems'),('DuoFertility is a home fertility monitoring service, proven equally effective as IVF for half of all IVF patients (with peer reviewed publications).  DuoFertility costs 1/10th what IVF does, and is suitable for 80% of all infertile couples (of which there are about 1.5M couples/year EU+US). CE and FDA cleared.\n\nDuoFertility retails online at www.DuoFertility.com and in the UK through Boots Pharmacy.  The price is £495 (~$800), and if you\'re not pregnant in 12 months we give your money back.','Home fertility service proven as effective as IVF','[\"Cambridge, UK\"]','Cambridge Temperature Concepts'),('Eko provides physicians with certainty when they are diagnosing heart conditions. We’ve built one of the world’s first stethoscopes that can automatically detect heart murmurs. Doctors currently have the almost impossible task of trying to hear minute differences between heart sounds, which results in frequent misdiagnosis and undetected heart abnormalities. Through a physician’s smartphone, the Eko software compares a patient’s heartbeat to a database of thousands of others and provides almost instantaneous feedback to the physician. Eko gives every physician the power of a cardiologist in their pocket.\n\nFEATURES\n| Digitize heart sounds from almost any analog stethoscope\n| Visualize the heart sounds; record and play them back\n| Get an instant analysis of a heart sound by comparing it to thousands of others\n| Attach heart sounds to patient\'s medical records\n| Securely share heart sounds with other physicians','A cardiologist in every physician\'s pocket','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eko Devices'),('We love Hardware.\n\nHighway1 (http://highway1.io) is part of PCH (http://www.pchintl.com/), a global supply chain company. We\'re been working with Fortune 500 companies for over 15 years. PCH is also known for bringing startups like littleBits and Lark to market. Now we want to use that expertise to help younger companies get ready for production and their first round of funding.\n\nOur four month program supplies you with:\n\n• A dedicated staff of experienced engineers ­\n• An inside view into the supply chain infrastructure in Southern China\n• An education in manufacturing, supply chain, and distribution as well as project and business management, finance, and strategy\n• Office & shop space for mechanical & electrical prototyping\n• Mentorship and guidance from across the tech sector\n• Seed Funding of $20,000 in return for 3-6% equity\n\nWe\'re looking for small teams that want to build hardware companies for the long term.\n\nIf this describes you, let us know.','Incubator for hardware start-ups','[\"San Francisco\"]','Highway1'),('EnChroma makes the only eyeglasses that offer true red/green color blindness correction for the 10 million Americans, 200 million worldwide who suffer from the condition. This application serves as a way to demonstrate and refine our optical lens coating capabilities in a niche market willing to pay early adopter rates as we begin value engineering our efforts and rolling out vastly improved eyewear products in every market segment.','Color for the Color Blind','[\"Berkeley\"]','EnChroma'),('Kickstart helps improve mobility and facilitate rehabilitation to help people with severe disabilities walk independently. People with severe mobility impairments due to medical conditions such as stroke, multiple sclerosis, or Lou Gehrig’s Disease have some strength and control in their legs, but not enough to walk independently. Consequently, they use wheelchairs for mobility at the cost of independence as well as any hope of maintaining or recovering function.\n','Medical Device helping people w/ severe disabilities walk','[\"Seattle\"]','Cadence Biomedical'),('ZernikeMeta Ventures has extensive experience in managing public-private venture capital funds that co-invest with angel investors in various regions including Southern Europe, Central Europe, Eastern Europe. Primary industry of focus are ICT, Biotech, Medical Devices, Manufacturing companies.\nActive funds are in Italy, Slovenia and Poland for an overall amount of around 90Mln Euro under management.','Early stage investor','[\"Europe\"]','ZernikeMeta Ventures'),('AdhereTech has created patented smart pill bottles that improve medication adherence. These bottles automatically measure the amount of medication in the bottle in real-time, and wirelessly transmit this HIPAA-compliant data to the cloud via the Verizon network. If a patient hasn’t taken his/her medication, our service reminds them via phone call or text message - as well as via on-bottle lights and chimes.\n\nAdhereTech has secured trials with: \n• Boehringer Ingelheim for a TBD medication\n• The Walter Reed National Military Medical Center for type 2 diabetes medication\n• Weill Cornell Medical College for single-dose HIV medication\n\nWinner:\n• Clinician\'s Choice at The Cleveland Clinic Medical Innovation Summit\n• Boehringer Ingelheim\'s 2013 Healthcare Innovation World Cup\n• NYCEDC\'s PILOT Health Tech NYC\n\nMain stage:\n• Pfizer Innovation Conference\n• TEDMED\n• Cleveland Clinic Medical Innovation Summit\n• Stanford Medicine X\n\nFeatured in: \n• WSJ\n• Fast Company\n• Wired\n• TIME','Patented wireless pill bottles to increase adherence and collect data','[\"New York City\"]','AdhereTech'),(NULL,'','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','University Venture Fund'),('Raising $4M Series A\n\nHourGlass has developed an transoral procedure to help morbidly obese patients lose weight. While surgeries like gastric bypass are effective and represent >$1B in sales annually, <2% of eligible patients elect treatment. HourGlass’ patented device replicates the anatomic results of proven surgeries but with an incision-free procedure performed outside expensive operating rooms in half the time. The result is a simpler, safer, and incision-free procedure for <$10k.','Incision-free obesity surgery','[\"Redwood City\"]','HourGlass Technologies'),('The Strong Arm™ is a lifting safety device with load distribution system, that removes the injury causing loads from the weaker hands, arms neck and lower back, and distributes those forces to stronger more capable areas of the torso. The company was founded and developed by two students at Rochester Institute of Technology in 2011. ','Increasing the Performance of the Workforce ','[\"Boston\"]','StrongArm Technologies'),('Bleeding or swelling of the brain due to head trauma can increase the pressure inside a patient\'s skull (ICP). Elevated ICP is dangerous and may be fatal if left untreated. The gold standard for measuring ICP requires a neurosurgeon to drill a hole in the patient\'s head and screw in a sensor. This procedure is often not performed due to the resources required and associated risks.\n\nRecognizing this unmet need, researchers in the UCLA Department of Neurosurgery have developed a non-invasive alternative to assess elevated ICP. The technology uses an algorithm and patient database to correlate elevated ICP with an ultrasound measure of blood flow in the brain.\n\nNeural Analytics is building RapidICP, a hand-held head trauma screening tool that encapsulates this technology. RapidICP will target a domestic total addressable market of $2B including first responders, the military and various clinical settings.\n','Non-invasive head trauma screening device for use in pre-hospital settings.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Neural Analytics'),('Widetronix’s mission is to enable autonomous sensors for the wireless world. The company is commercializing ultra low power sensors with betavoltaic micro-power sources, which have an energy density up to 5 µW/cm2. This technology is based on licensed patents from Cornell University, as well as Widetronix patents and patents pending. Known applications include critical system protection for defense ($200M), secure IT and networking ($840M), industrial sensors ($500M), and medical implants ($1B), where drivers are long-life, stability in harsh environments, and small size, respectively. Widetronix operates its own electronics packaging facility, as well as in the Cornell Nanofabrication Facility, both in Ithaca, New York. The company is venture, grant, and customer funded and is seeking to fill out $500K of a $1M bridge financing to lead to a $5M Series A in 2014. This will enable the company to transition into production and sales in 2014. ','Tiny batteries that last a lifetime','[\"Ithaca\"]','Widetronix'),('FitBionic is a consumer-centered prosthetics company with a first-in-industry focus on cultivating healthy lifestyles for amputees, with a special focus on the needs of people with diabetes. Founded in Boulder, Colorado, FitBionic is led by a team of top designers, technologists, and entrepreneurs from leading bionics and prosthetics companies. Development of our first product, the FitBionic Foot, was supported by a $1.2 million grant from the National Institutes of Health, and the foot has garnered multiple design awards and national recognition. Most importantly, the first amputees to use this biomechanically designed walking foot have loved it from the first steps.\n','Re-imaging bionic limbs, for everyday heroes','[\"Boulder\"]','FITBIONIC'),('Phthisis offers 3 product lines for clinical laboratories:\n\nG-Sphere® Standards - GMP-grade molecular standards for virtually any pathogen ~ better standards = quality diagnosis.\n\nE-Sphere® Extraction - Enzyme-based technology makes E-Sphere easier & faster than competitors ~ faster sample prep = faster diagnosis.\n\nR-Sphere™ Detect - Genetic \'fingerprint\' technology makes R-Sphere faster & more accurate than competitors ~ better diagnosis =  better patient care.','Infectious Disease Molecular Diagnostics','[\"Charlottesville\"]','Phthisis Diagnostics'),('Intelligent Ultrasound develops software that improves the quality, reliability and diagnostic power of medical ultrasound – the most widely used medical imaging tool in the world. The company’s products make ultrasound easier to use and help hospitals to provide a consistently high-quality ultrasound imaging service, thereby minimising the risk of wrong or missed diagnoses.\n\nIt\'s first product has been shown to improve rates of diagnosis in ultrasound scans of the heart by more than 40%.\n','Big data analytics for better diagnosis','[\"Oxford\"]','Intelligent Ultrasound'),('MatchedFlicker helps the clinician perform two of their most important functions, disease diagnosis and patient engagement, faster and more effectively using the medical images they already have available. Images are rapidly uploaded to the cloud and can be instantly compared using a single button. The system can be accessed from anywhere via a web browser, and is also enabled for future mobile medicine and telehealth applications.','Automates \'Spot the Difference\' to improve diagnosis and patient engagement','[\"Philadelphia\"]','EyeIC'),(NULL,'','[\"New York City\"]','Healthcare Innovation World Cup'),('The device is a proprietary, low cost, non-invasive, radiation-free tool that uses military grade thermal cameras to measure heat/vascular patterns which are indicative of breast cancer.  The test is painless and takes about 10 minutes. \r\n\r\nThe device will be used by OB/GYNs and Internists as part of an annual physical exam, as well as by oncologists to monitor patients subsequent to cancer diagnosis/treatment.  It’s projected sensitivity is 95% vs. a clinical breast exam by the doctor at 45% (mammogram at 75%. The device and software automate a manual process that has been perfected as a result of testing 1,000,000+ women over the past 40+ years.  The company has an exclusive worldwide license to this methodology that has been validated in a 2,000 woman clinical trial. The company has an experienced management team. Board is anchored by the co-developer of Lipitor, Roger Newton, PhD. \r\n\r\nCompany has potential to provide significant return to investors and save thousands of lives.','Revolutionary Early Breast Cancer Detection Device','[\"Pontiac\"]','First Sense Medical'),('AccelDx is developing pScreen™, a disruptive blood testing platform for the diagnosis and management of medical conditions in the Home/Point-of-Care setting. Accel’s solution enables physicians/patients to manage diseases in a timely and effective manner, thereby reducing cost and hospitalizations. AccelDx is currently focusing on pScreen-BNP™ for the in home daily monitoring of heart conductions to prevent heart failure (HF) related re-hospitalizations: an untapped market opportunity of $1.9B.','Diagnostic tests at your fingertips','[\"Berkeley\"]','Accel Diagnostics'),('JettStream minimizes asthma attacks and ER visits for children by providing a superior delivery system for nebulized medication. In addition, JettStream provides an educational system for parents and pediatricians treating childhood asthma.\nOur series of products create a pain free, non intrusive approach to the repetitive respiratory therapy demanded by this disease. The treatments that we target address both acute attacks and daily therapies.','A Superior Treatment System for Children with Asthma','[\"Bend\"]','JettStream '),('Nanofiber Solutions, LLC is a medical device manufacturer of a new class of human implants, three-dimensional (3-D) scaffolds and cell culture products that advance biological sciences.  We manufacture the only bioartificial tracheal implant with FDA Investigational New Device (IND) allowance in the U.S.  These implants have been used successfully in several European surgeries in the past year with upcoming surgeries scheduled in the U.S. ','Novel artificial implants','[\"Columbus\"]','Nanofiber Solutions'),('We make it easy for doctors, nurses and midwives to track innovation online and to buy prebundled tools to use overseas in emerging markets. We are a marketplace aggregating technologies and protocols that save lives in childbirth (obstetrics, gynecology, neonatal products and emergency care).','The first global fast track for medical innovations','[\"Providence\"]','Maternova '),('Digital Mammographer automatically diagnoses screening mammograms with above 90% accuracy (tested on over 2,000 mammograms). Turnaround is one minute. And you can use it anywhere with an Internet connection, without buying $200k of hardware. It will provide patients with peace of mind and clinics with low-cost, portable, highly accurate diagnostics. It could save thousands of lives.\n\nAnd that\'s just the beginning. We\'re disrupting medicine and we hope you\'ll join us for the ride.','Artificially Intelligent Cloud Diagnosis','[\"Rockville\"]','Living Discoveries'),('Forge Medical is a development stage medical device company focused on the commercialization of an innovative product for the $30B U.S. hemodialysis marketplace.  The Company’s first product platform, VasoStat, is a sterile, ergonomic, cost-effective device to control bleeding following removal of needles after hemodialysis.  This product will enable dialysis clinics to reduce staff overtime, infection risks and ancillary material costs.','Hemostasis device for dialysis and venous punctures','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Forge Medical'),('  The QuietNITE is a dentist-prescribed, FDA approved, Mandibular Repositioning Device sold in the rapidly growing Sleep Apnea market.  It\'s intended for treatment of mild to moderate Obstructive Sleep Apnea.  Our customer is a Dentist, a Dental Laboratory, or a Distributor.\n\n  The lower jaw is moved into a forward position, thus increasing the three-dimensional space in the airway and oxygen flow to the brain. Additionally, this reduces airway velocity and soft-tissue vibration (snoring).\n\n','Sleep Apnea Mandibular Repositioning Device','[\"Atlanta\"]','QuietNITE'),('Molecular Detection, Inc. (“MDI” or the “Company”) is a privately-held commercial-stage diagnostics company that has developed and commercialized a series of performance-leading highly-multiplexed, rapid and highly-accurate molecular diagnostic assay kits.  MDI’s initial commercial focus is on the rapid detection of infectious diseases.  Rapid detection of HAIs and infectious diseases represents >$2B worldwide market for diagnostics. \n\nMDI has commercialized its Detect-Ready® MRSA Panel, for the rapid MRSA, MSSA and MRCNS and is in full time hospital and laboratory use in the European Union. MDI is finalizing the development the Whole Blood Sepsis Panel, which will be the first molecular diagnostic test to provide timely, accurate identification of key antibiotic resistance determinants and pathogens within 3 hours direct from patient sample.  Finally, MDI is in advanced development of the Detect-Ready Gastro Panel, for the rapid detection of diarrhea-causing bacteria.  ','Advanced Molecular Diagnostic Panel Tests','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Molecular Detection Inc.'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"Milwaukee\"]','Granite Med Systems'),('Agile Devices aims to remove a major time bottleneck in a wide variety of catheter-based interventional procedures, resulting in improved patient outcomes and large cost savings for hospitals. Our unique variable-stiffness microcatheter accelerates interventional procedures by allowing clinicians to more rapidly navigate small, tortuous blood vessels.  Patients benefit from shorter procedure times, especially in time-critical emergencies such as stroke or acute arterial bleeding. Faster procedure times also allow treatment in patients who had would have otherwise fallen outside of their therapeutic time window. Physicians are attracted to our device by the improved ease-of-use over traditional microcatheters and maintained compatibility with other interventional equipment.  Hospitals benefit from lower costs per procedure, which could lead to savings of $1.8+ B/year for hospitals in the US upon complete adoption.','Fast-access microcatheter','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Agile Devices'),('There are 230,000 physician offices in the U.S. spending over $30B per year on medical supplies and equipment. 90% of them are small businesses with limited purchasing volume as individuals. By banding together through social commerce, we are bringing volume based purchasing discounts to these practices to capture a slice of this big pie. We are in beta, have had great press coverage and are generating sales with a small scale launch so far.','Reducing healthcare costs through social commerce.  Buy Together, Thrive Together.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Groundswell Health'),('A small Angel Investors Group, investing across all areas using Technology as an enabler....currently working on mentoring, strategising, and launching a Healthcare - ECG monitoring device....Looking at other medium ticket size deals from all you budding entrepreneurs out there!! ','','[]','Gurgaon Angels'),('Essex Capital acts as a financing source and lessor to credit worthy companies on a nationwide basis, leasing all assets except vehicles and commercial aircraft.\n\nEssex Capital Venture Leasing’s structured financing provides companies with access to the equipment they need, while our knowledge and relationships with venture capital companies offers the partnerships needed to face the challenges in the market, together.\n\nSpecialties include:\n\nVenture Capital Leasing, Equipment Leasing, Alternative Investment, Sale Leaseback, Private Equity, Llife Sciences, Medical Devices, Manufacturing Equipment, Capital Connections, Portfolio Companies ','','[\"Santa Barbara\"]','Essex Capital Corporation'),('Sentry Scientific is building a smart walker for the elderly. We aim to reduce risk of walker-related fall injuries, increase senior independence, and to alleviate the financial burden off healthcare sectors across the globe.','Sentry Scientific Inc. ','[\"Kitchener\"]','Sentry Scientific Inc'),('DocBox is a Waltham based small medical device informatics and analytics Company that was founded in 2007. DocBox is developing an innovative platform in order to create an intelligent internet of things at the point of care. The DocBox platform acquires data from multiple sources within the clinical environment, processes the data, and provides key information and decisions to clinicians at the right time.','Intelligent Point of Care Medical Device Platform','[\"Boston\"]','DocBox'),(NULL,'Inspiring great entrepreneurs and help building successful startups','[\"Lisbon\"]','Beta-i'),('CloudClinica is the 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials. This is the first Cloud Data Capture (CDC) system, to empower business users to build clinical studies themselves, remove today\'s high IT dependency and eliminate any financial barrier of entry through a pay-per-CRF pricing and a solution five times cheaper than existing solutions. CloudClinica offers a built-in integration layer for additional eClinical systems on its fully validated and compliant platform.','The 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials introducing Cloud Data Capture (CDC)','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','CloudClinica'),('Metamason is a healthcare-focused 3D scanning and 3D printing laboratory. Our proprietary Scan·Fit·Print process uses 3D body scanning, patented algorithmic design, and on-demand 3D printing to create individually customized, ergonomic products that are perfectly designed for you. Our flagship product is a revolutionized custom CPAP mask for sleep apnea patients.\n\nOur business model: Invent, De-risk, & License. Our team develops, patents, tests & prototypes custom products, copyrighted algorithms, patentable design processes, materials & printing techniques — all of which can be licensed in modular segments. \n\nAt Metamason, we are inspired by the way the Scan·Fit·Print process enables the cost-efficient, pulled demand production of innovative products shaped by your specific needs. We also believe in a more personal approach to medicine — that\'s why we\'ve developed a method for producing individually customized medical devices that can be worn with comfort, confidence and style. ','SaaS for 3D Printed Products','[\"Pasadena, CA\"]','Metamason'),('MANOS CTR™ is a medical device for carpal tunnel release (CTR). The procedure is performed using nerve stimulation and ultrasound guidance.  \n\nOpen carpal tunnel release requires a 1-2 inch incision in the palm. The incision is painful and the recovery is extensive. \n\nMANOS CTR™ is performed with an awake patient using local anesthetic. There is no incision in the palm and no stitches are required.\n\nMore than 500,000 carpal tunnel surgeries are performed in the United States annually. \n\n','Ultrasound guided carpal tunnel surgery - least invasive option','[\"San Francisco\"]','Thayer '),('Avomeen Analytical Services is a full-service chemical testing laboratory specializing in deformulation, pharmaceutical testing, product development, and chemical litigation support services.','Chemical Analysis for Product Development','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','Avomeen Analytical Services'),('CHECK™ is a revolutionary way to assess and monitor Training Readiness and recovery aimed especially for athletes (professional and recreational) engaged in sports requiring strength, explosive power, skill and coordination. These sports include most of the team sports (e.g. football, basketball, hockey and rugby), individual sports requiring skill and coordination (e.g. tennis, golf, athletics and badminton), fight sports (e.g. boxing, wrestling, MMA) and sports requiring explosive power (e.g. fitness, gym, crossfit and bodybuilding). Our solution also works in endurance sports providing additional information to heart-rate based assessments. \n\nCHECK™ is based on the physiological phenomena of muscle reflex generated by specific low-voltage current.The delay and intensity of the muscle reflex describes the total load on the neuro-muscular system of an athlete. \nCHECK™ is designed to be a training aid for athletes, coaches and medical professionals.','CHECK - we make you a better athlete','[\"Oulu\"]','CHECK'),('DIIME is developing a new medical device intended for use in autotransfusion in cases of ruptured ectopic pregnancy and other traumas, where blood can be salvaged from the abdomen and cleaned for reinfusion when donor blood is not available. In these cases, a woman has a massive internal hemorrhage and desperately needs a transfusion, but donor blood is frequently unavailable. Sub-Saharan Africa suffers from chronic shortages of donor blood, which significantly detracts from the ability to provide life-saving surgical care. Hemafuse allows a clinician to safely salvage blood from the internal hemorrhage and filter and transfuse it. DIIME is working closely with clinicians in Ghana to commercialize the technology. To date, we have completed laboratory testing with reconstituted human blood, which showed no damage to the blood cells incurred with the device, and a comparison test between the soup ladle method and Hemafuse using fresh pig blood.','DIIME is creating new medical devices to improve maternal health in developing countries.','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','DIIME'),('Pangianet is a comprehensive digital healthcare solution for patients, healthcare professionals, & hospital systems.\n\nOur solution is practical, easy to use, and very affordable.  Our customers are patients, healthcare professionals and providers, as well as all companies looking to provide added value to their employees through on demand health solutions.\n\nFor patients...Pangianet provides an on-demand answer to your concern\n\nFor doctors..you get enterprise grade tools to better track and diagnose your patients. DICOM for images and media and a complete electronic health record HIPAA compliant and certified by the US National Coordinator of Health Information Technology. No more paying for expensive EHRs. \n\nFor other healthcare professionals,  build your professional profile and generate revenue through professional advice and sales of your products.\n\nAs a hospital communiacate via HL7 standard.  256 bit encryption, save money, say goodbye to paper.\n\nPangianet is the google of health','Anyone Anywhere Anytime Health','[\"Bogota\", \"Earth\", \"Atlanta\", \"Georgia\", \"Colombia\", \"California\", \"North America\", \"South America\", \"Europe\", \"Asia\", \"Africa\", \"Central America\", \"Australia\", \"India\"]','Pangianet'),('The only medical device available directly to consumers, without a prescription, for treating insomnia.  ','Solving Insomnia without Drugs','[\"Portsmouth, NH\"]','InSomniSolv'),('Sensory Health Systems is creating a revolutionary preventive care and early detection platform with initial focus on cardio respiratory care for all age groups and other serious conditions like sleep apnea and hypothermia among newborns. Detection is done using wireless sensors worn by consumers like a bandaid and diagnosis on smartphone.\n\nThe platform is built using the simple philosophy that consumers are architects of their health and that each person is unique. The platform allows the medical team to personalize the risk alerts, thresholds and care based on the digital health record the patient created . The system in addition to diagnosis has adherence & compliance modules making it a complete digital healthcare solution for both the patient and the doctor. \n\nIts a personalized medicine with initial focus on cardio-respiratory care.\n','Early Detection of Cardio-respiratory conditions ','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','Sensory Health Systems'),('The superior characteristics of our product will mean that we shall largely displace the currently-available imperfect fertility tools (ovulation predictor kits and monitors) - and not only that. Because of the way our sensor works, it will also offer unheard of applications such as built-in screening for cervical cancer and other STDs. In fact, we are introducing not a single product but a medical technology platform with numerous applications (yes, much like the smart phones).   ','Personal fertility monitor for home use, ','[\"Colorado\"]','bioZhena Corp'),('We think that writing on a mobile device should be as easy as picking up a pen and scribbling down thoughts on a piece of paper. We are creating an input method that is:\n\n• Natural because it mimics handwriting. Letters are entered by drawing simple loops. \n• Fast because these loops fit together. Words are entered with quick, fluid gestures. \n• Fun because writing becomes a creative experience.','If the keyboard was invented today, what would it look like?','[\"Copenhagen\"]','8pen'),(NULL,'Designing, building, and testing things','[\"San Francisco\"]','Manufactory Co'),('Our software provides impactful diabetes management insights at the right time; when people test their blood sugar levels. We can present feedback on undesirable patterns occuring in upcoming problem areas of the day, patterns of glucose variability, risk of hypoglycemia, estimated HbA1c, and insulin sensitivity on monitoring devices or on connected mobile phones. ','Actionable diabetes management insight','[\"Charlottesville\"]','InSpark Technologies'),('MedStartr clients are over 20 times more successful than average for healthcare innovation.  This is because we drive massive exposure and let the crowd decide which ideas they like best. MedStartr innovation acceleration and crowdfunding clients succeed over 40% of the time as shown by the 108 partnerships, thousands of new customers, and over $25MM in investments they have garnered after going live on our platform. MedStartr has become the go-to platform to accelerate innovation in healthcare through our campaigns, challenges, and events.that drive press, partnerships, adoption, and funding. We bring together a \"Crowd that Cares\", namely patients, providers, institutions, payers, investors and corporate partners, and create a wave of support, adoption, and investmentlet the crowd show which ideas will be the best investments. We look forward to launching our equity platform in Q1 2014. ','Healthcare Crowd Funding','[\"New York City\"]','MedStartr'),('Until now, there has been little effort to stabilize or control a patient’s extremity during intravenous therapy.  An unstable limb may result in accidental needle sticks costing healthcare providers billions of dollars each year in treatment costs.  \n\nOur device is the first to stabilize a patient\'s extremity when starting an IV or drawing blood in an effort to reduce the number of preventable needle sticks.  Our versatile design is attachable to any ambulance cot or hospital bed.','Reduce Needlesticks with IV Support','[\"San Diego\"]','Life Support'),('NeuroTek Medical is an emerging device company developing non-invasive, electronic neuromodulation devices for the treatment of a variety of pathologies. Our founders have been a part of nearly $30M in active medical device development. Key personnel are inventors on 20+ patents and applications and own 15 issued patents in the medical device space. \r\n \r\nCurrently, NeuroTek is developing a battery-operated, self-administered home-based device that can safely and transcutaneously stimulate the occipital nerve for treating migraines. TONES is a non-surgical, non-drug based solution that is a cost-effective option for immediate relief at the onset of a migraine. Migraine headache pain is a serious debilitating condition affecting more than 10% of the population, with accepted figures of 30 million sufferers in the US and 240 million worldwide. NeuroTek\'s goal is to provide an alternative treatment option to the 50% of episodic migraineurs who are dissatisfied with their current therapy. ','The Future of Migraine Relief','[\"Dallas\"]','NeuroTek Medical'),('Due to its unique rectangular platform, the patented Proximerge dental implant system is the only product in the industry which naturally mimics the emergence profile of molars.  This eliminates food and bacteria traps, distributes stresses on the jaw bone, and provides a better foundation for crowns.  Molars represent 70% of the $3.1B dental implant market.  The company has applied for 510k clearance from the FDA and expects European regulatory approval (CE Mark) by May 2012.  ','Dental implants & surgical tools','[\"Colorado Springs\"]','Grant Dental Technology Corp.'),(NULL,'Beating cancer though innovative RF devices','[\"Montreal\"]','EMcision International Inc'),('Portable Medical Technology Ltd develops quality, accredited & trusted mobile software for medical specialists to reduce medical errors, improve efficiencies & progress patient communication. We combine the essential tools specialists need into easy-to-use smartphone & tablet applications that are FDA and CE approved and provide the latest updated tools to support critical medical decision-making. We launched our first app designed specifically for oncology professionals in December 2012. ','CE/FDA approved apps for specialist medics','[\"London\"]','Portable Medical Technology'),('CerMed brings IPAP, a personal cervical sample collector for standard laboratory testing and CerMark, a point of care, antibody based cervical cancer screening system which includes CerMap, a patented sample collector and cervical mapping device, screening cartridge employing nanotechnology and reader console providing test results in 15 minutes or less. CerMark will allow physicians to provide patient feedback at time of test or in the field where laboratory services are not easily available. ','Innovative point of care diagnostics','[\"Monterey\"]','CerMed'),('Cirle is a growing medical technology incubator based in Miami, Florida. We are focused on creating transformative medical technologies that will truly move the needle in healthcare delivery. Our mission is to to develop innovative medical devices and products with the aim of improving ocular health and conditions that cause blindness.','Engineering ophthalmic medical technologies','[\"Miami\"]','Cirle'),('The Owlet Baby Monitor is a sock, that measures heart rate and oxygen levels and alerts parent\'s if their child stops breathing during the night. The number one concern of any parent is the health and safety of their child.  The Owlet Baby Monitor addresses this concern by combining hospital-proven pulse oximetry (vital-sign-reading equipment) with modern communication in a personalized system that grows with your child.  By monitoring heart rate and blood oxygen levels (how well an infant is breathing), life-saving data is available at the click of a button, right where parents want it.  The Owlet Baby Monitor is up all night so parents don’t have to be, providing peace of mind and allowing them the rest they need with the assurance that their baby is getting the rest he or she needs.  Even in its early stages, this product has received impressive pull from the market, being featured on or in ABC, The Huffington Post, Mashable, Gizmodo, and 40 other U.S. and foreign news outlets.  ','Baby Sock That Monitors Heart Rate and Oxygen ','[\"Provo\"]','Owlet Baby Care'),('Contact lenses with disappearing ink. Why?  Outside the eye they are hard to find, can get mixed up between right and left eyes & most importantly can be flipped and inserted backwards into the eye. This is a disruptive technology that will provide a significant edge to contact lens manufactures - in addition to increased margins.     ','Contact Lenses With Disappearing Ink that are Better, Friendlier & Safer   ','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Leuko Tech'),('GITPx Investments is a Singapore based Corporate Angel Investor which invests in Startup & Seed companies in China, India, Singapore, Indonesia, Vietnam and other countries in Asia and beyond. GITPx is part of Rutledge Vine Capital which focuses on global investments.\n\nGITPx is driven by a high calibre team with a combined experience of over 80 years spent in Senior Management positions in diverse sectors in IT, Mobile, Gaming, Digital Media, Hospitality & Real Estate, Consumer marketing, Oil & Gas and the Commodities space.\n\nCollaborative partnerships with other Angels and Incubators in various countries for Co-investment and cross-pollination of ideas across technopreneurs, technology platforms and markets around the world are hallmarks of our investment and growth model.\n\nWe like a ‘High Risk- High Return’ portfolio, managing it with diligence and due care and having lots of fun in the process.\n\nWe invest in Ideas in discovery, Ideas in motion and Ideas in traction.\n','Investing in Technology Startups in Asia & beyond','[\"Singapore\"]','GITPx Investments, Singapore'),('Influent\'s fluid movers enable miniaturization and enhanced portability for dozens of today\'s electronic and medical devices. While chipsets, communications technologies, batteries and packaging have continued to keep up with the miniaturization trend, the fluid movers present in many of these devices have not.  Influent\'s innovation in fluid mover integration breaks through this barrier, providing all the performance in half the size, weight and power of conventional technologies.','Breakthrough miniature fluid movers','[\"Richmond\"]','Influent'),('We have created the uBox, a smart pillbox that helps people take medication as prescribed. Unlike other solutions, the uBox addresses all issues of adherence and convenience, not just some of them. The uBox fits seamlessly into a patient\'s life, makes the process and tools simple, and addresses each of the causes of non-adherence. It is portable, secure, and provides patients and their care circle real-time communication no matter where they are.','the uBox, a smart pillbox','[\"San Francisco\"]','Abiogenix'),('We\'ve developed an intelligent and adaptive joint rehabilitation device, the first application of which is providing low-risk treatment of knee osteoarthritis (OA). \n\nOur device helps those among the ~30M in the US with debilitating knee OA by eliciting contraction of muscles around a damaged knee as a user walks to restore knee stability and function. \n\nWe fill patients\' and physicians\' unmet need for effective, non-invasive, non-medicinal treatment options in the $6.5B knee OA care market.','Non-invasive, non-medicinal knee osteoarthritis treatment','[\"Austin\"]','Articulate Labs'),('Venture Catalysts is a company focused on commercialization of technologies through entrepreneurship. By supporting visionary researchers and entrepreneurs releasing the full potential of their technologies, the company acts as a catalyst on the development of new technology–based ventures','Shaping Technologies into Business','[\"Porto\"]','Venture Catalysts'),('Providence Medical Technology created DTRAX to be the least invasive treatment for neck and arm pain caused by pinched nerves in the neck (foraminal stenosis).  The procedure is performed under x-ray guidance through 1 cm tubes. DTRAX offers patients the benefits of minimal trauma and blood loss, greatly reduced scarring and reduces the need for more invasive cervical surgeries. ','neck surgery reinvented','[\"San Francisco\"]','Providence Medical Technology'),('Just in time kits..\nKits that capture essential safety items for car, home, and pack platforms.','Just in time Kit','[\"Denver\"]','Jit-Kit'),('The opportunity: take the world’s greatest glanceable display – the watch - and reinvent it as a stylish and simple, glanceable display for when we are really mobile and on the go. Glance is a powerful interface for mobile internet services.\n\nMeta Watch helps consumers do what they are already trying to do - consume mobile alerts & notifications effortlessly. This has become a big problem because alerts are often missed because of we carry our phones (guys in pocket; ladies in handbag). \n','Smart watches that function as a glanceable display for critical alerts & the mobile web','[\"Dallas\"]','Meta Watch'),('Autograft is the soft bone found within the hard white outer shell of most bones. Orthopaedic surgeons oftentimes harvest this autograft from a patient in order to use the bone graft in another part of the body that requires fusion or healing. \n\nBOSS Medical is currently developing its first product, the BOSS Harvester - a novel, intuitive system which will enable surgeons to harvest autologous bone graft (autograft) utilizing a minimally invasive approach. \n','Novel Minimally Invasive Orthopaedic Technologies','[\"Baltimore\"]','BOSS Medical'),(' AEGLE Life™. Where health, mobile tech and big data meet.\n\nStaying healthy is a challenge to most of us. AEGLE Life™ provides a smart, personalised health and wellness platform collating and analysing data from mobile enabled devices, which combined with self-assessments and scientific evidence, provide insights that help individuals make better lifestyle choices. AEGLE Work™ also provides aggregated insights that help companies validate their health initiatives.\n \nWe plan our initial pilot with a major employer in early 2014. The pilot will validate outcomes related to mental wellbeing and men’s health. The capabilities will be packaged into the AEGLE Work™ product, which will be sold to employers starting with the resources industry. Longer term, the platform will also collect data and provide correlations between environmental factors and human telemetry, a big data play of interest to public policy and technology developers.','Personalised, data-driven health, prevention and wellness','[\"Perth\"]','AEGLE Life'),('Neuroskill is a device that measures impairment in fine motor control by recording and analyzing the patient\'s handwriting dynamics in real time.  With the help of the Neuroskill device, physicians can potentially diagnose Parkinon\'s Disease as well as monitor progress of pharmacological treatment.','Surrogate Biomarker for Parkinson\'s Disease','[\"Boulder\"]','iNeuroskill '),('Apeliotus is commercializing a diagnostic for early detection of an eye disease call age-related macular degeneration. AMD is the leading cause of adult blindness in developed countries, affecting one in six people over age 65 and one in three over age 75. Despite the trememdous value of early detection, there is currently no good means for diagnosis before significant vision loss has already occurred. Our AdaptDx can detect and track AMD from its beginning stages allowing early intervention.','ophthalmic diagnostic for age-related macular degeneration','[\"Hershey\"]','Apeliotus Vision Science'),('Our medical devise helps in :\n\n1.Digitizing the inventory management  ( including automatic reordering ) of injectable medications by measuring initial and remaining  liquid volumes  inside sealed vials non-invasively \n2.Improving  practice managements by digitizing medical records for human , medical practice and hospitals and  animals and VETS  by cutting costs and enhancing traceability.  \n         \n','Non-Invasive Liquid Level Measurement ','[\"Lexington-fayette\"]','Fluid Management Systems'),('TeleSkin makes hardware, software, and mobile solutions for the early diagnosis of skin cancer, skin health, and other dermatological conditions.  skinScan is our Windows 8 mobile and tablet, Healthvault connected, application for patients and consumers to analyze their skin and connect with doctors for expert opinions. skinScan integrates seamlessly with our integrated hardware/software solution which includes a clinical multi-spectral dermascope for detailed dermascopic skin analysis.','Mobile and clinical skin cancer analysis','[\"Belgrade\"]','TeleSkin'),('Vital Nanometrics is developing a new class of glucose monitors that provide accurate diabetes management in a pain-free manner. Pain-free, automated and accurate blood-sugar monitoring awaits the diabetic. Significant cost reduction will result for both the patient and insurer. The device is based on patented nanotechnology developed by our team members.','A glucose monitor that is truly pain-free yet cost effective.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Vital Nanometrics'),('Industries we serve: all tech and medical device\nCustomers: from early stage startups to established corporate.\nServices:\ninvestor presentation decks,\nbranding and identity,\npromo/product animated video,\ngraphic design, \nweb design/development,\nmarketing materials design, \ncreative strategy consulting. \n\ncreate at theoriacreative dot com','Marketing design: we translate intricate tech ideas into simple visuals','[\"Redwood City\"]','Theoria Creative'),('Healbe is the simple way to manage your body weight, health and sport results, whoever you are.\n\nWristband on your hand fully automatically \n- calculates how much calories earned with the foods and spent duting any activity\n- trackes your heart rate, pulse wave, blood pressure, respiratory rate, temperature, sleep phase, level of dehydration and stress. \n\nApp on your mobile device synchronizes with wristband via bluetooth and gives you understanding, what happens with your body','Automatically trackes your body weight, health and sport results','[\"Moscow\"]','Healbe'),('Nearly 1 in 4 patients undergoing surgery for early-stage breast cancer will require re-operation. Cancer requires re-operation so frequently because surgeons lack tools to detect cancerous tissue during the operation.  \n\nLightpoint Medical is developing a novel molecular imaging technology to detect cancer in real-time during surgery. Our technology reduces the cost and size of a nuclear medicine scanner by 100-fold, enabling it to integrate into the operating room. Image-guided surgery has the potential to provide more accurate cancer treatment and thereby reduce the need for re-operation.','Reducing the burden of cancer through image-guided surgery','[\"United Kingdom\"]','Lightpoint Medical'),('Care Concepts has turned an old school DME (Durable Medical Equipment) company that bills Medicare to a high tech, very efficient technology based company reducing overhead while benefiting from high margin business.  We specialize in the Diabetic meter and monthly supplies.  Customers have a hassle free home delivery while we handle all of the paper work for billing Medicare.','Durable Medical Equipment','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Care Concepts'),('Entac Medical is developing medical devices for predictive and diagnostic medicine based on a novel platform technology, audio spectral analysis. Its first application, PrevisEA, is a late stage, Class II noninvasive, disposable device that is clinically proven to predict post-operative ileus (POI) in surgical patients (GI paralysis occurs 2-6 days after surgery in 25% of patients). Prediction of ileus risk improves treatment protocols and patient outcomes while reducing readmissions and saving hospitals millions of dollars in unnecessary treatment costs. \n\n-	Applied to the abdomen with existing medical adhesive tape \n-	Enclosed microphone detects certain sounds emitted from the bowels\n-	Microchip containing signal-processing algorithms analyzes sounds\n-	LED display indicates the level of risk that the patient will develop POI\n-	Worn up to 12 hours for maximum accuracy\n','Late-stage medical device for predictive and diagnostic medicine','[]','Entac Medical'),('Wave\'s mobile app allows epileptics to use their Smartphones paired wirelessly with a peripheral device and wearable sensors as an ambulatory EEG solution for the remote monitoring of epileptics. The app is downloaded free (e.g. Android, iOS, Blackberry) the peripheral and sensors purchased/rented through the app. Our services are fully reimbursable by payer groups at rate of approximately $750/day for each patient. ','Ambulatory EEG Mobile App','[\"Chicago\", \"San Diego\"]','Wave Technology Group'),('Obtaining a homogenous population of cells from a complex mixture is essential for improved downstream applications like QPCR, genomics, and imaging. Fluorescence Activated Cell Sorters (FACS) analyze and sort thousands of cells per minute and are essential systems for most biomedical research labs ($1B instrument market). NanoCellect was spunout from UCSD to commercialize a disruptive technology for analyzing and sorting cells at 1/5th the cost of current systems. The initial product, WOLF Cell Sorter is a small, affordable, and easy-to-use bench-top cell sorter with features and performance comparable to high-end complex flow cytometers that are primarily found in shared core facilities. The platform is accompanied by disposable microfluidic chips that makes setup and sorting easier while reducing contamination and improving cell viability during sorting. Since inception, NanoCellect has won 7 grants and contracts from the NIH for over $3.3M in non-dilutional funding.\n\n','Cell sorting made accessible (CoinStar for Cell Biologists)','[\"San Diego\"]','NanoCellect Biomedical, Inc.'),(NULL,'Delivering industry-leading viricidal and bacteriocidal technologies to reduce infections.','[\"San Francisco\"]','IonArmour'),('\nRAY is an integrated portable device designed to assist the community of visually impaired people and their families in their daily life. RAY leverages latest mobility technologies to increase independence, enrich social life and improve accessibility of essential services for the visually impaired.','Mobile accessibility tool for the Visually Impaired','[\"Israel\"]','Project-RAY'),('Our company is bringing stem cell therapy to the skin rejuvenation field, with a fast and inexpensive method to use your own cells to make your skin look young again!','Next-generation skin rejuvenation','[\"Santiago\"]','Cell Therapy'),('We help retail and ecommerce businesses build APIs so that they can sell their products on online marketplaces like Magento, Amazon, eBay, osCommerce.\n\nAn API which stands for Application Programming Interface, is a way to let businesses sell their products outside of their core ecommerce site. Except they take a lot technical expertise to build and manage and can get expensive very quickly.\n\nPliant Labs allows businesses to build APIs with an easy use tools and then publish their product data to marketplaces in 3 easy steps.\n\nWe then manage it for them. Its free to use and businesses only pay when they sell products or the APIs get accessed by marketplaces or developers.','We enable businesses to create, publish & use APIs to sell more of everything, anywhere.','[\"Atlanta\"]','Pliant Labs'),('Fosmo Med Introduced Maji™, a Forward Osmosis (FO) based IV solutions to be made using any water at the point of care. The IV bags are shipped sans water, thus: reduce the shipping cost; increase the product shelf life; reduce storage costs; and, reduces the risk of scrap due to leakage. Initial target is disaster relief org such as the Red Cross and will partner with existing manufacturers/distributors to serve the current market. We are a Delaware incorporated company. Market of $7.6B.','Saving Lives Through Technology','[\"San Mateo\"]','Fosmo Med'),('The secure cloud platform at the center of our technology enables a network of physicians, nurses, technicians, and billing specialists to securely access and annotate patient ECG tracings. From credentialed mobile devices, a recipient can instantly access captured ECG tracings, as well as select alerts and push notifications to aid the rapid turnaround of completed reports by busy practices and hospital departments.\r\n\r\nAs patients are increasingly treated in ambulatory surgery centers, rural hospitals, and care clinics, there is a need for technology to provide connectivity among geographically distant clinicians. Further, as technology travels within hospitals and to patients, conventional ECG devices are physically challenging to transport. The InvisionHeart ECG is small enough to be carried in a lab coat pocket, powerful enough to operate for several days, and transmit data via a HIPAA compliant, 256-bit encryption system.','InvisionHeart is developing a cardiac data solution to serve care providers.','[\"Nashville\"]','InvisionHeart'),('Walleye Technologies has developed a next-generation\nportable imaging technology that enables one to “see”—into and through—\nsolid objects, without relying on harmful X-rays. Based on patented microwave and lens technology, Walleye has created a new “imaging category” – the\nmicrowave digital camera. Markets include, Do-It-Yourself (DIY) home repair (e.g., locating pipesand wires in walls), homeland security (scanning packages and people noninvasively), and industrial inspection..','Handheld millimeter wave camera','[\"Boston\"]','Walleye Technologies'),('We\'re building a SAAS EMR for Canadian physicians. Its completely web-based and takes only minutes to set up without having to purchase costly servers or extra hardware. Best of all, no set-up fees.\n\nWe\'re taking the hassle out of EMR for Canadian docs. \n\nOur software is a complete practice management solution including full charting, scheduling and billing capabilities.','SAAS Electronic Medical Records for Canada','[\"Victoria\"]','Cloud Practice'),('Sparo Labs is bringing the power of modern technology to the world of asthma. We\'re developing an award-winning, patent-pending spirometer system that can be produced for a fraction of the cost of current devices today, while seamlessly connecting with smartphones and other mobile devices. Our powerful technology empowers patients to quantitatively track and proactively manage their asthma, while equipping doctors with the power of objective and real-time data to better treat and more efficiently manage their patients.','Bringing the power of modern technology to the world of asthma.','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Sparo Labs'),('AllaQuix™ is a professional-grade hemostat cleared by the FDA for over-the-counter (OTC) use and is now available without a prescription.\n \nAllaQuix™ is designed to work in everyone, even people who have trouble stopping bleeding.\n \nAllaQuix™ is a sterile gauze pad made of medical-grade chitosan.  Chitosan-based hemostats are not readily available to consumers, but have been widely used in the professional medical setting in trauma and surgical settings, including by the U.S. Military.  IMT is now bringing this professional-­grade technology directly to the consumer.\n\nFirst Market: Minor Bleeding\n1 in 3 adults in the US are prone to Nuisance Bleeding. Their blood is incapable of clotting in a few minutes as a result of genetic factors or medications (such as prescription blood thinners or daily aspirin therapy). This represents 80 million people in the US.  There are millions of additional people that want to stop bleeding fast.','Medical Grade Products for Consumers','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Inspiration Medical Technology, Inc.'),('Tidepool is building an open platform and better apps to help people reduce the burden of managing type 1 diabetes.','Open source diabetes platform and apps.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Tidepool'),('The LifeCradle preserves, monitors and transports hearts used in transplantation and will replace the picnic cooler currently used.  The LifeCradle has been proven in published research at leading academic research centers to significantly extend the life of procured hearts from 4 to 24 hours.  Over seventy percent of donated hearts are NOT transplanted in many cases because of a lack of preservation time in the picnic cooler...the LifeCradle will save lives and improve transplant outcomes.  ','Organ Preservation Device for Transplantation','[\"Dallas\"]','Organ Transport Systems'),('Eski tech is developing RemindMe, an automatic medicine dispenser for dosage packed medicine. \n\nWith RemindMe we intend to increase medical compliance and thereby increase people’s quality of life.\n\nIt is estimated that patients who don’t take their medicine as prescribed, cost the US healthcare system about $290 billion in avoidable medical spending each year.\n','Medical Solutions','[\"Reykjavik\"]','Eski Tech'),('One-in-eight women in U.S. will get breast cancer at some point in their lives. It is the most common non-skin cancer for American women. Early stage breast cancer is treated by removing the tumor then irradiating the whole breast to eliminate any remaining cancer cells. Yet post-operative radiation is problematic. It requires five to seven weeks of daily irradiation sessions, results in troubling short and long-term side effects, and costs more than the surgery itself. The result is an unfortunate and dangerous reality: one-in-three patients prematurely discontinue radiation therapy, and a similar proportion must undergo re-operation to remove cancer that was missed. We have designed an ablation probe that will allow surgeons to perform an intra-operative procedure that destroys residual cancer cells in minutes instead of weeks, does not require dangerous ionizing radiation, and dramatically reduces treatment costs compared to conventional therapy.','Making breast cancer treatment faster, safer, more convenient, and less expensive.','[\"Chicago\"]','Innoblative Designs'),('Grand prize winner 2012 Wisconsin Governor\'s business plan competition!  Rowheels solves a key human factors problem.  By pulling the handrim instead of pushing, Rowheels propels a wheelchair user forward with less effort and reduced strain on shoulders, joints and muscles. It replaces the traditional wheels of a manual wheelchair, reversing the motion and corresponding forces required to propel a wheelchair.  Rowheels is a market changer, transforming the lives of wheelchair users forever.','The Wheel Reinvented','[\"Madison\"]','Rowheels'),('Improving the outcomes of lumbar spine proceedures with a new interbody device.\nFully funded, Institutional and strategic investors\n\n2010 - initial invesors\n2011 - FDA approval\n2012 - traction in the marketplace\n2013 - sales and marketing initiatives','Expandable lumbar interbody fusion technology','[\"San Francisco\"]','CoAlign'),('Equipois is pioneering an exoskeletal arm technology that makes people safer and more productive, whether in a factory, laboratory, construction site, hospital, or military service.  By reducing exertion and fatigue for manual activities, Equipois\'s zeroG and X-Ar products can boost productivity by as much as 50% or more and virtually eliminate certain classes of workplace injuries.  ','Exoskeletal arm technology to make humans safer and more productive','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Equipois'),('The Virtual Medical Assistant® is a truly remote, totally noncontact, wireless, continuous cardiorespiratory monitor. It measures heart and respiration rates and movement, providing critical “spot” and “trend” data to a nurse’s station, tablet, cell phone or pager without the need for electrodes that touch the patient or pads that require contact with a mattress or other surface. The VMA is built on a dynamic, connected care platform that provides an extraordinary level of usability, scalability, interoperability and low cost. The VMA, the only cardiorespiratory monitor of its type to receive 510(k) Class II premarket clearance from the FDA, represents a disruptive scientific innovation that can help address critical unmet needs by expanding the proven benefits of continuous cardiorespiratory monitoring to a growing inpatient and outpatient population. The VMA is positioned to provide high value, low cost, location-agnostic monitoring solutions at any location where the need exists.\n','Star Trek Tricorder-style Noncontact Cardiorespiratory Monitoring System','[\"Atlanta\"]','Sensiotec'),('For patients, walking to keep the limbs moving and blood flowing is vitally important to avoid complications, including blood clots, pressure ulcers, and ventilator-associated pneumonia. This process, called ambulation, results in improved outcomes and shorter hospital stays. However, effective ambulation of critical care patients is complicated by all the medical equipment involved. Even the act of preparing the equipment requires two clinicians and twenty minutes, and it takes two clinicians another twenty minutes to return it all to the bedside when finished.  Mobilizer solves these problems with a single platform that holds all the equipment and easily moves with a patient. Only one clinician is needed to walk a patient, and equipment transfer is eliminated since Mobilizer is left at the bedside. In the average Intensive Care Unit, Mobilizer saves up to 160 labor hours per day that would otherwise be lost dealing with equipment instead of focusing on patients.','Ambulation Made Simple','[\"Memphis\"]','Mobilizer'),('The Surfacer™ Inside-Out Access Catheter System is a proprietary instrumentation set that allows physicians to perform a novel “inside-out” approach to gaining venous access. With the Surfacer™, physicians insert a guide wire through the femoral vein in the groin area and, using fluoroscopy, navigate it up through the torso with an exit point in the jugular or subclavian vein. The procedure is performed while the patient is under light sedation.','Medical device development company focused on complex central venous access cases.','[\"Lexington-fayette\"]','Bluegrass Vascular Technologies, Inc.'),('The Integrated Health Platform is a SaaS platform providing patients, physicians, hospitals, and insurance companies with valuable therapy adherence data for patients who suffer with chronic lung diseases like chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and cystic fibrosis. Our approach uses sensors which are applied to patients\' own existing FDA approved medical devices and transforms them into active data gathering tools. This will greatly improve patient health outcomes while giving physicians the capacity to understand hospitalizations before they occur. Our approach was developed through partnership with the Massachusetts Biotechnology Council\'s MassCONNECT mentoring program.','Patient monitoring SaaS for chronic lung disease','[\"Boston\"]','Aware Engineering'),(NULL,'We make great boobies','[]','Smart Implant'),('Current cancer screening tools are expensive, have limitations, may cause serious side effects and still fail to detect rapidly growing tumors early enough.\nEquivox is commercializing a clinically proven technology to detect cancer at its earliest clinically significant stage without patient discomfort or exposure to harmful x-rays. The technology uses safe visible and near infrared light. Functional images of tumors will be obtained and analyzed in real time in doctor’s office setup.\n','Imaging the sound of light to detect cancer early','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Equivox'),('Our mission is to develop and commercialize a portfolio of globally patented, proprietary, bioluminescent (light producing) protein based products that are edible.\n\nWe have many first-in-class applications in the food, beverage and cosmetic markets. We\'ve also made huge breakthroughs in medical diagnostics and imaging. We have no competition, nor do we expect any. It’s patented. It’s safe. It makes stuff glow.\n\nLike your mouth, when you suck on a lollipop. Or your heart, during surgery.','We Make Stuff Glow','[\"Denver\"]','LuminEssence'),('Gene therapy is a promising field which got a recent regulatory boost with the approval of first gene therapy drug in Europe. We are developing laser-controlled gene switches for gene therapy drugs. This will allow to repeatedly activate therapeutic genes in target organs when desired by turning on light at desired times in wearable multi-laser patches. This is way safer than traditional drugs or traditional gene therapy drugs.','laser switch for gene therapy','[\"Rochester\"]','Localized Therapeutics'),('Sentimed offers to patients a mobile platform which allow them to constantly inform their primary care community about their health status and obtain a continuously optimized treatment, thus improving their health and life expectancy while reducing costs, unplanned hospitalizations and readmissions.\n\nWe are presenting to Medical Organizations, Nursing Home Groups and Home Care Agencies a medical platform which identifies those patients whose signs have recently degraded.\n\nThese organizations are facing increased costs due to aging of the population and huge penalties in consequence of the Affordable Care Act. A gap currently exists between care and prevention, this gap is responsible for millions of unplanned hospitalizations and readmissions every year.\n\nSentimed is presenting a solution built for managing large cohorts of beneficiaries and provide early detection of abnormalities in the patients’ health status, thus ensuring on-time course of action and reduced costs.','Telemedicine ERP reducing readmissions and unplanned hospitalizations','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Sentimed'),('Our product is the UroGuide, a one-time, permanent cure for female stress urinary incontinence. The procedure is minimally invasive, and can be done under local anesthesia directly in the physician\'s office. It takes under twenty minutes to perform, and patients can be back at work the very next day. In addition, the UroGuide offers a high cure rate and a much lower risk of complications than the current standard of care, transvaginal slings.','Bringing the new standard of care to surgical treatment of Stress Urinary Incontinence','[\"Memphis\"]','Urova Medical'),('Genicell is developing a functional laboratory model of the blood-brain barrier that is capable of using human or animal cells. This system, which consists of tissue engineered blood vessels grown inside custom built chambers called bioreactors, allows Genicell to conduct drug permeability tests that are otherwise conducted on animals with much greater ease of scale up. This results in a service that would allow pharmaceutical companies to perform drug permeability tests cheaper and faster.','Expedited drug discovery','[\"Berkeley\"]','Genicell'),('At Spring Loaded, we are developing the first knee bracing technology that can effectively enhance the strength and power of the leg muscles. By increasing leg strength, our technology can be used in a wide range of applications including: injury prevention and rehabilitation, mobility assistance, and performance enhancement.\n\nThe idea of enhancing leg strength with knee bracing is not new. Previous solutions have failed however, primarily due to the fact that a powerful enough mechanism could not be implemented on a small enough scale to be built into a knee brace. At Spring Loaded, we have solved this problem by developing a novel technology that allows us to build a compact energy-returning hinge mechanism which can assist the leg muscles during knee extension (e.g. the motion that occurs while standing from a seated position). Our proprietary device can be retrofit to, or integrated with, knee braces that are similar to those already on the market.','Strength Enhancing Knee Braces','[\"Halifax\"]','Spring Loaded Technology'),('Trak allows couples to screen and monitor sperm quality in the comfort of their home.\n- Laboratory-precision sperm count and motility analysis\n- Inexpensive and easy to use\n- Closes the feedback loop for male fertility monitoring\n- Overcomes the apprehension, embarrassment, and cost of clinical semen analysis\n- Allows physicians to monitor results as desired\n- Take control of the problem, and improve your chances of conception\n\nThe system is currently in Beta testing at several Bay Area fertility clinics and with independent users for at-home testing.  Learn more at www.trakfertility.com','Trak - Male Fertility Tracker','[\"Livermore\"]','Sandstone Diagnostics'),('At the base of all human tissue is a form of skeleton or scaffold. We developed a broad technology platform that creates these scaffolds in a way that the body readily accepts, bridging the significant performance gap between the existing markets for biologics and synthetics.  Unlike competing solutions, we create and align a variety of FDA-approved fibers smaller than 1/100th the size of a human hair in multi-layer scaffolds that control cell growth and proliferation.  Our tissue integrates into the body quickly and without immune repression drugs. Our trachea technology and products were used for all the first five nanofiber human trachea replacements and can be used for a host of products including esophagus, tendon, bone, wound care, arteries and veins, intestine, etc, on a $20 billion annual global market.','Create revolutionary scaffolds for human tissue','[\"Columbus\"]','Nanofiber Solutions, LLC'),('Alnion’s product is low cost, non-invasive diagnostic appliance capable of early stage lung cancer detection.\nNovel tools are required to address raising costs of lung cancer screening, treatment and the high false positives (96%) of current invasive tools. Our advanced e-nose technology offers solutions to all of these current shortcomings through highly sensitive and patented CNT technology by detecting patterns of VOCs in human breath, thus identifying lung cancer and it’s sub-histologies.','Non-invasive early stage cancer detection','[\"Boston\"]','Alnion'),('The SRD is the only automated and objective device that measures reading acuity and speed. It will assist eye doctors in assessing reading acuity in patients that are:\n1. undergoing intra-ocular lens procedures with the new high tech IOLs designed to address presbyopia\n2. undergoing treatment for AMD and DR\n3. undergoing treatment for dry eye\n4. have other low vision problems\n\nNo directly competitive device.  Traditional technologies are subjective.  Reasonable regulatory requirements.\n','Automating assessment of Reading Acuity...an important measure of quality of life','[\"New York City\"]','SRD Vision'),('The morbidity of most cancers is related to the metastatic dissemination of cells sloughing off the primary tumor.  Sub-Micro is developing a novel therapeutic device to aid in the removal of residual tumor cells, which will limit metastatic spread and significantly improve long-term survival for cancer patients. The therapeutic system targets and mechanically removes malignant cells from the body using magnetic nanomaterials and a pump driven extracorporeal circuit containing a magnetic filter.','Novel Targeted Cancer Therapy','[\"Atlanta\"]','Sub-Micro'),('OvaPal is reinventing the way women track their fertility for faster, natural, stress free pregnancy achievement.  This is accomplished with a first of its kind,  fully integrated, Bluetooth enabled, wearable basal thermometer and fertility tracking mobile application.  ','Fertility Tracking, Reinvented. ','[\"San Diego\"]','OvaPal'),('ePatientFinder uses analytics technology to connect patients with cutting edge treatments which are recently approved by the FDA or still in clinical trials. We have a network of physicians who use our web app to discover, learn about and discuss novel treatment options. When a physician indicates they are interested in offering a treatment to their patients, ePatientFinder uses their electronic health record database to identify eligible patients. We facilitate this identification process through a 3 tier filter, including subjective analysis for which the physician is compensated.\n\nOur clients are the life sciences companies who are able to accelerate recruiting for their clinical trials (reducing time to market and maximizing profits) as well as providing a new way to market their new products. The physicians are able to offer the most advanced treatment options to their patients. Health insurers benefit from patients finding more effective treatment options, thereby cutting costs.\n','Analytics Driven Patient Identification for Clinical Trials','[\"Austin\"]','ePatientFinder'),('Making an effective fertility technique easy to practice','mobile fertility tracking','[\"Menlo Park\"]','TempSync'),('CathVision is a system for treating heart arrhythmia patients. It has superior signal quality, control features and set-up simplicity over existing systems. ','Clearer catheter signals - more information','[\"Copenhagen\"]','CathVision'),('MolecuLight’s first commercial application, PRODIGI, is a handheld optical imaging device using patented fluorescence technology to instantly detect, analyze and quantify bacterial loads and other parameters objectively at point-of-care. More than 5 years of clinical trial validation shows PRODIGI enables significant improvement to the wound care industry. PRODIGI anables real-time swabbing/biopsies, image-guided wound debridement and  quantitative monitoring of treatment response which results in improved patient outcomes and more efficient use of clinical resources. PRODIGI works with MolecuLight\'s next-generation proprietary disposable biological assays that will provide real-time diagnostic information about bacterial species ID, host/bacterial protease activity and other important biological parameters crucial for optimal diagnosis and treatment planning.  Moleculight’s disruptive imaging technology platform has additional applications in other medical and non-medical markets. ','Revolutionary Point-of-Care Diagnostic Imaging for Woundcare','[\"Toronto\"]','MolecuLight'),('We\'re developing technology-embedded headgear for data-driven protection from concussions.\n\nOur product contains proprietary padding and sensors engineered over the past year that:\n\n1) Protects athletes by reducing impact accelerations with a patented padding material that is optimized for each sport. Our material is designed to respond to the intensity of the impact and cover a wide range of forces.\n\n2) Informs athletes, trainers, and parents with diagnostic impact-data sent to an iPhone app. Our non-intrusive technology provides real-time impact data to the people that need it most.\n\n3) Prevents future injury by recommending proper training and optimal recovery time. Our app learns each athlete\'s strengths and weaknesses to personalize their training program.','Empowering youth athletes by helping them manage and understand brain injury.','[\"Rochester\"]','Nebula Sports'),('We are revolutionizing the diagnosis & management of obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) by replacing overnight sleep tests with a simple, accurate daytime test. This is the first & only test to enable ongoing measures of therapy response, vital for doctors & patients. \n\nInitially aimed at the growing problem of pediatric sleep apnea, where diagnosis is difficult, it will also be developed to solve adult needs. 20 million US adults have OSA but only 10-15% have been diagnosed to date.','First home kit for children\'s sleep apnea diagnosis','[\"Severna Park\"]','NuSomnea'),('Poor hand hygiene is the leading cause of hospital acquired infections that result in close to 100,000 deaths in the US every year. Government requirements regulate hand hygiene compliance in all 5,800 US hospitals. The current hand hygiene monitoring approach of direct observation is ineffective, carries a high labor cost and only captures 1-3% of all hand hygiene events. \n\nA 1% increase in hand hygiene can save a 200-bed hospital nearly $40,000 annually (Duke University Study). The Hyginex Solution has been proven to increase hand hygiene compliance by 20%. This is the only system that accurately captures hand hygiene events and monitors duration of wash/alcohol use on an individual basis.  \n\nHospital management can generate reports and analyze trends in compliance levels and identify areas for hand hygiene improvement by worker/department/hospital level. The system lends itself easily to gamification to regulate hand hygiene compliance by employees.\n','Hand washing & quality monitoring system to reduce hospital acquired infections','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Hyginex'),('Correlia Biosystems, Inc. develops novel microfluidic tools that are cost-efficient, rapid, and customizable. Our versatile SimpleScan technology has point-of-care applications ranging from STD diagnostics to allergen screening.\n\nInfectious Diseases:\nPain:  Patients seeking confirmatory diagnosis of infectious disease can wait days or weeks for results from slow, labor-intensive, and costly laboratory equipment.  \nSolution:  SimpleScan technology provides a platform to deliver rapid, inexpensive, and accurate point-of-care tests of co-infection (e.g. HIV/HCV), permitting doctors to make immediate and informed treatment decisions.\n\nAllergens:\nPain: Skin prick allergy tests are expensive, labor intensive and not patient friendly.  Alternative allergy blood testing requires long turnaround times.  \nSolution:  SimpleScan microfluidic technology can provide cost-efficient, user-friendly, rapid and multiplexed allergen testing at the doctor’s office.\n\n','Instant allergen and disease diagnostics','[\"Berkeley\"]','Correlia Biosystems'),('3 Million patients in the US suffer from Diastolic Heart Failure. Currently there is no specific therapy for DHF. \nDHS Medical develops a proprietary implantable medical device (IMD) that evaluates in real-time the filling pattern of the left ventricle. Based on the measured data, we can provide on-demand increasing cardiac output, which we believe would enable patients to perform greater physical tasks and avoid hospitalizations.','Increasing Cardiac Performance','[\"Haifa\"]','DHS Medical'),('Epigenetics is the heritable, long-term modification of gene activity without alterations to the DNA sequence. These modifications are caused by human development, aging, environmental exposures, and disease. In other words, a parent’s experiences can be inherited by future generations.\n \nEpisona is a digital health company evaluating how epigenetic modifications, specifically, changes in DNA methylation, are inherited and impact the very first pregnancy stages. Episona\'s first product is a panel measuring epigenetic changes on sperm DNA, which predict the likelihood of a successful pregnancy. This diagnostic test will reduce anxiety-causing unknowns and unnecessary costs to patients seeking reproductive assistance, and improve the success rates for fertility specialists.\n\nBroadly, Episona is developing a data aggregation and analytics platform to evaluate epigenetic patterns within the human genome that predict human diseases involving fertility and mental health. ','Heredity Beyond DNA','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Episona'),('Bionik Laboratories was established in 2010 as a Canadian research and development company.  It is focussed on the discovery and development of novel techniques and technologies for assistive technology in the medical field with the goal of introducing a new exoskeleton technology to the market.  Targeted diseases and injuries include complete and incomplete paraplegia, stoke, spina bifida, as well as multiple sclerosis.  \n\n','Assistive Technology for Paraplegia and Stroke','[\"Toronto\"]','Bionik Laboratories '),('MedPassage has created an Amazon-like market for implantable medical devices.  \r\n\r\nThis online market services a segment of the medical device market that MedPassage has identified values lower prices over sales support in the operating room, which is currently an industry norm.  By using MedPassage and foregoing in-person sales support, medical center members gain access to FDA approved implants at prices 40 – 60% below industry averages.\r\n\r\nThese implant savings address a major pain point for US medical centers, which are experiencing declining reimbursement rates for their surgical services.  Especially at surgery centers, where physicians are business owners and directly incentivized to lower implant costs, we are seeing rapid adoption of MedPassage.  As of June 2013, MedPassage has 6% of all US surgery centers on contract.\r\n\r\n','Medical Device E-Commerce','[\"Denver\"]','MedPassage'),('mir.I.am is a Point of care device that senses microRNA profiles from body fluids and analyze them on the cloud. this way it can screen for 50 types of cancer and in the future more deceases . \r\n \r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FbXjlm2epro','\"We aim to sneak up on cancer, before it sneaks up on us\"','[\"Mountain View\"]','mirOculus'),('BioRepeller develops catheters that resist infection over several months. The coating is an actual barrier for binding of foreign material.\r\n\r\n2M PICC lines (venous catheters) are inserted annually in the US for use in chemotherapy, blood transfusion and anti-biotic administration. 80,000 acquire serious infections in the hospital, of which 20,000 die. Today\'s technologies fail to prevent bacterial adhesion, biofilm formation and blood clooting.\r\n\r\nThe BioRepeller coating technology is developed by experienced scientists at Aarhus University, Denmark. Originally \"anti-fouling\" / \"fouling patterns\" for stem cell studies, the platform of FDA approved materials with a proprietory fabrication method is readily applied to polymers and metals.\r\n\r\nThe start-up team comprises two talented entrepreneurs and is backed by a strong advisory board of two scientific advisors and two commercial advisors. Novo Seeds granted 100k to cover testing through Q1-Q2 2014.','World\'s first anti-bacterial coating that never runs out','[\"Copenhagen\"]','BioRepeller'),('We are developing a novel in vitro diagnostic for the assessment of bleeding and clotting at the point of care. Our device is faster, clearer, and easier to use than anything on the market. We offer a compelling vision: to replace guesswork with data to treat critically ill patients. Our offering will be used in surgery, trauma, intensive care, and other clinical settings.','Replacing guesswork with data to manage bleeding and clotting','[\"Charlottesville\"]','HemoSonics'),('Dermoptics developed a UV lamp for dermatology (marketed as \"308 Lamp\" by its acquirer, Quantel).\nDermoptics developped an affordable excimer technology (alternative to expensive excimer lasers).\n','Innovative UV lamp for dermatological treatment (psoriasis, vitiligo)','[\"Paris\"]','Dermoptics'),('Medical device for the treatment of nail fungal infections, a $3 billion US market affecting over 35 million Americans.  Our device promises to have higher efficacy than the best of breed oral medications without side effects and can be done in one or two treatments in a doctor\'s office.','Revolutionizing fungal nail infection therapy','[\"Newark, CA\"]','DeviceFarm'),('The Ingen SeVIIn is the first fully-integrated shoulder replacement system and will reduce healthcare costs for hospitals, surgeons and patients.','7-in-1 Shoulder Replacement System','[\"New Jersey\"]','Ingen Orthopedics'),('The problem with existing guidance systems is that 1) learning to use ultrasound is time-consuming and difficult; 2) guidance devices are costly  and require dedicated hospital rooms; 3) guidance devices take a long time to calibrate, increasing the time the doctor spends on the procedure; 4) guidance devices require big changes to workflow and customary instruments; and 5) guidance devices cannot be used remotely by specialists.\n	The Clear Guide ONE was developed as a solution to these problems:\n•	A compact and complete ultrasound guidance system, combining a probe attachment and a portable touchscreen module (no sensors or additional components), compatible with any kind of needle, and undisturbed by surrounding ferromagnetic materials;\n•	A convenient and easy-to-use tool, calibration-free at the point of care \n•	A cost-effective device, affordable by clinics,outpatient centers and private practices.\n\n\n','Image-guided medical interventions, easier and at lower cost','[\"Baltimore\"]','Clear Guide Medical'),('Curewize Health Ltd. commercializes leading-edge technologies that can significantly improve the overall survival and health of young cancer patients. Curewize was awarded an Israeli Office of Chief Scientist grant for the commercialization of ProALL and is seeking matching funding. \n\nProALL  is a prognostic assay that can help improve ALL patients’ survival and quality of life by determining whether the patient needs a standard or intense treatment.  ProALL solves several drawbacks of MRD, which are currently used to determine ALL patients risk based treatment group. \n\nProALL results are available 2 days from diagnosis vs 1-3 months from diagnosis with MRD.\nUnlike MRD, ProALL is universal; there is no need to design the assay for each patient.\nProALL is performed in standard clinical labs; MRD is performed in a few labs with specific expertise.  ProAll has proven monitoring ability and fits well with routine practice. ProALL and MRD can be used together for even higher accuracy.','Personalizing  young cancer patients treatment','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Curewize'),('Thermablate is the \"gold standard\" for endometrial ablation.  It is a device that enables the doctor to perform the procedure in his office with local anaesthetic in two minutes.  It is the least painful and fastest way of dealing with excessive mennstrual bleeding.  We have used the device more than 35,000 times and in all cases successfully.  Reimbursement codes in the USA are in place and we are raising funds to continue the FDA trials.','best device available for a procedure to reduce excessive menstrual bleeding','[\"Toronto\"]','Idoman'),('Prostate cancer is the only cancer for which no reliable imaging modality exists for the detection of localized disease. There are over 2.3 Million men in the U.S. with prostate cancer and over 3 Million ultrasounds and biopsies performed every year. Prostate cancer results in 30,000 deaths per year in the U.S. alone – second only to lung cancer.\n\nImagistx is the World\'s only ultra-high frequency ultrasound product for the prostate. Imagistx high resolution ultrasound system allows urologists to see the exquisite details of the prostate, allowing for better diagnosis, surveillance and treatment.\n\nInitial clinical study at the John Hopkins Urology Center showed a 73% improvement in the detection of prostate cancer, a quantum leap over the current standard of care. Imagistx is now running a multi-site 960-patient clinical study that will statistically prove the superiority of\nthe system against the standard of care and drive up adoption.','World\'s only ultra-high frequency ultrasound product for the prostate.','[\"Toronto\"]','Imagistx'),('Infusion catheter brings a new treatment option to individuals battling life-threatening illnesses that can benefit from highly targeted drug delivery, such as cancer.\r\n\r\nSpecialized catheters designed to isolate a specific treatment region from blood flow.Products allow the infusion of fluids into the region and the perfusion of blood past the region to keep the blood flow intact during treatment.\r\n increase drug concentrations at targeted sites while reducing systemic exposure, thereby improving efficacy and patient outcomes. ',' Highly targeted drug delivery','[\"San Jose\"]','Vascular Designs Inc'),('Fourth Vital, Inc. has developed a simple, non-invasive, real-time method to measure and track the “elusive” fourth vital in medicine - “volume status”.  Until today, no gold standard has existed for accurately measuring volume status (the amount and ratio of fluids throughout a person’s body).  For the elderly, frail, and chronically ill, volume status turns out to be the most critical vital in predicting and preventing many serious and costly complications and hospitalizations.','Non-invasive, real-time method for tracking and measuring patient \"volume status\"','[\"San Francisco\"]','Fourth Vital'),('Prevue provides a web-based 3D printing services for doctors, who can quickly and easily create and order accurate 3D models of their own patient\'s anatomy from standard MRI and CT scans.\n\nThe Prevue interface leverages doctors\' extensive training with an interface that is familiar, fast, and easy to use. By providing seamless printing services, Prevue removes all the technical barriers to additive manufacturing and lets doctors do what they do best: care for their patients.\n','Easy 3D Printing Service for Doctors','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Prevue Medical'),('Dicom Systems also offers a 100% secure web-based DICOM and HL7 routing, transformation, and interface engine appliance for hospitals, clinics and diagnostic imaging centers. Trusted by top healthcare facilities, and providing the most effective integrated workflow in digital imaging, Dicom Systems ensure that doctors, practitioners and diagnosticians have the most reliable and most immediate access to patient data from across their Healthcare Enterprises.\n','Radiology Interface Engine, High efficiency Radiology Data exchange, Dicom and HL7 Router','[\"San Jose\"]','Dicom Systems'),('We design and manufacture solid and hollow microneedles for medical applications, which include transdermal and intradermal drug delivery, blood sampling for in-intro diagnostics and cosmetic applications.','Painless Microneedles in Plastics and Metals','[\"Singapore\"]','Micropoint Technologies '),('PlenSat is a preclinical stage biomedical device venture pursuing its patented technology for the treatment of obesity.  PlenSat ‘Digestible Balloons™” are a unique approach which may achieve the benefits of Bariatric therapy to treat obesity without invasive techniques such as surgery, laparoscopy or endoscopy. Digestible Balloons promise the simplicity of pharmaceutical dosage with the weight loss profile of Bariatric therapy.\nPlenSat’s technology involves the production of ingestible ‘pills’ that are self-inflating in the acidic environment within the stomach. The expanded capsule, a “Digestible Balloon”, is sized such that once inflated it will not pass beyond the stomach. Preclinical pilot studies in dogs have shown that the capsules do inflate to the appropriate size to remain in the stomach for an extended time. The Digestible Balloon is ultimately broken down in the stomach over time and residual material is digested in the intestine and passed. \n','Bariatric Therapy without Surgery','[\"San Clemente\"]','PlenSat'),('The Canary System is a caries detection system which is now available in the US and Canada.  It has created a new way of detecting, monitoring and communicating with patients about one of the most common oral diseases oral health providers treat – dental caries.  The Canary System not only detects caries but provides the patient and the dentist with a report that is available either in print or on-line. During the examination The Canary System voice gives the patient and provider instant feedback on the status of the tooth surface being examined.  Simple, clear concise measurements with a system that is measuring tooth structure changes means the patient can begin to understand the effects of caries and the dental team can easily educate the patient on ways to improve their oral health care and ultimately decrease their Canary Number. \n\n','Accurate detection & monitoring of tooth decay','[\"Toronto\"]','Quantum Dental Technologies '),('Portfolio Companies: http://www.misgav-venture.com/companies.asp\n\n\n','Medical Technology Incubator','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Misgav Venture Accelerator'),('BleepBleeps are little guys that help you get pregnant, give birth, look after your baby and raise your child. Each BleepBleeps character connects to the BleepBleeps app on your phone to give you simple guidance and content to make parenting easier.\r\n\r\nBleepBleeps is a new tech-parenting brand. Our aim is to build a fun, modern and trusted parenting brand relevant for the 21st Century.\r\n\r\nOur ultimate purpose is to make parenting easier. Our brand and products are for design-savvy parents (and wannabe parents). BleepsBleeps first range of products is a bunch of connected devices that sync with our smartphone app for tracking and guidance.\r\n\r\nWe are a small (but talented) multidisciplinary team that straddles innovation, branding, communications, new product development, digital, software/hardware development and user experience. We have extensive experience running creative businesses that build brands and ship world class products that consumers love.','A family of little friends that make parenting easier','[\"London\"]','BleepBleeps'),('The 3Derm System is a low cost skin monitoring solution that allows patients to take clinical quality 3D skin images from the comfort of their homes. Dermatologists can use the uploaded images to efficiently monitor high volumes of patients’ lesions while reserving in-clinic appointment times for patients whose images indicate a more alarming condition. 3Derm aims to revolutionize the field of teledermatology by providing greater access to dermatological care.','Inexpensive teledermatological home monitoring solution','[\"New Haven\"]','3Derm Systems'),('RUTLEDGE VINE CAPITAL (RVC) is a global Super Investor which provides early stage venture funding to Startup & Seed companies and Technovation research projects across the world.  To date, we have invested in technology companies in various stages of development and look to add to our portfolio by working with entrepreneurs who have innovative ideas and a need for capital to move to the next stage. RVC is the investment division of the Rutledge Global Group.\r\n\r\nRVC is driven by a high calibre team with many years spent in Senior Management positions in diverse sectors like IT, Mobile, Gaming, Digital Media, Hospitality & Real Estate, Consumer marketing, Oil & Gas and the Commodities space.\r\n\r\nRVC operates in Asia through its investment arm known as GITPx Investments which it leverages to help its investees expand into Asia or strike valuable partnerships in Asia.','ISRAEL - High Tech Investments','[\"Singapore\", \"Israel\"]','Rutledge Vine Capital'),('Contract manufacturer of wires, pin and screw components for medical devices.','Precision Grinding of Medical Device Component Wire. Contract Manufacturer.','[\"Port Washington\"]','Modern Grinding'),('A novel respiratory rehabilitation platform based on non-contact depth sensoring technology, that measure physiological information, either diagnosis of COPD or abdominal breathing exercise.\r\n','Interactive rehabilitation for Stroke, COPD','[\"Taiwan\"]','LongGood LTD'),('First Warning Systems (FWS) is an early breast cancer screening technology targeting the dense breast tissue population and improvement of mammography false positive biopsy results.  With over 650 patients completed through 3 clinical trials, and an additional 5 years of advanced predictive algorithm development out of Singapore\'s prestigious Nanyang Technical University, FWS intends to deliver an automated quantification screening system consisting of an advanced neural network predictive analytic software solution.\n\nUtilizing a wearable acquisition device, the FWS  will reduce human intervention and institutional costs, while delivering a low COG product with high margins. With a patient charge less than the average co-pay for current screening and diagnostic procedures, the FWS solution can be prescribed by the physician/healthcare worker, and used routinely and repetitively, supporting software as a solution (SaaS) economics, and scalable high-volume deployment of the product.','Non-invasive, N