]','X-Tech Group'),('Not building, but distributing and reselling of specific products.','ELISA Kits and Other R&D Products','[\"Ankara\"]','Invivo Healthcare'),('Ziptek LLC (the “Company”) is a Sarasota, FL-based medical device company that has developed what Ziptek believes to be the next generation state-of-the-art tissue repair and attachment devices. These knotless tissue repair solutions allow for rapid and easy repair in minimally invasive surgical procedures where the surgeon is working in small spaces or through small incisions using an arthroscope. The ZipE® device allows the surgeon to repair the tissue without having to tie knots in tight spaces-quick and simple. It’s like a Zip-Tie-cable wrap, with which you bind electric or electronic cables-ZipE® fast.\r\n\r\nZiptek believes these new generation, patent-protected, knotless ZipE® repair and attachment solutions allow for more surgical simplicity, efficiency, and accuracy for soft-tissue repair. These solutions also reduce operating time and eliminate human variance found with knot tying, thus removing one variable that can cause failure of repairs and should lead to better outcomes.\r\n','ZipE(R) knotless tissue repair solutions','[\"Sarasota\"]','Ziptek LLC'),('Ceramic Knee and Hip Implants. Patented Design and Material. Ceramic implants last 10x longer than the typical Metal Alloy implants commonly used in the market today. Ceramic is also 99.9% allergenic free. Roughly 14% of patients are allergic to metal alloy implants, resulting in medication for life, removal of implant, fusion of joints (peg leg), amputation, and even death. Ceramic is far superior to metal alloy in almost all medical applications.  ','7 World-Wide Patented Orthopedic Implants w/Plant and International Distribution','[\"San Francisco\"]','Ceramic Medical Devices (CMD)'),('Would you fly a plane without having the proper training? That\'s what\'s happening everyday with facial aesthetic injections. In 2012, there were 8.1M facial