ting devices; as a result, only 5 µL of blood is required to detect multiple proteins in a just a few minutes’ time.','Quick diagnosis of disease','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Protomex Life Sciences'),('The Better Walk crutch provides users with a more comfortable form of mobility when limited to crutch use. Our crutch reduces forces in the underarm that cause pain and involves more of your body\'s muscles in your motion to reduce forearm fatigue while reducing direct stress on your wrist through an ergonomic design.','Simple. Safe. Comfortable. Crutches.','[\"Atlanta\"]','Better Walk'),('We enable mobile phones to detect cancer, providing the billions of people around the world who have access to mobile phone but do not have access to a physician who can provide a life saving diagnosis. Our technology is not limited to mobile phones, too: MobileOCT can transform any digital camera into a powerful epithelial cancer discerning device. Our first focus is cervical cancer, the leading cause of cancer death for women in low resource settings - with a potential of 200M annual procedures. We will then expand the capabilities of our app to identify skin and oral cancer, among other diseases that can be imaged optically. ','Affordable diagnostics for the billions with access to a mobile phone. ','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','MobileOCT'),('Motivated by the rise of infection rates caused by sharps injuries, Sotera Instruments is designing a safety scalpel to increase activation rates. Engineered by Stanford University graduates and surgeons from the top Silicon Valley hospitals, Sotera Instruments\' is providing medical practitioners with better solutions to safety devices in the operating room. ','bringing passive to medical safety','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Sotera Instruments'),('Improving prosthetic arm technology NOW—innovatively, inexpensively, and incrementally. A soft prosthetic socket like today’s athletic shoes. We make prosthetic arms more wearable, functional, and comfortable. The most used arm device is over 100 years old, but that\'s not the worst. Half of patients don’t wear an arm at all, and 90 per cent of them cite fit and comfort as the reason. Suspension is key. The soft socket addresses that need. We share ownership shared with all Military arm amputees.','Better prosthetic arms by and for vets.','[\"Durham\"]','StumpworX'),('COPD is a chronic respiratory disease that is the third leading cause of death in the U.S. Despite current treatment options, many COPD patients cannot properly empty their lungs during activities of daily living, for example walking up the stairs. This causes the lungs to hyperinflate, which can lead to dyspnea (shortness of breath) and is the beginning of an unforgiving downward cycle that degrades quality of life, results in hospitalizations and often ends with death. \n\nLiberate’s patent-pending solution, SecondBreath, is a discreet and wearable belt that applies surface electrical stimulation to the abdominal muscles during exhalation. This causes the abdominal muscles to contract during exhalation, compressing the abdominal contents which push upward like a piston toward the lungs. This piston-like effect helps to squeeze out an extra volume of air every time the patient exhales and thereby rapidly reduces lung hyperinflation. ','Medical Device Targeting Hyperinflation','[\"Louisville\"]','Liberate Medical'),('In 2011 myself and Dr. Soffer and I developed a mobile & cloud based clinical photography tool intended for use by doctors in the US to assist them in treating vein disease.  Upon releasing our clinical photography tool for vein treatment, we quickly realized that we had in fact stumbled on to something much larger.  The software we created could very well revolutionize clinical photography industry, and thus positively impact & improve healthcare worldwide. ','Mobile / Cloud Based Clinical Photography','[\"Miami\"]','AppwoRx'),(NULL,'Telerobotic health services kiosk','[\"Chicago\"]','TeleHealthNow'),('ZumaTek’s technology eliminates painful breast compression of mammography while allowing for whole-breast and chest wall imaging, earlier detection, lower radiation dose, lower patient anxiety, and short scan time which will maintain clinical workflow. The resultant breast-only 3D CT images are well understood by radiologists. These factors could lead to an increase in participation compliance, and also provide a large gain in market share for an imaging provider in a competitive space.','Dedicated patient-friendly non-invasive breast imaging','[\"Chapel Hill\"]','ZumaTek'),('The most versatile PET Scanners (Positron Emission Tomography) in the world.  We build the smallest PET Scanners in medical imaging and research.  For the first time in the market:  1.) we can insert our PET Scanners into existing MRI devices for a dual image in both human and small animal markets, 2.) we can provide non invasive quantitative PET for humans, 3.) awake small animal neuronal imaging for research.','Miniaturized MRI Compatible PET Scanners','[\"New York City\"]','SynchroPET'),('Since 2006, Intanna is providing specialized medical devices consulting to bay area clients (start-ups, funded incubators and private funded companies). As a result of our products and services, we are proudly encourage to say, Intanna is about saving lives, mitigate or reduce suffering, relieving  pain, giving hopes to a child by controlled drug released technologies. Examples: \n1. Infusion pump \n2. Dental Tissues \n3. Capsule camera for screening your gut\n4. Orthopedic tools, sensors\n5. Other\n','Medical Devices Engineering and Consulting','[\"San Francisco\"]','Intanna Corporation'),('Currently, there is no single test to detect and predict multiple types of cancer throughout the body.  Instead, multiple different tests are used to find cancer in a variety of ways.  The diagnostic test Lazarus is developing will make checking for cancer as simple as checking cholesterol levels and may become a common part of a regular physical, leading to earlier detection, lower treatment costs and better patient outcomes.','Molecular Diagnostics to Detect Cancer','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Lazarus Bioscience'),('Looking for private equity investors for drug development, medical devices, nutraceuticals and healthcare IT technology ','Business Networking, Technology, Drug Development, Medical Devices, Healthcare','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Pharma Connections Worldwide'),('The aging population, chronic conditions, and recreational injuries all contribute to rising physical therapy costs. Move Right Health develops medical software for physical therapists allowing them to easily customize exercises for each patient. Our low-cost solution monitors patients exercising at home and provides a link between the clinic and home. Patients recover faster, and physical therapists assist more patients.','Revolutionizes physical therapy with custom patient exercises for interactive home use.','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Move Right Health'),('Medconcept is a medical supplies business in San Fernando Valley,CA. 15 minutes North of Los Angeles,CA. Medconcept sells a wide variety of incontinence products like Adult diapers,Underpads,Washcloth,Latex Gloves,Vinyl Gloves,Incontinence skin cream,Sanitary wash liquid,Wound care products,Gauze,Antiseptic wash liquid,Adult walker,Shower chair,Wheelchair,Rollator,Heating pads,Commode,Wrist & Ankle support braces.','Recession Proof Retail medical supplies/products ','[\"San Fernando, CA\"]','Medconcept'),('Zonular Capture Haptic based  Accommodative-Disaccommodative Intraocular Lens (AD-IOL) System.\n\nOur new approach, proven in animal models, has exceeded all current products on the market by producing up to 6 diopters of accommodation in a simple passive shift 1 optic IOL.','The only accommodative IOL that works','[\"Albany\"]','Zlens'),('Solving the \"Display Backplane Problem\" that is preventing next generation (OLED) displays from reaching the market.\n\nThe problem is to enable low cost manufacturing of large area electronic backplanes with Si mobility approaching that of single crystal Si. No lasers. No magic. No wafers. No materials of the future. Just Silicon.','solving intractable problems in optics and electronics.','[\"Waterloo\"]','DifTek Lasers'),('Astanza Laser is a fast-growing, profitable, and customer-focused laser manufacturer with one of the best brands in the exploding market for tattoo removal lasers.  No other company offers such an attractive pure play for investors interested in taking advantage of the trend to remove unwanted tattoos.  \r\n\r\nTattoo removal is the key indication for our laser systems, and with 36% of 18-25 years old and 40% of 26-40 years olds now possessing at least one tattoo, the market for the tattoo removal procedure already exists.  Greater efficacy, superior reliability, and training and marketing support make our lasers the choice of physicians and business owners.  \r\n\r\nAstanza Laser has a significant share of the market for tattoo removal lasers already, and with prestigious customers that serve as signals to the market of the strength and quality of the company.  A growing set of products that serve a range of price points and a growing sales team are key opportunities for growth.  ','Lasers for Tattoo Removal','[\"Houston\"]','Astanza Laser'),('Feather Sensors has developed a low-cost thin film spirometer which can be used by Pulmonologists to measure the lung function of people suffering from asthma or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).  The sensor will be coupled with the Force Oscillation Technique (FOT), which will allow individuals to measure their lung function on a daily basis in their home.  Daily home monitoring should reduce the risk of severe exacerbation, which often lead to emergency room visitation.','Helping People with Asthma Better Manage Their Disease','[\"Millville\"]','Feather Sensors'),('Advanced Suture Devices is a type of needle-free device that can close surgical or clean cut wounds without use of surgical needles.  Unlike traditional stitching and stapling that results in development of hypertrophic or keloid scars. ASD seals wound without over-stressing the skin, reducing the chance for skin deformities to develop. ASD maybe use in wider range of tension lacerations, as well as infected or contaminated wound due to its unique patented structure that permits wound drainage.\n','Scarless wound closure','[\"College Park\"]','Advanced Healing Technology'),('Surgery Theater is the world\'s first online educational surgery videos for all surgical procedures as well as a medical social media for healthcare professionals such as surgeons, doctors, nurses, medical students, surgical techs, and even patients. Surgery Theater aims to establish an online educational platforms so healthcare professionals can learn, share , and grow their medical knowledge.\nVisit http://www.surgerytheater.com for more info.','Youtube for Surgical procedures.','[\"Beverly Hills\"]','Surgery Theater'),('Sentire\'s Bowel Perforation Detection System can prevent one of the most devastating and costly risks of laparoscopic procedures, which include hysterectomy, prostatectomy, hernia repair, cholecystectomy (gall bladder removal) and many other abdominal surgeries.  \n\nThere are more than 5 million laparoscopic surgeries performed annually in the US and Europe.   \n\nThe average cost to care for a patient who has suffered a bowel perforation if not visualized at the time of the initial surgery is in excess of $100,000.  Many patients with undetected perforations require a colostomy and then reversal of the colostomy, as well as other corrective treatments/procedures and are subject to other long term risks should they survive the undetected perforation. The cost to repair a bowel perforation at the time of the injury is insignificant by comparison. In the United States the mortality rate from unobserved bowel perforation leading to sepsis exceeds 2,500 patients per year. ','Patient Safety - Prevent the most devastating risk of laparoscopic surgery','[\"New York City\"]','Sentire Medical Systems'),('Custom embedded and FPGA systems and software technology','Embedded custom hardware for financial and medical application','[\"Belgrade\"]','Technological Partnership'),('Targeted nanoparticle tumor ablation medical devices for diagnostics and therapy.  \n\nMulti-walled Carbon Nanotubes (MWCNT) are designed with internal antennae tuned to a specific Near Infrared (NIR) laser frequency, which, when activated, oscillate at high speeds, generating thermal energy (heat) sufficient to cause cell apoptosis.  Using targeting probes, the MWCNT seek out, attach to, and reside within, specific cancer cells the targeting probes are engineered to recognize.  The NIR laser is non-invasive, and does not injure the skin.  In addition to the ability to seek out and destroy cancer, the MWCNT can also be conjugated with probes for high resolution imaging for diagnostics purposes using existing MRI technology.','Targeted nanoparticle tumor ablation.','[\"Winston-salem\"]','Fortis Oncology'),('Regdy® is a web platform that enables visibility to all approved medical devices country-by-country. \n\nIt comprehensively tracks all current medical device approvals for manufacturers and serves as a platform to promote those approved products directly to users.  Approval allows marketability.  \n\nMedical Device companies can use Regdy to manage product approvals but also, market directly to doctors, hospital purchasing, and informed patients.  This results in a CNET-like platform for approved medical devices that is funded by an unbiased partnering with medical device manufacturers.  \n','Medical devices are born with an approval.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Regdy'),('BreastCare DTS™ is an easy-to-use device produced under patent which has been FDA-cleared as an adjunct to mammography and other procedures for the detection of breast disease, including breast cancer.\n\nBreastCare DTS™ has received FDA 510K clearance for marketing in the United States. Clinical studies have been conducted on over 5,000 women in prestigious cancer centers in the U.S., Europe and Latin America, including Memorial Sloan-Kettering in New York and M.D. Anderson in Houston, Texas.\n','BreastCare DTS FDA-cleared adjunct to mammography for detection breast cancer.','[]','Life Medical Technologies'),('TASSMA is a service based business model, and truly the first of its kind. We offset the cost of hiring, training, and developing a direct hire sales team for the small medical device start up sector by partnering with several small start ups and building a collaborative portfolio sold by our highly focused direct hire team.  We only sell into the largest 30 markets domestically, so our impact is huge. We are highly trained, and dedicated to accelerating our portfolio partners to their exits.','Outsourced Direct Hire Sales Channel','[\"Buffalo\"]','TASSMA'),('The ArthroTense - a novel surgical tool which enables consistent optimization of laryngoplasty (tie-back) and laryngeal repositioning (tie-foward) surgeries in equines','Laparoscopic diagnostic surgical tool','[\"Ithaca\"]','Varada Innovations'),('Rest-A-Desk is a patent-protected reclinable/supine computer workstation the use of which reduces and prevents back, neck, and shoulder pain. Rest-A-Desk uses wireless technology to interface a user\'s remote computer (e.g., desktop) to an adjustable desk equipped with a monitor/keyboard/trackball system. Rest-A-Desk safely locks into any degree of reclined or supine position that most comfortably suits the user (e.g., lying in bed or reclined in a lounge-type chair).','Patented, unique reclinable/supine computer workstation.','[\"Colorado Springs\"]','Rest-A-Desk'),('LabCloud is dedicated to the implementation of laboratory software designed to bring out the full capabilities of Research and Development organizations by providing them with an integrated cloud or server based system to effectively manage their data, inventory and R&D Pipeline.\n\nFounded in 2013, LabCloud Inc. was incorporated on the basis of creating a browser based Integrated Laboratory Management Software that accelerates the process of research and development by automating reporting, analytics, and experimental parameter selection, allowing researchers to make better-informed decisions in their research, while effectively managing their inventory and logistics, allowing for streamlining of the R&D Process.\n\nUsually, similar systems that meet the strict compliance requirements are out of the reach of customers based on integration and initial software costs. LabCloud has made that platform that is powerful and affordable for an under-served market, both in the US and abroad.','Better and Accessible Laboratory Software','[\"Boston\"]','LabCloud Inc.'),('Timesulin is a timer enabled replacement caps, for insulin pens that people with diabetes already use, that helps the user avoid dangerous double doses. The product was launched in January 2012 and is now available in app 40 countries through big Pharma partnerships, partnerships with diabetes associations, and with a mix of carefully selected medical device distributors. Timesulin was created in 2011 to address the needs of co-founder and CEO, John Sjölund, who has been living with Type 1 diabetes since he was three years old. John wanted a simple solution that would confirm the time since he last took an insulin shot and help avoid an accidental missed or double dose of insulin. After searching high and low for a solution that would allow him to maintain his current insulin treatment program John and his brother Andreas (co-creator of Skype) decided to create a solution that would make life for him – and all other people living with diabetes – just a little bit easier.','Replacement cap for growing insulin pen market to make life easier with diabetes','[\"London\"]','Timesulin'),('Guardicine solves a major gap in stroke treatment in which time is brain & life. In fact, there are treatments if acted early. The first line drug, tPA, can reverse the damage & reduce disability & mortality for most strokes. However, it must be injected to the patient within 4.5 hrs. Unfortunately, >90% of patients are late for the drug due to sleep or misjudgment. Other treatment also has similar time limit. Guardicine\'s proprietary device can auto detect the start of a stroke and alert the patient to a hospital in time for critical early treatment.\n\nCurrently there are 6.6 (80) million of stroke survivors in US (world), plus additional 0.78M (15) of strokes in US (world) each year. Stroke is a highly recurring disease. Our initial target is those highly motivated patients with stroke history and in great risk and fear of another stroke. The market size just for the group is about $1 billion in US and $10B in the world according to survey. No similar product on market now.\n','A Continuously Wearable Stroke Alarm ','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Guardicine'),('Vutilix is a medical imaging platform that puts \"you\" in control.  Patients can store their images here and find additional readers to get second and third opinions.\n\nVutilix also supports physicians who read images, with just a browser, including mobile devices.\n\nA high degree of connectivity is supported.  Imaging devices can transmit images directly to Vutilix. Imaging providers (radiologists, cardiologists, etc) can transfer scans from their PACS.\n\nVutilix also eases the pane of bringing new medical imaging innovation to market.  It provides APIs to developers so they can access images without having to build acquisition software (DICOM).  It also provides a marketplace so that readers (radiologists, etc) may try out new imaging tools easily and use them on a software-as-a-service (SaaS) basis.\n\n','Medical Imaging for Everyone','[]','Vutilix'),('SpectraSafe scans a body or package or container with harmless microwave radiation creating spectral profiles of the molecular materials within. This can create imaging scans or simply identify specific materials contained in the scan without having to profile body surfaces. The first obvious application is TSA Homeland Security for airports, subways, trains, stadia, ships, etc.. Materials handling and sorting in industry, environmental, drug testing, and medical applications are major markets.','Molecular Screening Solution for TSA','[\"San Jose\"]','RHT SpectraSafe'),('The EPCC is a portable, ruggedized electrosurgical device that represents a functional enhancement over proven  RF medical technology, such as the Bovie and Plasma Blade.    EPCC offers surgeons and medical technicians the ability to bloodlessly cut, cauterize(no charring), and ablate biological tissue in wet/dry environments without external grounding pad limitations eliminating the risk of patient burns/shock.  Advantages are portability, precision control, safety, cutting bone/cartilage.','Portable Ruggedized Electrosurgical Cauterizer Cutter','[\"Houston\"]','Laverne Douglas Technologies'),('We have developed a miniature auto-injection device for people that suffer from anaphylaxis: The Anadote.\n\nThe Anadote is small enough to fit comfortably in a pocket or on a keychain so that it is always accessible when needed.\n\nThe current devices on the market are large, bulky and difficult to carry for the average user.  We have created a device that is capable of injecting a larger amount of epinephrine than the current market standards in a more efficient way.\n\nWe believe that our device has the potential to alter the way that the current auto-injector market operates.  It is no longer necessary to sell consumers a bulky product that they are likely to leave at home.  A product that is convenient to carry, The Anadote, will soon be available to consumers worldwide.  \n\n','Miniature Auto-Injection Device','[\"Saskatoon\"]','Anadote Designs'),('Stroke is the #1 cause of disability and a leading cause of death. Delays in intervention put 73% of patients with ischemic stroke out of the “golden window” for drug intervention. Ischiban has developed a platform that can quickly and accurately position sensors on a patient’s head and prep them for use.  This active/passive device will be capable of performing stroke diagnosis and differentiation in the field. We will save lives by moving the point of diagnosis and care for victims of stroke.','Moving the point of care in stroke diagnosis/differentiation','[\"Cincinnati\"]','Ischiban Neural Engineering Systems'),('Hologic develops many software products for the visualization and analysis of medical images of the breast.  Image analytics products perform computer-aided detection of lesions and compute breast density of mammography images. Visualization and workflow products include: workstation software used by radiologists to view digital images, specialized MRI image analysis, and products to store and optimize the flow of medical images within a practice.','Women\'s Healthcare Leader','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','Hologic'),('FEELIGREEN develops micro-current based devices for the treatment of skin defects.\r\n\r\nOur first product, the FEELIGOLD anti-wrinkle eye patch, allows for significant wrinkle reduction in a natural, safe and effective way.\r\nDisposable and easy to use, the FEELIGOLD eye patch can be used by professionals for cabin usage, or marketed to the general public for at-home skin care.\r\n\r\nPartnering with leading cosmetics and pharmaceutical laboratories, FEELIGREEN is developing innovative devices to improve the ease of use and security of drug delivery methods.\r\n\r\nWith 5 patents in filing, FEELIGREEN is an innovation-driven startup targeting the dermo-cosmetic and dermo-medical segments of the medical devices market.','micro-current devices for dermo-cosmetics and dermo-pharma applications','[\"Nice\"]','FEELIGREEN'),('A patent pending medical device that avoids a step existing subintimal angioplasty (SIA) devices require that often fails. SIA devices create a channel between the intimal and medial layers of artery wall that bypasses occlusions in chronic totally occluded (CTO) arteries. CTOs constitute 1/3rd of 2 million occlusions treated each year and CTOs can\'t be entered by normal angioplasty balloons.  Existing SIA devices must first find the artery lumen then pierce the intimal layer with a hollow needle before a guidewire is advanced through the needle to re-enter artery lumen. A balloon is advanced on guidewire and inflated to push aside the occlusion. They fail to find the lumen so often that they have captured less than 10% of 700,000 potential cases. Our SIA device avoids the problem by having a stylet wire inside the guidewire allowing the balloon to be inflated first. This aligns axes of device and lumen so stylet wire pierces the intimal layer straight ahead where lumen is located.    ','Medical Device for $1B Niche','[\"North Miami\"]','Coronary Bypass Devices LLC'),('EasyG can accurately detect the heart’s electrical fields through the application of either non-contact or contact sensors. Non-contact sensors can be attached to a patient’s clothing, saving time and preserving patient modesty. The non-contact electrodes alleviate problems associated with allergies to adhesives, burns to the skin, or excessive body hair that typically complicate the use of contact electrodes. Our dual purpose device also allows use of the contact sensors if a patient requires CPR, needs a chest tube, or is simply not wearing a shirt. Using contact sensors, it can be attached to standard sticky electrodes without the hindrance of bulky wires. Both the contact and non-contact sensors of the EasyG system can accurately acquire the electrical field of the heart’s muscle activity to identify early signs of cardiac complication. Obtained ECG data can be viewed on the device’s display or transmitted wirelessly to a remote location for assessment.','Non-contact ECG sensor for instant, cardiac diagnosis - saving time, saving lives.','[\"Beverly Hills, MI\"]','EasyG '),('Biocentric Developments has developed a revolutionary device that creates a low-humidity environment localized around the eye. With a standardized climate around the eye, researchers and clinicians alike will be able to gather quantitative data consistently. The current industry leader relies on the construction of climate-controlled testing facilities available in only limited locations and costing millions of dollars. In contrast, our goggles will cost less than a fraction of the price and their small size will allow for their incorporation into nearly any ophthalmic research lab or clinic in the world. \n\nThe widespread availability of our goggles will streamline the development of dry eye treatments, increasing the quality of patient lives in both the home and work environments. \n\nOur goggles were developed with support from the Cullen Eye Institute at Baylor College of Medicine in Houston, Texas as well as the Oshman Engineering Design Kitchen at Rice University.','Medical Device for Dry Eye Research','[\"Austin\"]','Biocentric Developments'),('Ten million people in the U.S. have brain aneurysms. If the aneurysm is critical, because it has burst, or it may burst, it is treated surgically with either an aneurysm clip or an aneurysm coil.  Both of these devices are made of metal and obscure any post-operative MRI or CT imaging of the brain. We have invented a nonmetal aneurysm clip that does not affect imaging, thus enabling accurate, noninvasive evaluation of patients with one or more clipped aneurysms.','Aneurysm clipping without artifact','[\"Durham\"]','CranioVation'),(NULL,'Manufacturer of affordable & commercially viable MGB2 superconducting wires.','[\"Cambridge, UK\"]','Epoch Wires Inc.'),('The Company’s technology is centered in the area of immunoassay diagnostics where it offers a variety of immunochromatographic diagnostic devices designed to detect numerous human conditions. The Company’s R&D history has been in one-step qualitative (yes/no results) sandwich dye conjugate immunochromatographic assay, where unique combinations of monoclonal and polyclonal antibodies selectively identify the health condition being analyzed\nwith a very high degree of sensitivity.','For Point of Care Answers','[\"San Diego\"]','True Diagnostics'),('We\'ve completed Phase I Prototyping on a patent pending technology and are working with the Director of a major MIT lab to finalize proof of concept.  The product, which will allow people to communicate via touch wirelessly, is a market-disruptive technology that will serve several industry sectors - education, medical devices, gaming, mobile telephony and more, giving the company sustainability through its product\'s varied applications.  Research confirms that we have a large market in males and females aged 18-44, as well as Boomers, who will drive the medical industry in the near future.  We urgently seek financing to ensure that we are first to market!','Virtual, interactive touch - send your friends a real poke in FaceBook!','[\"New York\"]','PiezoTouch'),('V-Core is a wearable, scalable, sensor unit that harvest, in real-time, bio-med data [ECG(no less than 500 samples per second), temperature, and motion/force] from athletes in fitnees centers, practice, or competition, while also providing the information back to one central receive location such as the training facility or field house for historical record keeping.  V-Core separates itself from all other devices due to our scalability: the capability to monitor in real-time 1 to 1000 users ','We have developed a tool to detect the undetectable.','[\"Towson\"]','NeWo Technologies'),('MedPac Systems is a medical imaging company creating web based PACS, Teleradiology electronic medical records and Radiology workstations. Web Based PACS enables Hospitals and Imaging Centers to store, review and distribute Radiology Images like CT digital Xray MRI nuclear medicine and other images.Teleradiology enables radiologists to read and report from any part of the world. Electronic medical records enable hospitals and practitioners to keep records of medical records of the patients.\n','PACS and Teleradiology Making Hospitals Film Less','[\"Bangalore\"]','MedPac Systems'),('Growth strategies for early revenue and mid-sized companies.','We help clients Grow More, Predictably!','[\"Chicago\"]','Evergreen Growth Advisors'),('The Nuance Designs auto injector, Fusion, is poised to change the $1B self injection device market.  The Fusion auto injector provides better safety, reliability and convenience to patients who must inject themselves with medications at home.  This new approach improves on the major drawbacks of the other devices currently available.  \n\nFusion is smaller, smoother and smarter than current auto injection technology which makes it more convenient and less intimidating to patents of all kinds.  \n\nAfter over 15 years designing the most successful self injection devices for other firms, the principles of Nuance Designs recognized the need for new innovation. Multiple patents (already applied) will result from this approach and customer reaction so far  has been great - \"That\'s brilliant. We\'ve never seen anything like that before!.\"','Next generation self injection devices','[\"Livingston, NJ\"]','Nuance Designs'),('Physicians, like everyone else, want to use SMS to pass information easily between themselves.  The problem is SMS is not a HIPAA compliant method of passing patient information.   Mednyma will provide a secure, easy to use method for this quick correspondence.   \n\nAdditionally, the secure messaging engine could be used by other groups that need to securely pass SMS information.  Government departments are struggling with individuals using text messaging to communicate.  Current SMS systems are not encrypted, and not archivable.','Provide a easy, secure SMS system for Physicians','[\"Reno\", \"Baton Rouge\", \"Truckee\"]','Mednyma'),('For cancer patients and pharmaceutical companies worldwide who annually spend over 10 billion dollars on biomarker discovery and diagnostics, Apollo’s multivariate highly sensitive and specific non-invasive cancer signatures would predict clinical performance in diagnostics, as well as prognosis of disease progression, patient’s response to treatment options and the outcomes of the proposed therapy.','Non-invasive multivariate cancer biomarkers and signatures for early disease detection','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Apollo Diagnostics'),('The SensiMAT for Wheelchairs is the first and only mobile medical application that help users track, relieve, and analyze pressure and pressure trends. The SensiMAT for Wheelchairs is a thin mat containing pressure sensors that is inserted underneath your gel, air, or foam cushion. These sensors send pressure data to a mobile device, where SensiMAT Systems’ proprietary PressureRisk™ algorithm alerts the user when they have a high amount of built up pressure, and facilitates and tracks pressure relieving exercises. The SensiMAT can be thought of as an analog to many consumer-based “Quantified Self” devices (like Fitbit, Nike Fuel Band, BodyMedia, Jawbone UP, etc.) with the main measurable objective being that of seat pressure and user activity, providing SensiMAT with a “Quantified Seat”. ','\"Quantified Seat\" mHealth Bed Sore Prevention','[\"Toronto\"]','SensiMAT Systems'),('The Fast-Med Franchise — how health care will be delivered in the future — Think McScripps, simple, specialized, convenient, inexpensive, safe, minimally regulated and personal.\n\nFirst the CoolToes™ Franchise\n\nThree step treatment corrects 98% of nail diseases. Aesthetition-class treatment with remote expert diagnosis where necessary. \nStep 1 - nails transparent first visit (20min.)!!!\nStep 2 - fungus killed in 5 days!!!\nStep 3 - nail attachment accelerated!!!\nDelivering doctors presently averaging $1000/patient.\n25 patents in process\n','Luxury nail medispa - cures nail diseases','[\"San Diego\", \"Southern California\"]','Dhart Development'),('Provide BIMO Quality Assurance & Regulatory consulting for CROs, IRBs, Drug, and Device companies conducting IND,NDA, 510K, IDE, PMA clinical trials. Conduct mock FDA GCP clinical site audits, vendor qualification, data-management systems audits and medical device QSIT audits (including aseptic processing). 21 CFR Part 11 compliance of your IT system and equipment validation review (Biologics, Biotechnology, Drugs, & Devices). Mock FDA audits of API & sterile biotechnology/ pharmaceutical cGMP.','Quality Assurance & Regulatory consulting for CROs, IRBs, device and drug companies ','[\"Austin\"]','TradeStone QA');
INSERT INTO `startups_health_longinfo` VALUES ('A portable device and several biochemical products that can be used in many different field applications related to environmental safety and health, such clinical, food/beverage processing, water monitoring, dairy farm, etc.','Biotechnology for environmental/food/water safety','[\"Fremont\"]','W2 Optronics'),('WebMedicPro delivers AmbuPad™ - a complete mobile electronic Patientcare Reporting (ePCR) for the EMS industry.  Powered by private cellular network,  AmbuPad™ communicates and transmits data securely (and encrypted) over Private Network.\n\nWebMedicPro\'s is not a software company!  AmbuPad™ is a mobile medical device that helps Medics and Paramedics to accurately document and securely transmit patient data over private cellualr network.  It is the first and the ONLY HIPAA/ePHI complaint ePCR device for the EMS industry.\n\nOur mission is to use our extensive IT experience to deliver tangible business results enabling our clients in the EMS industry to become more productive, gain efficiency and to profit from the advanced use of mobile technology.\n\nOur client\'s testimonials can speak about who we are and what we do for this industry!\nhttp://www.webmedicpro.com/testimonials/index.html . \n','all-in-one ruggedized ePCR medical device','[\"Woburn\"]','WebMedicPro Corp.'),('SyMPL Technology, Inc. has a working prototype of a handheld biometric collection device for in-field identification of unknown persons for military, customs, border patrol, homeland security and public safety personnel.  The PocketPAD allows the user to capture biometric fingerprint, facial and iris scans and compare them to an internal database as well as the federal ABIS, IDENT and IAFIS databases over wireless communications.  ','Handheld biometric identification device','[\"The Woodlands\"]','SyMPL Technology'),('Ultradian has developed a pain-free and accurate continuous glucose monitor (CGM) for people with diabetes who require insulin to control their blood glucose levels. The device attaches to the skin and measures glucose within the interstitial fluid, just below the skin surface. Our CGM provides a continuous read-out of glucose levels on a hand-held monitor with built-in alarms for impending high and low glucose levels. ','continuous glucose monitor for diabetes','[\"Albany\"]','Ultradian Diagnostics'),('The product is related to Hearing Aid field. Our product uses Bone conduction technology (transmitting of sound through the skull by way of vibrations). Veryvoice designs a new hearing aid product that is totally implanted under the skin and operates without batteries.','Totally Implantable Bone-Conduction Hearing Aid (TIBHA)','[\"Israel\"]','Veryvoice'),('UV-Aid\'s patent pending technology helps prevent the common cold,  flu, and ear infections safely and effectively in the ear, nose, and oral passages where infections typically start. UV-Aid is a hand held device that is portable, easy to use, and only takes seconds to apply. UV-Aid uses 380nm light that is totally safe on skin cells. UV-Aid has been test marketed for 12 months resulting in 100% customer satisfaction, no complaints, zero returns and now has over 4500 facebook fans.\n','Personal Care Device','[\"Fort Myers\", \"Rochester\"]','UV Technologies'),('Envisioiner’s initial product suite – the endogo® and endogo® HD platforms - were designed to facilitate the capturing, sharing and storing of endoscopic multimedia any time, anywhere.  The introduction of eGo Works and eGo Manager were designed to network the endoscopic data from the examination automatically into a health record. Interoperability allows physician to quickly send endoscopic exams to a specialist in real time for their interpretation, thereby moving data rather than patients. \n\n','Mobile endoscopy wirelessly displayed on an IPad','[\"North Atlanta\"]','Envisionier'),('CRC Biomedical Services provides a comprehensive list of services on a wide variety of medical devices, specializing in medical lasers. We cater to purchasers of used medical devices, primarily medical spas, dermatologists, and clinics, or anybody who may own equipment that has come off manufacturer warranty. Our goal is to help our customers manage their service expenses by elevating the quality of service we deliver, and ensuring patient safety. ','Better device service and sales','[\"Alexandria, VA\"]','CRC Biomedical Services'),('Our first product, currently under development, is the EpiVoltTM biogenerator. It is an implantable electric generator designed to power implanted medical devices. It is unique among energy power sources either on the market or in development.','Biological batteries for lasting medical implants','[\"Boston\"]','Biotricity Biomedical'),('Early-stage development novel therapy for the 20B US$ market of prevention of cardiovascular diseases.  First-in-space patent on a small molecule with unique mechanism of action.','Accelerate success for life science endeavors','[\"Barcelona\"]','LifeScience Entrepreneurs S.L.'),('Breakthrough non-invasive medical device that measures/monitors intracranial pressure in real time using ultrasound tissue resonance analysis. Determines quantitative evaluation of traumatic brain injury, cerebral hemorrhage, stroke, midline shift. Customers of device are hospitals (surgical, ICU\'s, emergency rooms), ambulances, military field operations, contact sports organizations. Device is in FDA approved clinical trials At Columbia U Medical Ctr. First prouct of platform technology','Noninvasive device measuring/monitoring intracranial pressure                 ','[\"United States\"]','Non-Invasive Medical Systems'),('HemaMax™ is a novel recombinant human interleukin-12 for the treatment of Hematopoietic Syndrome of Acute Radiation Sickness and Chemotherapy Induced Thrombocytopenia. \n\nGlufosfamide is a third-generation alkylating agent designed for greater specificity and tumor uptake, with reduced systemic toxicities and side effects in second line pancreatic cancer.  \n\nRRX-101 is a first-in-class novel mechanism with synergistic anti-inflammatory and anti-angiogenic activity in AMD. ','Life Sciences Investment Banker ','[\"Chicago\"]','S. Jordan Associates'),('DTT’s product, ditto™, reduces children’s pain and improves healing time.\nWhen undergoing a medical or dental procedure with ditto™: \n        Stress scores were reduced by 70 %. \n	Reduces treatment times by 20%.\n        Clinics productivity improved by 27% \nditto™ technology combines hardware and software (no drugs) to create an interactive experience. The child is given a ditto™ before and during medical procedures, distracting them from stress and anxiety while educating them  \n','Pediatric healthcare device that reduces costs by lowering stress and treatment times.  ','[\"New York City\"]','Diversionary Therapy Technology'),('Through conferences and symposia, webinars, and our onine repository, we stimulate interactions that can lead to innovations across industry/academy silos.\r\n\r\nD2D: Data to Drugs and Diagnostics is our upcoming (November 2013) symposium and exhibition. With presentations from major pharma and biotech innovators, roundtables, and poster sessions, we bring together researchers and developers to build connections and community across multiple silos.','Connecting researchers, developers, and suppliers: drugs, diagnostics, and delivery','[\"Red Bank, NJ\"]','BioPharma Research Council'),('Automatic Interior & Semi Exterior Pocket Doors, single and converging acting\n The introduction of the automated pocket door represents a \nmonumental achievement in an industry that has stagnated with complacency. \nWe have created a modern innovation for market segments that will \nrevolutionize how the consumer uses an essential component in the way \nEVERYONE lives and works. APDI. will turn the overlooked into become a necessity in medical offices, and provide ease of access \nto the disabled. \n','Automatic Interior Pocket Doors','[\"Naples, FL\"]','AUTOMOTION POCKET DOORS '),('Elfi-Tech\'s mDLS sensor is focused on providing new parameters to the world of patient monitoring and wearable tech. Beyond measuring only pulse and motion, Elfi-Tech is now capable of measuring numerous parameters simultaneously and non-invasively through its patented optical sensing technology. \n\nThe flagship smart watch product will be showcased at the upcoming Health 2.0 conference 2013 as part of the Nokia Sensing X Challenge.\n\nOur innovative Elfi mDLS™ device non-invasively measures skin blood flow, blood velocity, coagulation, vascular health and relative cardiac output (RCO) in addition to already existing parameters like pulse and motion.\n\n','Innovation in Non-Invasive Physiological Measurement','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Elfi-Tech'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','spqs eyewear'),('We deliver strategic insights that help clients understand how to create continuing innovation as a basis for growth and competitive advantage. Clients range from early stage to F500 companies in B2B publishing, information services and medical technology.\n','We help companies develop and embed innovation thrughout their organizations','[\"New York City\"]','The Calyx Group'),('Cardioptimus LLC has developed the Embolisher. This patent-pending embolic deflection device, when deployed within the aortic arch, deflects emboli down the descending aorta to prevent neurological dysfunctions such as stroke. The Embolisher is introduced into the aortic arch via transfemoral catheterization at the beginning of the procedure and remains completely detached from the outside environment for the operation’s duration. Once complete, the implant is retrieved via a novel catheter developed specifically for minimizing operator time and effort.\r\nThe Embolisher safely conforms to the aortic arch while maintaining a superior seal within the aorta, yet has minimal interfacial contact, which reduces the risk of irritation. While in place, additional catheters – such as those carrying valve implants – are able to pass through the device. Ease of deployment and retrieval with radioscopic imaging and additional patent-pending technologies ensures convenient and effective use. ','Embolic Protection device for use with the TAVR procedure','[\"Columbia, MO\"]','Cardioptimus'),('We have developed a digital, behind-the-ear hearing aid that is\ncontrolled by the MyWay app on a Smartphone. Users are able to adjust their hearing aid profiles using an intuitive interface and to save them on their smart phone. \n\nOur technology eleminates the audiology channel and its high costs.  We\'ve partnered with the current Walmart hearing aid OEM to sell on walmart.com.  ','Digital Hearing Aid controlled by smartphone app','[\"Austin\"]','Audiotoniq'),('We believe you don\'t have to be a doctor to know if your heart is at risk.\r\nAn accurate diagnosis is the first step to preventing heart disease. CardioWise\'s non-invasive Cardiac Magnetic Resonance Imaging (cMRI) analysis software produces an easy-to-understand 3D image model of the human heart. Blue means healthy. Yellow is a warning sign. And red means your heart is at risk. \r\n \r\nThis heart analysis software combined with cardiac MRI has the opportunity to become the single most effective way for patients to recieve an accuarate and early diagnosis. ','Your heart at your fingertips','[\"Fayetteville, AR\"]','CardioWise'),('SMP will produce a full-line advanced wound care, ostomy, and incontinence products.  In the next five years, SMP will grow in three phases.  In years one and two, SMP will produce a private label manufacturer of ostomy and wound care products, which will fund our future growth.  In years two and three, we will bring patent pending wound care products and co-developed products to market.  In years three and four, we will commercialize our blockbuster products currently in development.','Advanced Wound Care Platform','[\"Sarasota\"]','Sarasota Medical Products'),(' “A Novel Formulation for Fertility Enhancement and Increasing Take-Home Baby Rate.”   \nFertiProt bases its innovative technology on evolutionary, chemical and biological properties of the fertility process and by enhancing both male and female potency through a non invasive technology for enhancing sperm properties and potential for fertilization using addition of formulated proteins. The unique formulation and technology will reduce the need for invasive and hormonal based treatments. ','Enhancing Fertility with Proteins','[\"Jerusalem\"]','FertiProt'),('There are hundreds of at-home exercise products designed to train the abs but the BODY-ALINE is the first exercise machine that goes the opposite direction to strengthen the back & realign postural muscles. \n\nPoor posture is the proven root cause of most chronic back pain. The BODY-ALINE treats root cause by strengthening the back & correcting poor posture from a seated position in mins/day with one easy motion.\n\nIt\'s been prescribed by MDs & purchased by 80+ medical professionals thus far. \n\n','BODY-ALINE: The World\'s First Back & Posture Exercise Machine!  USA Patent: #7,086,992','[\"Carpentersville\"]','Beyond the Curve'),('Non-intrusive Electronic Device kills all bacteria and viruses that causes STDs in human blood and tissue','Electronic Device kills bacteria and viruses','[\"Cheltenham\"]','Science Lab'),('Interoperability between interconnecting devices from different manufacturers. Compatible with any syringe size with luer-lock mount. It will fill the void of safety needles in veternary medicine.\n\nNo residual volume, reducing the transmission of HIV, and hepatitis B and C. Eliminates inaccurate dosing, and yields sizeable savings in the efficiency of medication delivery. (Production model will assure zero dead space inside the needle and syringe.)\n\nOffering health care providers worldwide new cost-reduction opportunities with a profoundly cost-effective design being composed of 4 inexpensive parts.\n\nFunctions just like a standard needle with one-hand activation and no separate movement required to deploy the needle tip. Distinctively minimizes air bubble and less medication waste.\n\nFacilitates exquisitely simple safe disposal (no recapping required) which significantly reduces packaging costs through elimination of a solid needle cap.\n\nFor more info see: http://stingershield.com','Intuitively protect everyone from infectious disease transmission with our safety needle.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','StingerSHIELD'),('Osteoporosis is becoming the epidemic in elderly people.\nFixation screws are failing to acquire the bone as the bones in elderly people are OSTEOPOROTIC meaning poor quality bones.\nOGEN developed ZIF Anchor, a bone implantable fixation device that cleaves the bone to the plate by using an own patented technology.\nThe device is implanted and, if needed, retracted at ZERO Insertion Force or Torque.\nThe bone interface is a set of wings that lean on the outer cortex, rather than threads.\n','Bone fixation Anchor','[\"Even Yehuda\"]','OGEN Medical.'),('Dr. Serge Afeli, a native of the Ivory Coast, has a PhD degree in pharmaceutical sciences and is also a certified global business professional. His company\'s mission is to address the unmet need for the consistent delivery of healthcare services in Africa through the distribution of critical U.S. made medical products that are vital in reducing mortality and morbidity associated with chronic disease states in Africa.\nOur customers are African government agencies and NGOs, Retail pharmacies, Community hospitals, and Patients. The company aims to develop a market for U.S. pharmaceutical companies in Africa which has more than 1.1 billion people. \nWe are planning the construction of a 50,000 sq. ft. distribution center which will be exclusively dedicated to exporting U.S. healthcare products throughout Africa.\nAlthough, there are more than 1552 pharmaceutical companies registered in the U.S. the total pharmaceutical export toward Africa remains low.','Address the unmet need for healthcare services in Africa','[\"Columbia\"]','AFELI Pharmaceuticals'),('Seeking investor support for R&D process which should return an object back to pure energy state.\n\nProcess can be used for mining (mineral extraction), removal of foreign mater from the body (medical), improved data transportation, increased data storage, energy storage and more.\n\nFunding to be used for facility, equipment, labor and testing.','R&D - Pure Energy','[\"Las Vegas\"]','Mountain Mining'),(NULL,'','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Medical Device Entrepreneurship Association at Drexel University'),(' Product/Services\n\nThe FDA cleared swallowable screening device is comprised of a medical grade foam ball is compressed into a swallowable capsule which is deployed and withdrawn orally within 5 minutes. Since this device is spherical in shape and will be harvesting cellular samples from the entire length of the esophagus, the resulting specimen has a higher likelihood of capturing the diseased indicator cells than conventional, single site, pinch biopsies.\n\n Customer problem\n\nWith the recent developments in Genome Sequencing, several corporations and medical institutions have developed Biomarker Test Kits to detect diseases of the esophagus without requiring the use of invasive and uncomfortable endoscopic techniques. The problem is that these Biomarker and H-pylori quick test companies do not have efficient non-endoscopic (non-invasive) methods of obtaining cellular specimens from patents.\n\n','FDA Cleared! Non-Endoscopic cellular collection Device for Barretts Esophagus & H-Pylori.','[\"Philadelphia\"]','CapNostics, LLC'),('The ResQTraQ is a real-time GPS tracking system used by emergency and disaster responders.   The system requires no existing infrastructure, has a limitless geographic envelope, uses no subscription services, and is all sealed up in an IP67 rated casing.   Incident commanders can watch the geographic locations of their personnel in real time across all computing platforms.   The software side supports topographic maps, weather radar overlays, discovered hazards/clues/etc, and offline mapping functions.   The target market is anyone who responds to emergencies, disasters, or large events - fire depts, EMS, rescue squads, humanitarian groups, police, security, rangers, forestry, utilities, etc.\n\nRecent events have underscored the need for this product.   The 19 members of the Granite Mountain HotShot crew that died 6/30/2013 and the death of Token Adams in late August 2013 could have potentially been avoided if the ResQTraQ had been issued to the firefighters. ','Electronic personnel accountability for emergency and disaster response','[\"Kingsport\"]','ResQTronics'),('The device is currently \"patent pending\" and intended to artificially maintain lymphatic circulation when one does not move.  Applications include every hospital bed, nursing homes, the elderly, or anyone seeking to maintain lymphatic circulation throughout the day.','Maintaining Lymphtic Circulation Synthetically','[\"Chicago\"]','Lymphatic System Mover'),('Circa Ventures works with leading organizations by deliverying unparalleled value and insights into the latest technologies, services, products, and strategies. Our global reach and array of consultative services bridges businesses of all stages resulting in innovation, new growth platforms, and competitive advantage.\n\n','\"go-to\" venture firm for entrepreneurs at the earliest stages of idea generation, ','[\"Houston\"]','Circa Ventures'),('InnerSpace Neuro has created the next generation brain monitoring sensor, AirPulse Intracranial Pressure (ICP) and access for multimodal monitoring.  \n\nAirPulse ICP:\n1. Eliminates ~$30k capital box required per bed\n2. Can be re-zeroed in situ\n3. MRI compatible\n4. Can drain the ventricle and measure ICP simultaneously\n\nMultimodal Monitoring:\n1. Integrates multiple functions through one hole in the skull\n2. Provides access for ventricular drainage, ICP monitoring and two brain probes\n\nOur customers are Neurosurgeons, Neurointensivists, PA\'s, Nurse Managers and Clinical Nurse Educators.\n','Revolutionizing brain pressure sensing','[\"Tustin\"]','InnerSpace Neuro'),('There are over 41 Million individuals in the US alone over the age of 65 years old, 10,000 are reaching retirement age each day.  This segment of the populaton desires to remain in their home for as long as possible.  \nCarla the companion, is an affordable mobile robotic companion that can assist the elderly with limitations due to: cognitive disorders (memory loss), limited mobility through use of its robotic arms and tele-health for caregivers to check in.  \n\nIt also provides features for safety and security for those elderly who live alone and are preyed on.  It can navigate the household as the senior needs it in other rooms, it is there on commmand-ready to assist.\n\nIt is friendly, easy to use and most importantly designed with the seniors needs in mind.It represents a cost saving to the user of 45% versus in home hired caregivers.','An affordable robotic companion designed to assist the elderly .','[\"Fairfax\"]','INF Robotics Inc.'),('Cryo-Therm precisely manages cryo and heat therapy used for treatment of post-operative patients and acute sports and other injuries.  Unlike any competitive devices including standard ice, Cryo-Therm provides the medical professional complete control of temperature (heat, cold, and contrast treatment), pressure, and treatment duration.  Cryo-Therm also provides a complete record of patient compliance.  Controled treatment with compliance history is a game changer for medical professionals.','Electronic ice: Cryo Therapeutic Device for treating accute sports injury or post surgery','[\"North Chicago\"]','Zenith Technical Innovations'),('Back pain affects 80% of Americans. Many times the only option to relieve pain is spinal surgery. There are no unproblematic options to monitor post-op progress. The gold standard is to take x-rays of each spinal movement, which cause a 50% increase in allowable radiation exposed to the annual 600,000 spinal surgeries. The non-invasive device measures angular rotation of spinal range of motion by 3 battery powered sensors, yields immediate results and can reduce evaluation costs by $5B/year. ','Measuring Spinal Motion in 3-Dimensions','[\"Cranford\"]','Versor Incorporated'),('Role Models Medical offers a range of services for distributors, start-ups and large corporations.  Our extensive network of client contacts allows us to quickly introduce innovative therapies and systems into the healthcare market and we work closely with industry contacts, clinical and surgical specialists to develop strategies for rapid and sustained success...','Healthcare Sales & Marketing Consultancy','[\"London\"]','Role Models Medical'),('Chemical detection by way of molecular imprint in the form of a Swab and Patch, to detect the presence of bacteria or explosive chemicals on a surface, staph infection on a worker/patient, or the presence of alcohol or drugs in the system of an individual.  These detections are molecular, instantaneous, and can be detected at the micromolar level.\r\nCurrent ventures include Joint IED Defeat Organization, Alexian Brother Behavioral Health Hospital, Hormel Foods, and IFSH.','Instant Detection Biosensors','[\"Chicago\"]','MedTech BioScience'),('The methods of disease diagnosis have certainly been revolutionized by numerous technologies over the past 20 years. In Ophthalmology, this progression has lagged behind other sectors, while blinding eye diseases continue to grow at a staggering pace because of the baby-boomer generation. Ocular Proteomics (OPL) aims to change this by using their discovery of proteins that are differentially activated in blinding diseases.\n\nThe Diagnostic Vitreous Proteome is a molecular based tool to provide Ophthalmologists with a better understanding about which treatments may work best, and conversely which ones that won\'t work at all! The benefits of this are two fold: administering effective treatment to patients at the earliest possible time saves their long term vision, &  costs savings from extended periods of non-effective treatments.\n\nIdentifying an individual patient\'s \"protein fingerprint\" is the future bedrock of disease treatment, much like HER2 is in breast cancer today.','Individualized Medicine for Eye Diseases','[\"Baltimore\"]','Ocular Proteomics'),('ZeroTo510 is a unique, entrepreneurial accelerator program that focuses on leveraging a key regional strength of Memphis area: medical device research and manufacturing.  The goal of ZeroTo510 is to help medical device startups to navigate the startup process, refine their business models and achieve the Food and Drug Administration\'s 510(k) premarket notification filing.  This goal is accomplished through an intensive, mentorship-driven, 90-day program of instruction and hands-on activities geared at guiding the entrepreneur through the process. In addition, each company chosen for the program will receive an investment of up to $150,000 in seed funding to help jump-start their finances.','Medical Device Accelerator','[\"Memphis\"]','ZeroTo510'),('Artes is a smart wristband developed in two different versions.\nArtes home is a wristband that makes a non-stop monitoring of body temperature and heart rate.\n\nArtes Hospital is a wristband dedicated to hospitals. It measures:\n•	Body temperature\n•	Blood pressure\n•	Oxygen saturation\n•	One-lead ECG\n•	Heart rate\n\nBoth versions of our product are hypoallergenic, rechargeable, wireless and non-invasive.','Smart wristband','[\"Milan\"]','Artes'),('drchrono was voted the #1 Mobile EHR for 2013 by Blackbook Rankings.  They surveyed over 16,000 physicians and drchrono won in 10 out of 16 categories that are tracked.\n\nSee the full Blackbook report here: https://www.drchrono.com/site_media/pdf/Black-Book-iPad-EHR-Report.pdf\n\ndrchrono is a free Meaningful Use Certified iPad EHR that offers paid upgrades to take over a Doctor\'s medical billing and Revenue Cycle Management.  \n\nWe use our award wining native iPad EHR and our cloud based medical billing platform to help office based Doctors comply with the U.S. government\'s Electronic Medical Records mandate (the HiTech act.)\n\nOur product is designed for office based private practice healthcare providers.  We don\'t sell to hospitals or larger healthcare systems, we are laser focused on making private practice doctors in small and large practices succeed with EHR and getting paid more on their medical billing.','iPad EHR + Medical Billing','[\"Mountain View\"]','drchrono'),('Our mission: one open system, created by the global medical community, that comprehensively maps any human health problem to its possible diagnoses. Over time, such a system could dramatically alter the cost of, access to, and efficacy of health care globally.\n\nThe Human Diagnosis Project will allow stakeholders across the healthcare value chain (patients, doctors, insurers, pharma companies, med schools, foundations, governments, etc.) to make both better health outcomes and resource allocation decisions.\n\nThe Project will initially be seeded via contributions from medical students, residents and physicians through a learning/licensing/practice tool. As the tool is used, Human Dx encodes structured data regarding how doctors think and uses machine learning, data mining, and other approaches to process and interpret this data.','Global medical project, creating an open diagnostic system.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Human Diagnosis Project'),('Ekso Bionics™ is a pioneer in the field of robotic exoskeletons to augment human strength, endurance and mobility. The company first developed a “wearable robot” called HULC for military applications, and has evolved the technology for the medical rehabilitation field. The company’s commercially available product called Ekso™, has enabled over 500 wheelchair users to stand and walk. Please visit our website at www.eksobionics.com to learn more.','Helping paraplegics walk again','[\"Richmond, CA\"]','Ekso Bionics'),(NULL,'The professional network for physicians','[\"San Mateo\"]','Doximity'),('Ritter\'s lead compound, RP-G28 has the potential to become the first FDA-approved drug for the treatment of lactose intolerance. RP-G28 has successfully completed Phase 2a clinical trials, and Ritter Pharma plans to partner the drug.','Therapeutic Treatments for Gastrointestinal Diseases','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Ritter Pharmaceuticals'),('2.4 billion people around the world don\'t have glasses who need them because of lack of access to eye diagnostics and care. We connect patients to eye care providers/vendors around the globe on our revolutionary cloud based platform, Test2Connect, through developing and disseminating low cost eye diagnostics on mobile phones that allow almost anyone to take an eye test, receive measurements for glasses, and access care from anywhere, at anytime. \n\nSee us on TechCrunch:  http://tcrn.ch/qmCUHZ','On-Demand Eye Care through Mobile Phones','[\"Boston\"]','EyeNetra'),('We built a pacemaker-like system that allows tinnitus and stroke patients to receive a novel therapy.  The implanted device is connected to the vagus nerve in the neck and sends tiny pulses of electricity, which cause the brain to release chemicals called neurostransmitters.  When these tiny pulses are paired with external stimulus such as tones or motor movements, specific regions of the brain are able to be rapidly rewired.  Research was published in Nature and New England Journal of Medicine.','Device Based Tinnitus and Stroke Therapy','[\"Dallas\"]','MicroTransponder'),('Spire is a next-generation wearable that creates value throughout your *entire* day - not only the ~16% of the day when you are moving, but also while commuting, working at the computer, or just lounging around.\n\nAs the 1st wearable movement + respiration tracker, Spire tracks the only actionable bio-signal that reveals and controls emotion and stress: breathing.\n\nEmotion affects how you breathe (see figure above). Deep breaths reduce cortisol (stress) and increase endorphins (positive feelings). Thus, Spire can both measure and actionably influence people throughout the day, leading to more productive work, healthier commutes, and better endurance. \n\nBeyond being a missing feature in the health+wellness wearable sensor equation, accurate respiration monitoring also solves major medical issues in the clinical space (ie Asthma and COPD). Spire ultimately intends to be an FDA-approved spirometry-like device allowing us to address this market as well.','Next-gen wearable for work and well-being. (Stanford/StartX/RockHealth)','[\"San Francisco\"]','Spire'),('Amulyte is an emergency response and activity tracking system that connects seniors with their friends, family and caregivers - providing them help when they need it, freedom when they don’t. \n\nThe Amulyte Pendant, worn by a senior, uses cell networks to work anywhere and leverages GPS and WiFi for both outdoor and indoor location detection. It contains a speaker and microphone to allow for 2-way voice communication via the pendant, a battery indicator light, and a help button. It is also equipped with an accelerometer to track activity.\n\nThe Amulyte Portal is an online web app used by family members and caregivers to find location, monitor activity level and trends, check battery life, and ensure everything is working.','Activity tracking & emergency response system for seniors','[\"Mountain View\"]','Amulyte'),('Biomeme\'s platform transforms your smartphone into a mobile lab for advanced DNA diagnostics and real-time disease surveillance. The system includes a docking station for real-time qPCR, a mobile app to control the system and analyze results, and targeted test kits for preparing samples and identifying pathogens or diseases by their specific DNA or RNA signatures. The cutting edge platform performs to the gold standard used by the world\'s most advanced central labs but requires no lab equipment or special experience to use.\n\nThe low-cost, user-friendly system enables mobile testing at the point-of-need for health care (mobile clinics, disease tracking, home use), agriculture (plant disease tracking, food safety), vector surveillance (Malaria, West Nile, Lyme disease), veterinary medicine, environmental monitoring (soil and water safety), and even education and citizen science.','Mobile real-time DNA analysis on your smartphone','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Biomeme'),('The Stanford-StartX Fund will help boost the entrepreneurial endeavors of Stanford students, faculty, alumni and staff at a critical, early stage in their ventures. StartX startup teams can now receive financial backing from the university and the hospital to help bring their innovations to market, faster and more efficiently. Any StartX founder raising a round of financing may, at their option, access investment by the Stanford-StartX Fund if the round of financing meets a set of clear and objective criteria. The fund will not take a lead role in company financings, but instead will participate as a minority investor alongside other venture capital and angel investors. This marks the first time either the university or the hospital has developed a fund to invest directly in the entrepreneurs emerging from the Stanford community.','Fund for StartX Founders','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Stanford-StartX Fund'),('Sols are next generation orthotics. We are developing all-in-one process to prescribe, generate and sell corrective orthoses at a fraction of the price and lead time currently available.\n\nEven better, our patent-pending technology utilizes a unique 3D printed spring system to maximize energy return, and enhance performance.  \n\nWith Sols technology anyone can become a retailer. Whether you\'re a tennis coach wanting to up your clients games, to a podiatrist looking to switch to a quicker,  reliable orthotic, to a retail outlet looking to make shoes fit.','3D Printed Custom Orthotics','[\"New York City\"]','Sols'),('Scanadu is sending your mobile phone to med school, creating a consumer medical Tricorder.\n\nHealthcare is rapidly becoming quantitative, a number\'s game. Patients as well as doctors will be overloaded with \"big\" data. This will open up a massive market for auto-diagnosis. But this market needs a tool, just like the mobile market needed a mobile phone. \n\nThe tool will be the Tricorder, putting a doctor at the fingertips of millions.','Scanadu Inc. is building a suite of mobile and digital health products for consumers.','[\"Mountain View\"]','Scanadu'),('We’re changing the way healthcare technology is purchased, consumed, and delivered to patients through our collaborative platform.  Our overarching mission is to enable life saving technology to be at the right place, at the right time, for the right cost.  Join our team in building more incredible partnerships with some of the best hospital groups, physicians, and clinical staff in the world.\n\nOn our platform doctors get access to any device in their health system\'s network through our proprietary application and logistics service.  Push a button on their smartphone, a robot or a laser shows up at their next surgery.\n\nWe have combined this on-demand capability with a real-time medical device and supply marketplace.  Our goal is to enable providers to have the same type of pricing transparency that consumers get when buying products off of Amazon.  We are flipping the archaic healthcare supply chain market on its head.  Join us.\n','Bringing collaborative consumption to healthcare','[\"Boston\"]','Cohealo'),('We build software that helps doctors, scientists, and programmers make sense of massive amounts of health data. The past decade has seen a revolution in molecular technology, which means we can now collect large amounts of precise medical data about anyone at low cost. The problem is that the data are not in a language doctors can understand.\n\nOur API for Medicine helps programmers and scientists at research hospitals, diagnostic companies, biotech and pharma companies, and CROs translate molecular data into information doctors can use to diagnose and treat patients. We\'ve compiled the world\'s molecular data and made it easy to work with and understand.','The Data Platform for Medicine','[\"New York City\"]','SolveBio'),('SharePractice is a doctor\'s only clinical reference that captures and shares your pearls and protocols for use at the point of care.  Treatments are ranked by you and your colleagues so you know that the info you get is current, integrative, and unbiased. \n\nAt SharePractice, we believe your experience is the best standard of care.\n\nShare Practice is in beta & designed by a group of physicians in San Francisco. Join the movement and make medical knowledge open, transparent & decentralized.\n','Integrative Medical Reference for Doctors, by Doctors','[\"San Francisco\"]','SharePractice'),('The NeuroEPG System will assist ER doctors and hospital staff in identifying potential stroke patients faster. \nFor the majority of stroke victims, damage caused by stroke can be reversed by a drug called t-PA if given within the first 4 hours of the stroke. However, less than 5% of stroke patients receive t-PA because they are not triaged and treated within the 4-hour time window. \nOur product provides objective neurophysiologic data to identify stroke patients sooner so more patients get t-PA.','Fast Emergency Room test to ID stroke patients.  An \"EKG-like\" test, but for stroke.','[\"Boston\"]','Strohl Medical'),('Common Sensing is developing GoCap, a pen cap for insulin pens that automatically tracks doses and transmits wirelessly to a mobile phone. The goal is to empower diabetics with better interfaces that connect family and members of the care community while providing actionable safety reminders and trends by contextualizing insulin dose information with blood glucose, exercise and meal data.\n\nWe are tired of medical interfaces that are dysfunctional, clunky and down-right ugly. We want to design an experience for diabetics as people, and not as patients. We can create an experience that caters to the needs of different lifestyles, integrates contemporary data visualization, and is fun and engaging to use. We want to see the line between consumer products and medical products merge into one. This is how we can change the face of diabetes care.','Simple Dose Tracking for Diabetics','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Common Sensing'),('A recent report prepared by McKinsey & Co estimates that the cost of medical errors introduced by inadequate track & trace on medical devices is estimated to be between $18 and $115 billion annually. In response to the need in the industry for such a track & trace solution, 121nexus developed MDDTrack™, which is a cloud-based software solution integrated with product packaging for manufacturers to enhance recall management and post-market surveillance in the medical devices and diagnostics industry.','Cloud-based track & trace solutions for biomedical manufacturers','[\"Providence\"]','121nexus'),('Morpheus Medical has developed a platform technology to assess hemodynamic function (flow rate, blood velocity, pressure and shear stress) non-invasively within the heart. \n\nPatient specific medical images are sent to the Morpheus and a report is rendered for the client.\n\nPatients benefit by avoiding the need for invasive and lengthy catheterizations. \n\nDoctors can have faster, comprehensive, and more accurate information of heart function compared to current gold standards. ','First diagnostic for heart failure with 3D interactivity flow and pressure non-invasively','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Morpheus Medical'),('Nurep is a mobile health company that has developed a medical device support network that links hospital systems with medical device expertise for real-time operative support.\n\nThe medical device industry spends over $40B a year to send expensive personnel onsite to support healthcare providers in the operating room. The evolution of value-based healthcare has made this expensive and inefficient in-person model no longer sustainable. \n\nNurep will improve patient outcomes, reduce healthcare costs and streamline healthcare delivery through a secure and trusted network that allows on-demand operative support to anywhere in the world. \n\nNurep is creating clinically relevant features to allow for quality support in a remote setting. They will be the first to track novel operative data, record procedures and obtain clinical info to improve healthcare.\n',' Medical Device Support Network (Stanford StartX Med, Blueprint Health)','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Nurep'),('CardioSleeve is the first FDA cleared stethoscope add-on device for clinicians to acquire 3-Lead ECG and Digital heart sound at any point of care. CardioSleeve enhances the traditional stethoscope by recording, displaying and analyzing the heart\'s ECG and acoustical footprints in real time via any wirelessly connected portable device.  \r\n\r\nPatient heart sound auscultations are subjective to the hearing, experience and training limitations of the clinician, leading to missed diagnosis and additional costly tests.  A traditional ECG requires wired electrode cart machines which limits their access.  \r\n\r\nCardioSleeve disrupts this cardio-diagnostic process by allowing clinicians an attachment to their current stethoscope to acquire digital heart sound and ECG and perform real time analysis at any point of care via mobile.\r\n\r\nCardioSleeve\'s device/ mobile app platform offers:   \r\nUniversal stethoscope attachment\r\nDigital Auscultation\r\n3- Lead ECG\r\nMurmur Analysis\r\nCloud EHR','Stethoscope attachment with mobile heart sound and ECG','[\"Pittsburgh\"]','Rijuven'),('The Blueprint Health accelerator program is geared towards healthcare companies that want an intensive three-month program to help find customers and capital. Blueprint Health is a Charter Member of the Global Accelerator Network, which was started by TechStars. Selected companies range from two founders with an idea to businesses that have customers, investors and are generating significant revenue.\n\nThe foundation of the program is a community of over 150 healthcare entrepreneurs, investors and industry executives that are committed to helping you build and grow your business. We have the largest network of mentors with healthcare expertise of any accelerator, which can provide you with warm introductions and the strategic and tactile advice you need. If you are accepted to the accelerator program, you will receive $20,000 in cash, over $50,000 in perks, office space at our SoHo office, and a community that is dedicated to seeing you succeed.','Community, Capital and Customers for your Health Startup','[\"New York City\"]','Blueprint Health'),('Lynx Design is developing a new class of assistive devices for the elderly and individuals with motion disorders. Our first product is an active tremor cancellation technology that will assist individuals affected by motion disorders such as Essential Tremor. The system will facilitate daily living, reduce social isolation, and re-enable the affected public to participate in activities/occupations that were lost upon disease onset.','Active Stabilization for Parkinson\'s and Essential Tremor Patients','[\"San Francisco\"]','Lift Labs'),('Innovative Surgical Designs, Inc. (ISD) is a medtech start-up company that has developed Altum, the first and only minimally invasive cure for lumbar spinal stenosis that maintains the natural dynamics of the spine. \n\nAltum is a percutaneous device that goes in through the pedicles and cuts the pedicles from the inside out. Our bone saw is the first and only saw in the world that can cut bone from the inside out.  After the pedicles are cut, we insert our implant that expands the central and foraminal opens on average 50%.  It is a simple procedure with advanced technology that takes about 30 minutes per level to perform.\n','Edwards Lifesciences SAPIEN for spine','[\"Bloomington, IN\"]','Innovative Surgical Designs'),('Procured Health is a web-accessible information platform that enables allows hospitals to tackle their fastest growing cost - medical devices. The platform leverages the collective knowledge of hospital members, along with public data from vendors and the FDA, to facilitate adoption of high value products to both reduce spend and improve care. ','Making the medical device market efficient','[\"Chicago\"]','Procured Health'),('Podimetrics is a system for keeping diabetic feet healthy.','Podimetrics is a system for keeping diabetic feet healthy.','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Podimetrics'),('Spartan is bringing complete sample-to-result DNA testing systems to medicine. Spartan’s technology fully integrates DNA collection, extraction and analysis, with an intuitive interface that is easy to operate. For the first time, healthcare providers and their patients can get DNA results on demand.','Sample to result in 1 hour','[]','Spartan Bioscience'),('MobileCT is a medical image viewer for the iPad. It can display images stored in the DICOM format, which is the industry standard for storing medical images. MobileCT supports the most common imaging modalities (X-Ray, MRI, CT, PET, etc.).  The PRO version supports collaboration with other users of the same app, whether they are in the same location or not.  This enables doctors to provide consultations from remote locations.  \n\nhttp://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id431495135','collaborative medical imaging, anywhere, anytime.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Nephosity'),('Venipuncture is the most common invasive medical procedure, with over 1.4B procedures performed annually in the US alone. It is also one of the most overlooked problems in medicine. 20% of first attempts to gain access to a vein fail, often leading to patient complications and additional expenses for medical facilities. Veebot is automating venipuncture through computer vision and robotics, making it safer for both patients and medical staff, and cost efficient for medical facilities.\n','Automated Venipuncture Solutions (e.g., phlebotomy, IV insertion, blood gasses etc.)','[\"Mountain View\"]','Veebot'),('EnteroWave is creating innovative needle-delivered neurostimulation devices for gastrointestinal (GI) disorders.  We use proprietary neuromodulation methods that elicit specific physiological responses, including the ability to mimic the therapeutic effect of a gastric bypass. Diabetes and obesity are a worldwide epidemic, and our devices offer a low-cost, low-risk alternative to surgical intervention.  These versatile devices can also be reconfigured for the treatment of other conditions including GERD, IBS, or motility disorders.  Our patented miniaturization technology comes from Stanford, and our proprietary neuromodulation techniques come from years of research at both Johns Hopkins Medical Center and the University of Texas Medical Branch.\n\nOur millimeter-sized devices are externally powered and controlled, and open a new realm of applications because of the lower costs and risk without surgery.  Currently we are building wireless prototypes for animal and clinical studies. ','Minimally Invasive Neurostimulators for GI Disorders','[\"San Carlos, CA\"]','EnteroWave'),('iOS app for tracking your mindful brainwaves.','Consumer neurotechnology for health and wellness','[\"San Francisco\"]','BrainBot'),('SoniTrack\'s technology integrates robotics and ultrasound imaging to enable real-time markerless targeting for radiation therapy.','Precision targeting for radiation therapy','[\"Palo Alto\"]','SoniTrack Systems'),('DuoFertility is a home fertility monitoring service, proven equally effective as IVF for half of all IVF patients (with peer reviewed publications).  DuoFertility costs 1/10th what IVF does, and is suitable for 80% of all infertile couples (of which there are about 1.5M couples/year EU+US). CE and FDA cleared.\n\nDuoFertility retails online at www.DuoFertility.com and in the UK through Boots Pharmacy.  The price is £495 (~$800), and if you\'re not pregnant in 12 months we give your money back.','Home fertility service proven as effective as IVF','[\"Cambridge, UK\"]','Cambridge Temperature Concepts'),('Eko provides physicians with certainty when they are diagnosing heart conditions. We’ve built one of the world’s first stethoscopes that can automatically detect heart murmurs. Doctors currently have the almost impossible task of trying to hear minute differences between heart sounds, which results in frequent misdiagnosis and undetected heart abnormalities. Through a physician’s smartphone, the Eko software compares a patient’s heartbeat to a database of thousands of others and provides almost instantaneous feedback to the physician. Eko gives every physician the power of a cardiologist in their pocket.\n\nFEATURES\n| Digitize heart sounds from almost any analog stethoscope\n| Visualize the heart sounds; record and play them back\n| Get an instant analysis of a heart sound by comparing it to thousands of others\n| Attach heart sounds to patient\'s medical records\n| Securely share heart sounds with other physicians','A cardiologist in every physician\'s pocket','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eko Devices'),('We love Hardware.\n\nHighway1 (http://highway1.io) is part of PCH (http://www.pchintl.com/), a global supply chain company. We\'re been working with Fortune 500 companies for over 15 years. PCH is also known for bringing startups like littleBits and Lark to market. Now we want to use that expertise to help younger companies get ready for production and their first round of funding.\n\nOur four month program supplies you with:\n\n• A dedicated staff of experienced engineers ­\n• An inside view into the supply chain infrastructure in Southern China\n• An education in manufacturing, supply chain, and distribution as well as project and business management, finance, and strategy\n• Office & shop space for mechanical & electrical prototyping\n• Mentorship and guidance from across the tech sector\n• Seed Funding of $20,000 in return for 3-6% equity\n\nWe\'re looking for small teams that want to build hardware companies for the long term.\n\nIf this describes you, let us know.','Incubator for hardware start-ups','[\"San Francisco\"]','Highway1'),('HealthEngage helps people live better lifestyles with diabetes. We make  easy to use daily tools and engaging health data intelligence programs to make life analysis and diabetes tracking availalble to anyone around the world. Easy, free and in 58 languages, already used by over 100 thousand people.','patient-driven health opinion & data platform','[\"Washington, DC\"]','HealthEngage'),('HelloMD is a marketplace of the best doctors, advisors and treatment options from around the globe. This $40B cash market (medical tourism and second opinions) is poorly served by technology today. \n\nJust as Ebay created the market for online auctions, HelloMD will dramatically expand access to global healthcare by creating a friction-free marketplace for cash-based treatment options. \n\nThe HelloMD Telehealth platform is already developed and deployed with two paying healthcare customers. We are now onboarding treatment centers and doctors from around the world into our marketplace.\n\nWe make money by taking a 10% commision on all medical treatments and second opinions. We will generate $80m in revenue with just 2% of the existing global market.\n\n\n\n','AirBnB for Healthcare','[\"San Francisco\"]','HelloMD'),('EnChroma makes the only eyeglasses that offer true red/green color blindness correction for the 10 million Americans, 200 million worldwide who suffer from the condition. This application serves as a way to demonstrate and refine our optical lens coating capabilities in a niche market willing to pay early adopter rates as we begin value engineering our efforts and rolling out vastly improved eyewear products in every market segment.','Color for the Color Blind','[\"Berkeley\"]','EnChroma'),('Are you one of those people who use the back of the toothbrush or the bathroom counter to squeeze all the toothpaste from the tube? What a mess! In addition, it’s frustrating, and wasteful!  So, do you also hide the twisted, rolled-up and unattractive tube in a drawer so guests will not see it??  If so, you are like a million other consumers that have been doing this ritual your entire life! \n\nTHE PROBLEM: \n\nHow do you eliminate the frustrating, and wasteful tasks of getting the toothpaste out the tube without squeezing it, and how do you hide the unattractive tube until the next time used?\n\nTHE SOLUTION: \n\nNu-b-2b is the most advanced hygiene dispenser that eliminates the waste, the squeezing and the rolling. Plus, it hides unsightly tubes, and has an area for corporate or personal branding. ','No Squeeze Toothpaste Dispenser - Developed by HCP','[\"Dubuque\"]',' Nu-B-2B'),('referralMD is a web  application that offers a comprehensive business management solution designed to track and help monetize healthcare referrals.\n\nSimilar in structure to a Customer Relationship Management (CRM) program, referralMD manages healthcare referral network exchanges, economic and new business development efforts. It’s an application to specifically track referral sources, collaboration opportunities, follow-up activity and measure localized network growth.\n\nSpecialists & primary care doctors and other healthcare professionals, utilize the tools for tracking and measuring their network referral activity, business development efforts and collaborative projects. Integrated reporting tools provide network-to-business development proof of conversion – valuable for new healthcare facilities and retention campaigns.\n\nOur Unique selling point\nWe have developed a niche application focused on localized organization development and business collaboration. Scalable in “Any Town USA”.\n','The Salesforce.com of Healthcare (A Private Social Healthcare Referral Network)','[\"San Francisco\"]','ReferralMD'),('Kickstart helps improve mobility and facilitate rehabilitation to help people with severe disabilities walk independently. People with severe mobility impairments due to medical conditions such as stroke, multiple sclerosis, or Lou Gehrig’s Disease have some strength and control in their legs, but not enough to walk independently. Consequently, they use wheelchairs for mobility at the cost of independence as well as any hope of maintaining or recovering function.\n','Medical Device helping people w/ severe disabilities walk','[\"Seattle\"]','Cadence Biomedical'),('ZernikeMeta Ventures has extensive experience in managing public-private venture capital funds that co-invest with angel investors in various regions including Southern Europe, Central Europe, Eastern Europe. Primary industry of focus are ICT, Biotech, Medical Devices, Manufacturing companies.\nActive funds are in Italy, Slovenia and Poland for an overall amount of around 90Mln Euro under management.','Early stage investor','[\"Europe\"]','ZernikeMeta Ventures'),('AdhereTech has created patented smart pill bottles that improve medication adherence. These bottles automatically measure the amount of medication in the bottle in real-time, and wirelessly transmit this HIPAA-compliant data to the cloud via the Verizon network. If a patient hasn’t taken his/her medication, our service reminds them via phone call or text message - as well as via on-bottle lights and chimes.\n\nAdhereTech has secured trials with: \n• Boehringer Ingelheim for a TBD medication\n• The Walter Reed National Military Medical Center for type 2 diabetes medication\n• Weill Cornell Medical College for single-dose HIV medication\n\nWinner:\n• Clinician\'s Choice at The Cleveland Clinic Medical Innovation Summit\n• Boehringer Ingelheim\'s 2013 Healthcare Innovation World Cup\n• NYCEDC\'s PILOT Health Tech NYC\n\nMain stage:\n• Pfizer Innovation Conference\n• TEDMED\n• Cleveland Clinic Medical Innovation Summit\n• Stanford Medicine X\n\nFeatured in: \n• WSJ\n• Fast Company\n• Wired\n• TIME','Patented wireless pill bottles to increase adherence and collect data','[\"New York City\"]','AdhereTech'),(NULL,'','[\"Salt Lake City\"]','University Venture Fund'),('Umbie Health Corporation is a cloud based, HIPAA compliant application platform that structures the processes, communications, and productivity for specialty healthcare practices. Umbie DentalCare is our premier product that is designed for dental professionals; it can be accessed with just a web browser, is maintenance free to the end-user.\n\nUmbie DentalCare’s comprehensive office management solution streamlines: human resources; billing and receivables; insurances and medical records; appointment scheduling; charting and documenting exams and procedures, and so much more. In addition to office management, Umbie DentalCare offers practice accountability through role-based user authentication, customizable reports and metrics, and automated data entry tracking for each user. Lastly, Umbie DentalCare encourages patient engagement through an interactive office-patient communication portal, customizable appointment reminders, and chair-side x-ray viewing and treatment plans.  \n','We deliver office management, practice accountability,  and patient engagement solutions.','[\"East Hartford\"]','Umbie DentalCare'),('Based in Khobar, Saudi Arabia. Elite Derma Care aims to provide the best of both worlds; a synergy of non-invasive cosmetic dermatology as well as cutting edge plastic surgery. This unique marriage of non-invasive and invasive aesthetics allows us to serve all beauty needs without prejudice or limitations. It allows our fully trained medical & surgical team to create the most pleasing aesthetic outcome using our wide range of services and treatments as well as the expertise of a team of dedicated doctors and accredited plastic surgeons.\n','Skin, Laser & Anti Aging Center','[\"Khobar\"]','Elite Derma Care'),('Tired of investing in X for Y?  Join us and solve a REAL problem. Insulin-dependent diabetics have a daily grind that is humbling:\n\n- 4-6 injections/day, basal insulin in the morning, mealtime insulin before each snack/meal;\n- Constant finger pricks to monitor blood sugar; and\n- You are always worried about what you eat... diabetes is a \"lifetime sentence.\"\n\nThat\'s ~6,000 procedures/year.  We solve all 3 problems with a true once-a-day insulin.   Ask any diabetic, this would be _huge_.','Once-a-day insulin for type I/II diabetes, that gives patients a chance at a normal life.','[\"Houston\"]','Sensulin'),('Real Food Blends provides shelf-stable, 100% real food meals that can be fed through a feeding tube. Unlike the current commercial formulas that make up the $10 billion enteral market, Real Food Blends meals do not contain corn syrup, additives, preservatives or anything other than real food. \n\n','100% real food meals for those on feeding tubes. Disrupting the $10B enteral food market. ','[\"Chicago\"]','Real Food Blends'),('Raising $4M Series A\n\nHourGlass has developed an transoral procedure to help morbidly obese patients lose weight. While surgeries like gastric bypass are effective and represent >$1B in sales annually, <2% of eligible patients elect treatment. HourGlass’ patented device replicates the anatomic results of proven surgeries but with an incision-free procedure performed outside expensive operating rooms in half the time. The result is a simpler, safer, and incision-free procedure for <$10k.','Incision-free obesity surgery','[\"Redwood City\"]','HourGlass Technologies'),('The Strong Arm™ is a lifting safety device with load distribution system, that removes the injury causing loads from the weaker hands, arms neck and lower back, and distributes those forces to stronger more capable areas of the torso. The company was founded and developed by two students at Rochester Institute of Technology in 2011. ','Increasing the Performance of the Workforce ','[\"Boston\"]','StrongArm Technologies'),('NetworksMD makes collaboration between healthcare practitioners possible. ','Enabling Collaboration in Healthcare','[\"San Francisco\"]','NetworksMD'),('Bleeding or swelling of the brain due to head trauma can increase the pressure inside a patient\'s skull (ICP). Elevated ICP is dangerous and may be fatal if left untreated. The gold standard for measuring ICP requires a neurosurgeon to drill a hole in the patient\'s head and screw in a sensor. This procedure is often not performed due to the resources required and associated risks.\n\nRecognizing this unmet need, researchers in the UCLA Department of Neurosurgery have developed a non-invasive alternative to assess elevated ICP. The technology uses an algorithm and patient database to correlate elevated ICP with an ultrasound measure of blood flow in the brain.\n\nNeural Analytics is building RapidICP, a hand-held head trauma screening tool that encapsulates this technology. RapidICP will target a domestic total addressable market of $2B including first responders, the military and various clinical settings.\n','Non-invasive head trauma screening device for use in pre-hospital settings.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Neural Analytics'),('Widetronix’s mission is to enable autonomous sensors for the wireless world. The company is commercializing ultra low power sensors with betavoltaic micro-power sources, which have an energy density up to 5 µW/cm2. This technology is based on licensed patents from Cornell University, as well as Widetronix patents and patents pending. Known applications include critical system protection for defense ($200M), secure IT and networking ($840M), industrial sensors ($500M), and medical implants ($1B), where drivers are long-life, stability in harsh environments, and small size, respectively. Widetronix operates its own electronics packaging facility, as well as in the Cornell Nanofabrication Facility, both in Ithaca, New York. The company is venture, grant, and customer funded and is seeking to fill out $500K of a $1M bridge financing to lead to a $5M Series A in 2014. This will enable the company to transition into production and sales in 2014. ','Tiny batteries that last a lifetime','[\"Ithaca\"]','Widetronix'),('Talking20 is blood tests made simple. We offer the first affordable at-home blood test service you can do by simply putting a few drops of blood on a filter card and mailing it in. Hundreds of tests can be analyzed this way and sent to you online from anywhere, anytime.\n\nWe ran a crowd funding campaign Dec. 2012 and raised 60K in pre-sales over 45 days .We started doing global sales within 2 weeks of launch.\n\nYour body is talking to you. Let\'s find out what it\'s saying. ','Blood testing made simple. Meet the facebook of health.','[\"Menlo Park\"]','Talking20'),('Osmosis is an individualized learning system that helps institutions produce clinicians who better retain and apply knowledge via a web and mobile platform that takes advantage of cutting-edge cognitive techniques and software tools.','A med ed tech start-up that helps clinicians discover, learn, and retain more information','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Osmosis'),('FitBionic is a consumer-centered prosthetics company with a first-in-industry focus on cultivating healthy lifestyles for amputees, with a special focus on the needs of people with diabetes. Founded in Boulder, Colorado, FitBionic is led by a team of top designers, technologists, and entrepreneurs from leading bionics and prosthetics companies. Development of our first product, the FitBionic Foot, was supported by a $1.2 million grant from the National Institutes of Health, and the foot has garnered multiple design awards and national recognition. Most importantly, the first amputees to use this biomechanically designed walking foot have loved it from the first steps.\n','Re-imaging bionic limbs, for everyday heroes','[\"Boulder\"]','FITBIONIC'),('According to the WHO, 26 million children are not immunized, exposing them to disabilities or premature death. People living in hard-to-reach areas of the world struggle to receive vaccinations. Nanoly’s technology enables cheap, effective, and safe delivery of vaccines to anywhere in the world. We are developing a nanoparticle based chemical shield that protects vaccines for improved storage and transportation without refrigeration. ','Improving Vaccine Delivery','[\"Boulder\"]','Nanoly'),('Phthisis offers 3 product lines for clinical laboratories:\n\nG-Sphere® Standards - GMP-grade molecular standards for virtually any pathogen ~ better standards = quality diagnosis.\n\nE-Sphere® Extraction - Enzyme-based technology makes E-Sphere easier & faster than competitors ~ faster sample prep = faster diagnosis.\n\nR-Sphere™ Detect - Genetic \'fingerprint\' technology makes R-Sphere faster & more accurate than competitors ~ better diagnosis =  better patient care.','Infectious Disease Molecular Diagnostics','[\"Charlottesville\"]','Phthisis Diagnostics'),('Intelligent Ultrasound develops software that improves the quality, reliability and diagnostic power of medical ultrasound – the most widely used medical imaging tool in the world. The company’s products make ultrasound easier to use and help hospitals to provide a consistently high-quality ultrasound imaging service, thereby minimising the risk of wrong or missed diagnoses.\n\nIt\'s first product has been shown to improve rates of diagnosis in ultrasound scans of the heart by more than 40%.\n','Big data analytics for better diagnosis','[\"Oxford\"]','Intelligent Ultrasound'),('MatchedFlicker helps the clinician perform two of their most important functions, disease diagnosis and patient engagement, faster and more effectively using the medical images they already have available. Images are rapidly uploaded to the cloud and can be instantly compared using a single button. The system can be accessed from anywhere via a web browser, and is also enabled for future mobile medicine and telehealth applications.','Automates \'Spot the Difference\' to improve diagnosis and patient engagement','[\"Philadelphia\"]','EyeIC'),(NULL,'','[\"Milwaukee\"]','Scanalytics, Inc.'),('MyMedLeads is a lead management tool that tracks marketing ROI, improves staff performance and automated email marketing and appointment reminders.  \r\n\r\nMyMedLeads has been growing in the plastic surgery industry and has key integration partners with top practice management software. Customers are able to eliminate marketing that doesn\'t work while improving their lead to patients conversion rate.\r\n\r\nhttp://mymedleads.com/view-demo.asp','Lead management & ROI tracking for doctors','[\"Austin\"]','MyMedLeads.com'),(NULL,'','[\"New York City\"]','Healthcare Innovation World Cup'),('The device is a proprietary, low cost, non-invasive, radiation-free tool that uses military grade thermal cameras to measure heat/vascular patterns which are indicative of breast cancer.  The test is painless and takes about 10 minutes. \r\n\r\nThe device will be used by OB/GYNs and Internists as part of an annual physical exam, as well as by oncologists to monitor patients subsequent to cancer diagnosis/treatment.  It’s projected sensitivity is 95% vs. a clinical breast exam by the doctor at 45% (mammogram at 75%. The device and software automate a manual process that has been perfected as a result of testing 1,000,000+ women over the past 40+ years.  The company has an exclusive worldwide license to this methodology that has been validated in a 2,000 woman clinical trial. The company has an experienced management team. Board is anchored by the co-developer of Lipitor, Roger Newton, PhD. \r\n\r\nCompany has potential to provide significant return to investors and save thousands of lives.','Revolutionary Early Breast Cancer Detection Device','[\"Pontiac\"]','First Sense Medical'),('Within3 is fundamentally changing healthcare by becoming the ubiquitous underlying secure web, mobile, and API platform. Through our social, professional, and community based products Within3’s is connecting all healthcare practitioners, institutions, and pharmaceutical companies worldwide to create better patient outcomes.','Fundamentally changing healthcare by becoming \"the\" platform for all communications. ','[\"Cleveland\"]','Within3'),('AccelDx is developing pScreen™, a disruptive blood testing platform for the diagnosis and management of medical conditions in the Home/Point-of-Care setting. Accel’s solution enables physicians/patients to manage diseases in a timely and effective manner, thereby reducing cost and hospitalizations. AccelDx is currently focusing on pScreen-BNP™ for the in home daily monitoring of heart conductions to prevent heart failure (HF) related re-hospitalizations: an untapped market opportunity of $1.9B.','Diagnostic tests at your fingertips','[\"Berkeley\"]','Accel Diagnostics'),('JettStream minimizes asthma attacks and ER visits for children by providing a superior delivery system for nebulized medication. In addition, JettStream provides an educational system for parents and pediatricians treating childhood asthma.\nOur series of products create a pain free, non intrusive approach to the repetitive respiratory therapy demanded by this disease. The treatments that we target address both acute attacks and daily therapies.','A Superior Treatment System for Children with Asthma','[\"Bend\"]','JettStream '),('MDmatic is a powerful mobile platform that gives healthcare providers control of patient report creation & management from the palm of their hand.  MDmatic allows providers to create, finalize, upload to EHR, and share patient reports, within minutes, from anywhere at any time.\n\nFederal legal mandates are driving U.S. medical providers to adopt Electronic Health Record (EHR) systems by 2014, but all are struggling to overcome decreased productivity due to inefficient data entry & access, yielding significant user frustration & diminished ROI.  \n\nMDmatic uniquely solves this challenge for both users and organizations - saving time, boosting productivity & facilitating universal connectivity.','Enhancing clinical connectivity & facilitating EHR adoption through the mobile cloud','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','MDmatic'),('Nanofiber Solutions, LLC is a medical device manufacturer of a new class of human implants, three-dimensional (3-D) scaffolds and cell culture products that advance biological sciences.  We manufacture the only bioartificial tracheal implant with FDA Investigational New Device (IND) allowance in the U.S.  These implants have been used successfully in several European surgeries in the past year with upcoming surgeries scheduled in the U.S. ','Novel artificial implants','[\"Columbus\"]','Nanofiber Solutions'),('BABYBE is a biocord that keeps mothers and her babies connected through the process of artificial incubation.\nWe bring haptic information from the mother to the baby on real time, making the environment inside the incubator machine less stressing while giving the mother an active role in the care of her preterm son.\n\nWe do this by collecting the mother´s body signs like heart beat, breathing and voice, through a device installed in the her chest and translates those signals into movement on a Bionic Mattress that emulates the mother chest in all of its nuances.\n\n1 of every 8 births is premature in USA. A preterm baby stays average 21 days inside of an incubator, costing an average of USD$76,000. \n \nBABYBE aims to bring the preterm babies out of the incubator machine sooner, involve the mother actively in the care of her baby and, finally, give our customers -the hospitals- the strategic advantage of being in the front edge of emotional care to capture new clients.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','Soft robotic for neonatal healthcare','[]','BABYBE'),('We make it easy for doctors, nurses and midwives to track innovation online and to buy prebundled tools to use overseas in emerging markets. We are a marketplace aggregating technologies and protocols that save lives in childbirth (obstetrics, gynecology, neonatal products and emergency care).','The first global fast track for medical innovations','[\"Providence\"]','Maternova '),('Digital Mammographer automatically diagnoses screening mammograms with above 90% accuracy (tested on over 2,000 mammograms). Turnaround is one minute. And you can use it anywhere with an Internet connection, without buying $200k of hardware. It will provide patients with peace of mind and clinics with low-cost, portable, highly accurate diagnostics. It could save thousands of lives.\n\nAnd that\'s just the beginning. We\'re disrupting medicine and we hope you\'ll join us for the ride.','Artificially Intelligent Cloud Diagnosis','[\"Rockville\"]','Living Discoveries'),('Image-based surgery is critical for implant dentistry. It has two components: CT scan based treatment planning and customized surgical guide CAD/CAM. Treatment planning with advanced imaging technology ensures a successful procedure with accuracy, safety, efficiency and esthetics, and the surgical guides transfer the treatment plans into personalized devices that make surgery easier and safer. GuideMia is the only system in the market that offers surgical guide design solution. FDA approved.','The first turn-key system planning and guiding dental implants','[\"Los Angeles\"]','GuideMia Digital Dentistry'),('Remote patient monitoring is expensive and limited. There are thousands of monitors, zero standards, pragmatically speaking and no connection for non-API hardware. Infometers is the abstraction layer, providing a standardized API to access monitoring-data streams.\n\nWe are working with premier centers (like UCSF) and patient management startups to test out solutions on their populations. Our goal is to help shave off a big chunk of Healthcare costs. ','aggregates patient monitoring data, provides a standardized platform','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','Infometers '),('Forge Medical is a development stage medical device company focused on the commercialization of an innovative product for the $30B U.S. hemodialysis marketplace.  The Company’s first product platform, VasoStat, is a sterile, ergonomic, cost-effective device to control bleeding following removal of needles after hemodialysis.  This product will enable dialysis clinics to reduce staff overtime, infection risks and ancillary material costs.','Hemostasis device for dialysis and venous punctures','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Forge Medical'),('  The QuietNITE is a dentist-prescribed, FDA approved, Mandibular Repositioning Device sold in the rapidly growing Sleep Apnea market.  It\'s intended for treatment of mild to moderate Obstructive Sleep Apnea.  Our customer is a Dentist, a Dental Laboratory, or a Distributor.\n\n  The lower jaw is moved into a forward position, thus increasing the three-dimensional space in the airway and oxygen flow to the brain. Additionally, this reduces airway velocity and soft-tissue vibration (snoring).\n\n','Sleep Apnea Mandibular Repositioning Device','[\"Atlanta\"]','QuietNITE'),('Molecular Detection, Inc. (“MDI” or the “Company”) is a privately-held commercial-stage diagnostics company that has developed and commercialized a series of performance-leading highly-multiplexed, rapid and highly-accurate molecular diagnostic assay kits.  MDI’s initial commercial focus is on the rapid detection of infectious diseases.  Rapid detection of HAIs and infectious diseases represents >$2B worldwide market for diagnostics. \n\nMDI has commercialized its Detect-Ready® MRSA Panel, for the rapid MRSA, MSSA and MRCNS and is in full time hospital and laboratory use in the European Union. MDI is finalizing the development the Whole Blood Sepsis Panel, which will be the first molecular diagnostic test to provide timely, accurate identification of key antibiotic resistance determinants and pathogens within 3 hours direct from patient sample.  Finally, MDI is in advanced development of the Detect-Ready Gastro Panel, for the rapid detection of diarrhea-causing bacteria.  ','Advanced Molecular Diagnostic Panel Tests','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Molecular Detection Inc.'),('Dropsense is a convenient and affordable low blood sugar alert system created by harnessing the power of modern sensing, mobile, and machine learning technologies. \n\nDropsense monitors continuously overnight and alerts you upon sudden drops in blood sugar for a fraction of the price of continuous glucose monitors. \n\nNighttime hypoglycemia is one of the biggest risks for the roughly 94 million people with diabetes worldwide using insulin. These individuals are living without a painless monitoring solution to keep them safe. \n\nAt Dropsense, we believe everyone should be able to monitor their blood sugar overnight. Our goal is to provide this technology at a price anyone can afford.','non-invasive low blood sugar alert systems','[\"Berkeley\"]','Dropsense'),('At Symvato we believe that HIPAA compliance tools should be as affordable as they are easy. Healthcare providers should be focused on their patients, not regulatory compliance. Symvato allows providers to focus on their patients by providing a creative and innovative HIPAA compliance solution. At Symvato, we are HIPAA compliance made simple!','HIPAA Compliance Made Simple','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Symvato'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"Milwaukee\"]','Granite Med Systems'),('for[MD] is a private network of physician communities.  Medical societies and alumni programs receive a community on our network where they can engage with their physician membership more effectively.  Their members also access the larger for[MD] network to crowdsource solutions to patient care and practice management challenges. ','Private communities for medical organizations.','[\"New York City\"]','for[MD]'),('Agile Devices aims to remove a major time bottleneck in a wide variety of catheter-based interventional procedures, resulting in improved patient outcomes and large cost savings for hospitals. Our unique variable-stiffness microcatheter accelerates interventional procedures by allowing clinicians to more rapidly navigate small, tortuous blood vessels.  Patients benefit from shorter procedure times, especially in time-critical emergencies such as stroke or acute arterial bleeding. Faster procedure times also allow treatment in patients who had would have otherwise fallen outside of their therapeutic time window. Physicians are attracted to our device by the improved ease-of-use over traditional microcatheters and maintained compatibility with other interventional equipment.  Hospitals benefit from lower costs per procedure, which could lead to savings of $1.8+ B/year for hospitals in the US upon complete adoption.','Fast-access microcatheter','[\"Cambridge, MA\"]','Agile Devices'),('There are 230,000 physician offices in the U.S. spending over $30B per year on medical supplies and equipment. 90% of them are small businesses with limited purchasing volume as individuals. By banding together through social commerce, we are bringing volume based purchasing discounts to these practices to capture a slice of this big pie. We are in beta, have had great press coverage and are generating sales with a small scale launch so far.','Reducing healthcare costs through social commerce.  Buy Together, Thrive Together.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Groundswell Health'),('What people do when they are sick? They have too many pieses of paper to keep track \ntoo many pills and so often forget to kake their pills or they take the wrong ones.\nWith be healthy they no longer worry about these problems!\nThey can have a medicines log to help track of medicines.\nThey get notification to remind them to take their pills.\nAnd there is even a rharmacy map to tell them where the nearest pharmacy is located.\n\nFot more information please visit our page www.be-healthy.me\n \nYou can test android version here https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-QMh27zC8FjV3hqOVJkbU1nTDA/edit?usp=drive_web','looks after your health! ','[\"Kiev\"]','Be healthy'),('A small Angel Investors Group, investing across all areas using Technology as an enabler....currently working on mentoring, strategising, and launching a Healthcare - ECG monitoring device....Looking at other medium ticket size deals from all you budding entrepreneurs out there!! ','','[]','Gurgaon Angels'),('Essex Capital acts as a financing source and lessor to credit worthy companies on a nationwide basis, leasing all assets except vehicles and commercial aircraft.\n\nEssex Capital Venture Leasing’s structured financing provides companies with access to the equipment they need, while our knowledge and relationships with venture capital companies offers the partnerships needed to face the challenges in the market, together.\n\nSpecialties include:\n\nVenture Capital Leasing, Equipment Leasing, Alternative Investment, Sale Leaseback, Private Equity, Llife Sciences, Medical Devices, Manufacturing Equipment, Capital Connections, Portfolio Companies ','','[\"Santa Barbara\"]','Essex Capital Corporation'),('Our platform engages cancer patients in their care by combining evidence-based guidelines, clinical trials, and patient preferences to generate personalized recommendations that allow the patient and doctor to jointly plan the best course of care for the patient. This results in patients who are healthier and happier, while also significantly reducing the cost of care.','Engaging patients through personalized guidelines','[\"Montreal\"]','Evinance'),('Sentry Scientific is building a smart walker for the elderly. We aim to reduce risk of walker-related fall injuries, increase senior independence, and to alleviate the financial burden off healthcare sectors across the globe.','Sentry Scientific Inc. ','[\"Kitchener\"]','Sentry Scientific Inc'),('DocBox is a Waltham based small medical device informatics and analytics Company that was founded in 2007. DocBox is developing an innovative platform in order to create an intelligent internet of things at the point of care. The DocBox platform acquires data from multiple sources within the clinical environment, processes the data, and provides key information and decisions to clinicians at the right time.','Intelligent Point of Care Medical Device Platform','[\"Boston\"]','DocBox'),(NULL,'Inspiring great entrepreneurs and help building successful startups','[\"Lisbon\"]','Beta-i'),('Autistic children will work with many different partners as they grow and develop, like doctors, therapists and teachers. With every new association the parents have to try to communicate their child\'s story, and the partners have to get to know and understand the child.\n\nPragma is an online tool for parents of children with autism to record their history, track their progress, and collaborate with treatment partners.','History, tracking and communication for parents of autistic children','[\"Austin\"]','Pragma'),('CloudClinica is the 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials. This is the first Cloud Data Capture (CDC) system, to empower business users to build clinical studies themselves, remove today\'s high IT dependency and eliminate any financial barrier of entry through a pay-per-CRF pricing and a solution five times cheaper than existing solutions. CloudClinica offers a built-in integration layer for additional eClinical systems on its fully validated and compliant platform.','The 1st cloud-based platform for clinical trials introducing Cloud Data Capture (CDC)','[\"Sunnyvale\"]','CloudClinica'),('Metamason is a healthcare-focused 3D scanning and 3D printing laboratory. Our proprietary Scan·Fit·Print process uses 3D body scanning, patented algorithmic design, and on-demand 3D printing to create individually customized, ergonomic products that are perfectly designed for you. Our flagship product is a revolutionized custom CPAP mask for sleep apnea patients.\n\nOur business model: Invent, De-risk, & License. Our team develops, patents, tests & prototypes custom products, copyrighted algorithms, patentable design processes, materials & printing techniques — all of which can be licensed in modular segments. \n\nAt Metamason, we are inspired by the way the Scan·Fit·Print process enables the cost-efficient, pulled demand production of innovative products shaped by your specific needs. We also believe in a more personal approach to medicine — that\'s why we\'ve developed a method for producing individually customized medical devices that can be worn with comfort, confidence and style. ','SaaS for 3D Printed Products','[\"Pasadena, CA\"]','Metamason'),('Comparadentistas.com is the leading cost comparisons service for dental treatments in Spain.\nWe bring together patients looking for cheaper prices for a desired treatment with dentists that are looking for more costumers. \n“Find a good dentist and service for a cheaper price” is the question. We answer it by offer our users enter their existing cost estimate and receive alternative prices from dentists in their area. \nOur inverse auction model guarantees lower prices, up to 40%. \nTo ensure a high quality of service and treatment, participating dentists are rated by their patients. \n\nOur business model is based on retaining a commission from the dentist for every mediated treatment-lead. It´s proven and highly scalable.\n\nvisit: www.comparadentistas.com','Price comparison of dental treatments','[\"Spain\"]','ComparaDentistas'),('MANOS CTR™ is a medical device for carpal tunnel release (CTR). The procedure is performed using nerve stimulation and ultrasound guidance.  \n\nOpen carpal tunnel release requires a 1-2 inch incision in the palm. The incision is painful and the recovery is extensive. \n\nMANOS CTR™ is performed with an awake patient using local anesthetic. There is no incision in the palm and no stitches are required.\n\nMore than 500,000 carpal tunnel surgeries are performed in the United States annually. \n\n','Ultrasound guided carpal tunnel surgery - least invasive option','[\"San Francisco\"]','Thayer '),('Avomeen Analytical Services is a full-service chemical testing laboratory specializing in deformulation, pharmaceutical testing, product development, and chemical litigation support services.','Chemical Analysis for Product Development','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','Avomeen Analytical Services'),('MoodUp - all dental stuff in one app\n\nWe create mobile apps for developing good healthy habits in children. We connect the app with both their dentists (to get known of any special offers & free slots) as well as with the Amazon Store (to easily buy oral hygiene products in great prices).','Mobile Apps for Dental Care','[\"London\"]','MoodUp'),('CHECK™ is a revolutionary way to assess and monitor Training Readiness and recovery aimed especially for athletes (professional and recreational) engaged in sports requiring strength, explosive power, skill and coordination. These sports include most of the team sports (e.g. football, basketball, hockey and rugby), individual sports requiring skill and coordination (e.g. tennis, golf, athletics and badminton), fight sports (e.g. boxing, wrestling, MMA) and sports requiring explosive power (e.g. fitness, gym, crossfit and bodybuilding). Our solution also works in endurance sports providing additional information to heart-rate based assessments. \n\nCHECK™ is based on the physiological phenomena of muscle reflex generated by specific low-voltage current.The delay and intensity of the muscle reflex describes the total load on the neuro-muscular system of an athlete. \nCHECK™ is designed to be a training aid for athletes, coaches and medical professionals.','CHECK - we make you a better athlete','[\"Oulu\"]','CHECK'),('DIIME is developing a new medical device intended for use in autotransfusion in cases of ruptured ectopic pregnancy and other traumas, where blood can be salvaged from the abdomen and cleaned for reinfusion when donor blood is not available. In these cases, a woman has a massive internal hemorrhage and desperately needs a transfusion, but donor blood is frequently unavailable. Sub-Saharan Africa suffers from chronic shortages of donor blood, which significantly detracts from the ability to provide life-saving surgical care. Hemafuse allows a clinician to safely salvage blood from the internal hemorrhage and filter and transfuse it. DIIME is working closely with clinicians in Ghana to commercialize the technology. To date, we have completed laboratory testing with reconstituted human blood, which showed no damage to the blood cells incurred with the device, and a comparison test between the soup ladle method and Hemafuse using fresh pig blood.','DIIME is creating new medical devices to improve maternal health in developing countries.','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','DIIME'),('Pangianet is a comprehensive digital healthcare solution for patients, healthcare professionals, & hospital systems.\n\nOur solution is practical, easy to use, and very affordable.  Our customers are patients, healthcare professionals and providers, as well as all companies looking to provide added value to their employees through on demand health solutions.\n\nFor patients...Pangianet provides an on-demand answer to your concern\n\nFor doctors..you get enterprise grade tools to better track and diagnose your patients. DICOM for images and media and a complete electronic health record HIPAA compliant and certified by the US National Coordinator of Health Information Technology. No more paying for expensive EHRs. \n\nFor other healthcare professionals,  build your professional profile and generate revenue through professional advice and sales of your products.\n\nAs a hospital communiacate via HL7 standard.  256 bit encryption, save money, say goodbye to paper.\n\nPangianet is the google of health','Anyone Anywhere Anytime Health','[\"Bogota\", \"Earth\", \"Atlanta\", \"Georgia\", \"Colombia\", \"California\", \"North America\", \"South America\", \"Europe\", \"Asia\", \"Africa\", \"Central America\", \"Australia\", \"India\"]','Pangianet'),('The only medical device available directly to consumers, without a prescription, for treating insomnia.  ','Solving Insomnia without Drugs','[\"Portsmouth, NH\"]','InSomniSolv'),('Medix is a unique online solution to a dentist\'s daily professional activities, providing convenience and ease to dentists and patients alike. It keeps records, profiles and appointments necessary for both markets.','Medix is a cloud based clinic management platform for dentists.','[\"Manila\"]','Medix'),('Sensory Health Systems is creating a revolutionary preventive care and early detection platform with initial focus on cardio respiratory care for all age groups and other serious conditions like sleep apnea and hypothermia among newborns. Detection is done using wireless sensors worn by consumers like a bandaid and diagnosis on smartphone.\n\nThe platform is built using the simple philosophy that consumers are architects of their health and that each person is unique. The platform allows the medical team to personalize the risk alerts, thresholds and care based on the digital health record the patient created . The system in addition to diagnosis has adherence & compliance modules making it a complete digital healthcare solution for both the patient and the doctor. \n\nIts a personalized medicine with initial focus on cardio-respiratory care.\n','Early Detection of Cardio-respiratory conditions ','[\"Santa Clara, CA\"]','Sensory Health Systems'),('At IDerma we engage in development of  analytic and interpretive methods to optimize the transformation of increasingly voluminous personal care data, and dermatological data, into proactive, predictive, preventive, and participatory health.','New era of medical apps. Data driven healthcare.','[\"Zagreb\"]','IDerma'),('The superior characteristics of our product will mean that we shall largely displace the currently-available imperfect fertility tools (ovulation predictor kits and monitors) - and not only that. Because of the way our sensor works, it will also offer unheard of applications such as built-in screening for cervical cancer and other STDs. In fact, we are introducing not a single product but a medical technology platform with numerous applications (yes, much like the smart phones).   ','Personal fertility monitor for home use, ','[\"Colorado\"]','bioZhena Corp'),('Soxxy is a performance-fashion sock brand with unique IP. Soxxy\'s XO non-slip grip is applied to the inside top rim of the ankle, knee and thigh-high socks keeping your socks securely in place.  Soxxy\'s tagline \"socks hug you all day long\" is a play on the XO grip.\nSoxxyAir are travel compression socks designed for airline passengers and crew. SoxxyAir will launch on SkyMall and select global airlines Q1 2014.\nSoxxy02 are athletic compression socks designed for skiing, soccer, football, rugby, baseball, cycling, running, lacrosse, basketball, etc.\nSoxxyRx are medical compression socks designed for post-operative patients, DVT, pregnant women, diabetics...\nSoxxy is adding much needed STYLE to compression socks. We\'re also changing up the packaging and distribution channels.','Soxxy is a performance-fashion sock brand.','[\"New York City\"]','Soxxy'),('We think that writing on a mobile device should be as easy as picking up a pen and scribbling down thoughts on a piece of paper. We are creating an input method that is:\n\n• Natural because it mimics handwriting. Letters are entered