e we drive massive exposure and let the crowd decide which ideas they like best. MedStartr innovation acceleration and crowdfunding clients succeed over 40% of the time as shown by the 108 partnerships, thousands of new customers, and over $25MM in investments they have garnered after going live on our platform. MedStartr has become the go-to platform to accelerate innovation in healthcare through our campaigns, challenges, and events.that drive press, partnerships, adoption, and funding. We bring together a \"Crowd that Cares\", namely patients, providers, institutions, payers, investors and corporate partners, and create a wave of support, adoption, and investmentlet the crowd show which ideas will be the best investments. We look forward to launching our equity platform in Q1 2014. ','Healthcare Crowd Funding','[\"New York City\"]','MedStartr'),('Our product/service is focused on addressing the problem of finding an appointments that suit your agenda and your needs at the same time, from anywhere, using geo-location and outstanding userfriendly interface from your smartphone, pad or pc.  Healthcare is a very dynamic market and because of this, its very difficult to be aware of all the market offer of practitioners or centres for health studies.\n\nThe site is inspired in the Zocdoc model but applied adapted to the Latin American market.','Intelligent Medical Appointment Booking System for Latin America','[\"South America\"]','BuscoTurno'),('Until now, there has been little effort to stabilize or control a patient’s extremity during intravenous therapy.  An unstable limb may result in accidental needle sticks costing healthcare providers billions of dollars each year in treatment costs.  \n\nOur device is the first to stabilize a patient\'s extremity when starting an IV or drawing blood in an effort to reduce the number of preventable needle sticks.  Our versatile design is attachable to any ambulance cot or hospital bed.','Reduce Needlesticks with IV Support','[\"San Diego\"]','Life Support'),('NeuroTek Medical is an emerging device company developing non-invasive, electronic neuromodulation devices for the treatment of a variety of pathologies. Our founders have been a part of nearly $30M in active medical device development. Key personnel are inventors on 20+ patents and applications and own 15 issued patents in the medical device space. \r\n \r\nCurrently, NeuroTek is developing a battery-operated, self-administered home-based device that can safely and transcutaneously stimulate the occipital nerve for treating migraines. TONES is a non-surgical, non-drug based solution that is a cost-effective option for immediate relief at the onset of a migraine. Migraine headache pain is a serious debilitating condition affecting more than 10% of the population, with accepted figures of 30 million sufferers in the US and 240 million worldwide. NeuroTek\'s goal is to provide an alternative treatment option to the 50% of episodic migraineurs who are dissatisfied with their current therapy. ','The Future of Migraine Relief','[\"Dallas\"]','NeuroTek Medical'),('Due to its unique rectangular platform, the patented Proximerge dental implant system is the only product in the industry which naturally mimics the emergence profile of molars.  This eliminates food and bacteria traps, distributes stresses on the jaw bone, and provides a better foundation for crowns.  Molars represent 70% of the $3.1B dental implant market.  The company has applied for 510k clearance from the FDA and expects European regulatory approval (CE Mark) by May 2012.  ','Dental implants & surgical tools','[\"Colorado Springs\"]','Grant Dental Technology Corp.'),('SafeWhite developed after 4 years of research by leading protein chemists based upon how nature provides color and adheres in wet environments. SafeWhite combines the adhesion and fluorescent lighting power of marine life to create a patent-pending combination that whitens teeth by coating them, not by bleaching and etching them as is more commonly seen with the leading teeth whiteners. What that means is no harmful peroxide touching your gums or your teeth. Instead, a veneer of white that shines white in a manner similar to how your teeth typically fluoresce, sits in a microscopic layer on the surface of your teeth, undetectable to touch and tasteless.','Teeth whitening inspired by nature','[\"Dublin, OH\"]','SafeWhite'),('Better.me measures and displays your overall health in the socially connected world. \n\nThe platform distills users’ health-related social connections and medical results into a single numerical representation.  Attempting to maintain and improve upon the score, users prescribe a better life for themselves.  Revenue will be derived from targeted advertising and fees paid by insurance companies for the referral of healthy new customers. ','Klout for health.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Better.me'),(NULL,'Beating cancer though innovative RF devices','[\"Montreal\"]','EMcision International Inc'),('Portable Medical Technology Ltd develops quality, accredited & trusted mobile software for medical specialists to reduce medical errors, improve efficiencies & progress patient communication. We combine the essential tools specialists need into easy-to-use smartphone & tablet applications that are FDA and CE approved and provide the latest updated tools to support critical medical decision-making. We launched our first app designed specifically for oncology professionals in December 2012. ','CE/FDA approved apps for specialist medics','[\"London\"]','Portable Medical Technology'),('Created by a group of type one diabetic students at the University of California, Davis, Liveabetes aims to be both a resource for diabetics to track and monitor their condition and a way to let those closest to you stay up to date with live updates for blood glucose, insulin delivery, and more.','The central hub for diabetics and those around them.','[\"Davis\"]','Liveabetes'),('CerMed brings IPAP, a personal cervical sample collector for standard laboratory testing and CerMark, a point of care, antibody based cervical cancer screening system which includes CerMap, a patented sample collector and cervical mapping device, screening cartridge employing nanotechnology and reader console providing test results in 15 minutes or less. CerMark will allow physicians to provide patient feedback at time of test or in the field where laboratory services are not easily available. ','Innovative point of care diagnostics','[\"Monterey\"]','CerMed'),('Cirle is a growing medical technology incubator based in Miami, Florida. We are focused on creating transformative medical technologies that will truly move the needle in healthcare delivery. Our mission is to to develop innovative medical devices and products with the aim of improving ocular health and conditions that cause blindness.','Engineering ophthalmic medical technologies','[\"Miami\"]','Cirle'),('DAQRI is the world’s leading augmented reality developer, providing custom software and creative solutions to clients across a broad spectrum of industries. From groundbreaking interactive consumer marketing campaigns to multi-year industrial manufacturing deployments, we help businesses leverage the latest innovations in computer-human interaction.','4D Augmented Reality Platform','[\"Los Angeles\"]','DAQRI'),('The Owlet Baby Monitor is a sock, that measures heart rate and oxygen levels and alerts parent\'s if their child stops breathing during the night. The number one concern of any parent is the health and safety of their child.  The Owlet Baby Monitor addresses this concern by combining hospital-proven pulse oximetry (vital-sign-reading equipment) with modern communication in a personalized system that grows with your child.  By monitoring heart rate and blood oxygen levels (how well an infant is breathing), life-saving data is available at the click of a button, right where parents want it.  The Owlet Baby Monitor is up all night so parents don’t have to be, providing peace of mind and allowing them the rest they need with the assurance that their baby is getting the rest he or she needs.  Even in its early stages, this product has received impressive pull from the market, being featured on or in ABC, The Huffington Post, Mashable, Gizmodo, and 40 other U.S. and foreign news outlets.  ','Baby Sock That Monitors Heart Rate and Oxygen ','[\"Provo\"]','Owlet Baby Care'),('Glytrix is an early stage biotech company that is developing a novel platform technology for tissue healing and regeneration. We are leading this development with Pellagen, a locally delivered drug in late stage preclinical development for promoting healthy scar-free healing in the skin.','Pellagen promotes scar-free healing in the skin','[\"San Francisco\"]','Glytrix'),('Contact lenses with disappearing ink. Why?  Outside the eye they are hard to find, can get mixed up between right and left eyes & most importantly can be flipped and inserted backwards into the eye. This is a disruptive technology that will provide a significant edge to contact lens manufactures - in addition to increased margins.     ','Contact Lenses With Disappearing Ink that are Better, Friendlier & Safer   ','[\"Tel Aviv-yafo\"]','Leuko Tech'),('GITPx Investments is a Singapore based Corporate Angel Investor which invests in Startup & Seed companies in China, India, Singapore, Indonesia, Vietnam and other countries in Asia and beyond. GITPx is part of Rutledge Vine Capital which focuses on global investments.\n\nGITPx is driven by a high calibre team with a combined experience of over 80 years spent in Senior Management positions in diverse sectors in IT, Mobile, Gaming, Digital Media, Hospitality & Real Estate, Consumer marketing, Oil & Gas and the Commodities space.\n\nCollaborative partnerships with other Angels and Incubators in various countries for Co-investment and cross-pollination of ideas across technopreneurs, technology 