-medicinal knee osteoarthritis treatment','[\"Austin\"]','Articulate Labs'),('Venture Catalysts is a company focused on commercialization of technologies through entrepreneurship. By supporting visionary researchers and entrepreneurs releasing the full potential of their technologies, the company acts as a catalyst on the development of new technology–based ventures','Shaping Technologies into Business','[\"Porto\"]','Venture Catalysts'),('Providence Medical Technology created DTRAX to be the least invasive treatment for neck and arm pain caused by pinched nerves in the neck (foraminal stenosis).  The procedure is performed under x-ray guidance through 1 cm tubes. DTRAX offers patients the benefits of minimal trauma and blood loss, greatly reduced scarring and reduces the need for more invasive cervical surgeries. ','neck surgery reinvented','[\"San Francisco\"]','Providence Medical Technology'),('Just in time kits..\nKits that capture essential safety items for car, home, and pack platforms.','Just in time Kit','[\"Denver\"]','Jit-Kit'),('We built a web-based and mobile app platform that allows individuals to book, reschedule and cancel appointments with any Service Businesses from one place.  For the Service Businesses, the product to them is inserting a \"book now\" button on their website powered by Chimpped.','Book Any Appointments From One Place','[\"San Jose\"]','Mustang Ventures'),('Orzata\'s Protoboard enables engineers to rapidly develop sophisticated methods of analyzing images or video. Protoboard reduces the time required to perform image analysis by months and saves companies millions of dollars in product development cost.','Making devices aware','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Orzata'),('The opportunity: take the world’s greatest glanceable display – the watch - and reinvent it as a stylish and simple, glanceable display for when we are really mobile and on the go. Glance is a powerful interface for mobile internet services.\n\nMeta Watch helps consumers do what they are already trying to do - consume mobile alerts & notifications effortlessly. This has become a big problem because alerts are often missed because of we carry our phones (guys in pocket; ladies in handbag). \n','Smart watches that function as a glanceable display for critical alerts & the mobile web','[\"Dallas\"]','Meta Watch'),('Autograft is the soft bone found within the hard white outer shell of most bones. Orthopaedic surgeons oftentimes harvest this autograft from a patient in order to use the bone graft in another part of the body that requires fusion or healing. \n\nBOSS Medical is currently developing its first product, the BOSS Harvester - a novel, intuitive system which will enable surgeons to harvest autologous bone graft (autograft) utilizing a minimally invasive approach. \n','Novel Minimally Invasive Orthopaedic Technologies','[\"Baltimore\"]','BOSS Medical'),(' AEGLE Life™. Where health, mobile tech and big data meet.\n\nStaying healthy is a challenge to most of us. AEGLE Life™ provides a smart, personalised health and wellness platform collating and analysing data from mobile enabled devices, which combined with self-assessments and scientific evidence, provide insights that help individuals make better lifestyle choices. AEGLE Work™ also provides aggregated insights that help companies validate their health initiatives.\n \nWe plan our initial pilot with a major employer in early 2014. The pilot will validate outcomes related to mental wellbeing and men’s health. The capabilities will be packaged into the AEGLE Work™ product, which will be sold to employers starting with the resources industry. Longer term, the platform will also collect data and provide correlations between environmental factors and human telemetry, a big data play of interest to public policy and technology developers.','Personalised, data-driven health, prevention and wellness','[\"Perth\"]','AEGLE Life'),('Neuroskill is a device that measures impairment in fine motor control by recording and analyzing the patient\'s handwriting dynamics in real time.  With the help of the Neuroskill device, physicians can potentially diagnose Parkinon\'s Disease as well as monitor progress of pharmacological treatment.','Surrogate Biomarker for Parkinson\'s Disease','[\"Boulder\"]','iNeuroskill '),('eMedPub publishes international ejournals in several specialty areas of  Medical Sciences. Articles reporting original basic sciences, clinical, epidemiological, policy, and social research which are of a high standard and contribute to the overall knowledge of the field of Medical Sciences are published. The eJournals publish Original Papers, Concise Communications, Field Notes, Case Reports, Research Letters, and Correspondence, as well as invited Editorial Reviews, and Editorial Comments.','Series of online Medical Journals','[\"Mumbai\"]','emedpub'),('Apeliotus is commercializing a diagnostic for early detection of an eye disease call age-related macular degeneration. AMD is the leading cause of adult blindness in developed countries, affecting one in six people over age 65 and one in three over age 75. Despite the trememdous value of early detection, there is currently no good means for diagnosis before significant vision loss has already occurred. Our AdaptDx can detect and track AMD from its beginning stages allowing early intervention.','ophthalmic diagnostic for age-related macular degeneration','[\"Hershey\"]','Apeliotus Vision Science'),('Our medical devise helps in :\n\n1.Digitizing the inventory management  ( including automatic reordering ) of injectable medications by measuring initial and remaining  liquid volumes  inside sealed vials non-invasively \n2.Improving  practice managements by digitizing medical records for human , medical practice and hospitals and  animals and VETS  by cutting costs and enhancing traceability.  \n         \n','Non-Invasive Liquid Level Measurement ','[\"Lexington-fayette\"]','Fluid Management Systems'),('Medical Joyworks aims to inject fun into medicine by creating mobile games for healthcare professionals and patients.','Making Learning Medicine Fun','[\"Santiago\"]','Medical Joyworks'),('TeleSkin makes hardware, software, and mobile solutions for the early diagnosis of skin cancer, skin health, and other dermatological conditions.  skinScan is our Windows 8 mobile and tablet, Healthvault connected, application for patients and consumers to analyze their skin and connect with doctors for expert opinions. skinScan integrates seamlessly with our integrated hardware/software solution which includes a clinical multi-spectral dermascope for detailed dermascopic skin analysis.','Mobile and clinical skin cancer analysis','[\"Belgrade\"]','TeleSkin'),('Vital Nanometrics is developing a new class of glucose monitors that provide accurate diabetes management in a pain-free manner. Pain-free, automated and accurate blood-sugar monitoring awaits the diabetic. Significant cost reduction will result for both the patient and insurer. The device is based on patented nanotechnology developed by our team members.','A glucose monitor that is truly pain-free yet cost effective.','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Vital Nanometrics'),('Industries we serve: all tech and medical device\nCustomers: from early stage startups to established corporate.\nServices:\ninvestor presentation decks,\nbranding and identity,\npromo/product animated video,\ngraphic design, \nweb design/development,\nmarketing materials design, \ncreative strategy consulting. \n\ncreate at theoriacreative dot com','Marketing design: we translate intricate tech ideas into simple visuals','[\"Redwood City\"]','Theoria Creative'),('We have developed the First Medical Travel Marketplace and are in beta testing mode now. Looking for funding to rebrand, support marketing and add more technology enhancements.  This new platform will allow anyone the ability to directly connect with quality medical and dental professionals worldwide. The system offers resources to coordinate all aspects of their medical travel procedure, as well as purchase all needed supplemental products or services from our merchant marketplace.','First Medical Tourism Marketplace','[\"Los Angeles\"]','SkyMedicus'),('Healbe is the simple way to manage your body weight, health and sport results, whoever you are.\n\nWristband on your hand fully automatically \n- calculates how much calories earned with the foods and spent duting any activity\n- trackes your heart rate, pulse wave, blood pressure, respiratory rate, temperature, sleep phase, level of dehydration and stress. \n\nApp on your mobile device synchronizes with wristband via bluetooth and gives you understanding, what happens with your body','Automatically trackes your body weight, health and sport results','[\"Moscow\"]','Healbe'),('Medelita designs, manufactures and sells best in class medical apparel, and is the only company making lab coats and scrubs specifically for high-income clinicians including Physicians, Surgeons, PAs, NPs, Dentists & Vets.\n\nLab coats & scrubs of unmatched quality and innovation. Focus on ergonomic fit, high-performance fabrics, and styling representative of aptitude and prestige. Innovation through gender specific designs, professional styling, and concierge logo design services.  \n\n\n \n','Lululemon for Physicians ','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Medelita '),('Nearly 1 in 4 patients undergoing surgery for early-stage breast cancer will require re-operation. Cancer requires re-operation so frequently because surgeons lack tools to detect cancerous tissue during the operation.  \n\nLightpoint Medical is developing a novel molecular imaging technology to detect cancer in real-time during surgery. Our technology reduces the cost and size of a nuclear medicine scanner by 100-fold, enabling it to integrate into the operating room. Image-guided surgery has the potential to provide more accurate cancer treatment and thereby reduce the need for re-operation.','Reducing the burden of cancer through image-guided surgery','[\"United Kingdom\"]','Lightpoint Medical'),('Our first product is a drinkable mouthwash made of natural ingredients and is formulated to meet the guidelines of The American Academy of Pediatrics and American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry in its recommendation for cavity prevention.  Our second product has two active ingredients that specifically eliminate the cavity-causing bacteria and prevent the bacteria from adhering to the surface of the teeth. ','Pediatric Drinkable Anti-Cavity Mouthwash','[\"Hamilton\"]','Apollonia Health'),('Care Concepts has turned an old school DME (Durable Medical Equipment) company that bills Medicare to a high tech, very efficient technology based company reducing overhead while benefiting from high margin business.  We specialize in the Diabetic meter and monthly supplies.  Customers have a hassle free home delivery while we handle all of the paper work for billing Medicare.','Durable Medical Equipment','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Care Concepts'),('Entac Medical is developing medical devices for predictive and diagnostic medicine based on a novel platform technology, audio spectral analysis. Its first application, PrevisEA, is a late stage, Class II noninvasive, disposable device that is clinically proven to predict post-operative ileus (POI) in surgical patients (GI paralysis occurs 2-6 days after surgery in 25% of patients). Prediction of ileus risk improves treatment protocols and patient outcomes while reducing readmissions and saving hospitals millions of dollars in unnecessary treatment costs. \n\n-	Applied to the abdomen with existing medical adhesive tape \n-	Enclosed microphone detects certain sounds emitted from the bowels\n-	Microchip containing signal-processing algorithms analyzes sounds\n-	LED display indicates the level of risk that the patient will develop POI\n-	Worn up to 12 hours for maximum accuracy\n','Late-stage medical device for predictive and diagnostic medicine','[]','Entac Medical'),('Wave\'s mobile app allows epileptics to use their Smartphones paired wirelessly with a peripheral device and wearable sensors as an ambulatory EEG solution for the remote monitoring of epileptics. The app is downloaded free (e.g. Android, iOS, Blackberry) the peripheral and sensors purchased/rented through the app. Our services are fully reimbursable by payer groups at rate of approximately $750/day for each patient. ','Ambulatory EEG Mobile App','[\"Chicago\", \"San Diego\"]','Wave Technology Group'),('Obtaining a homogenous population of cells from a complex mixture is essential for improved downstream applications like QPCR, genomics, and imaging. Fluorescence Activated Cell Sorters (FACS) analyze and sort thousands of cells per minute and are essential systems for most biomedical research labs ($1B instrument market). NanoCellect was spunout from UCSD to commercialize a disruptive technology for analyzing and sorting cells at 1/5th the cost of current systems. The initial product, WOLF Cell Sorter is a small, affordable, and easy-to-use bench-top cell sorter with features and performance comparable to high-end complex flow cytometers that are primarily found in shared core facilities. The platform is accompanied by disposable microfluidic chips that makes setup and sorting easier while reducing contamination and improving cell viability during sorting. Since inception, NanoCellect has won 7 grants and contracts from the NIH for over $3.3M in non-dilutional funding.\n\n','Cell sorting made accessible (CoinStar for Cell Biologists)','[\"San Diego\"]','NanoCellect Biomedical, Inc.'),(NULL,'Delivering industry-leading viricidal and bacteriocidal technologies to reduce infections.','[\"San Francisco\"]','IonArmour'),('Fitrock is an online based personal coaching service. We help young men get in shape and bring sexy back to life. After all, like you, we are sick and tired of counting calories for WeightWatchers or having to workout our entire free time next to all these wanna-be bodybuilders. We have a more sustainable solution, that\'s fool proof: Gradual changes towards building healthier everyday habits. And the best part: We personally go every step of the way with our customers. What you get (among other great stuff):\n\n- A personal coach, providing you with personal feedback and plans on the platform\n- Daily missions, goals and challenges to gradually change your habits.\n- A desktop & mobile app to stay on track!','Online personal health coaching','[\"San Francisco\"]','Fitrock'),('\nRAY is an integrated portable device designed to assist the community of visually impaired people and their families in their daily life. RAY leverages latest mobility technologies to increase independence, enrich social life and improve accessibility of essential services for the visually impaired.','Mobile accessibility tool for the Visually Impaired','[\"Israel\"]','Project-RAY'),('Hiwave is an online retail store of dry seafood. With a three generations family history in Chinese medicine, Hiwave started with a strong foundation in the traditional business; with web presence and e-marketing, the company has expanded its business coverage to US, UK, Germany, Netherlands and Canada. A classic example of meshup between old business with new technology.','Online retail store of chinese dry seafood.','[\"Hong Kong\"]','Hiwave Dry Seafood'),('Our company is bringing stem cell therapy to the skin rejuvenation field, with a fast and inexpensive method to use your own cells to make your skin look young again!','Next-generation skin rejuvenation','[\"Santiago\"]','Cell Therapy'),('We help retail and ecommerce businesses build APIs so that they can sell their products on online marketplaces like Magento, Amazon, eBay, osCommerce.\n\nAn API which stands for Application Programming Interface, is a way to let businesses sell their products outside of their core ecommerce site. Except they take a lot technical expertise to build and manage and can get expensive very quickly.\n\nPliant Labs allows businesses to build APIs with an easy use tools and then publish their product data to marketplaces in 3 easy steps.\n\nWe then manage it for them. Its free to use and businesses only pay when they sell products or the APIs get accessed by marketplaces or developers.','We enable businesses to create, publish & use APIs to sell more of everything, anywhere.','[\"Atlanta\"]','Pliant Labs'),('PeoplePledge is a medical crowdfunding website, helping people to easily and quickly create online pledge pages to raise funds for loved ones with an illness or disability. Once a pledge page has been created and approved, then friends, family and extended social networks can make pledges on the page within seconds.','Medical Crowdfunding Platform','[\"Sydney\"]','PeoplePledge'),('Fosmo Med Introduced Maji™, a Forward Osmosis (FO) based IV solutions to be made using any water at the point of care. The IV bags are shipped sans water, thus: reduce the shipping cost; increase the product shelf life; reduce storage costs; and, reduces the risk of scrap due to leakage. Initial target is disaster relief org such as the Red Cross and will partner with existing manufacturers/distributors to serve the current market. We are a Delaware incorporated company. Market of $7.6B.','Saving Lives Through Technology','[\"San Mateo\"]','Fosmo Med'),('\"Smile Merchants” provides dental services to semi-urban & rural population of India, viz. more than 800 million people.\nWe aim to improve the national standards of oral health by opening up a nation-wide chain of dental clinics in non-metro India, which accounts for more than 70% of our population.','The McDonald\'s of Dentistry!!!','[\"Mumbai\"]','Smile Merchants'),('Adaptive is commercializing advanced diabetes technology research from the University of Virginia\'s Center for Diabetes Technology.\n\nThe CDC predicts 1 in 3 in the US will have diabetes by 2050.\n\nWe move diabetes care from a dumb, context-free regime to a connected, contextualized one.  We improve diabetes sufferers\' lives, differentiate and increase profit for our customers (big pharma device makers), and create an ecosystem of applications around data previously considered dark matter.','Diabetes Care for the Internet Age','[\"Charlottesville\"]','Adaptive Medical Technologies'),('Umbie Office is the leading all-in-one practice management solution for small to medium sized dental clinics; it\'s the best way to apply healthcare information technology to your practice. Imagine having the freedom to access your practice\'s information from anywhere; check schedules and finish up notes from your home, or even review charts while on the road.','Practice Management in the Cloud','[\"Connecticut\"]','Umbie Office'),('Diabetes Daily helps people around the world become healthier, happier, and less expensive to the health care system. Originally founded as a social network for people with diabetes, we have evolved into a social educational platform powered by behavior modification techniques. With over 70,000 members, 3 million annual visitors, and major advertisers like Sanofi-Aventis, Roche Diabetes Care, Novo Nordisk, and Medtronic, we have the traction, influence, and platform to save lives and money!','Empowering healthier and happier lives','[\"Cleveland\"]','Diabetes Daily'),('The secure cloud platform at the center of our technology enables a network of physicians, nurses, technicians, and billing specialists to securely access and annotate patient ECG tracings. From credentialed mobile devices, a recipient can instantly access captured ECG tracings, as well as select alerts and push notifications to aid the rapid turnaround of completed reports by busy practices and hospital departments.\r\n\r\nAs patients are increasingly treated in ambulatory surgery centers, rural hospitals, and care clinics, there is a need for technology to provide connectivity among geographically distant clinicians. Further, as technology travels within hospitals and to patients, conventional ECG devices are physically challenging to transport. The InvisionHeart ECG is small enough to be carried in a lab coat pocket, powerful enough to operate for several days, and transmit data via a HIPAA compliant, 256-bit encryption system.','InvisionHeart is developing a cardiac data solution to serve care providers.','[\"Nashville\"]','InvisionHeart'),('Walleye Technologies has developed a next-generation\nportable imaging technology that enables one to “see”—into and through—\nsolid objects, without relying on harmful X-rays. Based on patented microwave and lens technology, Walleye has created a new “imaging category” – the\nmicrowave digital camera. Markets include, Do-It-Yourself (DIY) home repair (e.g., locating pipesand wires in walls), homeland security (scanning packages and people noninvasively), and industrial inspection..','Handheld millimeter wave camera','[\"Boston\"]','Walleye Technologies'),('We\'re building a SAAS EMR for Canadian physicians. Its completely web-based and takes only minutes to set up without having to purchase costly servers or extra hardware. Best of all, no set-up fees.\n\nWe\'re taking the hassle out of EMR for Canadian docs. \n\nOur software is a complete practice management solution including full charting, scheduling and billing capabilities.','SAAS Electronic Medical Records for Canada','[\"Victoria\"]','Cloud Practice'),('Sparo Labs is bringing the power of modern technology to the world of asthma. We\'re developing an award-winning, patent-pending spirometer system that can be produced for a fraction of the cost of current devices today, while seamlessly connecting with smartphones and other mobile devices. Our powerful technology empowers patients to quantitatively track and proactively manage their asthma, while equipping doctors with the power of objective and real-time data to better treat and more efficiently manage their patients.','Bringing the power of modern technology to the world of asthma.','[\"Saint Louis\"]','Sparo Labs'),('AllaQuix™ is a professional-grade hemostat cleared by the FDA for over-the-counter (OTC) use and is now available without a prescription.\n \nAllaQuix™ is designed to work in everyone, even people who have trouble stopping bleeding.\n \nAllaQuix™ is a sterile gauze pad made of medical-grade chitosan.  Chitosan-based hemostats are not readily available to consumers, but have been widely used in the professional medical setting in trauma and surgical settings, including by the U.S. Military.  IMT is now bringing this professional-­grade technology directly to the consumer.\n\nFirst Market: Minor Bleeding\n1 in 3 adults in the US are prone to Nuisance Bleeding. Their blood is incapable of clotting in a few minutes as a result of genetic factors or medications (such as prescription blood thinners or daily aspirin therapy). This represents 80 million people in the US.  There are millions of additional people that want to stop bleeding fast.','Medical Grade Products for Consumers','[\"Minneapolis\"]','Inspiration Medical Technology, Inc.'),('FindDoc is uniquely positioned to serve as Hong Kong’s first multilingual centralized online healthcare information and appointment platform. FindDoc lets you find doctor\'s information and also make appointment with them for free.','Hong Kong’s first online healthcare information and appointment platform','[\"Hong Kong\"]','FindDoc'),('Tidepool is building an open platform and better apps to help people reduce the burden of managing type 1 diabetes.','Open source diabetes platform and apps.','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Tidepool'),('Smarter doctors = a healthier world\n\nAgoraMed is an open marketplace for medical education courses. \nExpert doctors and researchers with something to teach can come to our site, create a course and then share it with learners, for free or for a price. Medical learners can then enroll and start learning. Our robust rating system promotes the best content to the top, and rewards the best teachers.\n\nOur goal: to create the highest quality, most comprehensive medical education library ever created.','Marketplace for Medical Education Courses','[\"Durham\"]','AgoraMed'),('The LifeCradle preserves, monitors and transports hearts used in transplantation and will replace the picnic cooler currently used.  The LifeCradle has been proven in published research at leading academic research centers to significantly extend the life of procured hearts from 4 to 24 hours.  Over seventy percent of donated hearts are NOT transplanted in many cases because of a lack of preservation time in the picnic cooler...the LifeCradle will save lives and improve transplant outcomes.  ','Organ Preservation Device for Transplantation','[\"Dallas\"]','Organ Transport Systems'),('iLowerBP is a easy-to-do hypertension fitness & preventive maintenance program designed to lower blood pressure naturally in just 12 minutes a day. The complete iLowerBP program includes an instructor-led exercise video, High Blood Pressure For Dummies®, a convenient at-home blood pressure monitor and access to iLowerBP\'s online journal to track your results. ','Hypertension Fitness & Preventive Maintenance Program','[\"Chicago\"]','♥ iLowerBP'),('Longevity Biotech is developing novel therapeutics to treat the unmet needs of Cardiovascular, Metabolics and Oncology patients worldwide.  Our Hybridtide molecular scaffold has unprecedented and medically necessary characteristics which enable us to pursue novel mechanisms of action, a requirement in todays competitive biotechnology marketplace.','','[\"Philadelphia\"]','Longevity Biotech'),('TroopsDirect.org is the nation’s leading non-profit supplier to our units in Afghanistan and beyond.  Contrary to other organizations, TroopsDirect supplies entire units of 1000+ servicemembers in bulk.  We communicate daily with military command, filling and shipping their specific requests often within 24 hours. TroopsDirect has filled ‘orders’ totaling over 10 tons for items including critically needed nutritional, medical, hygiene & equipment supplies. Nobody does what TroopsDirect.org does.','Real-time critical support for our deployed troops','[\"San Francisco\"]','TroopsDirect'),('Eski tech is developing RemindMe, an automatic medicine dispenser for dosage packed medicine. \n\nWith RemindMe we intend to increase medical compliance and thereby increase people’s quality of life.\n\nIt is estimated that patients who don’t take their medicine as prescribed, cost the US healthcare system about $290 billion in avoidable medical spending each year.\n','Medical Solutions','[\"Reykjavik\"]','Eski Tech'),('One-in-eight women in U.S. will get breast cancer at some point in their lives. It is the most common non-skin cancer for American women. Early stage breast cancer is treated by removing the tumor then irradiating the whole breast to eliminate any remaining cancer cells. Yet post-operative radiation is problematic. It requires five to seven weeks of daily irradiation sessions, results in troubling short and long-term side effects, and costs more than the surgery itself. The result is an unfortunate and dangerous reality: one-in-three patients prematurely discontinue radiation therapy, and a similar proportion must undergo re-operation to remove cancer that was missed. We have designed an ablation probe that will allow surgeons to perform an intra-operative procedure that destroys residual cancer cells in minutes instead of weeks, does not require dangerous ionizing radiation, and dramatically reduces treatment costs compared to conventional therapy.','Making breast cancer treatment faster, safer, more convenient, and less expensive.','[\"Chicago\"]','Innoblative Designs'),('Medicinal marijuana is a multi-million dollar industry in Colorado.  Colorado Springs alone has over 30 medicinal shops open today, however the majority of these shops are low-grade facilities, run by incapable or unprofessional owners/staff.  Even while lacking, patients deal with these facilities unwillingly due to a lack of local options for their needs. Sativa Medicinal Marijuana Center will change that, giving the customer the most professional experience in the alternative medicine field.','Higher standard Medicinal Marijuana shop','[\"Colorado Springs\"]','Sativa Medicinal Marijuana Center'),('Immudicon is developing MacroVax, an intracellular vaccine delivery technology, to activate the immune system against cancer and potentially other disease indications.\n\nInitial research & trials of our technology have been shown in vitro in both mouse and human cell types, as well as in vivo to explicate T-cell specificity to tumor antigens, cytokine activation profiles, and early-stage prophylactic trials.','Training the body\'s immune system to defeat cancer & other deadly diseases.','[\"Washington, DC\"]','Immudicon'),('\"It has been a long time since a new app has changed the way I look at how a task can be accomplished. LogFrog DB is a truly new experience in diabetes management on a mobile device.\" —diabeticnerd.com\n\nAmphistyle\'s flagship product, LogFrog DB, helps people with diabetes track and understand the myriad factors that affect and reflect control of their condition.  Its beautiful, uniquely non-clinical user interface has gained a passionate user following and praise in the press.','Mobile health rethought + redesigned','[\"San Francisco\"]','Amphistyle'),('Grand prize winner 2012 Wisconsin Governor\'s business plan competition!  Rowheels solves a key human factors problem.  By pulling the handrim instead of pushing, Rowheels propels a wheelchair user forward with less effort and reduced strain on shoulders, joints and muscles. It replaces the traditional wheels of a manual wheelchair, reversing the motion and corresponding forces required to propel a wheelchair.  Rowheels is a market changer, transforming the lives of wheelchair users forever.','The Wheel Reinvented','[\"Madison\"]','Rowheels'),('Improving the outcomes of lumbar spine proceedures with a new interbody device.\nFully funded, Institutional and strategic investors\n\n2010 - initial invesors\n2011 - FDA approval\n2012 - traction in the marketplace\n2013 - sales and marketing initiatives','Expandable lumbar interbody fusion technology','[\"San Francisco\"]','CoAlign');
