INSERT INTO `startups_seed_longinfo` VALUES (NULL,NULL,'[]','Biographicon'),(NULL,'Jamglue (YCombinator S\'06) was the biggest music remixing community on the web.','[]','Jamglue'),('Notifo lets companies send mobile push notifications to their users without building mobile apps. It\'s far cheaper than SMS. Take a test drive at http://notifo.com.','Twilio for the mobile data-layer','[\"San Francisco\"]','Notifo'),(NULL,'AdWords for the Recruiting Industry','[\"San Francisco\"]','Snaptalent'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"Arlington\"]','Tipjoy'),(NULL,NULL,'[]','Wundrbar'),(NULL,NULL,'[]','Youlicit'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','1000memories'),('Often times when you are browsing the web you will find an awesome photo of a gorgeous landscape, marvelous city, amazing beach area or event, but you can’t find out the exact location of where the photo was made? It sometimes says a country or city, but most of the time you are left guessing. Frustrating?\nThis is where Anywhere comes in!\nWith Anywhere every single photo has it’s own GPS-tag for you to explore and our built in navigation system helps you easily track and navigate to that location. Share photos instantly with family, friends and even authorities for immediate response in emergency situations. Eg. an accident happens right in front of you, snap and share a photo through Anywhere and put in your local authority hashtags. This way authorities instantly get a clearer view of what they are dealing with, and can easily navigate to its location through our navigation system. Anywhere pushes exploring, traveling and public safety to the next level. Your journey starts Anywhere.','Find out the exact location where every photo was taken, and easily visit them!','[\"Amsterdam\"]','Anywhere'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"San Francisco\"]','Auctomatic'),('BackType is a marketing intelligence platform that helps brands and agencies understand the business impact of social media. Our dashboard helps marketers quantify and profile engagement and audiences so they can make better marketing decisions. You can try the free product at http://www.backtype.com','Acquired by Twitter','[\"San Francisco\"]','BackType'),(NULL,'Makes it ridiculously easy to buy and sell pre-owned gift cards','[\"San Francisco\"]','CardPool'),('Carsabi makes finding and purchasing cars easy again.\n\nSimply indicate what you\'re looking for, and we\'ll find the best deal whether on Ebay, Craigslist, or a nearby dealership lot. We also dynamically inform model choices with guided comparison and individually computed TCO (total cost of ownership).\n\nTry our instantaneous search and see an automotive shopping experience that is fun instead of agonizing.\n','all the cars on the internet','[\"Mountain View\"]','Carsabi'),('Clickpass offered webmasters a single code installation with which they could allow their users to log in using Google, Facebook, AOL, Microsoft or OpenID.\n\nThe company was founded in June 2007 and acquired by Yola.com in December 2008.','','[]','Clickpass'),('DailyBooth lets users follow their friends and update them in real-time through the use of pictures and status updates.',NULL,'[]','Dailybooth'),('Divvyshot allows groups of friends to share their photos easily, at their full resolutions.\n','Allows groups of friends to share their photos easily','[\"San Francisco\"]','Divvyshot'),('GazeHawk allows advertisers to see whether or not users are looking at ads.  By accessing, via opt-in, a user\'s webcam, GazeHawk can tell where on a page they are looking.  This data provides unique insight into the effectiveness of brand advertising.','Better display ads via eye tracking','[\"Mountain View\"]','GazeHawk'),(NULL,'GraffitiGeo was part of YC S2009 program. GraffitiGeo was acquired by Loopt in 2009.','[]','GraffitiGeo'),('Grove is hosted IRC for companies. We provide an IRC (chat) server for your business with additional features such as hosted searchable archives and channel access controls.\n\nOur vision is to create a virtual office for distributed teams. Good communication is vital to the success of businesses, and Grove provides the best way to get your team on the same page.','Hosted IRC and so much more.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Grove'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','Heroku'),('APIs that allow developers and their apps to send, receive, track and store emails effortlessly.','Modern Email Platform for Developers','[\"San Francisco\"]','Mailgun'),('Mertado enables users to discover high quality, unique, lifestyle-oriented products to consumers wherever they spend their time. Mertado strives to create shopping experiences that build bridges between content, commerce & community.','Mertado','[]','Mertado'),(NULL,NULL,'[\"San Francisco\"]','Posterous'),('Rapportive shows you everything about your contacts right inside your inbox. \n\nYou can immediately see what people look like, where they\'re based, and what they do. You can establish rapport by mentioning shared interests. You can grow your network by connecting on LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook and more. And you can record thoughts for later by leaving notes. \n\nImagine relationship management built into your email. For free.','Be brilliant with people','[\"United States\"]','Rapportive'),('SocialPicks lets you generate an Investor Trust Score (Klout for finance with performance and ID verification baked in).  It\'s free and takes less than a minute to set up.','Investor Reputation Management (Klout for finance)','[\"New York City\"]','SocialPicks'),('Wufoo is a web application that helps anybody build amazing online forms. When you design a form with Wufoo, it automatically builds the database, backend and scripts needed to make collecting and understanding your data easy, fast and fun.','Online Form Builder','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Wufoo'),(NULL,'Performance Leader in Cloud Encoding','[\"San Francisco\"]','Zencoder'),('42Floors was founded in November of 2011 with the vision of making it easy to discover and create your dream office space. Based in San Francisco, California, the 42Floors team is made up of experienced entrepreneurs and engineers with a passion for making the commercial real estate process easier for everyone.\n\nOn the site, you\'ll find available spaces, complete with high quality photography and all the data you need to make a decision. The site 100% free to use.\n\n42Floors currently in a few cities, but we\'re expanding as fast as we can.','Discover and create your dream office','[\"San Francisco\"]','42Floors'),('500friends is the trusted provider of next generation loyalty marketing solutions to over 40 of the Internet Retailer 1,000 brands.\n','Enabling retailers to increase customer LTV','[\"San Francisco\", \"Silicon Valley\"]','500friends'),('99dresses is an fun, social, low-cost way for women to refresh their closets.\n\nOur members list their unwanted fashion to instantly earn \'buttons\' to spend. They then use their buttons to \'claim\' fashion that other women are giving away. All items are free - the receiver just pays shipping and a fee (5% of the item\'s MSRP). She might wear the item once or twice, then re-list it in a tap and go claim something new!\n\nOur girls absolutely ADORE us:\n\n\"You guys are amazing. I am seriously OBSESSED with this app. I look at it right when I wake up and before I go to sleep… and all the time in between :)\" - Anyssa C.\n\n\"Almost all my outfits this week have been from 99dresses. Help. Me.\" - Jackie M.\n\n\"Loving it! This app is like crack! It has replaced eBay and me taking my clothing to a local consignment.\" - Nicole S.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','Fashion Trading Community','[\"New York City\"]','99dresses'),('9GAG is a Hong-Kong based startup with an open and collaborative platform that makes life more fun by giving people the fastest and easiest way to share and spread visual entertainment.\n\nWith more than 65 million unique visitors and more than a billion page views per month, 9GAG has the most actively engaged user community of any humor website.','We make having fun a part of daily life for anyone, anytime, anywhere in the world.','[\"Hong Kong\"]','9GAG'),('Adioso is a travel search consumer app, powered by a new technology platform that enables the next generation of travel search.\n\nTravel applications of the future will:\n - Accept natural language, fuzzy searches that reflect the way people think about leisure travel.\n - Answer any search with sub-second response times, no matter how complex.\n - Learn about the user\'s interests and preferences and give personalised results and offers.\n - Not require people to work so hard to give their money to the travel industry\n\nAdioso answers complex travel questions in a single search, such as:\n - \"Southeast Asia next month for 15 to 20 days\"\n - \"Anywhere international next week for 10 days under $1000\"\n - \"Vegas any Friday for 2 days\"\n - \"Somewhere warm in late January for 10 to 15 days\"\n\nAnd Adioso\'s novel UI presents results to these complex searches and allows the user to interact with them in a way that reflects a conversational interaction with a human travel agent.','Travel search that works the way you think.','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Adioso'),(NULL,'Find a place to stay.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Airbnb'),('Airbrite is a developer API that enables commerce functionality for any website or app. \n\nAirbrite-powered Celery (trycelery.com) is a checkout system for crowdfunders and hardware companies to accept pre-orders for their products.','Add Commerce to Any App (YC S12)','[\"San Francisco\"]','Airbrite'),('Aisle50 gives consumers an easy, fully digital way to save big on groceries at their normal grocery stores.  \n\nWe offer the best ROI in the industry for CPG marketing teams, who spend more than $40 billion a year. \n\nWe will supplant newspaper coupon books, which have remained a multi-billion-dollar business despite a zero ROI transparency and a fading reach. These marketing vehicles have managed to hang on because there have been no worthy replacements. Until now.','Aisle50 sells grocery deals direct to shoppers and partners with retailers for redemption.','[\"Chicago\"]','Aisle50'),('Amicus allows nonprofits and universities to turn their supporters into fundraisers and advocates.\n\nEvery year, non-profits spend $60 billion to raise $300 billion. That\'s 20 cents on the dollar. By enabling truly social outreach and fundraising, Amicus allows cause-based organizations to raise more and spend less in the process.','Turn supporters into fundraisers and advocates (YC S12)','[\"New York City\"]','Amicus'),('We provide hundreds of high-quality employee perks to companies of any size. ','Great perks for everyone in your company. (YC W12)','[\"San Francisco\"]','AnyPerk'),('Ark is a modern people search engine.\n\n· 30% of all online searches are people searches.  \n\n· Ark enables users to search for new friends, find old classmates, and expanding their professional networks, or even their friends.\n\n·  Founding team of Berkeley graduate students who concentrated on search, and who also worked at social network and search companies.\n\n\nArk is proud to have been part of the talented YCombinator Class of W2012. \n\n*Want to join us? Email careers@ark.com with your resume.*','Modern People Search Engine. YC W2012. Ark.com','[\"San Francisco\"]','Ark'),('Authy is a simple API to add two-factor authentication to any website or app.\n\nWe are a developer centric product. We focus on making it easier for developers to add two-factor authentication to their products.\n\nWe provide apps for all major phones, support for both text-message and voice tokens internationally.\n\nWe also provide plugins for major applications such as SSH.','We make it easy for anyone to use two-factor authentication.','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Authy'),('Beatdeck brings intelligent data to a blind industry. Using a unique crawling algorithm, Beatdeck carefully analyzes the music industry and it\'s audience at scale to understand trends, demographics, and response. ','Big data music analytics.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Beatdeck'),(NULL,'','[\"Mountain View\"]','Beetailer'),('The App Store for Server Software. Deploy server applications with one click: in your laptop, as a virtual machine or in the cloud. Choose from dozens of popular applications and development environments including Rails, Django, CRMs, blogs, document management systems and many others.','The App Store for Server Software','[\"Mountain View\"]','BitNami'),('Bridge is a website that helps you find like-minded people to do activities with and make meaningful connections.','We solve the problem of meeting like-minded people','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Bridge'),('We solve the problem of failed parcel deliveries by leveraging automated, self-serve locker kiosks. Welcome to the world of receiving packages on your schedule!\n\nTech Crunch: http://tcrn.ch/N3gjsG\n\nAcquired by Google 11/2012: http://natpo.st/XQYIUQ','Self-serve parcel delivery kiosks','[\"Mountain View\"]','BufferBox'),('BuildZoom offers a better way to remodel your home. The company helps people find and hire the best contractors to make sure their remodeling project is completed properly.\n\nOn BuildZoom, homeowners can research contractors, browse through completed project photos in our gallery and get answers to questions about home improvement from our community of experts.','Simplified remodeling','[\"San Francisco\"]','BuildZoom'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','Chirply'),('Chute is a backend platform that allows developers to add any photo and video functionality to their apps or sites. While app developers and site publishers focus on the user experience and front end development, we handle the entire backend from uploading, image processing, API integration, and moderation. We\'re still in private beta but usage is more than tripling each month.','Chute helps apps & sites capture, manage and display media files (YC W12)','[\"Silicon Valley\"]','Chute'),('Circle takes the pain out of automated testing, greatly increasing your developers\' productivity.\n\nEvery time you push code to GitHub, Circle will automatically test your code, pushing working code immediately to Heroku/EC2/etc.\n\nCircle does for testing what Heroku did for hosting.  It is incredibly easy to use, fits into developers\' workflow, and requires no maintenance. It is demonstrably fast, and so low friction that your entire team can be set up in one click.\n\n','Easy, fast, automated testing','[\"San Francisco\"]','CircleCI'),('Online learning software in K12 is one of the fastest growing markets on the planet, and Clever is quickly becoming the infrastructure these apps depend on.  Today, many of the biggest and most innovative applications in education are already powered by Clever, and our platform is just getting started.','Online Learning Platform Used in Over 15,000 Schools','[\"San Francisco\"]','Clever'),('Cloudant’s distributed database-as-a-service (DBaaS) allows developers of fast-growing web and mobile apps to focus on building and improving their products, instead of worrying about scaling and managing their databases on their own.\n\nWe manage and distribute your data globally so you can grow more users, build more app features, and sleep more knowing we’re keeping the servers up and humming.','NoSQL database-as-a-service (DBaaS) for web and mobile apps.','[\"Boston\"]','Cloudant'),('Codecademy is the easiest way to learn to code.  Millions of people have used Codecademy to learn the basics of coding in an interactive, easy to use interface.  Learn by doing.','The Easiest Way to Learn to Code','[\"New York City\"]','Codecademy'),('Assembly is a web collaboration platform that allows anyone around the world to build software apps collectively while retaining ownership and receiving profit for their contributions. Each month Assembly rewards contributors by splitting the apps’ proceeds between them.','Quirky for software products','[\"San Francisco\"]','Assembly'),('Coinbase is a hosted bitcoin wallet.  What is bitcoin?  It\'s a new digital currency that is being used all over the world (about $2M USD in daily transaction volume right now).  Coinbase is an easy to use platform on top of bitcoin.\n\nIn the same way GitHub is a hosted platform for Git (a popular open source platform), Coinbase is a hosted platform for Bitcoin (another popular open source project).','Your hosted bitcoin wallet','[\"San Francisco\"]','Coinbase'),('Crocodoc converts Microsoft Office and PDF documents to HTML5 so your users can view and collaborate right in your web app. \n\nWe\'ve developed the world\'s most advanced web-based document viewing and collaboration technology for Microsoft Office and PDF files, built on open standards such as HTML5 and CSS3. We make it easy for companies to create amazing experiences for their users with technology that is secure, scalable, and trusted by top brands in the consumer and enterprise space. ','Easy document embedding and collaboration using HTML5','[\"San Francisco\"]','Crocodoc'),('Crowdbooster helps social media marketers make better decisions about what to share, when, and with whom, all from a real-time analytics dashboard that gives you suggestions as you go. Tens of thousands of business around the world have chosen Crowdbooster to make them smarter and more effective when navigating social media.','Optimized social media marketing (YC S2010)','[\"Palo Alto\"]','Crowdbooster'),('CrowdMed (www.crowdmed.com) harnesses ‘the wisdom of crowds’ to solve even the world\'s most difficult medical cases quickly and accurately online. Using patented prediction market technology, CrowdMed has accurately diagnosed real-world cases that stumped doctors for years, in just a few days and at nominal cost. Launched publicly in April 2013. \n\nOver 350 million people worldwide suffer from one of 7,000 rare or difficult-to-diagnose diseases. It often takes them many years and over a dozen doctors to find a correct diagnosis. Some of them die without one.\n\nUntil now.','Using crowd wisdom to save lives (YC W13)','[\"San Francisco\"]','CrowdMed'),('Pool funds with friends for anything. We\'ve taken our favorite elements of crowdfunding models on the web and provided those same tools to groups of friends instead.\n\n','Simple, Social, Pooling of funds... For anything.','[\"Palo Alto\", \"San Francisco\", \"San Francisco\"]','Crowdtilt'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','Cue'),('Curebit increases profits of online companies by optimizing customer acquisition through referrals.\n\nSocial referral marketing is a disruptive method of customer acquisition. Most companies today do not use referral systems at all or to their full potential. Curebit provides a SaaS referral platform that enables companies to execute, track, and optimize different types of incentivized referral campaigns.\n\nWe optimize our referral systems using aggregate data.\n\nDemo: http://curebit.com/investors','Customer Referral Platform (YC W11)','[\"San Francisco\"]','Curebit'),(NULL,NULL,'[]','Custora'),('Disqus is a commenting platform that enables websites to build active communities.\r\n\r\nCommunities powered by Disqus are connected through a shared network of users and discussion. \r\n\r\nExplore Disqus communities at http://disqus.com/explore','Networked community platform','[\"San Francisco\", \"New York City\"]','DISQUS'),('DotCloud is a 2nd-generation platform-as-a-service. It makes it incredibly simple for developers to deploy and scale their applications, while at the same time delivering the flexibility and robustness required by critical business software. Developers can mix and match from a large choice of languages, databases, caching and messaging components, leaving them in full control of their technology stack.','Cloud application platform','[\"San Francisco\"]','DotCloud'),('Y Combinator Alum DoubleRecall Nabs $1.6 Million To Give Brands An Alternative To Paywalls\nhttp://techcrunch.com/2012/02/12/doublerecall-funding/\n\nDoubleRecall Turns Paywalls Into Advertising Dollars\nhttp://nyti.ms/odHOgy','Content Monetization Goodies and Advertising with Impact','[\"Palo Alto\"]','DoubleRecall'),('Earbits is revolutionizing music marketing by combining free streaming music with an Adwords business model.  Our bands and labels bid per-song for airtime and use the consumer exposure to market their music and live events.  This model eliminates the need for listener subscription fees or commercial interruptions, and artists are reporting that it\'s more effective than Facebook advertising.  \n\nOver 650 record labels and 12,700 artists are on Earbits, including countless Grammy winning and Platinum-certified artists.  Earbits is available on the web, Android and iPhone.\nwww.earbits.com \nhttps://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.earbits.earbitsradio\nhttps://itunes.apple.com/us/app/earbits-free-radio/id701027627?ls=1&mt=8','Artists and Labels Bid for Online Radio Airtime to Acquire Fans and Market New Releases','[\"Los Angeles\"]','Earbits (YC w11)'),('Eligible makes it simple for healthcare companies to pass and receive financial transactions with over 1,000 health insurance companies across the country.  Transactions include queries to determine patient’s health coverage for certain services, claims (invoice) submissions, remittances (payments), preauthorizations, and more. \n\nTransaction pricing varies by type with a range of 5 cents per for coverage information queries to 25 cents per for claims (invoice) submissions. \n\n','Stripe for Health Care Transactions - YCS12','[\"San Francisco\"]','Eligible'),('At Embedly, we make front-end tools that help web and app developers create better user experiences. We believe the best tools are simple, easy to use, and perfectly suited to their task. You’ll find that embodied in Embed, Extract, and Display—tools that provide ultra-fast ways to present richer content more effectively.','Make any URL embeddable.','[\"Boston\"]','Embedly'),('Errplane provides a platform for organizations to instrument, monitor, and get alerted on anomalies in metrics in their applications and infrastructure. Customers send metrics up to Errplane\'s API, see real-time charts and graphs through custom dashboards, and set up monitoring conditions to get alerted via email, text, chat, or web hook for anything they\'re tracking.\n\nErrplane\'s API allows developers to slice and dice metrics on multiple dimensions while everything is monitored in real time to point out detected anomalies. With Errplane, customers can instrument everything and let us filter through the noise.','Metrics and anomaly detection for applications and infrastructure','[\"New York City\"]','Errplane'),(NULL,'Art commissioning market place','[\"San Francisco\"]','EveryArt'),('Origami is an online home for families.\n\nWith Origami, your family receives a private, customizable website on which to share daily updates and store lasting memories in the form of photos, videos, quotes and more.','A home for your family','[\"Mountain View\"]','Origami Labs (acquired by eFamily)'),('We find the best Exec in your area to do your job within 10 minutes. No complex selection process or scheduling required.\n\nYou get help right when you want it from one of our screened, professional Execs. We\'ve only hired people we\'d want as our own assistants.\n','Exec will get anything you want done right now for $25 / hour','[\"San Francisco\"]','Exec'),(NULL,'','[]','Fabricly'),('We\'re part of the \"Facebook generation,\" and we\'ve been connecting with our friends online forever. But global families have never connected well online. They\'ve tried Yahoo Groups, social networks, or even making their own websites. But moms still email us photos and estranged uncles try to \"friend\" us.\n\nFamilyLeaf is a simple way to keep all the family\'s information in one place, and to share photos and updates with everyone at once. Families around the world are using it every single day.','Private networks for families. YC W12.','[\"San Francisco\"]','FamilyLeaf'),('FanChatter lets you collect, refine, and promote social content about your interest to:\n\n- Engage current fans\n\n- Stimulate more chatter\n\n- Create new fans*\n\n* A fan isn\'t a fan because they \"Like\" you. A fan is a fan because they chatter about you.\n\n','Concentrate your crowd','[\"Minneapolis\"]','FanChatter'),('FarmLogs puts all the data farmers need to make better decisions and manage their business into one place. We save them time, help them make more money, and make their lives easier. ','Building the future of farming (YC W2012)','[\"Ann Arbor\"]','FarmLogs'),('Firebase lets you build real-time, collaborative apps in a fraction of the time it used to take.\n\nWe store and synchronizes your app\'s data between clients (web browser & phones) in miliseconds.\n\nWe\'re used by 35,000 developers and are growing 20% per month. Games, social tools, and collaboration apps are the most popular use-cases, but you can build virtually any app on Firebase.\n\nWired: http://bit.ly/HzjhwJ\nTechCrunch: http://tcrn.ch/Jgml5Y\nScoble: http://bit.ly/IW4q0r','The Realtime Application Platform','[\"San Francisco\"]','Firebase'),(NULL,NULL,'[]','Fivetran'),('We are the first company to establish a marketplace that allows vehicle owners who have parked their cars at the airport to rent them out to other travelers. We\'re the peer-to-peer alternative to the traditional airport car rental. Our founders are Harvard, Princeton, and MIT dropouts.','The Airbnb of car rentals at airports.','[\"Boston\"]','FlightCar'),('Flightfox is a marketplace for freelance travel experts.\n\nYou pay a finder\'s fee and our experts compete to save you the most time and money. No other website covers all the airlines, frequent flyer programs, special offers and travel routes. We do... because we\'re human powered.','A Marketplace 