ted Advertising for eBooks (YC S12)','[\"San Francisco\"]','Hiptype'),('We\'re taking on the $100bn/yr employment agency industry, which still relies almost entirely on brick-and-mortar retail locations and high-cost personnel (and has 2% margins). Employers specify the kinds of candidates they need and we use a smart matching algorithm to send them a short-list of applicants along with video interview and work samples (e.g., sales pitch over video, excel analysis, responses to complex emails).','Employment Agency 2.0','[\"Mountain View\"]','HireArt'),(NULL,'','[]','HyperInk'),('         Consider iCracked as the “AAA for iOS devices” offering the world’s only on-demand service for managing the wellness of your smartphone. Unlike the traditional mail-in smartphone insurance – iCracked leverages software, and an army of 300+ on-demand iTechs to do on-site repairs in 30 minutes or less with one click of a button. Yes we come to your office, make house calls, meet you at a Starbucks, you name it - it’s that awesome.\n\n       \n\n        \n          ','On-Demand Buyback & Repair for iOS devices - 320 iTechs in 10 countries.','[\"Redwood City\"]','iCracked  '),(NULL,NULL,'[]','imgfave'),('inDinero helps small businesses manage their finances with automated accounting, payroll, and tax services.','Better accounting for small business','[\"San Francisco\"]','inDinero'),('Instacart is an iPhone/Android/Web app that allows you to buy groceries from all local grocery stores and have them delivered to your door within minutes.\n\nWe are currently available in the SF Bay Area & Chicago serving stores such as Whole Foods, Safeway, Costco, Mariano\'s, Dominick\'s and more. \n\nBy end of 2014, Instacart will available in 10 high population regions in the US while supporting all the local grocery stores in those areas. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n','Never go to a grocery store again.','[\"San Francisco\"]','Instacart'),('Interstate provides a way for companies to get more from their project management flow. With Interstate you can secure more users and sales by being more transparent and open with your customers and potential tire kickers.\n\nOur users can embed their projects anywhere on the web and share with as many or as few people as they like. Many have used this to benefit them in highly competitive markets in order to obtain customers who may have been tire kickers before.','The future of open project management','[\"San Francisco\"]','Interstate'),('Welcome to the optimal technical recruiting screening process: fully-customizable programming challenges that can be deployed to candidates in seconds, and which save our customers hours of frustration and thousands of dollars in avoidable costs for every hire made. ','#1 technical recruiting platform, used by leading companies to hire the best programmers.','[\"Mountain View\"]','Interviewstreet'),(NULL,'','[\"San Francisco\"]','JobSpice'),(NULL,NULL,'[]','Kaleidoscope'),('Mobile gaming is growing at 30% per year, and Kamcord is creating the future distribution channel for these games.\n\nKamcord is focused on two components:\n1) Allow users to record and share a video of their mobile gameplay\n2) Build a community of mobile gamers showing off their best videos\n\nKamcord is creating a new way for people to discover mobile games. The App Store is broken for games and Kamcord is ready to fix it.','Future distribution channel for mobile games (YC S12)','[\"San Francisco\"]','Kamcord'),('Kicksend is a technology company that focuses on building unique mobile and desktop experiences that help non-technical people keep in touch with people they love through photos.\n\nWe have apps on iPhone, Android, Windows 8 and the Web that let people send and receive photo albums privately with close family and friends. They can also print photos they took or received at Walgreens, CVS, Duane Reade and Target stores directly from the Kicksend app.','Send & print photo albums with people you love','[\"Silicon Valley\", 